1. Each server has a player limit. Request to transfer character to a new 
server may be denied if too many players rush to a specific server or 
if too many players leave a specific server.

2. The request to transfer servers may take up to 1 hour and the game is 
unavailable until server transfer is complete.

3. In case of character nickname overlaps, a temporary letter is added
to the specific character’s nickname. 
(Character Nickname Change Ticket is sent to the Inventory of the 
overlapping character after server transfer.)

4. When a server transfer request is received, the transaction cannot be 
canceled and a refund is not permitted.

5. Transfer is unavailable to players in clans.

6. Transfer is unavailable to players with items in their Storage. 
In case of Storages with expanded slots in the previous server,
the expansion cost is refunded in Red Diamonds.

7. Existing Friend Lists are deleted and relevant player names 
in other players’ Friend Lists are deleted as well.

8. Arena Rank is reset after server transfer.
Items registered in the Trading Post and those that have been 
sold are sent to the Mailbox.

How arrogant!

the last breath you take!

Lucien!

your lives depend on it!

rose to legendary status.

Marlow has fallen!
Onwards to the castle gate!

It is within
the Elven Ruins...

The fragment seems to be
reacting to this place...

Warchief! This is the
object you spoke of.

We no longer need
this Human monument!

Huh? It should be
here somewhere...

Did you really think
you could catch me?

In the name
of Gran Kain...

Ah, it’s true!
It was so funny!

So he would say...

We can’t lose
this place to them!!!

killed the cat.

better left... secret.

Be sure to bring
back the blueprint!

is the place?

Entry is prohibited.
Please turn back.

It’s cute that you think

encountered some Lizardman?

I wonder if
Leto Lizardman from
west of the town
are involved...

You’ll make a
worthy sacrifice!
Kill them!

I finally found you!
I’ve been looking all over the place!

Seems you had some trouble
despite how confident you were. Hehe.

Kill!
Grunky will surely be pleased!

Showing your face here
is proof of your stupidity!
Aisa, I’ll leave it to you!

What are you trying
to do to the Crystal?!!
Arghh!!!

You lizards!
What the heck are
you up to?

Hehehe.
You Humans are
so foolish...

Don’t you understand
that you’ve played
right into our
hands?

My babies!!!
How dare you kill them!

You there!
Send out the call!
Burn all the Humans!
Sacrifice them all!

My children!
I will avenge you!

I’ll make sure you
share this pain!

Just the thought of your
suffering gives me joy!
Hahahahaha!

Salein!!!
Salein is over there!
I’ll trust you to deal with the shamans!

Hurry!
The shamans have
begun their ritual!
We must hurry for Salein’s sake!

Their blood will
enhance our intelligence.

We must not give up!
Salein was swallowed whole,
so she might still be alive!

You lot honestly
think you stand a chance
against me? Die!!!

You’ve ruined everything,
you wretched
Silverlight Mercenary!

I’ll make sure to
kill you slowly!

Aha! You’re in
cahoots with Caraku!

Kazan, the new chief,
will be unbeatable no matter
what you do!

How foolish.
They would still be alive
if they’d stayed still!

Not too shabby!
But now - you will know
Kazan’s strength!

I saved you because
you were the chief. And this
is how you repay me?

You will pay for your
mistake with your life.

You guys are
nothing as long as
I have this.

You should’ve been thankful
that I made you humans!
Kill them all!

This is so much more
fun than I expected!!!
But playtime stops now.
Time for you to die!

Do you recall the
agreement with the Tanor Chief
on the Summit of Dissonance?

We formed an alliance
with the Tanor in order to
help their unification efforts.

However, the Tanor here
are cousins of
Kankoon, the Tribal Chief.

The local chief heard
about Kankoon and has taken Durzel,
who was here as a diplomat, hostage.

Durzel?
You mean... that Human?
Why would I tell you anything?

I’ve heard countless tales
of your wicked ways!

Did you think
I didn’t know
you stole the relic?

What are you talking about?
We asked you about Durzel.

Calm down.
Sheesh. They sure are
difficult to talk to...
You leave me with no choice.

Hey, look!
It’s the Dark Brotherhood!

Silverlight Mercenaries?
Are you here
looking for her, too?

Her?
Who are you talking about?

Anyway, this is fantastic.
Elizabeth will definitely be pleased!

When we capture you,
Elizabeth will see
how loyal we are!

You goons
dare stand in our way?

Bah!
We’ll finish this
next time!!!

Hurry!
We need to get out of here!

I can feel my
pursuers’ presence!

We’ll hold them off!
Everyone else,
take care of the kid!

Go!
Take the kid
somewhere safe!

The Bugbears are coming!
We can’t leave the cage
until they’re gone!

They’re trying to escape!
There goes our dinner!

What happened to Steiner?
I thought he was captured alongside you.

He managed to escape,
but I’m sure he was greatly
troubled by his country’s betrayal.

Steiner...
Do you mean the
Oren Royal Guard Captain?
How could someone like that...

Darn it!
They’re on to us!
Be careful!

It seems safe now!
Free the captives.
Hurry!

The Northwind Plateau
belongs to us!

Ah, that’s right.
I have something
to tell you.
Am I wrong? I brought the adventurer along!
If I hadn’t, you could’ve died here!
Hah. I see what you’re saying.
Repay my favor! I want repayment!
Fine! Fine! Let me recover, then I’ll get you some Grendel Leather.
I didn’t know your life was so cheap!
Alright! Fine! I’ll get you some Adena, too!
That’s better! I can live with that!
(Just you watch, Pan. I’ll get you next time!)
See for yourself! It is Guillotine, the Lord of the Keep of Agony!
Hehe... Now you will all die... Argh!!!
Guillotine... Oh, no! What do we do...?
Your final duty is to use your blood to release me!

I see some tasty
Grendel over there!
I think we have enough meat.
You’ll need fire if you plan on cooking.
My lord may be displeased if we only have bear meat.
Please bring back some Windsus meat as well.
Help me! Help! There are Grendels everywhere!
Eek! You damn bears! Are you crazy?!
Wh... What the heck is that huge bear?!
Don’t bother with the middling ones!
Get me something large - something gigantic!!!
Those starving Grendels are such an eyesore... I can’t concentrate on cooking like this!
Get them too while you’re at it, will you?
Catching a Windsus is a handful as is!
Do let me know if you spot any large Windsus tracks!

Those large footprints
can only belong
to a gigantic Windsus!
I think we’re close to finding it.

Gasp!!!
It must be a mother Windsus.

As for the babies,
we can barbecue them!
I’m sure they’ll be tasty!
The mother! The mother is here!
Hurry up and finish her off!
I’m gonna take cover... this is scary!
Let me know if you spot a dark cloak while you’re fighting the Bugbears!

Found the cloak!
Quick! Over here!
I found the cloak! Shayden!!! Shayden!!!
Forget revenge! My life is more important!!!
First, defeat the fighter by the armory!!!

We must move
quickly and precisely.
I’ve dealt with all the lookouts.
Now it’s time to take the weapons from the armory.
Drave, over here! Help us, too!

You haven’t taken care of
those petty thieves yet?
I’ll destroy anyone who touches them!
Well, now it seems to have your attention.
The Prinsis I mentioned is here. It’s a large white flower!
Oh, my... You like me that much?
Oh, no! It’s a trap! Hurry - get out of there!
Listen carefully and do as I say.
The Prinsis over there seems real!
As expected. You like me, don’t you? Haha!
Another fake! I can’t believe this. Get out of there.
We can’t help it if we die.
Shouldn’t you pay the price for trying to kill the flower?
Th-this one is legitimate. I’m sure this one’s the real deal.
I’m impressed he shook off the hallucination!
This Prinsis will grow larger with your blood!
It will be good to defeat the Lizardmen first!
They treasure their eggs very dearly!
Many have attempted to steal their egg before - and died trying!
Stop making a ruckus and bring that egg over here!
Bring back a clean one, not one tainted with black magic!

You let that
fool get near
the egg?
Be wary - they have quick hands!
Uh oh... they’re headed my way! HELP!

After them!
I have a great reward for whoever catches them!
I’ll look for a way to deal with their numbers.
First, deal with the nearby elite soldiers!
Oh!!! They’re sleeping in the barracks.
This is our chance! Set fire to the barracks!
How dare you set fire to the barracks?!
I’ll rend you limb from limb!

Whoa - who is this guy?!
Looks like he’s in charge around here!
Let’s capture him! That should tank their morale!
Hurry meow! Let’s search for the Mace of Punishment!
You must be out of your mind!
I’ll catch you and make you my pet!

Eh? Who’s there!
Who’s making all that ruckus?

There!
That Tanor is holding
the Mace of Punishment!
Let’s deal with the minions first!
These guys don’t have much fight in them!
There! The Chief’s Token! Let’s take that first!
Careful! They’ll charge in to take the Chief’s Token!
How dare a human touch the Chief’s Token!
We’ll show you the might of the Tanor Silenos!
Wait! Hold it! They’re holding the Chief’s Token.
Not that they’ll last long, heh!
Have a taste of my magic!!!
Not too shabby, facing off against Varpio.
I expected you to lose quickly!
Bring it on! I’ll take you on!
Looks like meat’s back on the menu!
That guy! Jeez! What’s his problem?
Quick, grab more! We need more herbs!
There are a lot more quality herbs than expected!
It’s unlikely, but let me know if you find it!
I’ll start a fire while you deal with the Bugbears.
We must move swiftly and precisely!
Be careful! Nymphs are quite violent!
You could be killed instantly if you don’t watch out!
I would collect them myself, but...

Renner’ll definitely be surprised when he sees I defeated a fighter!
Hmm. So that’s how they fight!
He doesn’t seem like much of a talker.
Well, we don’t have much of a choice...
Now we need to defeat all of them...

I’ll make sure we get our vengeance!

He might show up if we’re lucky!

I think he’ll be a good sample, don’t you?

It was turned into a wasteland by powerful magic.
The Sea of Spores is toxic.
No ordinary creatures can live there.

You’re saying the magic caused the mutation?

while she was escaping the dark brotherhood.

I’m not sure why exactly the Dark Brotherhood is after Molly,
but I’m certain we shouldn’t let them get their hands on her.
Hey! This way! Look at this!
There’s a big one over there!
A big one is coming. This is dangerous.

We need to stop them from coming close, okay?
Emon said we need those to restore the barrier device.
This way! Help! I’m being attacked!

Something’s fishy! Someone must be behind all this.
Spore flowers will bloom from your corpses!

Emon and Pan, protect Molly and the survivor!

You’re a total merchant, aren’t you?

Sure, take it however way you will.

Meow! This wasn’t in our plans!
Ugh... My energy isn’t coming back.
Huh? The Oel Mahum and the Dark Brotherhood are in cahoots?

The Oel Mahum have two masters.
Let’s take care of White Captain Labaki first.
You arrogant fools! How dare you challenge me!
Labaki, isn’t this for the better?
Oh, yeah! I’ll take a big reward for myself while I’m at it! Hahaha!
Uh oh! It seems you’re looking down at us!
We need to show them that we’re stronger.
Now we deal with High Shaman Ukra!
We need to travel south a ways.
Do your best to ignore anyone who attacks from behind.
There will be no end to this if we deal with them individually.
Hey merchant, why are you working so hard?
Hardin made a special request of me.
There is no adventurer who has traveled Oren more than I have.

I’m not dumb! I don’t do anything if the pay’s not good.

Here we go! Who wants to die?
You sure are reckless! I’ll kill you myself!
I’m afraid we’re only going to make him more angry...

I wonder if “flaunting” will have any effect...?

Pan! You said there were only two!
Meow meow! That’s not important right now!
It’s him! He planted the flag!
Labaki and Ukra were two of my favorites!
Oh, my... I didn’t see things going this badly!
Meow! What do we do? I’m scared!
Pan’s hurt! Let’s finish this - fast!
I’m disappointed that you don’t know me!

I’m Aymel of the Silverlight Mercenaries! Got it?

Elizabeth... How dare you speak that name in my presence!
Argh! Damn it! What’s wrong with this girl?

The Dark Brotherhood is after her.

Oh, sir. I sincerely need some filters!

Uh... You’re not talking about me, right?
I-I wouldn’t taste good!! I promise!
Meow! Put your backs into it! Do something!
They caught up to us! Meow!
Whoa! You were doing something fun here!
Do one thing for Pan and he won’t stop asking for favors!
This isn’t my fault! Do something, meow!
Over here, you walking compost piles!
Come here once you deal with those winged beasts!
This must be the device Emon mentioned.
Meow! I’m pushing myself too hard today!
Why exactly are you destroying the barrier device?!
It’s your fault the Sea of Spores is like this!
Hmph. I have no obligation to answer your questions.
Either hand Molly over or die!
I’ll be right back. Please take care of Molly.
I’ll use a Teleportation Stone to go there and back.
Hahaha. This is great! I was thinking about running.
Let’s go! We need to cross the bridge!
I didn’t think it would be this easy to break your ranks!

Perfect! My stomach was just starting to rumble.
The wardstone is over there. I’ll be on my way.
Not all of us! I’m a credit to my profession.
Of course! And I’m good at what I do!
Please defeat the vampire bats first.
Monsters have been appearing non-stop since the storm.
The situation here is more severe than at the graveyard.
Hurry back! I don’t have a good feeling about this!
Argh! What the heck? These guys are a ton stronger than anyone we’ve faced before!
Well, looks like the kid gloves are off!
The kid gloves were ever on...?
You don’t pose any kind of threat to Embrion!
Hehehe... you’ve been a mere plaything!
I highly doubt a fool such as yourself would understand. Hahaha.
Wh-why are you doing this? Theodore!
Aymel and Molly are in danger!
We’ll follow you as soon as we retrieve Aymel and Molly!
What did you do to the mushrooms?
I’m worried about my grandpa. He’s alone.
For now, let’s go to your old home.
We aren’t sure what caused the accident at Ivory Tower.
Let’s think about that after we’ve defeated the Dark Brotherhood.
The Ivory Tower Wizards have sent a request for help.
Go rescue the Ivory Tower Wizards and bring them here!

One of our friends is collapsed over there!

Go rescue the Ivory Tower Wizards and bring them here!

Defeat as many Fallen Knights as possible!
Could that Soulstone have brought the Fallen Knights?
Stop them from coming close to the Soulstone!
We need to destroy that Soulstone!
Uh oh! I feel our lord’s anger!
Boost the Doll of Emptiness’s drive to maximum!
Defeat the enemy quickly so we can restore the Soulstone!
Oh my goodness! What do we do?!
Defeat as many Fallen Knights as possible!
Could that Soulstone have brought the Fallen Knights?
Stop them from coming close to the Soulstone!

It will be to your advantage to leave as soon as you find the recipe!

I refuse to die before I kill you!
Krrr! I’ll beat you halfway to death and have you begging for your life!
I see you still have your sick fantasies! This is the end for you!

Get your filthy hands off it!
Don’t let your guard down. This is their territory.
I’m getting ready to go outside and see Dorothy...
I passed out when I was teleported out of the tower.
I could’ve been eaten by a Grendel!
Hey! Are you close by? I think I’m in just a touch of danger!
Popularity isn’t always a good thing! Aren’t you going to help me?
I’m getting ready to go outside and see Dorothy...
I passed out when I was teleported out of the tower.
I could’ve been eaten by a Grendel!
Thankfully, this is a curse I can deal with.
But even I can’t be sure if we delay any longer!
Huh? A thief? Wow! I am absolutely lost for words!
You sure are bold, stealing from bandits!
Over there! Let’s get those guys too!
This way! Hurry! Theodore is waiting!
Gasp! In all the time I’ve been a bandit - this is a first!
Bandits steal! They aren’t stolen from!
Just you watch, you thieves! I’ll steal from you!
We don’t have time for this...
What brings you here? What reason?
You’re chasing after the Dark Brotherhood?
I’m not sure what this has to do with us being attacked...
But we can think about that after we save our friends.
Steal the armor from the Bandit Plunderer?
What are you doing to my prisoner? Get your hands off!
Hey! I’m not an object! How rude!
That’s rude to ask! And it hardly matters right now!
Nice. Let’s grab and sell these guys too!
We won’t be caught a second time, you fools!
Let’s take care of this before he calls his minions!
Oh! It’s you from the Ivory Tower! You’ve made a mistake.
Perfect! I’ve always wanted to wreck you!
You want to know why the treasure has caught fire?
I can’t tell you... but it’s Ivory Tower Arcane Magic.
Argh! A fire? We’re all done for if the boss finds out about this!
They seem to have lit the fire!
Everyone! Put out the fire! Now!
Who are you? Are you the one causing a ruckus in our base?
What’s your deal?! You’re not even an Ivory Tower Wizard!
Anyone who helps the Ivory Tower Wizard will die!
What?! Hold them tight until I get there!
Sheesh, you guys catch on quick!
Huff huff. A little bit slower... Argh!
I’ll be there to help soon.
So it wasn’t just an attack...
So the Bandit Stronghold has been conquered...
Hardin said the best thing to do is to attack the Ivory Tower Wizard.
I don’t think Hardin’s judgment is wrong...
But he doesn’t seem to be paying much attention to finding Molly...
Doesn’t this guy seem pretty useful?
Atrox’s shell will make the good-luck charm stronger.
The Dark Witches and the Ivory Tower are known to have a bad relationship.
Well, I don’t think anyone in the area would like Ivory Tower Wizards.
They’ve always used their magic to rule this place with an iron fist.
You’re in cahoots with the Ivory Tower Wizards!
The Timak Orcs and Dark Witches are also known to have a bad relationship.
But they’ve formed an alliance against the Ivory Tower.
As promised, these two are now yours.
We are quite pleased with our alliance! Krrr!
They’ll be a great sacrifice! Krrr!
Krr. What’s their deal? Unwelcome guests?
Catch them alive! Otherwise they’re worthless!
Why don’t you go back and wait? Krrr. There is no change to the trade conditions.
Hmm.. well, one thing’s going right! The Orcs are retreating!
What a big mouth you have. Can you defeat our sisters?
Fools! To think you all would come here on your own accord.
I expected a Wizard would be smarter.
I guess they’re not too bad!
What are you supposed to be? The Ivory Tower’s dogs?
They’re pretty strong - keep your guard up!
I thought the Dark Witches and Timak Orcs hated each other.
Since when do they get along?
I overheard something while I was captured...
It seems the Timak Orcs, Dark Witches, and the Bandits have formed an alliance.
We have an escapee! Krrr! Get them!
You’re in league with those Ivory Tower fools!
We’ve come to see your cowardly leader!
We hear your leader is a cower who goes knock-kneed in front of that Dark Elf woman!
I thought Wizards were supposed to be smart. Perhaps you’re an exception!
I am not a coward! You insulted me! You’re done for!
Thank you, Theodore! Best of luck to you!
I’ll deal with them all at once.
Hurry, let’s search the inside! Valter’s already left.
Finish checking here and then follow Theodore.
This way! We found them! Krrr!
How dare you attack us! Krr!!!
Don’t be startled. We’re stronger than them.
That’s funny! Krr! You puny twig!
Move! Out of the way, fools! What are you doing?
Krrr! Avakar! We were just about to deal with the situation...
Quiet, you useless fool! Didn’t I tell you to strike enemies with full force?
Don’t underestimate your enemies! Everyone, attack!
There’s something different about these guys!
Don’t let them live! Kill them all!
They have no idea how strong their enemies are!
That’s reassuring, isn’t it? Hmm... I wonder why I’m such a burden. Argh!
Is there a battle there? Help me after you deal with it!
Theodore? We need to clean up this situation quickly.
This is perfect! I needed some meat to give to the wolves!
The wolves are faster than us.
We won’t be able to pass until we deal with all the wolves.
Those stubborn Silverlight Mercenaries! I’m so sick of them!
Elizabeth, how could you be so cruel?
I feel reassured with you here, Hardin!
To think they’d follow us here! Krr!
Give up, Orcs! Your leader has already surrendered.
Well, then I’m the new leader! Die!!! Krrr!
We have to get to the Ivory Tower. Defeat these Orcs and clear the path!
I don’t remember it feeling so ominous before...
I have no intention of going against Hardin, but...
We can’t waste any more time...
Don’t you worry! This isn’t the first time!
Over there! The Ivory Tower Wizards!
How dare you sneak a peak! This should put you off your bad habit.
How dare you do that do the dean?
Seems the dean of the Ivory Tower doesn’t have much power...
Eeek! Who are you? What did you do to the dean?
It is as you saw. You will face the same fate, Wizard.
My subordinates will carry out their duties to their fullest.
I wonder who’ll survive this fight.
Hey! What are you after? Are you after a Nebulite?
Hehehe. I’m not sure why Elizabeth is letting you live.
I’ll kill you for everyone’s benefit, Theodore.
Enjoy the rest of your life... short as it may be. Hehehe...
Emerson seems to have regained his strength.
If you want to enter the Ivory Tower,
you need two more High Wizards in addition to myself.
The majority of magic-powered devices have broken.
That’s correct! I knew this would work! Hehehe.
I’ll get to kill you now!
You know the dean is dead, right?
That’s why the Silverlight Mercenaries are trying to enter the Ivory Tower.
Ah. I met Emerson. He’s quite alright.
That’s a relief. I wonder if we’ll have a chance with the Silverlight Mercenaries.
The enemies are strong. I’m concerned whether this will only lead to more casualties...
Getting caught is only a matter of time!
You don’t necessarily have to face them. Run away! We should join forces with our friends!
That’s not the right attitude, Theodore! Where do you think you’re going?
That Dark Elf wizard is Theodore! After him!
They’re trying to buy some time. Defeat them quickly!
My mission is to keep you here.
Since that’s the case, how about you hold still? Or maybe just die?
You don’t even know what Hardin wants, right?
Ha. So you’re interested? Well, you’ll need to find me then.
Well, if you want to know who wants Beleth’s return the most...
What are you trying to say, Elizabeth...?
I’m using detection magic to look for Elizabeth.
Do your best to ignore any monsters that approach us.
Arrogant and rude! Say my name with respect!
I’ll have to teach you a lesson about manners, Dark Elf!
As expected... security around the Nebulite is tight.
Is that why the plan is to stop the flow of magic into the Summoning Circle?
Hmmph! Don’t you fools recognize your master?
You should’ve done this sooner, you idiots! Not to me, but to the Dark Brotherhood!
You’re quick on the uptake. You want to cut off power to the magic circle?
Oh? You’re not as dumb as you seem, are you?
You cannot take the Nebulite! It’s too dangerous!
Well, I’m sure that’s true - for idiots!
I’m sure Hardin would like that to happen.
I mean, he would like us to take the Nebulite.
You want to bet on that, Theodore?
The one who wants Beleth’s return the most...
Hahaha! Exactly the reaction I expected!
Well, that’s too bad. You’ll never be able to stop us now!
Intruder located! All Guardians, battle stations!
We can’t hold out much longer! There’s too many of them! How long until we can escape?
Argh! Don’t give up! We still have time!
Hard to focus when we’re being attacked!
Huff! Huff! I can’t hold on much... longer...
Damn! Is this how I die...? Argh!
We’re almost there! Look! The hunters’ campsite!
That over there is the impregnable fortress, the Town of Oren!
The traitors of Oren have shown up on their own accord!
What? Traitors? What are you talking about?
We all know you betrayed Oren and murdered the first lady!
I see there are Giran informants with you!
This is the end for you!
There’s no need to hide this anymore!
Oh no, it’s too late! Ugh! What a mess!
Don’t you dare act arrogant! Get them!
These guys sure aren’t pushovers. Careful!
I’ll hand it back to you!
You’re all rats in a hole.
Is that a sentry? They’ve spotted us!
By Gran Kain, I command you!
Hurry and activate the barrier device!
We’re almost here! Hang in there!
Did you think you could get away so easily?
Pan! I’ll trust you with him!
H-how can you do this to me?
Hey, look here. I’ll spare your life if you head back.
I think you’re going to be the one to die, don’t you?
You useless simpletons! Do I really have to take matters into my own hands?
Nothing will change, even if you bother us.
We’re done for the moment we step through that door.
When I give you the signal, follow the plan.
Almost done! Just a little more!
You dumb Orcs! Can’t you do your jobs properly?
You’re in cahoots with the ambushers!
I guess Embrion isn’t as great as I thought since you imbeciles were able to escape!
Oh no... Is this it for me...
Is everyone okay? I’m glad I’m not too late.
Not bad. As expected from a dean.
I was just thinking that magic users must be worthless since we were able to conquer the Ivory Tower so easily.
Oh my. My apologies. That was quite rude of me.
But I couldn’t come empty handed.
I hope you enjoy my gift...
There’s no use, Theodore. I’ve already set up a barrier.
You’re dangerous because you know the secret of the Giants!
Shut up, Theodore! You don’t even understand the situation you’re in.
Theodore, know this... I must defeat him. For her sake.
The mana is starting to run low.
Just a bit more... Hang on a bit longer!
I see it’s not too late. Is everyone alright?
How dare a Wizard try to steal our product!
I’ll make sure they can’t follow us!
It’s too early to feel relieved. We have to keep moving.
Your current equipment isn’t doing you or your abilities justice.
I hear the Shop has great items in stock.
Your equipment looks like it needs a boost in power.
Head over to the Forge and “level up” your equipment.
Runes are full of untapped potential.
You can imprint runes in the Rune menu.
Collect Monster Cores and complete Codices to become stronger.
The Monster Codex menu is found under Challenges.
Make sure you complete as many as you can!
Elixirs are mystical potions that boost your strength.
You can brew elixirs in the Elixir menu.
Your achievement progress can be found under Challenges.
Your achievement progress can be found under Challenges.
Soul Crystals imbue equipment with power.
You can equip them in the Items menu.
Why don’t you give it a try?
Hone your skills for a better chance of survival in battle.
You can level up skills in the Skill menu.
Honor is bestowed upon the worthy and the skilled.
Earn Honor by participating in Arena Battles in the Battlefield menu.
You’re now an official member of the Silverlight Mercenaries!
It’s all thanks to me and my support, right? Hehe.
You are now the ray of hope for the world.
I look forward to even greater things from you!
Talking Island is always bustling with people!
You’ll fit right in with the other rookies. You all have overwhelmed looks on your faces!
Work together to bring peace to the land.
I will always be here to lend you my full support.
West Talking Island is full of traces of the Elves.
We hoped the land would retain its beauty, but it fell into ruins.
Let’s band together to drive out the Orcs and return the land to its former beauty.
You can do it! I have faith in you!
I believe you can do it!
Gludin Highway used to be the trading hub for merchants.
All that is left now are graves.
The plague came and went, leaving behind despair and nostalgia in its wake.
Help Gludin become the bustling center of commerce that it once was.
I will be with you in spirit and mind.
There are more soldiers than farmers here in Gludio Plains.
Where are all these Lizardmen and Orcs coming from?
Please help the soldiers of Gludio.
Show them that peace is not a false dream.
I will do my best to provide support!
Windawood Manor was the battleground for wars between Elves, Humans, and Orcs.
As a result, the land is full of towns that now lay in ruin.
The Elves lost the war and went into hiding.
You’ll help me find them, won’t you?
The Wasteland is as desolate and lonely as its name.
Many tales are told here about Beleth, the Great Wizard.
I’m a little scared, but I know that you’ll protect me!
Let’s not stay any longer than we need!
The Plains of Dion have recently been regaining their vitality and are bustling with activity.
Though from the perspective of the Elves, Humans come off a little uncouth and aggressive.
Even so, we should believe that it is Eva’s will that Humans and nature coexist in harmony.
We should do our part to figure out how!
Cruma Swamp was named after Cruma, the giant turtle that supposedly lives there.
I’ve never seen the turtle, but I heard it was enormous!
Oh, legends say that Lesser Giants also lived here.
Perhaps this place was a safe haven for the oversized.
I want us to leave a huge lasting impression here, too!
We’ve finally arrived at the Summit of Dissonance.
This is one of the places that we Elves avoid like the plague.
All lives are valuable, but the Ol Mahum are maybe a little less valuable.
Let’s complete our mission and move onto the next territory as soon as possible.
Good luck! Don’t forget that I’m here for you!
The Shrieking Hallows is literally a groaning land of pain.
Will we be able to help this land full of fear and sadness?
I don’t have an answer, but if anyone can do it, I know you can.
Do your best so that this land can be renamed to something happier.
I’ll do my best to withstand this overwhelming sadness and stay strong.
Giran! We’ve finally arrived at Giran!
Giran is a refuge during our long travels.
We can soothe our aching bodies and repair our equipment.
I’m really looking forward to the delicious food and comfy beds.
This is your chance to kick back and relax.
Welcome. Is this your first time on Talking Island? Well then! It’s a good thing quests are automated.
The automated quest stops once the quest is complete. Tap to begin the next quest.
Okay. You're a natural. Let's try another quest.
All of your items can be found in your Inventory.
Auto-Equip is a quick and easy way to equip your best equipment.
It’s a useful feature for new adventurers like yourself, so make good use of it.
You should start by using Soulshots automatically!
Soulshots are only used <YellowBold>when you attack</>.
They stay safe and sound with you at all other times.
Don’t want to use them automatically? Just tap again.
<YellowBold>Soulshots are available in the Shop</>, so stay well stocked!
You can find the entrance in the Dungeons menu.
If you keep up with your training, you’ll be able to tackle them soon!
For now, let’s check out the Daily Dungeon.
In <YellowBold>Daily Dungeons</>, <YellowBold>different monsters appear every day</>.
Stronger monsters drop better rewards, so work on becoming stronger yourself.
Auto-Battle is available if you need help.
Wow! That was one powerful monster you knocked out!
You can only enter a few times per day, but don’t worry! The count <YellowBold>resets daily</>.
<YellowBold>It won’t count as an entry</> if you fail, so don’t be afraid to challenge yourself!
That was a solid effort. Better luck next time!
Time to check your achievements and claim rewards.
The first step is to enter Challenges.
That will lead you to Achievements.
Have your <YellowBold>achievements</> acknowledged and receive <YellowBold>rewards</> for them.
It seems you’ve been working hard. You’ve already completed some <YellowBold>achievements</>.
Go ahead and claim this reward.
Well done. You will acquire <YellowBold>titles and abilities</> based on your meritorious deeds.
So stop by often to stay updated.
Keep working hard, and your efforts will be quickly rewarded.
The higher your achievement level, the stronger your abilities - and you’ll receive supply items as daily rewards.
Be mindful of <YellowBold>the different kinds of achievements</> to complete, and don’t ignore any of them.
The Shop is full of helpful supplies.
Like this one right here. Remember what it looks like - it’ll come in handy later on!
What are you waiting for? Open it up!
Wow! That’s a fantastic piece of equipment!
Do you know how to make equipment stronger? You <YellowBold>level it up</>!
<YellowBold>A free High-grade Equipment Box is available every 12 hours.</> Don’t forget to stop by!
You came to the right man if you want to <YellowBold>level up</> equipment. I’m the best blacksmith on Talking Island!
Here, take this equipment. It should be useful for you.
Let’s take a look at the equipment you received.
It should be in the armor tab.
Go on and select the equipment I gave you.
You can level up equipment at the Forge. Follow me.
There are <YellowBold>various ways to strengthen equipment</> using the Forge.
<YellowBold>Level up</> uses other equipment as material to <YellowBold>improve</> the equipment you primarily use.
Now, there is a small fee for the service... I’d be out on the streets if I did this for free, heh!
Use this as material. Let’s call it a gift!
Well, we’re all set! I can do this for free just this once. Our secret!
The materials will disappear during the process.
All finished! Let’s take a look. Hey, it’s a success!
Go ahead and equip it now that it’s leveled up!
It’s as easy as tapping Auto-Equip!
Leveling up your equipment <YellowBold>is the easiest way to improve your combat abilities</>. Try leveling up your equipment if enemies are too powerful.
Well then! Let's move onto leveling up your skills.
Before we start, we’ll need to see what skills you use.
Let’s take a look at your skills.
Here, you can raise your <YellowBold>skill levels</> and <YellowBold>switch the locations of skill buttons</>.
You’ll need Skill Points to raise the level of your skills.
You can acquire SP by raising your character’s level and by playing consistently.
Do you see the level up button? It’s tempting, right?
You can use <YellowBold>SP</> to <YellowBold>raise skill levels</>.
Normally, this would cost some Adena... However, I’ll help you out this time since you were so helpful recently.
<YellowBold>Passive skills</> can be leveled up the same way. Let’s try it out.
Then, you can spend SP and Adena to raise its level.
<YellowBold>Passive skill</> effects are automatically activated, so they can be easy to overlook - but it’s important to remember them if you want to become stronger.
The Arena is the best place to test your skills.
You can find it on the Battlefield!
See the Arena entrance? Prepare yourself!
You can fight <YellowBold>1 on 1 duels</> against other adventurers. It’s a great place to prove your skills!
Select one of the 4 opponents from the list and defeat them! You can rise to greater heights by fighting and defeating stronger opponents!
<YellowBold>Weekly rewards</> are given out based on your weekly ranking. Work hard to consistently place high!
Don’t forget that duels go hand-in-hand with Honor!
Honor is given to winners and losers alike.
Accumulate Honor to reach higher ranks and acquire <YellowBold>stat rewards</>!
Hmm... you don’t have any Honor to speak of right now...
With dedication, you’ll earn more Honor and better rewards!
Don’t be modest - let’s get dueling right away!
Select Start. There’s no telling who your opponent will be, but I’m sure you’ll beat them to a pulp!
Ouch... That was close! Well, there’s always next time!
Allow me to teach you another way to improve equipment.
Combine is relatively straightforward, but it gets the job done.
You’ll need to use the Forge to combine equipment.
Combine two level 30 equipment pieces of the same grade and type to acquire one piece of equipment of a grade one greater than the material used.
Equipment is categorized into target equipment and material equipment.
Check the details of the target equipment here.
Let’s not waste any more time - it’s time to combine. Use this as combining material.
Take this and use it as material equipment.
If the material is ready, let’s combine.
There’s no time. Hurry up with it.
Success! Seems the preparations are ready.
Don’t forget to equip your equipment! Oh! Combine <YellowBold>produces the same type as the main material equipment</> so keep that in mind! Well then, good luck!
Want to know about clans? Tap the main menu.
You would do well to join a clan that matches your beliefs.
You’ll find that there are many benefits to membership.
Oops! Here I am suggesting you join a clan without even explaining what clans are!
The key aspects of clans are <YellowBold>Fortress Siege</>, where you can battle other clans over various fortresses.
And of course, clans can’t be competitive without significant power.
All citizens of Aden can <YellowBold>bet on the winners of a Castle Siege and win prizes</> during the <YellowBold>Castle Seige Festival.</>
And that’s not all! When you’re in a clan, you can reap benefits from <YellowBold>buffs, the clan shop, clan quests, and rewards</>.
Let’s look at <YellowBold>how to join clans</>.
This is how you join clans.
Anyone can choose a clan leader they believe in and work together to reach the top!
If you like the look of one of these clan leaders, tap <YellowBold>Apply</>!
I’m excited to see what clan you’ll join!
Or maybe you’ll strike out on your own and become the leader of a new powerful clan!
Have you heard about the <YellowBold>Tower of Insolence</>? Every Adventurer in Aden should enter it at least once.
Well, then. Let’s try the Tower of Insolence now.
You can enter the Tower of Insolence through the Dungeons menu.
Do you see the infinitely tall tower? That is the Tower of Insolence.
<YellowBold>The Tower of Insolence</> was constructed by Emperor Baium of Elmoreden in defiance of the gods.
Although it was once called the Tower of Eternity, enraged with wrath, the god Einhasad filled it with monsters.
The higher you climb in the tower, the stronger the monsters you’ll encounter - and the better the treasures you’ll find.
Curious? At present, you should be able to at least clear the first floor.
For each floor you’ve already cleared, you can acquire additional rewards once per day using <YellowBold>Auto-Clear</>.
Here, you can check the Auto-Clear reward for each floor.
You can acquire <YellowBold>Rune Fragments</> using Auto-Clear. Think of it as a key to improve your combat abilities.
I'll teach you more the next time I see you.
Hmm... Seems you haven’t trained enough...
Let’s return by tapping the screen.
I’ll teach you how to use the Rune Fragments to become stronger. The process is called Rune Imprinting.
Rune imprinting is a means of directly improving your character.
Use this to try out rune imprinting for yourself.
Through rune imprinting, the abilities of each rune become yours <YellowBold>permanently</>.
Rune imprinting requires <YellowBold>Rune Fragments</>. Yes indeed, those things you acquired through auto-clearing the Tower of Insolence.
We’ll perform the most basic kind of rune imprint.
You can check here to see the materials required for rune imprinting.
Now, give rune imprinting a try.
Since this is your first time, I’ll provide you with the materials necessary.
The preparations are ready. Try imprinting.
Did you notice the large rune in the middle? That is the <YellowBold>Core Rune</>.
The <YellowBold>Core Rune</> level increases when all the runes on each page are imprinted to the same tier.
Remember, Core Runes grant <YellowBold>many more stats</> than ordinary runes do.
As you’ve noticed, this is the Core Rune.
Core Runes grant many stats that you can look forward to.
And finally... these aren’t all the runes that can be imprinted.
You can use this to unlock more rune pages.
You can imprint <YellowBold>more diverse and powerful runes as you gain access to more pages</>.
However, <YellowBold>all runes on a page need to be imprinted a level greater than Lv. 1</> in order to unlock the next page.
Rune imprinting draws out powerful abilities, so it requires adequate preparations.
Well then! I look forward to seeing how strong you’ll become through the power of rune imprinting.
You can equip Soul Crystals onto equipment to increase performance. Let’s open the inventory.
I’ll teach you how to equip Soul Crystals. Select the armor tab.
Equip the headgear I gave you.
You do know to tap equip, right?
If you carefully inspect the headgear you just equipped...
You can find the slot to equip Soul Crystals.
Soul Crystals are gemstones containing the souls of monsters. Equipping them results in <YellowBold>soul stats being applied to equipment</>.
The traits of Soul Crystals determine their stats. Stronger souls provide <YellowBold>more powerful stats</>.
You can use Soul Crystals as material to create <YellowBold>more powerful ones</>.
We’ll be equipping Soul Crystals to this equipment.
Here’s a Soul Crystal acquired from defeating that monster.
Well done. Next, we’ll look into improving Soul Crystals.
You level up Soul Crystals the same way you would equipment.
Select the Soul Crystal you would like to level up.
Then, select another Soul Crystal as material.
Tap level up, and you’re all set.
Well done. Let’s get out of here.
If you have better headgear, equip that instead.
Keep in mind that once Soul Crystals reach <YellowBold>Level 5</>, they can be <YellowBold>upgraded</> to the next grade.
That’s all for explanations about Soul Crystals.
One Soul Crystal could be all the difference between victory and loss. Use them wisely.
You can enter Elite Dungeons from the Dungeons menu.
I trust you know how to get there.
There! See the Elite Dungeon? Select it.
These are the places I found during my time as an archaeologist... The most vile monsters in Aden appear here.
There may be monsters you can’t handle on your own, so be sure to enter <YellowBold>with trusty comrades</>. The higher the risk, the greater the rewards.
Elite Dungeon missions are posted by the lord each day.
You will receive additional rewards each time you complete 5 missions.
You can acquire additional Exp. daily during this time.
It’s dangerous to venture into Elite Dungeons alone. Parties provide safety in numbers.
I’ll teach you how to upgrade equipment.
You remember how to get to the Forge, right?
Use Upgrade Stones <YellowBold>to raise equipment grades while maintaining their appearance and stats.</>
In order to upgrade equipment, you need <YellowBold>Upgrade Stones specific to the equipment parts</>.
For example, you need <YellowBold>Accessory Upgrade Stones</> to upgrade accessories.
Check here to see the expected upgrade result.
Tap this ring to place it in the upgrade slot.
Tap this button to start the upgrade.
Use the upgrade feature if you want to <YellowBold>keep a preferred piece of equipment’s stats or match set equipment</>.
Keep in mind that Upgrade Stones are rare and difficult to obtain.
You need to go to the Forge to enhance equipment.
<YellowBold>Equipment-specific enhancement scrolls</> are required to enhance specific equipment types.
Remember, <YellowBold>Blessed Scrolls</> can enhance up to +3 at once.
You can gain additional bonus stats for matching the enhancement levels of multiple pieces of equipment. It pays to keep things even.
Don’t forget, equipment has maximum enhancement levels depending on its grade.
Enhancement scrolls are kept on the Other tab.
Steady... enhancing has a chance of failure.
If you’re all set, start enhancing.
Success! I hope you like it.
Be careful. Successful enhancements can raise a piece of equipment’s stats, but failure can lead to the enhancement level dropping.
I’ll teach you how to use the Codex. Follow me.
You can find the Codex in the Challenge menu.
You can register Cores obtained from monsters in the <YellowBold>Codex</>. Collect Cores to level up the Codex and <YellowBold>increase your stats</>!
If you collect <YellowBold>all of the Monster Cores in a specific region</>, your <YellowBold>stat bonus increases even more</>.
I’ll teach you <YellowBold>how to register Cores</>.
Red Rouse is a monster that appears in West Talking Island. Select it.
There are enough Cores to complete the Codex. Good. Craft the Codex!
All monsters can drop Cores, but regular monsters won’t drop them very often.
Focus your hunt on Named Monsters. They’re guaranteed to drop Cores.
I’ll teach you one rare skill I know.
It should be of some help. This way...
Here, you can learn rare skills.
<YellowBold>Rare skills</> are different from normal skills and <YellowBold>are both efficient and powerful</>. Anyone can use them, regardless of their class.
But, it’s important to note that rare skills cannot be learned normally or leveled up. You must gather <YellowBold>Forgotten Scroll pages</> to complete your Forgotten Scroll.
Select the skill page I handed you just now.
We need to create a Forgotten Scroll.
You can use your <YellowBold>Forgotten Scroll</> to learn a rare skill. Check your inventory.
This is the Forgotten Scroll that was made just now.
Tap use to learn the skill.
Well done! Now try registering a rare skill to a slot.
Okay. Let’s go back to the Manage Skills screen.
I trust you know what to do.
It’s the rare skill you learned just now.
You must register a rare skill to a rare skill slot in order to use it.
Well done. You can acquire other rare skills from powerful monsters like <YellowBold>raid bosses</> and the Trading Post.
Using rare skills in battle should yield tremendous results! Try to collect as many rare skills as you possibly can.
Hmm... to think the space created by the Dark Mystic was connected to the tunnel beneath Ivory Tower.
The tunnel beneath Ivory Tower? It’s where you can collect special herbs used for crafting <YellowBold>Elixirs</>.
You want to go there again? Well, how about this for now.
You can get there from the Dungeons menu.
It’s also known as an Extraction Dungeon.
You can combine the available herbs to craft <YellowBold>Elixirs</> that permanently increase your stats.
However, the Nebullite in the tunnel means you cannot stay there for long. Extended exposure will drive any sentient beings insane.
As a result, you can only extract a set number of herbs per day.
The existence of magical herbs means the gods are on our side. We can craft <YellowBold>Elixirs</> with them.
Time is short, so listen carefully.
In order to craft an Elixir...
Here, you can craft Elixirs. Crafting requires <YellowBold>4 herbs</>.
Different Elixirs have different effects, so choose carefully.
The materials are ready. Let’s start!
Elixirs <YellowBold>are used the moment they are crafted</>! You should feel stronger already!
You can also acquire materials for Elixirs from Daily Dungeons, monsters, and the Shop.
Collect as many <YellowBold>herbs and essences</> as you can, because they are crucial for becoming stronger.

Let me teach you how to ride that Black Bear!
Pay attention, and you’ll be a rider in no time!
Head over to the main menu.
See how the Black Bear is selected?
Make sure the summoned Black Bear enters battle in order to mount it.
Let’s head out so you can mount it.
This guy is clearly attached to you already! Please raise the Black Bear well!
Be careful at Mount Eborga since Kresous lives there. Not to mention, demons appear in Summoning Stone Dungeons.
Feldheim might be in trouble right about now!
Enter the Summoning Stone Dungeon through here!
Oh! Be sure to gather other players before you go into a Summoning Stone Dungeon. It is quite dangerous inside!
Adventures are more fun with companions. Here, you can add friends and greet each other to send and receive <YellowBold>Friendship Points</>.
Oh! I have some friends to introduce you to!
Making friends has many advantages! You can embark on adventures together and exchange friendship! With your combined strength, you can even defeat huge monsters!
It’s easy. I’ll explain it to you!
You can <YellowBold>create a party</> and recruit other players.
<YellowBold>Manual party search</> allows you to find and join another player’s party.
If you use <YellowBold>Auto-Join</>, you’ll automatically join a party that matches your preferences.
Want to learn about the Trading Post? Tap the main menu button meow.
Meow, tap the Trading Post button.
You must have some items that are too good to sell in the shop but are wasting away in your inventory!
In the Trading Post, you can strike a deal on your extra items, or purchase rare goods from other players!
Set your search conditions, and the Trading Post employee will show you a myriad of items that you might like!
Sell something meow and see for yourself!
Over here. This is what you want to use.
Just list your item and sale price, and we’ll take care of the rest! Meow, I do gotta warn you - there is a limit on how cheap you make things.
Hold on! Is that a <YellowBold>Grade A</> item? The Trading Post only works with <YellowBold>S</> or higher items...
Don’t take it purrsonally! We have to make sure our stock matches the quality our customers have come to expect.
Use this to keep up with your bids and check if your items have sold!
Let’s review how Daily Quests work.
You can receive and complete up to <YellowBold>12</> quests every day.
However, you can only have up to 3 quests active at once.
Choose your quests carefully - the difficulty, and the rewards, are based on the quest’s grade.
Here, you can see how to complete the quest.
You can also check the quest’s rewards.
Let’s start a quest and see for ourselves!
See how the quest content changes.
You can complete quests you have taken on, or they will <YellowBold>be completed automatically once a certain amount of time passes</>.
Or, if you’re feeling impatient, you can <YellowBold>spend Adena to complete quests instantly</>.
You can check your Daily Quest completion rate and acquire additional rewards here.
Here, you can change all the quests on standby.
<YellowBold>Changing quests</> efficiently should prove helpful in growing stronger.
Take advantage of it now, or you might regret it later!
Now we’ll go over Weekly Quests!
Here, you can take on quests that can be completed over one week.
You can complete up to <YellowBold>15 quests daily</>.
You’ll have to work on quests consistently if you want to reap the rewards!
You can review details of ongoing quests here.
Let’s start a quest! Tap Accept Quest.
Finish Weekly Quests consistently and reap the rewards!
Remember - the most important thing about Weekly Quests is to <YellowBold>do them every day</>!
You’re finally eligible to make <YellowBold>clan donations</>!
Donations are what keep clans running smoothly!
Let’s go over how to make donations.
Your donation will go further if you use Proof of Blood or Red Starstones,
but acquiring those can be a little tricky.
I’ll share some Proof of Blood with you this time.
Try donating some Proof of Blood.
Be sure to collect the donation rewards!
The contribution scores show which clan members have made the most donations.
Oh! I almost forgot about <YellowBold>Clan Coins</>. You’ll receive Clan Coins every time you donate, and you can use them to make purchases in the Clan Shop or buy clan buffs.
Now, let’s get out of here.
This is the Clan Shop I mentioned earlier.
There are items here for both improving the clan and for your own benefit, so look around.
Some items can only be purchased after fulfilling certain conditions, but I’m sure you won’t have any trouble with that.
What? You’re not in a <YellowBold>clan</> yet?!
Let me remind you how to join one.
There are so many benefits to joining a clan!
I’m certain you won’t regret it.
I hope you’re settling into your clan just fine.
It’s time for me to teach you about something new.
Let’s go back to the Clan menu.
I want to show you Clan Achievements!
All clan members contribute to Clan Achievements, and the entire clan receives rewards when they are completed!
Individual rewards are sent to each individual member.
<YellowBold>Clan rewards are sent to Clan Storage</>.
However, rewards are only available if achievements are completed in a timely manner, so the whole clan will have to work together.
Achievements require a great deal of cooperation to fulfill, but working together will bring your clan closer together!
How do you like being in a clan?
There’s something very important I need to tell you about clans.
Let’s go to the Clan menu.
Players from the same clan can enter the Clan Dungeon together and challenge powerful bosses.
Clan members must work together to conquer the Clan Dungeon - it’s the ultimate test of a clan’s strength!
It’ll be a hard battle - but the rewards are worth it!
Challenging the Clan Dungeon is good for the clan, and for improving your own abilities!
Cooperate with other clan members, and together you’ll be unstoppable!
Welcome. You can check your <YellowBold>quest progress</> here.
Here, you can view <YellowBold>ongoing quests</>, <GreenBold>completed quests</>, and quests to be done all at once.
Look! You can even view additional <YellowBold>rewards</>.
Whoa! You’re ready to transfer classes? That’s incredible!
I have a message for your regarding taking the class transfer test.
The Silverlight Mercenaries are granting new classes to anyone strong enough to pass their test.
You can learn <YellowBold>new skills</> upon transferring classes, enabling you to become even stronger than you are now.
Look, this is the first test.
To pass the first test, you have to defeat 50 monsters.
This will gauge your basic combat abilities.
I have faith that you’ll pass with flying colors!
The next test will be revealed once you pass the first.
Once you pass all seven tests, you’ll be able to transfer classes.
And then... you’ll be even stronger!!!
I’ll see the new, stronger you next time!
I thought you might need more Adena around now...
Here, I’ll show you the best place to find Adena.
This is the home of Kresous the Gold Dragon.
Defeat Kresous to loot his stash of Adena!
There’s a daily entry limit for the Adena dungeon, so make the most of every attempt!
I look forward to hearing about your victory over the dragon!
Hey! Want to hear about a great place to find equipment?
Look no further than this special dungeon!
Protect the <YellowBold>Holy Artifact</>, and you’re sure to find all the <YellowBold>equipment</> you need.
There’s just one catch. The Equipment Dungeon is only open to players in <YellowBold>a party</>, and you can only enter <YellowBold>a few times a day</>.
Are you perhaps running short on scrolls for enhancing equipment?
Unseal the Holy Artifact and acquire Enhancement Scrolls! Do your best, because there’s a <YellowBold>daily entry limit</>!
Enhancing your weapons is the <YellowBold>simplest and most powerful</> way to become stronger!
A little birdie told me you might need some help becoming stronger.
I’ll show you a good place to level up!
Here, you can acquire large amounts of Exp. at once... but don’t rely too heavily on it, since there’s a <YellowBold>daily entry limit</>.
Challenge yourself, and you’ll level up in no time! I bet you’ll be really buff next time I see you!

I can’t believe you are already so strong. You continue to amaze me.

I have prepared a gift to celebrate how strong you have become.

Go find Staris at the Wasteland. He will present you with a very useful gift.

Are you finally taking some interest in crafting?

Hahaha!!! That makes me so happy!

As you know, Grade UR can only be acquired through crafting! I’ll tell you about it, so listen carefully!
To start, place the equipment you want to craft here!
You’ll need the recipe for the equipment you want to craft!
Next, you need rare minerals or wood!
What was the next thing... Oh, yeah! You need materials like Radiant Upgrade Stones!
And then you need the Scraps acquired from salvaging weapons or armor!
You can make Grade UR equipment as long as you have those four things!

Oh! I almost forgot!

You can only craft Grade UR equipment by using Lv. 30 Grade SR equipment!

Also, Grade UR equipment maintains its enhancement, limit break, substat, and attribute details!

And the four materials can all enhance equipment. Be sure to enhance your equipment whenever you collect a type of material. You’ll surely enjoy how much stronger your equipment becomes!

Of course, Grade UR equipment crafted using all four material types would be incomparably stronger! Hahaha!

You can get Titles based on your accomplishments as you journey across Aden.

These titles increase your stats. Of course, higher grade titles are more difficult to acquire but offer greater bonus stats!

Now, I’ll tell you how to equip those titles.
Here, check out the titles you’ve acquired.
You must learn the titles you have acquired in order to get bonus stats.
Your stats increase simply from learning titles, so you can equip any title you want without worrying about losing the stats from others!
Try equipping the title you learned just now.

Be careful! Certain titles you acquire can be stolen by other people. The title for 1st place in the Arena is one such title.

That’s all there is to know about titles. Go forth and find some of your own!
Talking Island’s the perfect place to get stronger!
Watch out for monsters from here on out!
We uphold the security of Talking Island!
Good equipment will keep you alive!
Hear ye! An auction for Gludio specialties starts soon!
Buy your tickets to Gludio from me!
See the Obelisk of Victory on Talking Island!
A harbor is only a harbor when it’s bustling with people!
Tourists have been flocking to Talking Island lately.
Orcs? What do you mean Orcs?!
The ship to Gludio embarks soon, so board quickly.
Did you see those tourists Some of them were my type!
Ah, a perfect day to set sail!
Hehe. I wonder if I’ll be discharged from the army...
Here are Talking Island specialties! We have golden fur!
This can only live here on Talking Island.
You need one of these to truly tour Talking Island.
Hehe. Our precious child is already 3 years old!
Adventurers foolishly risk their lives just for money...
Fishing at Talking Island is the best - this fish is huge!
You think it’s true that Orcs appeared north of town?
Use this spot to move to other regions.
Join a clan! Comrades are a huge source of support!
Enhance equipment to easily deal with your enemies!!
I’m selling Soulshots that deal more damage to monsters!
We’ll take care of them Orcs.
Talking Island Town is safe now.
There are some odd things going on here...
The quicker you can get off the island, the better.
I heard there are more than 10,000 Orcs to the north.
Orcs have appeared in the north!!
Don’t worry! You’ll be discharged from duty safely.
Damn Orcs! I’ll avenge my comrades!
We can’t lose this battle. My family is hiding in the town.
These Orcs attacked just before my discharge...
If we lose against these Orcs, they’ll reach the town.
We’re holding the Orcs at bay with magic for now, but...
Please enlist Talking Island’s hunting troop!
Have you come to join the hunting troop?
I’ll be watching to see if anything funny happens!
There’s no need to go easy!
Cut them down with one swing!
T-thank you! It was so scary!
Soulshots are just what you need for fighting golems!
I would’ve fought if I had my staff!
You were crying and hiding earlier!
Einhasad told me she would be sending you.
I saw your incredible performance! Thank you so much!
What’s all this?! It’s not even the age of pirates!
Ahh... I knew I shouldn’t have come here...
Tickets to Talking Island Harbor are this way.
Won’t you enlist as a Gludin soldier?
La-di-da... Where could have my friends gone...
Next time, I’ll be the hero instead of you!
Welcome, this is Gludin Harbor town.
So you’re the one Einhasad sent.
Use this spot to travel where you want.
Register here to participate in Castle Siege.
Selling Soulshots is a hobby of mine.
Store items if your inventory is full.
Goodness, it’s noisy. I just want to live and fish quietly.
I’ll discount your bill since you’re our town’s hero!
We’re tasked with protecting this place.
*Sigh*... When will our shift be over...
I’m giving this to you at a great price!
Not before I become a sphinx cat!
We’re tasked with protecting this place.
There are lots of outlaws. Be careful.
You wouldn’t have any smuggled goods, would you?
It’s a member of the Silverlight Mercenaries!!! Welcome!
The recent ambush was thwarted a Silverlight Mercenary.
Oh really? That mercenary was so cool!
No way I’m going to an island. I’m made to live in cities.
Ah, the good old days when we traveled by boat!
Thank you! My passengers are safe thanks to you!
You defeated those pirates, right? That’s incredible!
Careful. Here on out, there will be Ol Mahums.
Are you enlisting to hunt Ol Mahum?
Safety of the hostage is our foremost priority. Got it?
Are you crazy? Me, I wouldn’t go into the graveyard!
You’ll need potions to hunt Ol Mahums!
Don’t be a cheapskate - give me more, you scrooge!
Nothing beats Soulshots when hunting the Undead!
Hey you, adventurer! You should buy some potions.
Preparation is basic in battle! So, you should buy some...
Sheesh, all these Undead make business hard...
Hey! Make a coffin for yourself while you’re here! Ha!
You should be careful, ghosts appear here. Haha.
Really! I really saw a ghost! Trust me!
There was definitely a blonde female Elf ghost!
Quit lying so much, you liar!
Seriously? You really saw a Chaotic?
You aren’t lying, right? You are also a likely suspect!
I’m telling the truth! What about me says I’m a Chaotic?!
I’m sure even the person over there is stronger than you!
Be careful starting from Gludio - there will be Chaotics.
Have you come to investigate the missing incident?
Check that guy out! Word is, he’s a Silverlight Mercenary.
If only I could have joined the Silverlight Mercenaries...
I’ve been requested to investigate the disappearance...
As expected of a harbor town, it’s brimming with energy!
Hurry up! Let’s go over there too!
Phew. Can’t you go a bit slower?
Slow down, won’t you? My legs hurt.
Hey, you! Do something about them!
This is a lot of trouble after coming all the way here.
Won’t you join the hunting squad?
No use in sitting idly by! Hurry up and join us!
Can’t believe these damn lizards ransacked our town...!
Why isn’t the ruler sending out reinforcements?
Damn it... Just you watch, I’ll definitely survive.
I’ll survive and see my family.
Only fools underestimate Bugbears for their low intellect!
Keeping the missing members safe is our top priority.
You the mercenary who hunts monsters? Take a breather!
My sword is ideal for cutting them lizards!
The monsters are close... I hope things will be ok.
Did any Lizardman happen to follow you?
It’s impressive to pass through the Devastated Farmland!
Ah... I wonder when I can go home...
How many more of these monsters do we have to kill?
Mom... I want to see my mom...
It’s dangerous here. Go back if you’re not a combatant.
Report to the captain to join the hunting squad.
Joining the hunting squad if you need a job.
We can’t let Lizardmen continue coming over!
Damn lizards are constantly looking for opportunities.
Hmm... Should I join to hunt monsters?
Won’t we have a difficult time at our level?
Let’s just go for it! I doubt we’ll die.
We’ll turn those Bugbears into shish kabab!
I heard Sir Vaughn would command the recovery operation.
Windawood’s revival is bound to happen soon...
We need to recover Windawood quickly.
Windawood’s tragedies need to end soon. Tsktsk
I hear the attack on Gludio Castle will start soon?!
Ah, I’d love to participate in a Castle Siege!
I’d cut my enemies down in one fell swoop!
Boo! There’s going to be a Castle Siege without me...!
Recruiting participants for the Gludio Castle Siege, eh...?
An Elf ruling a Human kingdom doesn’t sound too bad!
Don’t get any funny ideas of applying to the castle clan!
I’ll definitely become a beautiful Knight of the castle clan!
These Soulshots are best for hunting Lizardman!
Keep a ready formation as we make preparations!
Did you perhaps see any more scattered soldiers?
Have the Ol Mahums gone crazy?
Why are Bandits expressing interest in crystals?
Can’t believe the Undead are suddenly running rampant!
Everyone stay focused so we don’t scatter!
Windawood’s recovery is almost complete! Onwards!
It’s time we drive the Orcs from our home!
Beautiful Windawood has fallen into such disarray...
Damn you Orcs. I’ll have my vengeance!
I heard screams coming from the surrounding area...
Buy some potions before you go see them Orcs.
That’s not enough Soulshots to deal with Orcs.
Uh... Uh oh... Some items seem to be missing.
When will I move all this...
On duty! No problems at all!
When will the merchant supplies arrive...?
Hmm, our goods are running low.
You’re woefully under-prepared. Buy some potions!
These Soulshots do the trick when dealing with ants.
What could’ve caused such an ant to be created?
There’s a huge Queen in the underground Ant Nest.
Queen Ant? I wonder how beautiful she is!
I hear Ivory Tower Wizards died mysteriously?
Who could’ve killed the Ivory Tower Wizards?
To the north is Dion Territory. You know who’s wanted?
Be sure to identify yourself before heading to Dion.
They’re not allowing me passage into Dion Territory!
I’m sick and tired of this desert!
Aren’t you thirsty? Have some potion!
Take something from the Campsite with you!
Be careful. I hear Kazir appears right in front!
I’ve heard of Kazir! It’s the desert’s predator?
You’ll need potions to traverse the rough Wasteland!
Hey, you! Your sword is rusty!
I shouldn’t be selling items right now...
Did you see that kid from before?
Just say the word if you need my help!
Hahaha. I wonder if Gus is running the business well.
Looks like I’ll be scolded by Sara again!
Oh, a kid. Don’t you need a drug to make you taller?
You’ll grow big as a Bugbear if you eat this!
Woah! But why are you so small, Mr. Cat?
Ehh, what a liar! There’s no drug like that!
I can’t go outside because of the monsters.
Ah... I need to gather Herbs...
Will we drink today as well?
Great! See you when we’re done with our shift!
Did you see that girl just now?
Of course! She seemed mysterious, no?
They say spiders are eating Humans!
They say there are tons of spiders to the north!
You will not leave this place alive!
Ah sheesh. I’m telling the truth!
I personally struck the Orc Captain on its head!
Orcs have made it all the way to Dion Castle?
We need to hurry and support Dion Castle - it’s in danger!
Pfft! You defeated the Orc Captain? You and what army?
Your lies are too incredulous! Hahaha!
Careful, the Agricultural Area is full of Lizardman.
We made sure the Lizardmen and couldn’t go anywhere.
Cruma Tower has been emitting energy.
Cruma Tower... I definitely want to challenge it!
Tower of Lesser Giants? I wanna uncover its secrets!
I hear the Dark Brotherhood is after the Cruma Tower...
Hehe. Catch me if you can!
The attack on Dion Castle gets my blood boiling!
I wonder who the ruler of Dion Territory will be!
We don’t have enough passion to make it... *sob*...
I-if you do it, I’ll do it too!
Ah, I’d love to be in a clan as cool as the castle clan!
Hmm. Should I apply to join the castle clan?
They’re looking for clans for the Dion Castle Siege!
No simple tasks anywhere? Like capturing a cat...?
Shhh! That cat hasn’t noticed us yet! Get him!
Let’s take one or two of these mangy cats!
Now! He’s distracted by the kid!
You want to join? You’ll be an accomplice too.
Look! That con artist cat will rip off more people.
You plan on ripping off that kid too? Sheesh!
I won’t let you get away this time!
This spell will swallow you all whole.
Ah! It’s dangerous! Buy these Soulshots!
Have you come to see Cruma Tower?
The tower of Lesser Giants - it’s getting me all riled up!
Hmm... As expected of a swamp, it’s chilly.
Can’t you light a stronger fire?
One, two... huh? A few seem to be missing.
I can’t believe I’m investigating goods at this age!
Welcome to Feldheim Excavation Unit research camp!
I hear there are tons of magical lifeforms in Cruma!
Ugh... Why do I always have to organize the documents?
You should’ve organized regularly. Look at this mess!
Be careful going forward - there’s a lot of corpses!
If you find anyone we lost contact with, bring them here!
What’s needed in this dangerous place? This potion!
Race isn’t a factor when doing business!
Buy more Soulshots for the Shrieking Hallows, okay?
Hey, won’t you help in the operation?
This isn’t a good place for adventure.
Are you making apt preparations against the Undead?
May Einhasad’s Blessing be with you.
I pray that you would give them rest.
Watching them is making me sad.
Be careful if you don’t want to end up like them.
It’s dangerous to step outside of the Furnace.
We’ve come to observe the Army of Agony.
Are you an adventurer? Giran is currently sealed off.
Giran is sealed until the Shrieking Hallows quiet down.
You can’t go to Giran right now.
The ruler ordered entry be prohibited.
We have to face that army of death...?
Hey there beautiful! Need some weapons?
With a dress so pretty, beware the Gorgon’s collections!
Come! Buy some equipment with those full pockets!
Don’t let your guard down with so many people around!
Don’t follow strangers even if they offer you food.
Can you remember the way back home?
Come in for a moment and have a glass of tasty rum!
Hey there you cool adventurer. Come in for a moment.
Aren’t you tired from traveling? Come in and take a rest!
Welcome to the Town of Giran!
Welcome to Giran, the center of commerce!
Thugs hang out in here. Be sure not to go inside.
Any further in and it will be dangerous. Head back.
Ready to head to the Gorgon Flower Garden?
Hand in your will when you’re done filling it out.
Never look Medusa in her eyes. Got it?
What do you want? You want to go a round?
Turn around before you get hurt, okay?
What are you looking at? Bug off!
You hear Giran and Oren’s relationship has gotten worse?
I’m anxious... You don’t think there will be a war, right?
I really want to visit Oren once...
Adventure and whatnot... Kids these days tsk tsk...
I’ll need to make connections when the envoys come.
Come in for a bowl of warm soup!
Are you from out of town? Come stay a night here!
You look exhausted. Come and get some rest.
Won’t you buy this one ring?
For the low price of 10 million Adena! It’s a steal!
Count and make sure it’s the right amount.
Keep your guard up, the merchant will be here soon.
We’re trading for rare magical materials - watch carefully.
Mm... Should we have a taste to see if it’s cooking well?
It’s lacking something... Would a bit of magical MSG do?
Hey, what are you looking at? Stealing our secrets!?
Vegetables! Buy some vegetables on the cheap!
Got this from Dion and bypassed the Shrieking Hallows!
Have a taste! A taste of the Plains!
I’m telling you that Mischa glanced at me!
I’m certain Gerard is interested in me!
What should I do...? Should I start a conversation?
What? First time seeing a cat?
You’ll be in for a beating if you underestimate me, punk!
Stick around if you wanna get beaten down.
What’s so scary about that witch Medusa?
Let’s join the hunt! What’s the worst that could happen?
Should I join the Gorgon hunt? It’d be good experience...
I don’t wanna become one of Medusa’s playthings...
I’m too young and pretty to die... Hunt or not to hunt...!
Drink this - you’ll be immune to Medusa’s gaze!
Afraid of heading to Oren? Buy this disguise tool!
This fluoroscope helps catch spies and earn bounties!
Hey, are you a Silverlight Mercenary? I’m envious.
All adventurers want to join the Silverlight Mercenaries.
I’ll be a wizard like Lucien of the Silverlight Mercenaries.

I dedicated my life to a lie?!
- Please calm down, Grace!
Let me go! You don’t know how I feel!

Yeah... Even this temple itself is a lie then...
Yeah... Yeah, that’s it. That’s it...
Pay for your sins with your death!
The light is gone! There’s no hope for you now!
Oh... Oh, no! The sun is being blocked!
We’re doomed! The sun is almost completely gone!
I don’t know what a Giran aristocrat is doing here.
Hey, you there! You’re smuggling, aren’t you?
W-what? What are you talking about? I am an officer of the army!
We caught him red-handed! Arrest him!
Don’t worry, Alexander. I’m sure this is all just a misunderstanding.
I’ll send you to the gallows!
So you’re Zaken! You... You’ve ruined everything!
You’ve ruined her chance to become Aden’s Archduchess...
I heard enough about you from Trisha.
Do you remember abusing her when she was a child?
She shudders at a mere thought of you.
It’s a happy life compared to the one she would’ve suffered with you!
Don’t pretend you’re doing this for her! Hypocrite!
Ugh... You! What have you done to me?!
I took over your body. You no longer have freedom.
I will take this hypocrite away.
Follow me to my flagship if you can!
S-save me! My body is... Moving on its own! Help!
It seems battle is inevitable because of Zaken’s minions.
That was just a Phantom of Zaken. His main body must be somewhere else.
I think he’s waiting for you to come to him, with Sir Alexander as his hostage.
You must be wary of the flagship where Zaken awaits.
Zaken is able to create an Outworld, different from reality.
Within his realm, you must avoid night.
During nightfall, his power reaches its height and
no one is able to stop him.
He’s... done something strange to me...
Grrr... Huh? What’s wrong with me?!
What happened to me? Zaken you bastard!!!
It looks like he’s gotten extremely aggressive when he mutated! Watch out!
Hate... I hate you all! Look at me... It’s all your fault!
What was that? Zaken? Where is he?
Kill... then kill again! Kill each other to survive!
Even if you manage to withstand this hell... another one awaits!
We’ve become mere entertainment for Zaken to enjoy...
Ugh... We can’t... go easy on this monster.
We must defeat him no matter what!
Meow there, adventurer! Do you need necessities?!
My wares require less coin than the Common Shop, so come right meow!
You should pay attention to how you look even if you’re an adventurer!
I’ll make you look amazing! Come find me!

Clear a Daily Dungeon on Easy Mode

Woah! You already defeated 50 monsters? That’s incredible!

Your next test is to clear an Easy Daily Dungeon! These bosses are known to be very powerful.

Only true combatants can defeat them! Go and prove yourself!

You are the first to have defeated the boss of the holy ground so quickly! You really are something, you know that?

The next test is... Hmm... Well, it’s not so much of a test. You need to collect C-grade items.

You will need to level up your equipment as you fight! What you need at such moments are C-grade items. Collect and use them for enhancing your equipment! They’ll be really helpful!

Well? Leveling up your equipment with C-grade items really helped, right?

Now that you’ve leveled up your equipment, let’s check out your abilities.

Oh, you think you’ll be fighting monsters? Nice try! You need to show off your abilities against other players!

It would be a shame if you lost in the Arena without putting up a fight!

Hmm, this should work! One fight in the Arena! Just participate one time in the Arena - easy, right?

Don’t be a baby! When I was a newbie, I participated in 100 fights! Go on. Now, it’s your turn!

What?! You already fought in the Arena?

Well, then we should move on to the next test.

You need to earn 10,000 Adena.

This is a test of your hunting and finance management skills! You could die at a crucial moment if you don’t do a good job of managing your finances!

Go earn 10,000 Adena!

On to the next test!

Now you need to enhance your equipment.

Equipment is as important to a mercenary as their own life! Enhance your equipment diligently if you want to survive on the battlefield!

Try enhancing one piece of equipment!

Wow, is it already the final test? Congratulations! Looks like the higher ups have high expectations of you for a reason.

Because of your extraordinary abilities, we’ve decided you should hunt Kyrios Blood Ranger! Kyrios is a terrible monster that kills Humans!

Only the most talented mercenaries are asked to hunt it! You should be flattered the higher-ups want you on the task!

I've never seen them invite a rookie before! It’s proof that really see your potential!

This is your last test, so don't blow it! It will be tough but I wish you the best of luck!

Oh! By the way - this is going to be a really tough fight, so take some friends!

A creation of Gran Kain, Humans have well-balanced stats and adapt quickly to any class. Humans worship Einhasad, the goddess of light.
Einhasad formed the Elves from water, making them agile and light on their feet. They are protected by the goddess of water, Eva.
Dark Elves specialize in dark magic. They used to worship the goddess Shilen until their race’s downfall led them to deny their faith.
Einhasad created the Dwarves from land. They have strong physiques and are handy. They worship Maphr, the goddess of land.

A place filled magic energy, this is the academy where Elves taught magic to Humans. Humans built their foundations here to eventually become the rulers of the continent.
When the Elves ruled the continent, this floor was only opened for Humans with exceptional talent. The magical energy here is stronger than on the first floor.
A cave filled with Giant Ants that adapted and survived in the Wasteland that was created by the gigantic black magic explosion.
The ants created an even more complicated maze here to protect their precious goods. Only ants can find their way around.
A moving fortress and science facility used by ancient giants for biological experiments aimed to create a new type of lifeform. Used to protect the laboratory.
Staying true to the tower’s original intention, this floor has many biological research laboratories. It is filled with the Giants’ magical energy.
A space formed when the meteorite Nebulite fell on earth. It was originally a laboratory and library, but was closed down in the aftermath of the Rampant Wizards Incident.
There was originally an alchemic laboratory here, but it is now overrun with hard, rock-like mushrooms that grew through the ground.
There are many powerful Evil Summoning Stones installed by the Dark Brotherhood that have yet to be discovered. You must enter Outworld and defeat monsters to remove them.

Shunaiman, the Emperor of Elmoreden, used this place to store gold required to build the Tower of Insolence. The structure was forgotten with Shunaiman’s death, and now it is occupied by Kresous the Gold Dragon.
The Elven temple that houses the Water Crystal blessed by Eva. Hardin ordered the Silverlight Mercenaries to guard the temple in order to protect the Water Crystal from the Dark Brotherhood.
The Ivory Tower Wizard’s laboratory, as well as his place of sealing. The Human test subjects he used to study the Nebulite still roam around.
This area used to be the home of the Fairies, but when the Fairies fled from the threat of war, monsters took the land for themselves.
The countless trees in the Forest of Secrets block the rays of the sun. The area seems to have been destroyed by the monsters.
This is where many Fairies met their end while trying to escape the Fairy Hunt. The ominous crimson fog serves as a reminder of the Fairies’ last stand.
Protect the Shaman who lifts the spell from the sealed Holy Artifact and clear the dungeon to acquire Enhancement Scrolls.
Destroy the dimensional gate that summons monsters and acquire rewards.
A secret mine formed underneath the Ivory Tower that stores Nebulite the meteorite. Many herbs with mysterious powers grow here.
