Since humans killed his entire family,
he believed that power was the only way 
to save the orcs.

One day, when an unknown Orc, <RedBold>Ramog</>,
gained immense power unlike any other,
and became the new <RedBold>Timak Orc Leader</>,
he could not help but yearn to be like him
and follow him.

He vowed that one day he would be a
powerful Orc like <RedBold>Ramog</>. That was his one
and only goal in life. To accomplish his goals,
he led the annihilation of the <GreenBold>Timak Orc</>
<GreenBold>Shaman Village.</>

By coincidence, Nebulite shards are now
stuck in his heart.
Days away from death, he was one day saved by an
<RedBold>unidentified shadow</>.

When he opened his eyes, he realized that he 
now had amazing but terrifying strength.
He called himself the warrior, <RedBold>Ramog</>,
and killed any orcs that got in his way.
He then became the new tribal leader of the
<RedBold>Timak Orcs</>.

In his constant search for power, he began to
 look for the power of <RedBold>Paagrio</>, the god of orcs.
Eventually, he attacked <GreenBold>The Timak Orc</>
<GreenBold>Shaman Village</> where <GreenBold>Paagrio’s Altar</>
was located.
The Shamans who tried to stop him were
annihilated.
The ritual to gain the power of <RedBold>Paagrio</> is now
almost complete.

He was once the <RedBold>Guardian Knight</>
of <RedBold>Countess Trisha</>.
Though he is an incorruptible soul,
he is solely sworn to <RedBold>Countess Trisha</>.
He will serve her, no matter the decisions
she may make.

<RedBold>Trisha</> was born into one of Giran’s 
aristocratic families.
She always wanted to escape her boring life,
which prompted her to pursue a forbidden
love.
A love so powerful she left everything of her 
old life behind to pursue it.
Boranta received the power of the Nebulite shards from Ramog. He is able to use fire with his newfound strength.
Nebulite shards are embedded in the heart of Ramog. He is able to use magic more powerful than any orcs who have come before him.
Leonard was transformed by magic. He is different than the average vampire in that he has magical abilities.
Trisha, who was transformed by a lesser giant like her lover, is unlike the average vampire in that she has magical abilities.

The wizards of the <GreenBold>Ivory Tower</>
endeavor to find a portion of the shards that were stolen.

During their investigation
they discovered <BlueBold>Leanis</>, one of the wizards 
from the <GreenBold>Ivory Tower</>, had disappeared.
While searching for her tracks
they stumble upon a village where the <RedBold>Timak Orc Shamans</> live.

The wizards deduce that <BlueBold>Laenis</> has been kidnapped
by the <RedBold>Orcs</>
and enter the village to save her.
However, they are forced to retreat after experiencing 
a strength they had never encountered before from the <RedBold>Orcs</>.
The wizards of the <GreenBold>Ivory Tower</> have doubled down
on investigating the <RedBold>Orcs</>, and have recruited
the <BlueBold>Silverlight Mercenaries</> to help rescue <BlueBold>Laenis</>.

The <RedBold>Countess Trisha</>, who was once dearly beloved
by the Lord of Giran,

suddenly disappeared, causing an uproar among the Giran
nobility.
They knew that if this information was leaked to the hostile land
of Oren, they’d be put in an unfavorable situation politically.
Knowing this, the Lord of Giran secretly deployed <BlueBold>Captain Tark</>
to lead a search party to find her.

After hearing that the <RedBold>Countess Trisha</> was last seen with
her <RedBold>Guardian Knight</> in <GreenBold>Giran Harbor</>, <BlueBold>Captain Tark</> and
his search party disguised themselves as Blood Rangers
from the Devil’s Isle and secretly began searching <GreenBold>Devil’s Isle</>.
However, after being exposed to various dangerous situations,
<BlueBold>Captain Tark</> is forced to request help from the
<BlueBold>Silverlight Mercenaries</>.

Head to the
crazed Orc village!

Find the Giran soldiers
and the Countess!

<RedBold>Dike</> was created by Gran Kain with the help 
of Maphr, and is a sentient Lesser Giant 
statue.

By orders of her creator, Gran Kain,
she judges those unworthy of entering 
the Temple.

<RedBold>Hagios</> is a Lesser Giant warrior that was close to
Gran Kain.

Held in the highest esteem by Gran Kain, Hagios
volunteered himself without hesitation when
Gran Kain was searching for a Guardian for his secret experiment.
Gran Kain’s creation, Dike, is special in that she is more of a magical construct than a lifeform.
Hagios did not hesitate to modify his own body in order to protect the Temple for all eternity.

Rescue Feldheim’s Archaeologists
and uncover Gran Kain’s secrets!

<BlueBold>Feldheim</> had access to the Class 2 Magnadin materials archive.

There, he discovered that <RedBold>Gran Kain</>, coveting <BlueBold>Einhasad</>’s 
authority, ran creation experiments through the records of the 
Lesser Giants. With brimming curiosity, he led his 
archaeologists to the <GreenBold>Wasteland</> on an expedition to find a 
temple mentioned in the archive.

After continuous research and excavation, Feldheim and his 
archaeologists find the entrance to the <GreenBold>Temple of Creation</>.
However, they are captured by <RedBold>Kel Mahum</> hordes who have 
been worshipping at the temple.

<BlueBold>Nia</> barely escapes amidst the chaos and requests help from the
<BlueBold>Silverlight Mercenaries</> to rescue the archaeologists. <BlueBold>Hardin</>, 
receiving this message of distress, dispatches the greatest of 
the Mercenaries on a rescue mission.
You can only claim rewards by clicking “Claim”, meow!

Roles are assigned using the<YellowBold>4 Elements</>.

Challengers must <YellowBold>fulfill actions</> that match
<YellowBold>their assigned Element</> in order to protect their comrades.

<RedBold>- Fire: Attack Dike with Increased Atk.</>
<BlueBold>- Water: Quickly defeat the Fire Spirit.</>
<YellowBold>- Earth: Take charge of fighting Dike with increased durability.</>
<GreenBold>- Wind: Quickly defeat the Earth Spirit</>
<GreenBold>to help in defeating the Fire Spirit.</>

A powerful, destructive attack is cast
using <YellowBold>one of the 4 Elements</>.

Challengers must obtain <YellowBold>a superior Element</>
to Dike’s Element to survive.

<RedBold>- Fire consumes Wind.</>
<BlueBold>- Water quenches Fire.</>
<YellowBold>- Earth blocks the flow of Water.</>
<GreenBold>- Wind erodes Earth.</>

An <RedBold>Elemental Column</> is set into the ground.

If the column is not destroyed within the time limit,
the column <YellowBold>is infused with the Elements and starts to attack</>.

<RedBold>- Fire: Fireballs are cast in 4 directions.</>
<GreenBold>- Wind: Lightning crashes down at any location.</>

Uses the element of Water to
churn up a <YellowBold>Giant Tidal Wave</> that sweeps enemies away.

<YellowBold>- Applies Petrification to 1 Adventurer.</>
<YellowBold>- The Tidal Wave can be blocked if Petrified.</>
<YellowBold>- Suffocation may occur if Petrification continues.</>
<YellowBold>- Shattering rocks will remove Petrification.</>

<YellowBold>Resonates with one of the 4 Elements</> to

Lady Nine, a Black Market Merchant

I know that you are a member of the Silverlight Mercenaries. I was hoping to entrust you with a task. Keep in mind, it can be dangerous.

The Ivory Tower Wizards are not sure of the cause, but a monster that was previously sealed has been set free. The proof of its release is the Seal of Death found on those Parasite Zombies.

The monster grows stronger with time so we must defeat him as soon as possible. Let’s gather up and burn the Seals of Death. It seems to be the source of his growing power...
You truly live up to the Silverlight Mercenaries’ reputation. You are already well known among the bailiffs. I’m sure we’ll work together again in the future.

Hey, can I see you for a minute? You must be quite an adventurer to be wandering around here.

Would you help me out? I’ll pay you well!

First things first, I need you to gather Obsidian Golem hearts for me. They fetch quite a price.

If lucky, you’ll also find an Ancient Obsidian Golem. Get me its heart as well! I’ll pay you even more for that!
Not too shabby, if I do say so myself! Here, hand over the hearts. This is your payment. Lend me a hand whenever you have some time, alright?

Woah! Long time no see! What brings you to Oren? Haha, same old, same old- still doing anything for the right price! Anyway, have you heard of Grandis?

I was hoping you would bring me his equipment! Anything goes in business when you’re having an off-season. Hahaha.
Ha! To be honest, I didn’t have any desire to jump into that fiasco. I would’ve run away if I was in your shoes. You are incredible!

Hey there! Did you come to me in search of a job? Well, let’s get to it then. There are many Oel Mahums in Oren.

Those monsters carry a lot of items we can sell! We need to be aggressive and on the attack. Rob them clean and bring me back everything!
I wasn’t worried in the slightest! I know fully well how talented you are, <YellowBold>[player]</>. Don’t even think about asking for more money, I knew the risks!

Hey, over here! I am Jayhan, a great Dark Mystic. Unfortunately, I’m in this sorry state because of a damn spell!

I’ve got to set myself free! I haven’t been able to find the culprit but I have a hunch that the Oel Mahum Shamans are somehow resolved.

Look around for any clues! The Oel Mahum Shamans must know something! Ugh... I’m losing focus. Use this Crystal of Activation when I fall asleep.

Hey! Is Jenis alive? You didn’t... kill her, right? There is still much I haven’t said!

Hey! Hold it!

You’re a Silverlight Mercenary, right? Do you remember trading with me in the past? I was recently robbed while I was walking by this area.

I’m dismayed about the stolen goods but mostly my late wife’s locket was stolen! It’s the only thing I have to remember her by! Please teach those thieves a lesson!

This is it! I... I thought I’d never see your locket again Joanna... Thank you so much [player]!

Could you give me a moment? I don’t want to be seen crying.

Nice to meet you, meow! I have long known of the unique items that can only be found here, but it’s my first time coming here!

Well, let’s get started! Time is money! Get me some Nymph hair!
I have been called many things in my profession but never have I been called a pest! At least I’m not as bad as Pan...

This is the first time a monster like Pan Luem has appeared in town. The situation has continued to worsen since the Evil Wardstone arrived. Although uncertain, they seem to have a leader among them.

Defeat the leader and the Pan Luems shouldn’t be able to wreak as much havoc. Would you defeat the Pan Luems and their leader?
Thank you. Waika, who you defeated, is infamous around these parts! Not that he’ll be a problem any longer.

I had no idea the Walking Fungi had such interest in plant specimens. What were they thinking? A month’s worth of work has resulted in nothing because the specimens have been stolen.

I can’t leave like this! I need to gather Spore Fungus specimens! I can’t ask this of anyone since not everyone can enter the Sea of Spores. Would you help me?
Thank you! A month’s worth of research almost went to waste. I was able to recover some time thanks to your help. Now, let’s start the research!

I wonder where the bailiff went. I look away for a split second and he’s gone! You look like a mercenary. Would you do me a favor?

There should be a monster around here called a Soul Eater. I’ve been tasked with defeating it but I can’t find the bailiff anywhere. Could you defeat it in my place?

Use this Seal Jar to capture its soul. Don’t overthink it. You only need to hold this while you defeat it.
When did it get damaged? Phew... that was close. I don’t even want to think about what we would do if it was completely broken...

As always, thank you for your help. You made it possible for me to gather such good research material. This time I have something different to ask of you.

Have you seen the Barrier Watchman here? I don’t know if the Ivory Tower Wizards are keeping watch because they are completely out of control. I don’t know why, but they can’t even differentiate scholars from villains!

[player]Can you take care of them for me? I’ve asked the Ivory Tower many times but they haven’t done anything.
You should be able to find some Magic Vines from the body of a dead Barrier Watchman. That’s what they are made out of. Can you bring me some?
Maybe this is a good thing, for now I can at least explain myself to the Ivory Tower. I hope they find this to be alarming as well. Thanks for the help!

My work would be a lot easier if we continued our business partnership. Perhaps it would be a good idea to take a trip to collect some specimens. Thank you for your help!

They are sorely mistaken if they think I will continue to bear their harassment! It’s about time they find out that you, [player], are helping me! Go teach them a lesson!
Phew! I feel as though a weight has been lifted off my chest! The beating they received should be enough to keep those meatheads quiet for a while, right?

To all the reputable adventurers of Orren! There is a small deed that needs attention! It should be like taking candy from a baby for adventurers such as yourselves!

Take care of the Water Seer, and we will compensate you handsomely for your efforts in the name of Lord Orren!
I’m very happy to reward you this tremendous amount of Adena for your great work on the mission.

To all the reputable adventurers of Orren! There is a small deed that needs attention! It should be like taking candy from a baby for adventurers such as yourselves!

Take care of the Water Seer, and we will compensate you handsomely for your efforts in the name of Lord Orren!
I’m very happy to reward you this tremendous amount of Adena for your great work on the mission.

Hey! You might find it strange to see a crystal talking but this isn’t my actual form!

I’ tried to revert to my original form but I can’t do anything as I am now. Please bring me the good-luck charms the Oel Mahum Shredders have. That should help me out!
Oh, my. My apologies for falling asleep. My sleep duration continues to increase... Ah, I can feel that you have brought me the good-luck charm. Thank you!

I regret cutting the number of escorts in half. Those damn Oel Mahum got me good!

They didn’t stop at taking the money, they also lit all of my goods on fire! Help me get vengeance! I’ll even pay you from my hidden funds to do so.
I’ll start my business back up with what remains of my hidden funds. This sort of vengeance is good because it will prevent any future casualties...

Have you seen the Oel Mahums’ equipment? It’s strange that they are carrying around such things and even tougher to think that they made them. They must’ve stolen them!

I remember seeing similar equipment in Aden. Oh! We’ll definitely be rewarded for returning the stolen goods! Go recover the equipment, meow!
What in the world did they use the equipment for? This quality sword has been unbelievably damaged... I’m not even sure if I’ll be compensated for returning this stuff. Well, here is your payment!

Oh, the Dark Brotherhood. I had heard rumors but never had a chance to see them. They have never appeared in public until now.

I hear they are aristocrats. They must have valuable items. So? We ambush the Dark Brotherhood and rob them clean, of course! You think they’re gonna report us to the guards? Hahaha.

As the saying goes, “Arrogance and ignorance go hand in hand.” I’m sure they learned that lesson this time and that their power came from hiding in the shadows. How should I say this? They weren’t very intimidating after showing themselves in public.

Be careful of any ambushes they might attempt. They will likely return to the shadows.

The majority of young knights grew up with stories of heroes battling dragons, but not many have realized those are just stories. Stories are important but realistically speaking, it is almost impossible to meet a dragon.

Well, a Wyrm is no dragon but catching one would be better than doing nothing. Could you check out how strong the Wyrm in this area are?

An adventurer of your abilities shouldn’t have much trouble defeating a Wyrm, right? I’m certain most novice knights wouldn’t be up for the challenge. I guess I should lower the standards. Anyway, well done.

Celebrities like the bailiff are always in various danger. Among the most troublesome is assassination by poison. Even Alchemists have a difficult time dealing with all poisons in real-time.

That’s precisely why I spend my free time collecting samples of various poisons. Creating an antidote becomes a much easier task with a sample of a poison. Speaking of which, I need samples of the poison from the Spore Spiders around here.

I’ll pay you well for it! Just get me the poison pouches of those venomous spiders.
That’s plenty for me to create an antidote. In fact, I think there is enough for me to donate to the association. They’ll be very interested by the poison pouches of spiders from the Sea of Spores!

It will be difficult to distinguish between the Corrupted Willows and Soul Collectors. Even scholars confuse the two of them. Well, I thought this would be a great opportunity to secure some materials.

Please bring me Soul Collector specimens. I’ll be waiting for you to bring me some quality ones!
Oh wow, these are great! This will make the research much easier!

[player]! It seems not enough people have heard about how you will take care of those who bother me!

We have no choice but to teach those thick-skulled Sadistic Grandis Destroyers a lesson! I’m tired of running from them!
I wonder if things will get any better... They are so stubborn and relentless.

To all the reputable adventurers of Orren! There is a small deed that needs attention! It should be like taking candy from a baby for adventurers such as yourselves!

Take care of the Water Seer, and we will compensate you handsomely for your efforts in the name of Lord Orren!
I’m very happy to reward you this tremendous amount of Adena for your great work on the mission.

I’ll start my business back up with what remains of my hidden funds. This sort of vengeance is good because it will prevent any future casualties...

This is one of the areas where our Cat Caravan hasn’t established business yet. I’ll seize this opportunity to establish one, meow.

Do you see those Oel Mahum Fighters? The equipment they have can’t be found around here. I’m certain that they stole those goods. Recovering them will surely be a lucrative opportunity.
Good thing those guys took good care of this equipment. They might be genuine fighters after all. Despite being used, these will surely fetch a high price!

I wonder why those Oel Mahum Destroyers are there. I’ve got personal matters with that barrier device over there.

Can you help me clear that area of them?
A keepsake that belonged to an old friend of mine was over there. My consciousness keeps telling me to deliver it to his family. Thank you for your help.

Could you do me a favor? I need to find the duty list. Luckily, the bailiff hasn’t realized I lost it.

He is quite the perfectionist so if he found out I would get an earful. Please deal with it as quietly as possible!
You didn’t happen to see the bailiff during the mission, right? Well, now to get rid of the list. Let’s say this never happened and continue with what we were doing before. What do you say?

Hmm. This is odd. A product I requested of a dark mystic from Giran has disappeared. I wonder where it could have gone? Perhaps it was stolen? Oh well, I guess I have no other choice.

Have you ever seen a Pan Luem? I need their back mane fur. I’m not quite sure where such a thing would be used. Well, I’ll be here waiting.
Want to know what’s so great about <YellowBold>[player]</>? Speed! Time to a merchant is as valuable as gold. I’m sure we can be great partners.

This is called a purification orb. Defeat a Nightmare Spirit and this purification orb should purify its spirit.

Why such a sad face? This is no different from what we have been doing. Well, go on!
You came to me for work, didn’t you? It’s tiring to explain every little detail. I’ll see you again later.

The Bats around here aren’t just aggressive, they are deadly! Those unfamiliar with this area often pass by the Bats dwellings and learn that the hard way.

The number of Bats have increased so much, that even the natives can’t pass by without any problems. Would you help me reduce the number of those darn Bats?
Thank you! We wouldn’t be safe walking outside without mercenaries like yourself.

Hi there, I’m Maychel, a maid. I’ve come out to hunt because my lord wanted to eat fresh meat.

I hear the meat of Grendels in the Northwind Plateau is absolutely delicious! Could you get some for me?

I’m only supposed to cook for my lord, but I’ll cook for you as well if you lend me a hand!

Thanks to you, I now have some quality meat! I really appreciate it! I made some tartar with the meat you brought me. Have a taste!

Once again, thank you! I have to go now, I need to cook some for my lord!

Hi there, I’m Maychel, a maid. I’ve come out to hunt because my lord wanted to eat fresh meat.

I hear the meat of Grendels in the Northwind Plateau is absolutely delicious! Could you get some for me?

I’m only supposed to cook for my lord, but I’ll cook for you as well if you lend me a hand!
Woah! This is so much meat! My lord loves meat and will be so pleased to know that I’ve procured such a haul! Thank you so much!

Wow, what brings a youngster like you to the country? You look as though you’ve been through a lot. Here, have this porridge.

Seeing as you are an adventure, I have a favor to ask of you.

Well, you didn’t think that porridge was free, did you? We need a fantastic dish for the hunter town festival.

Windsus barbecue would be perfect! Go bring me a giant Windsus fitting of a festival! I heard the hunters speak of a giant Windsus roaming nearby.
I knew you could do it. I’ll surely be noticed at the hunter town festival with such a giant Windsus! Well, thanks a bunch!

It’s a shame you couldn’t catch the big one, but these small ones will still make for a great barbecue! I can already see the hunters drooling over these! Here’s the payment I promise!

You shouldn’t be here! What brings you to such a dangerous place?

Oh, you’re a mercenary! Then would you lend me a hand? You heard about the Bugbears that attacked the hunter town, right? I came here to Avenge my friend, Shayden!

The problem is that they look so similar and I can’t single out the one who killed my friend! Could you take care of the Bugbears around here?

I’ll look for the bastard while you do.
*Pant*... *pant*... That was quite a fight! Thank you so much! Now Shayden can rest in peace... If only I could find his body...

The problem is that they look so similar and I can’t single out the one who killed my friend!

We should just wipe them all out! Would you help me do that?
Hahaha! Vengeance is mine! You did well, but not as well as myself! I could see the two of us becoming a dynamic duo. Hehe.

You’re a mercenary? Oh, thank the heavens!

I am an Oren soldier in Steiner’s unit. Steiner spoke of the importance of taking the weapons of the Razorwind Bugbears as a prerequisite to conquering this area.

Unfortunately, some we were spotted and I was the only one who made it out alive! I would like to fulfill my mission despite the situation.

Would you help me?
Thank you for taking on that giant Bugbear! I thought my colleague and I were done for. Now I can return and face Steiner without shame.

Would you help me?
Phew... I thought I was done for! I didn’t expect you to move so quickly and you even saved my colleagues! Now I can face Steiner without shame. Thank you so much!

Hello there. It must be my luck to meet a mercenary here. Would you do me a favor? It shouldn’t be difficult.

What I need are some Prinsis, the flower of the Nymphs. I’ll pay you well for some!
You must’ve been hallucinating. Don’t you see that you’re quite alright? Well, hand me the flower in exchange for your compensation. Hehehehe.

Hello there. It must be my luck to meet a mercenary here. Would you do me a favor? It shouldn’t be difficult.

What I need are some Prinsis, the flower of the Nymphs. I’ll pay you well for some!
About the Nymphs attacking you? Surely you had expected them to? You should consider yourself lucky enough for not experiencing any hallucinations! Hehehe. Here is your reward.

Hold on a minute! It’s our lucky day!

The eggs of Lizardmen are considered delicacies and are traded at extremely high prices! Do you understand what I’m saying? Go get me some! This will benefit both of us! Get going already!
Wow, you came back alive! I kept a safe distance after seeing the Lizardmen charge towards you. Hehe. Anyway, job well done and here is your compensation.

Hold on a minute! It’s our lucky day!

The eggs of Lizardmen are considered delicacies and are sold at extremely high prices! Do you understand what I’m saying? Go get me some! This will benefit both of us! Get going already!
Thank goodness, meow! I knew you could do it! Hand over those sweet eggs! Oh, here is your reward. I’ll have to keep an egg for myself. Meow!

*Pant*... *Pant*... It’s been 10 days since I got here!

Woah, who are you?

How incredible to see that someone has managed to get here alive!

I am Shayden, from the hunter town. I came here to prove to Renner I’m no coward!

I’ll show him what I’m made of by catching a Tanguri and taking it to town!

Would you help me do that? I’m only asking for help to catch it faster, not because I am scared!
Haha! I could’ve done it myself, but you helped me get it done way faster! Here is your reward. Oh, hand me the talisman the Tanguri had!

Sigh. I guess I should head back to town. Staying here will place my life in greater danger. Oh, thank you for saving me!

Great to see you again! It’s like you are one of us.

I’m actually here to eliminate the Orc Seekers as a request of the Oren Lord.

The lord spoke of how Orc Seekers have been attacking the people more frequently.

The Orcs have never done such things in the past so it’s quite strange. Anyway, shall we eliminate them?
Haha! I’m curious what the Oren Lord will say when I display proof of my feat! Job well done! This is your compensation.

The Orcs have never done such things in the past so it’s quite strange. Anyway, shall we eliminate them?

Did you see the barracks on fire? Hahaha. That was hilarious!

That should teach them a lesson. Well, here is your payment!

Welcome! I’m in a pickle because unlike Nero and Pan’s businesses, mine hasn’t been doing that well. I just need one big break!

And you know what? I have a good lead. I heard talks of a fantastic mace that a Tanor Blacksmith made. Many people are aiming to get it for themselves!

You want to help me look for the mace in this armory? I think it’s here somewhere, meow.

I’ll be able to stand tall in front of the caravan with this accomplishment! Now I’ll think happily about where to sell this. Oh, this is for you. Don’t even think of complaining about how much it is!

We found it because of my research, you merely sped up the situation! You’re getting exactly what you deserve, meow!

And you know what? I have a good lead. I heard talks of a fantastic mace that a Tanor Blacksmith made. Many people are aiming to get it for themselves!

You want to help me look for the mace in this armory? I think it’s here somewhere, meow.

Meow... The mace has gone missing... I’m done for. Nero and Pan will run me out of business... You still want me to pay you after seeing me in this state? Wait... Leave behind the mace you got a while ago, meow...

Welcome! I’m so relieved to see you. I just happened to have taken on a tough task.

The Aden Exploration Team has earned recognition among various lords and has been tasked with numerous missions. There is one particularly difficult.

The mission has to do with defeating the Tanor Silenos Tribe.

Well, we don’t technically have to defeat all of them. Every year around this time, the chief candidates battle for the Chief’s Token, with the winner ruling the Tanor Silenos.

The mission is to win that battle and take charge. Well, we don’t have much time. Let’s get to it!
Woohoo! We succeeded! Can you see the Silenos that follow my lead? Well, this is fantastic. I completed the mission and also gained authority! Everyone, follow me!

Welcome! I’m so relieved to see you. I may be in over my head.

The Aden Exploration Team has earned recognition among various lords and have been tasked with numerous missions. There is a particularly difficult one we took on.

The mission is to defeat Barka Silenos Tribe.

Well, we don’t technically have to defeat all of them. Every year around this time, there is a battle for the Chief’s Token, with the winner becoming the ruler the Barka Silenos.

If we win that battle, we can rule the Baraka Silenos and add them to our forces. We don’t have much time. Let’s go!
Woohoo! We succeeded! That was much easier than I expected. Can you see all the Silenos that are following my lead? Everyone, follow me!

Mmmm. Such fragrance! I can smell the Windsus meat cooking. One of the local delicacies is Windsus lung stew, but its particular smell is a turn off for some.

I’m going to try that dish after cooking my lord some bugbear steak. Speaking of which, could you get me some Windsus lung? Just the thought of it has me salivating.
A person who brings good food is always a good-hearted person. You must be a great person! But don’t get ahead of yourself. This stew is all for me!

Hey youngster, would you like to try some barbecue?

Well? Is it good? Haha. Hmm, you think something is missing?

Oh, that’s right. The spices! My spices spilled over while I was running from some Grendels on my way here. That’s the reason I couldn’t add any spices to the barbecue.

The word is that there are some choice spices over where the Atroxes are. Would you do me a favor and distract them so that I can get some?

Thank you, youngster! Well, have a taste of this.

Well? Isn’t it good? Hehehe.

I can’t wait to let the hunters have a taste!

Ugh... How could such a thing have happened?

My wife Barry told me to find her apron, which she thinks the Bugbears stole.

The thought of Bugbears taking her apron is ridiculous, don’t you think? But a happy wife means happy life.

Just to be on the safe side, could you go check if the Bugbears have her apron?

Oh wow, would you look at that! They really took her apron! Haha, this is ridiculous.

I’ll have to tell Barry. Thanks for your help!

I know who you are. I have a request for you. Could you ward off the Bugbears while I start a fire?

It was originally a group was task, but now I’m alone... Please, it would be a great help.
Thanks to your help, I was able to complete my mission. Now, I’ll just wait for the main army.

Nice to see you! I’ve never been more relieved to see a mercenary!

Flowers are always sprouting from the bodies of Nymphs! Isn’t that interesting?

I’ve always wanted to research the Nymph petals. Could you get me some so I can do research on them?
Thank you so much! There are so many! I can’t wait to start researching!

Hi. I have request that I was hoping you could help me with. I’ll pay you well.

The Atroxes around here have poisonous fangs they use to paralyze their enemies. I need their fangs for my black magic. You’d be surprised how useful they are in magic.
Seeing as you came back without a scratch, I must’ve chosen the right person for the job. This is your reward, and I added a bit more considering how difficult the job was.

Welcome! I’m Shayden from the hunter town. That damn Renner called me a coward, so I came here to prove him wrong!

The problem is that I’ve been injured and I... I would really appreciate your help.

It’s not a difficult job. All you need to do is get me 10 Leto Lizardman Sentinel spears. I’ll be waiting!
Haha. I would normally have been able to do it myself! Anyway, thanks for your help and please keep helping me a secret. Oh, here is the payment for your discretion!

It’s intriguing to find you at such a place!

Have you fought a Slave Foremen before? It’s my first time seeing one and I never thought they could be that big!

Could you engage some and tell me how they fight? I need to know my enemy if I’m to defeat them!

I’ll be watching the fight from the sideline. Well, best of luck!
I’ve studied their fighting styles and feel ready to take them on! This is a small token of my appreciation for your help.

Welcome! The recent battle between the Orcs and Tanors have the Oren people terrified.

The simple-minded Orcs are quick to forget about any grudges but the Tanors continue seeking vengeance for any who die.

The battle will never stop if we do nothing about the Tanors. Should we try speaking with the Tanor Chiefs? It’s fine to resort to violence if talking to them doesn’t work.

Our main goal is to put an end to the battle!
Phew. The situation has died down since we’ve disposed of the chiefs. I sure hope this armistice endures.

Great to see you! Seeing you makes me feel better despite the burdensome task I have on my plate.

I currently have my hands full with the mission of wiping out the Barka Silenos. Would you help me by defeating the Wizards?
Thank you for helping! I was able to defeat the elder Silenos. Here, this is to show my appreciation. I’d appreciate your help next time as well if you’re available.

Thank you for the compliment. Could you help me out?

I heard a Nymph cry once, before its death. I want to research the various effects it supposedly has, but I, unfortunately, don’t have the ability to defeat them.

Could you help me out and collect some tears for me?
Thank you! I didn’t expect you to bring me so much! I’m eager to start conducting some research.

D-did you... see the giant Atrox over there?

I only expected to see beautiful Nymphs, not something grotesque like that Spider.

Could you deal with it for me? I’m not sure when they’ll attack and... they scare me...
Thanks to you, this place has become a lot safer! This is payment for your help!

Great to see you. *Sneeze*!

If possible, could you help me get rid of those Nymph Roses?

Their pollen is giving me a really tough time. *Sneeze*! It would be really wonderful if you helped me.
Phew. That is much better. My pollen allergies were driving me nuts. Please take this as a personal thank you.

Help me, meow!

The Lizardmen eggs are considered very rare, but luckily enough, I was able to get my paws on some of them!

But I clumsily dropped a few and they were taken by the priests. I would like your help getting them back!
Oh, my lovely eggs have come back to me! Thank you so much, meow!

Welcome! I’m Shayden from the hunter town. That damn Renner called me a coward, so I came here to prove him wrong!

Taking the Bone Headgears of the Shamans should be enough to show him I’m no coward! Could you get me some? I’m a little busy right now so I can’t, but I’ll pay you well for it.
Haha. Thanks! Of course, I could’ve done it myself but someone as talented as myself can’t be wasting my time defeating some Shamans, right?

Great to see you. I saw some Orcs around here fighting amongst each other.

They’ll be killing humans regardless of the outcome of their scuffle.

In fact, we should seize this opportunity to defeat their Archers!
Hearing them scream is enough to let go of the anger inside of me. You did a great job during the battle!

Do you see those barbaric Orcs? All they do is fight and it causes a lot of harm to humans. I can’t have them continue wildly thrashing everything.

Even through extensive research, we do not know why they’re fighting. I don’t care anymore and it doesn’t change the fact that they are enemies I need to kill.

Would you help me defeat the Guards?
Those dumb Orcs are too stupid to function without a commander. Idiots! Anyway, you did well. Take this as payment!

Hey there. Did you perhaps hear about the Orcs attacking the humans? The families of the fallen are asking to gather their keepsakes as a way to remember them.

I agreed to help out considering their unfortunate circumstances, but it’s been a difficult task. Could you help me defeat the Elite Soldiers and find any keepsakes?
Phew. Thanks for your help. I hope this offers condolences to the grieving families.

Come on over and lend me a paw, meow!

Do you see the leather corsets on the Tanor Recruits? The Tanors are quite skilled in their leather craftmanship.

I’m positive they will fetch a high price! Well? I’ll pay you well for bringing me those leather corsets!
What is this, meow? It’s bloody and ripped! I can’t sell this! I can only pay you this much for these scraps. Go somewhere else if you don’t like it!

Come, come! Have you come to get some horns as well?

Oh my, I guess you weren’t aware.

The horns of the Tribe Guardians are good mediums for spreading mana. They fetch quite a price!

On that note, could you defeat them and get me some horns? Of course, I’ll pay you well. Well, not as much as you would get for selling them at a shop.
Wow! These are very good quality! Thank you! I’ll pay you as much as I can, just not as much as a shop would haha.

Come, come. I received word that High Priests of the Dark Brotherhood have been active in my jurisdiction. They are truly reckless!

I issued a draft, but the soldiers haven’t arrived yet. If possible, could you go ahead and deal with those Dark Brotherhood High Priests?
That Dark Brotherhood is unyielding! We only made it out thanks to your help. Thank you for saving us!
Well done! The soldiers haven’t arrived yet, but having you here is more than enough.

Could you help us look for some clues? I think defeating the Fallen Knights around here should lead to something. After all, they weren’t here before this situation arose.

My gut says defeating them will reveal some secrets. My gut feeling is never wrong about these things!
I’m at a loss for words... You overcame such odds? You really are incredible!

Ah! Where am I? The High Wizard teleported me, saying, “We need to escape.” I wonder what is happening at the Ivory Tower...

Uh oh... Have you seen my recipe anywhere?

The monsters must’ve taken it while I was unconscious! That recipe could be dangerous in the wrong hands! This could be bad...

You’re an adventurer, aren’t you? Could you lend me a hand and bring the recipe back to me?
Phew. This is such a relief. My apologies for not introducing myself earlier. My name is Bella and I am the exclusive chef of the Ivory Tower. I hope to see you again some other time.

Are you with me? Let’s make them pay for all that they’ve done!
I feel great but a little winded... Maybe I’m slowly going insane. Regardless, our vengeance must continue!

Rumor is that the Orcs here have been creating bombs. Rumor or not, I would still love to see those bombs. Could you perhaps procure some?
Such a rude guy deserves to die! Meow! Now let’s take a look at the bomb. It wouldn’t spontaneously explode, right?

Rumor is that the Orcs here have been creating bombs. Rumor or not, I would still love to see those bombs. Could you perhaps procure some?
Such a rude guy deserves to die! Meow! Now let’s take a look at the bomb. It wouldn’t spontaneously explode, right?

I told my regular customers that I would meet them here. I don’t quite have a problem waiting here, but I could make good use of this time.

Have you ever faced off against any of the Dark Witches around here? They are actually Medusas. Their waving hair is the source of their powerful magic.

Bring me some of their hair and I will pay you generously in Adena. Of course, you’ll have to figure out how to get the hair on your own. I’ll wait here.

Oh wow, you are very skilled, aren’t you?

Kutcher, I’d like to ask your friend to do me a favor if you don’t mind.
Feel free. It would be great if you lent Mancini a hand, <YellowBold>[player]</>.

Would you protect me? The item I received from my friend draws in dark power. Think of me as a sheep bleeding in a den of lions.

I’d appreciate it if you kept me safe until I get somewhere safe!
I should be good from here. Today has been quite a day. I never thought Kutcher would know someone like you. I’ll be sure to remember you in case I need you for the future. Hahaha!

Haha. He is so incredibly fickle! I don’t think any of my regular customers would require any kind of protection. Maybe he is thinking of it as a sort of entertainment...

Be careful, [player]. The dark power seems to favor you.

I told my regular customers that I would meet them here. I don’t quite have a problem waiting here, but I could make good use of this time.

Have you ever faced off against any of the Dark Witches around here? They are actually Medusas. Their waving hair is the source of their powerful magic.

Bring me some of their hair and I will pay you generously in Adena. Of course, you’ll have to figure out how to get the hair on your own. I’ll wait here.
My patron seems to have taken a liking to you. I find it quite amusing, hahaha.

Wow, this is such a wonderful place! Can you smell the money? Have you ever seen such a giant Leech?

This is our chance! Go get me that giant Leech! It will shrink once we dry it, so don’t worry about its size!

Wow, this is incredible! I’ve never seen such a giant Leech before!

Can I have this, meow? I’ll pay you extra! Thanks, [player]!

Wow, this is such a wonderful place! Can you smell the money? Have you ever seen such a giant Leech?

This is our chance! Go get me that giant Leech! It will shrink once we dry it, so don’t worry about its size!
Meow! Is it over? They must be the dumbest Orcs alive! They tried to rob us while you were here, <YellowBold>[player]</>. You have my thanks!

The Oel Mahum around here are all fighters. I’m not sure how, but they got their hands on some quality equipment. As embarrassing as it is for me to admit, I think some of their equipment is better than mine.

The Bandit Shamans’ equipment will actually fetch quite a price. Those should be of more worth than the Oel Mahum equipment.
Are you alright? My goodness, what was that? What did those darn Oel Mahums do? Nevermind that, I’m glad to see you are alright. They really are a wild bunch.

The Oel Mahum around here are all fighters. I’m not sure how, but they got their hands on some quality equipment. As embarrassing as it is for me to admit, I think some of their equipment is better than mine.

The Bandit Shamans’ equipment will actually fetch quite a price. Those should be of more worth than the Oel Mahum equipment.
As expected, they are quite a handful. Thank goodness you got away safe!

Those Bandit Plunderers are quite a handful. I had a fight with them yesterday and barely came out alive. There must be a secret to their strength.

We should check out their equipment. Please tell me if you find any special equipment.
Hmm. This is no ordinary equipment. I’ve got to conduct some research. Anyway, here is your compensation. Thanks!

Those Bandit Plunderers are quite a handful. I had a fight with them yesterday and barely came out alive. There must be a secret to their strength.

We should check out their equipment. Please tell me if you find any special equipment.
This is quite an unusual piece of equipment, but I can’t learn anything by simply by looking at it. I’ll have to do some research.

I promised to meet an old friend here, but I haven’t heard any word yet... I did in hear that something happened at the Ivory Tower. That worries me because my friend is an Ivory Tower Wizard.

Perhaps something happened to my friend on the way here. Could you lend me a hand and search the area? It would be even better if you dealt with any Grendels since they can be of potential danger!

Ugh... Where am I? And who are you??

You came looking for me on Dorothy’s behalf? Now that’s a name I’m happy to hear. Oh, we should get out of here first.
Thanks to you, my friend and I are safe. Even better, you are also safe. Don’t you think things turned out well? This is for helping us.

I promised to meet an old friend here, but I haven’t heard any word yet... I did in hear that something happened at the Ivory Tower. That worries me because my friend is an Ivory Tower Wizard.

Perhaps something happened to my friend on the way here. Could you lend me a hand and search the area? It would be even better if you dealt with any Grendels since they can be of potential danger!

Ugh... Where am I? And who are you??

You came looking for me on Dorothy’s behalf? Now that’s a name I’m happy to hear. Oh, we should get out of here first.
Kirinaldo is a hometown friend of mine. Thanks to you, I haven’t lost a friend.

That’s weird... It should be here... Have you seen a brown sack by any chance? One that could hold a couple of apples. Did I lose it?

I suspect a few places where it might be. Can you help me find it? Head East from here and you’ll see something that resembles a tent. I might’ve lost it somewhere around there.

What? You’re saying that it’s empty? I worked my butt off all month for that money!

There is nobody around this area. A bear would never take off with Adena, so it has to be the bandits. Can you get it back for me?
What a horrible day. I feel terrible. Not only did I lose my money, but I’m in a fight that’s paying me close to nothing. Sigh...

That’s weird... It should be here... Have you seen a brown sack by any chance? One that could hold a couple of apples. Did I lose it?

I suspect a few places where it might be. Can you help me find it? Head East from here and you’ll see something that resembles a tent. I might’ve lost it somewhere around there.

What? You’re saying that it’s empty? I worked my butt off all month for that money!

There is nobody around this area. A bear would never take off with Adena, so it has to be the bandits. Can you get it back for me?
What a horrible day. I feel terrible. Not only did I lose my money, but I’m in a fight that’s paying me close to nothing. Sigh...

Why haven’t the soldiers we summoned arrived yet? The situation is very complicated with Embrion’s Squire running about...

You’ll have to help us out since we don’t have any men to act with. Head to the Ivory Tower territory and defeat Embrion’s Squire.
Hmm, you are quick... With your speed, you might be able to wrap up the situation up before the army gets here. Thanks.

The bailiff seems to be happier lately. He must be pleased with your actions. It’s been amazing for me as well. Speaking of which, could I ask for one more thing?

Could you defeat the Void Hounds? I believe the soldiers will have a difficult time dealing with such monsters.
You have my thanks. Having the normal soldiers deal with such monsters would have resulted in heavy casualties.

The malfunctioning Guardian was originally constructed for security purposes. Although trustworthy, it isn’t exactly reliable. In situations like these, it is merely a murder machine.

Would you eliminate that malfunctioning guardian? I honestly don’t think it can be repaired.
Could you keep this request a secret? I fear it may have repercussions. Your help is much appreciated.
The Orc Seekers need to be dealt with first. With them gone, we would be able to keep more people hidden from the Orcs.
Ah, you’re back. Surely you didn’t go easy on them? Haha, well done.
Meow! Come on over, <YellowBold>[player]</>! Do you see the Timak Orc Fighter over there? I’ve got to have its knife, it’s of superb quality! I need it! Well, go on! Go get it!
I am curious to know where the Orc got such a high-quality item. I could get rich if I knew their source.

Would you quit looking around and come over here? I was hoping to give you something to keep you and I busy while I wait for my patron.

Take this small soul collector and defeat the Timak Orc Archers. This collector should store their dark souls.
You did well. This is a small token of appreciation for my patron. If you would like, I will even tell my patron where it was acquired. Hahaha.
Hear ye, brave adventurers! The Oren Lord has said that anyone who defeats the Timak Orc Fighters and brings back their headgear as proof will be rewarded!
Your help is duly noted. On behalf of the lord of Oren, here is your reward. Any other volunteers?

Look around! There must be something useful among all this junk the Oel Mahums have gathered. It will be a shame to see something of value in the hands of villains.

The Bandit Warrior should have the keys to the boxes in the treasure lot. I need those keys to start with.
Now we only need to find the box that this key fits in. I can do that on my own. Hahaha!

Sigh... I had no intention of putting in any effort since I wasn’t even requested... Have you perhaps seen Mitchell? Perhaps he went to steal from the treasure lot?

I’ll have to use my magic to take a deeper look. Could you eliminate the Bandit Cutthroats in the vicinity so that I can focus?
Wow, I only expected you to scare them off. You’re kind of an overachiever. Oh, I managed to find Mitchell. He found his way deep inside the stronghold... Ugh... I’m sure he’ll find his own way out.

Something must have happened at the Ivory Tower. Oel Mahums wouldn’t be wandering around under normal circumstances. I’m sure the Ivory Tower’s weakened influence have given monsters more freedom to roam around.

This is a complicated situation. I need to do my research but I still have to complete what was requested of me... Could you defeat the Bandit Looters in my place? I’ll give you the reward that was promised to me for this task.
I was able to conduct some research thanks to you. Seeing as the friend I was supposed to meet seems too busy with the problem at hand, I should probably make some plan of action.
I have been tasked with collecting ingredients. I need Grendel’s sole. Can you do this for me? I don’t feel like going all the way back after traveling all this way.
I just don’t understand how you can cook food with this. What kind of person could’ve come up with this recipe?

The soldiers should be here soon, but I can’t simply wait without doing anything when the Dark Knights are running amuck.

Would you be up to help me once more? Show them that justice will prevail!
As expected, you truly are reliable. Your help is very much appreciated!
Bella, the Ivory Tower’s Exclusive Chef has requested us to defeat the Ivory Tower Gargoyles who seem to be after her stolen magic recipe.
I hear you’ve undertaken a similar task in the past? That must be why you had relative ease with this task. Thanks!

There were ingredients among the goods that were teleported with me. One of the items is dark meat fermented with mana bean sauce. Monsters who consume it will become more violent.

We still have some time until the effect of the meat shows itself in them. Defeat the Void Hounds before the meat kicks in.
I hope you don’t misunderstand and think Ivory Tower Wizards consume such things. It is merely for research.

The Orcs move in such unison because of their commander. The vile nature of Orcs pales in comparison to how wicked the Timak Orc Officers are.

Defeat the Timak Orc Officers and consider it a preemptive strike on their sure-to-happen wicked deeds.
They were bound to commit wicked deeds, I am sure of it. It was a necessary preemptive strike!

The Orcs here are on bad terms with Ivory Tower Wizards. Perhaps that’s why they are so skilled at fighting against them.

Bring me the weapons of the Timak Orc Berserkers. I’m sure there are secrets to be uncovered.
Our caravan will look into this, meow. I am confident that I can use these to make some incredible products. Well done!
There is something I need. Atroxes have many legs, but what I need are their front legs. I’ll be waiting for you to bring me some in exchange for a bunch of Adena.
You finished almost as quickly as I expected you to. Well, I wouldn’t have been surprised if you finished any sooner either. Oh, here is the Adena I promised you.
Hear ye, brave adventurers! The Oren Lord has said that anyone who defeats a Forest Wyrm and brings back its suckers as proof will be rewarded!
Your help is duly noted. On behalf of the lord of Oren, here is your reward. Any other volunteers?

I wonder what relation these Oel Mahums have with the Ferocious Grendels? I did not expect Ferocious Grendels to be in the stronghold! Oh man, I can’t believe they are on my path.

Would you defeat them? I wouldn’t stand a chance if those brutes rushed me!
Judging by your abilities, I’m sure you could handle 10 Ferocious Grendels on your own! Quite incredible, I say!

The source of the magic buffs used by Bandit Shamans is a curse.

They are suppressing the harmful effects of the curse while still drawing out the beneficial effects. Such a complex practice is impossible without a suitable tool.

They must have some sort item that enables such magic. Should we acquire it, I’m positive we can sell for good price. Shall we go find it?
That was a great plan. It isn’t something we can use right now, but knowledge of how it works should prove useful to us in the future.
Would you defeat the Bandit Rookies? I had originally planned to request Sara Ra, but she must’ve gone to look for Mitchell. She’s worrying for nothing if you ask me.
Oh, you’re back. You sure are quick. I was able to do what I had to thanks to your help. I’ll be sure to count on you in the future!

I heard the town nearby was attacked by bandits. Me? I’m just really tired after trying to complete the free quest that Mitchell accepted. Can you help me by taking care of the Mountain Bandits Scouts?
Thanks to you I’m all rested now. Although there are still things left to do... Life isn’t about complaining all the time right?
Talk to Hardin in Shrieking Hallows
Defend Against the Incoming Army of Death
Investigate Traces of the Ancient Obsidian Golem
Defeat the Incoming Tanor Tribe Guardian
Theron the Town Crier of Dion
Evna the High Priest of Eva

Greetings! I received orders from the Lord of Gludio to defeat the Ol Mahum leader.

But, it seems he knew I was coming because he’s gone into hiding! But maybe you could find him since he doesn’t know you!

I suggest interrogating one of the guards for information!

New intel!

He’s going to steal the loot and escape! Head to storage and find him!
You live up to your reputation! I shall personally report your deeds! Here, take this! My lord always rewards the worthy!

May the blessing of the light of Einhasad be with you.

The Goddess’s oracle dictates that we must purify this land.

Our investigation tells us that the cursed trees are one cause of the corruption.

Someone has cursed the trees, causing them to absorb energy from the ground and convert it to dark energy.

I want to bring the responsible party to justice, but we must deal with the trees first!

We found three trees so far, but beasts attracted by the dark energy are making approaching them difficult.

We’d be truly grateful if a warrior as valiant as yourself could assist us.

If it isn’t the Silverlight Mercenaries. I was wondering who could be so foolish.

Excellent, this place shall be your grave!

Undead Soldiers, rise!
You did well. We shall continue purifying this land.

One of our comrades was captured by the Ol Mahum during an escape attempt. I can’t leave one of our brothers behind!

Could you rescue him?

We’ll give you everything we have. Please, help us!

Our comrades are locked inside the cage!

Please rescue our them!

Thank you so much!

I will regroup with my comrades over here. Please, send my regards to Varn.

Bolt is free thanks to you!

We’ll repay our debt as soon as we reach safety!

Si-Silverlight Mercenaries! Can you help us escape?

We’ll never be able to hide from the arrows of the Ol Mahum Shooters!

If you take out the archers, we’ll be able to get past safely!
We are eternally grateful! Thanks to you, I’ve rediscovered my courage. Now we can escape without worrying about the archers.

We want to leave, but the guards took away all our weapons.

We can’t escape if we’re unarmed.

If you can recover our equipment from the Loot Guards, it would be of great help!
Thank you. We won’t have to fear the enemy anymore.

Did you see the Ol Mahum Master Marksmen?

We want to escape, but they’re making it difficult. Their arrows never miss.

We won’t make it out of here with them around. I really want to see my parents again. Please help us...
Thank you. I may just live to hug my mother!

By the decree of the Lord of Gludio, I hereby announce a bounty.

Kill the Ol Mahum Foreman on the Gludin Highway and bring proof of his death!

The one who does shall be rewarded!
Thank you for your hard work. By the power vested in me as an agent of the Lord of Gludio, here is your reward.

By the decree of the Lord of Gludio, I hereby announce a bounty!

Execute the Ol Mahum Warrior who is raiding farms and killing peddlers on the Gludin Highway!

The one who brings proof of his death shall be rewarded!

May the blessing of Einhasad’s light be with you. The Goddess’s oracle dictates that we purify this place.

The Grave Bat’s foul energy corrupts this land. We must defeat the monster and restore the light. Will you aid us?
We are grateful for your help. The monster you defeated shall be purified by Einhasad and reborn.

The Goddess’s oracle dictates that we purify this land.

Dungeon Skeleton Soldiers are raiding the land and spreading dark energy in the graveyard.

Please defeat them so that we may purify this place.

The Goddess’s oracle dictates that we purify this place.

Malevolent Skeleton Soldiers are spreading dark energy to the dead and corrupting the land.

Defeating them would be a great help.
We are grateful for your aid. The purification shall move swiftly thanks to you.

Welcome. I sense the light guiding you. The Goddess has informed us that Reapers are spreading their evil energy.

We tried to purify this land, but we lack the strength. We would be eternally grateful if you would help us.
Thank you. Einhasad will bless your path. May the light be with you, always...

Greetings. The Goddess told us you would come.

We are purifying the corruption of this land, but Bugbears have been attacking us.

Please defeat the Bugbears and protect us.
We are grateful. We shall no longer suffer thanks to you. May the Goddess bless you...

We received a vision: the arrival of a holy warrior. I think you are that warrior.

We are purifying this land, but we’re under non-stop attack by Skeleton Archers.

We would be grateful if you could defeat them.
We are grateful. May the blessings of Einhasad light your way...

Welcome, meow! What brings you to the Cat Caravan?

I’ve heard that the Turek Orc Troopers are collecting Iron Rings!

Bring me Iron Rings from the Troopers, and I will pay you handso-meowly!
Did you bring them? Purr-fect! It’s fur-tunate that the Orcs are collecting such valuables!

What is it meow? We only deal in purr-ofits!

Bring 20 Ol Mahum Tailfurs! I will buy them at a high purr-ice!
Did you bring them? These are in purr-fect condition! Paw-some!

Welcome! Did you hear the mews? Health Tonics are paw-sitively out of stock!

Want to earn some meow-ney?

Need some gold in that purr-se? Collect 20 bottles of Werewolf Blood, an ingredient in Health Tonics!

It will en-tail a worthwhile reward!

The Cat Caravan only deals with purr-ofitable business!

Now is the season when Werewolf Leather is purr-emium quality!

Gather some Werewolf leather right meow!

I will buy them all at a higher purr-ice than the market! Why are you still here? Pounce on it!

You must have the keen eyes of a cat!

These are all high quality! This is the payment I purr-omised!

Tiger skin! Tiger skin is the cat-ch of the season!

Bring me tiger-striped leather for more Adena than you can shake your tail at!

Here at the Cat Caravan, we always buy for a good purr-ice!
Thanks for bringing it in such purr-fect condition! Want to work paw-in-hand?

Have you heard of Plain Cougar Claws?

It’s an accessory hot in the town of Giran right meow!

We are purr-chasing as many as we can get our paws on!

Bring back some Plain Cougar Claws. I will make it paw-sitively worthwhile!
Meow! So meowch! Here, a bonus!

I am Faute, bailiff of Gludio. The Lord of Gludio sent me!

Bakum, the new chieftain of the Turek Orcs, is immensely powerful. Strangely, Bakum has challenged Gludio to a duel! How funny it is, an Orc demanding a duel!

But the fighters who went to challenge him never returned. These Orcs are causing much distress for my lord.

Perhaps you should challenge him! A great reward has been promised for killing Bakum.
You’ve done well. Intel says that Bakum is in the barracks over there. Go on, finish him!
Isn’t this Bakum’s Necklace? You’ve done it! Marvelous! Here, take this special reward from my lord! Your heroic feat shall be remembered!

I am Faute, bailiff of Gludio. The Lord of Gludio sent me!

We subdued the Turek Orcs several times before, but they’ve recovered quickly.

The Orc Tukan is the most rambunctious of them all! My lord announced a large bounty for Tukan. Perhaps an adventurer such as yourself could collect it?

This should be enough.

They say that Tukan is near the beacon.
Great job! The rowdiest one is dead, and now the rest of the Orcs might quiet down! Gludio owes you for this!

The Turek War Hounds are causing a havoc! We have to get rid of them.

The soldiers are on it, but it’s taking longer than expected. Could you join us?

Oh! Be careful around the handlers! They always surround themselves with War Hounds!

We’re in trouble! The War Dog Handler has arrived!

Our soldiers have been captured! We have to rescue them!

Thank you, thank you!

We’ll go over there to regroup!

We’ve been saved!
Good job! Well done! Here’s a bonus - we’re truly grateful to you!

We are explorers of the Aden continent. We came here to find a Spell Book!

They say that the Lizardmen have a Spell Book that was passed down for generations, and wizards should learn as many spells as they can, right?

We heard the scouts have it. Why scouts have a Spell Book, we don’t know, but it’s not like we care, either.

You’re coming with us, right? It’ll be a good experience! Find the Spell Book and we will reward you handsomely!

A Spell Book!! A big, fat, Spell Book!! Now, we can learn new spells!

Here, the reward as promised! Aw, this is written in Lizardman!

I have to find a translator in town!

We are explorers of the Aden continent. We came to find good equipment!

There are accessories that can power up Mana.

Lizardmen accessories temporarily amplify Mana, strengthening magic powers.

Good to know, right? Well, nothing’s free. Pay up!

Money? Who do you think I am? Just bring me the accessory I mentioned! Only a few of the Lizardmen will have it, so hurry up!

Wow! You really brought it! Here, take this. Maybe you can help me again later!

Oh!!! Oh! I can feel the magical power! Ohhh!

We are explorers of the Aden continent! Lizardmen are killing the people around here!

I’ll bring them to justice! Will you join me?

A hero must help the weak and combat evil! Come! Let’s defeat the Raiders!

Yes, sweat shed for justice is so sweet!

Good job! Take this reward! Heroes have to eat, too!

We are explorers of Aden! We came for the bountiful hunting grounds.

They say that bringing a Lizardman rake to the Marshal of Gludio will improve our reputation.

New adventurers like us need all the good reputation we can get! Do you think you could help us for a bit?

They’re stronger than we thought...
Woah! You’re so cool! Thank you! We can earn our reputation now!

We are explorers of Aden! We came to find good hunting grounds.

There’s a sword that’s used for witch doctor rituals, and it casts an awesome curse on its target!

This dagger is too weak - I need to find a better weapon! I can’t even join a proper party with this thing!

I’m doing my best, but can you help me find that sword? I’ll reward you well!
Oh, wow!!! How did you get this? I never found anything remotely close to it! Here, the reward as promised! Heh heh, Mitchell and Ringo, here I come!

By orders of the Lord of Gludio, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded.

Kill the Red Bear, and my lord shall reward you!

By orders of the Lord of Gludio, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded.

Kill the Bugbear Looter, and my lord shall reward you!

By orders of the Lord of Gludio, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded.

Kills the Bugbear Plunderer, and my lord shall reward you!

Please help me! I am Hamon, a soldier from the 1st Platoon. I’m stranded here - there’s too many monsters for me to leave.

Have you seen wolves with black fur? Those are Famished Black Wolves. They follow their prey until they catch it.

Please take them out! I can’t run forever.
Huff. Huff. Thanks to you, I can finally escape! Thank you so much! I can live another day!

Please help me! I am Hamon, a soldier from the 1st Platoon. I’m stranded here - there’s too many monsters for me to leave.

Have you seen muscular monsters with huge, round bellies? Those are Tumran Bugbears. If one of them catches me, I’m toast!

It’s dangerous, but I would be grateful if you could defeat them! Be careful! Their maces are powerful!

Please help me! I am Hamon, a soldier from the 1st Platoon. I’m stranded here - there’s too many monsters for me to leave.

Have you seen a black, demonic face floating around? It’s a monster called the Dark Weaver. They signal others once they discover an enemy.

Please defeat the Dark Weaver! If it calls more, I’m finished!

There’s been an increase in monster attacks recently. As a town guard, I have to do something!

Red Bears are coming down from the mountains, attacking and eating anything they see! Please defeat the Red Bears and, uh, bring me their livers as proof!
These are Red Bear livers! Awesome! Give them to me, and I’ll let everyone know what you did for us!

There’s been an increase in monster attacks recently. As a town guard, I have to do something!

I’ve heard that Red Foxes are stealing grain from the caravan. I can’t leave my post, so I want to offer you a job.

Please help the town and bring me 6 pieces of Red Fox leather.
6 Red Fox leathers! Great job - these must have been hard to get! The townspeople all chipped in to give you this. Well done!

There’s been an increase in monster attacks recently. As a town guard, I have to do something!

Crazed Black Wolves are attacking the townspeople. I can’t leave my post, so I want to offer you a job.

Can you help me secure the town?
Thank you! The town is secure once again!

Join paws with the Cat Caravan! We’re always on the prowl for goods! Bring good items for a good purr-ice!

Bring us 20 Lizardman Seeker Leathers!

Join paws with the Cat Caravan! We’re always on the prowl for goods! Bring good items for a good purr-ice!

Bring us 20 Lizardman Sentry Scales!

Join paws with the Cat Caravan! We’re always on the prowl for goods! Bring good items for a good purr-ice!

Bring us 20 Lizardman Pillager Spear Tips!

Greetings. I am Psy, servant of the Gran Kain, bearer of destruction.

A few days ago, the Orcs attacked our followers and kidnapped them. The Orcs also stole a sculpture of Gran Kain.

Orcs never steal sculptures; this is very suspicious. We must recover the sculpture.

If you could aid us, please defeat the Orc Troopers first. We will search for traces of the sculpture’s Mana.
We found it! The sculpture is in Chief Kekoon’s barracks. We must make haste!
Thank you. I can feel the power of destruction inside you. Please visit the temple when you can.

I never expected to see another person in a place like this!

Would you mind doing me a favor? You see, Elves and Orcs used to live here at the Windawood Ruins until the Elves fled because of the war.

Ancient history, really. Anyway, the Elves left behind some amazing treasures!

As far as I can tell, the artifacts are scattered all around here. What do you say - do you want to help me look?
Wow, this must be very valuable! It was definitely worth the risk! Here’s your payment, and now our deal’s done!

Greetings. I am Sara Ra. I am here because of the missing people in Windawood.

Can you help me? I’ve heard that there are Cursed Hunters causing trouble south of here.

We should capture some Cursed Hunters and find out what they’re up to!
A break in the case! Great! If you hand this over to the government, you’ll be rewarded handsomely!

It’s a cat-astrophe!

My caravan was raided by those claw-ful Ol Mahum!

I’m so in-fur-iated! Help meow-t to get my revenge!
Great job, you really showed those Ol Mahum your claws! They’ll think twice about rustling our litter! Here, your reward!

Greetings! It’s been a while since I’ve been so glad to see a mercenary!

I came looking for gemstones for Alchemy, but those Ol Mahums took them all!

Can you get them back for me? I’ll make it worth your while!
Wow, you’re really amazing! This is your reward! Thank you very much!

Hey! A competitor! Are you looking for the Elven Treasure, too?

Well... how about we look together and split it 50/50?

Great! Let’s defeat the monsters around here! I know just where to look!
Whew, treasure sure is hard to find! The wraiths weren’t helping either! I’m going to take a little break. Here’s your payment!

Wow! I asked for help from the Silverlight Mercenaries and they sent you! Nice to meet you!

This is a former Elven sanctuary. There’s a lot of research to be done, but there are too many monsters around.

Why don’t you start by defeating them?

Wow, I’ve never seen such a large Cougar!

I’d have been eaten for sure if you weren’t here! Thank you!

Greetings! Listen carefully, time is short!

Word is that townspeople of Gludio have been taken by the butcher, Kirk!

Kirk’s infamy is well known! Fortunately, it seems that he has left his post for now. Time is running out! Let’s rescue the townspeople - fast!
Whew, we rescued all of them thanks to you! Here’s the payment as promised! Thanks again!

Greetings, I am Psy, servant of the Gran Kain, bearer of destruction.

A few days ago, the Orcs attacked our followers and kidnapped them. The Orcs also stole a sculpture of Gran Kain.

This is sacrilege beyond all bounds. We have decided to take a stand.

Please punish the Orcs for us. We shall reward you accordingly.
The kidnapped followers have been located. Please rescue them!

Well done. Here is the reward, as promised.

Orcs resurrecting Mammon... They can’t be doing this for themselves. Someone is behind all this.

I will have to report this. I will contact you when I have another job for you.

Never thought I’d meet someone out here. I’m Darian. You look like a merc - can you help me?

I’m sure you already know how cruel Orcs are... We have to annihilate them.

There’s one called Korum, and he’s the most cruel Orc of all. He must be killed.

Please clear the way so I can reach him! Kill the Turek Orc Shooters! Do that, and I’ll take care of the rest!

Th... thank you. I couldn’t have done it without you... thank you.

This is the reward I promised. I’m going to dedicate my life to killing Orcs. We shall meet again.

Whew, that was close. Nothing so far... damn it!

But it may still be around here! I won’t give up!
Whew, it’s a good thing we found them! This should be enough for the reward, right? Now, let’s go get the money!
Damn! A bust! Nothing valuable here. I’ll have to look for another site. Here, your reward. I was safe thanks to you!

Join paws with the Cat Caravan! We’re always on the prowl for goods! Bring good items for a good purr-ice!

We came to trade Mana Crystals here, but un-fur-tunately the Ol Mahum stole all of them! I can’t leave here with empty paws!

Kill the Rangers and bring back the Mana Crystals, I’ll be sure to reward you!
Thank you! They gathered so meowch! Paw-ful Ol Mahum bastards! They are always such a purr-oblem...

Join paws with the Cat Caravan! We’re always on the prowl for goods! Bring good items for a good purr-ice!

My co-worker Nero got robbed by those paw-ful Ol Mahum while passing through here! I’ll show them what happens when you bo-fur the Cat Caravan!

Why don’t you join me and make Ol Mahum Guards tremble in mew-sery? I will reward you, of course!
Meow-velous! Here’s the reward, fur-end! I took care of some of them as well with my flying claws!

Hello there! Are you [player]? I am Azir. Feldheim sent me to investigate on his behalf.

As you already know, this is where a battle between Elves and Orcs took place. I’m looking for Elven Relics!

There’s just a small problem. I can’t investigate safely because of the cougars over there! Can you get rid of them for me? I would be in your debt!
Thanks! I finished the investigation safely! It looks like there really were some relics around here, but somebody took them. If only I had been here sooner...

Hello there! Are you [player]? I am Azir. Feldheim sent me to investigate on his behalf. I’ve heard a lot about you.

As you already know, this is where a battle between Elves and Orcs took place. I’m looking for Elven Relics!

I have a small favor to ask... I want you to get rid of those Gludio Bears. They’re stomping all over the area where I need to excavate.

They’re dragging their feet and wrecking the ruin! Fend them off quickly!

Thanks! These ruins are an important piece of Aden’s history, and with those bears gone, I can investigate them properly.

It seems that this area is somehow connected to an ancient demon...

Hey, you’re here. Did you hear about the Elven relics that’re still out here? You’re quick on the uptake, I’ll give you that!

Good! Why don’t we make a deal? I know where the relic is, so if you help me, I’ll give you a reward. What do you think?

Your role is very simple! Just kill the Venomous Spider right over there. Not that I’m afraid of spiders or anything!
Good work! I got the relic thanks to you! I don’t know how much this is worth, though! Oh, here’s your reward. Now, our deal is done!

Hey, you’re here. Did you hear about the Elven relics that’re still out here? You’re quick, I’ll give you that!

Why don’t we make a deal? I know where a relic is, so if you help me, I’ll give you a reward. What do you think?

Your role is very simple! Just kill the Ferocious Cougar. Not that I’m afraid of cougars or anything!

Good work! I got the relic thanks to you! This’ll let me eat like a king

Oh, here’s your reward. Of course, I’m not trying to stiff you! I risked my life for this thing!

A mercenary! What luck! Greetings. My name is Arche. I’m an alchemist here to study the Mana Crystals.

I discovered that Premium Mana Crystals, which are more powerful than normal crystals, have been gathered by the Ol Mahum Vanguards!

I need to research them. Please, bring me some Premium Mana Crystals.

Wow! It’s full of Mana! I must start my experiments right away!

Here’s your reward! Visit my lab someday. I’ll give you a hero’s welcome!

A mercenary! What luck! Greetings. My name is Arche. I’m an alchemist here to study the Mana Crystals.

But... I’m having a hard time because Ol Mahum Guards are taking all of the crystals. Please, can you deal with them for me? I will make it worth your while!
Thank you! Now I can research Mana Crystals more closely! So this is what they look like!

Did you come here to serve justice?! I am Mitchell, a humble soul delivering justice to Aden!

I heard that Soul Slashers attack passersby and absorb their souls! I have to intervene - but I’ve been separated from my companions.

How would you like to join my fight for justice?
Glad to know that you’re with me! We would make good partners! Let’s go hunting together next time!

Hey, you! You’re a mercenary, right? I’ll give you however much you want, please help me. I am exploring Aden and have developed an interest in necromancy!

I’m studying the Cursed Hunters in this area for my research. Can you get me their marks? It’s located on their necks! Careful not to destroy them!

You did better than I expected! These are all in good condition. These marks should provide valuable insight into necromancy! Thank you!

This is your reward. Thank you again!

It’s surprising meeting someone in a ruin like this! I am an adventurer exploring Aden! I saw a good Dagger in the auction, but I’m short on funds!

Do you have any Skeleton Soldier Ribs? Sell them to me when you find them! I’ll give you a square deal, I promise!
These are in excellent condition. Thank you! Here’s your money! I added a tip!

A mercenary! What luck! Greetings. My name is Arche. I’m an alchemist here to study the Mana Crystals.

I’ve located some perfect crystals for use in alchemy...

But there’s a catch. The Ol Mahum took them all! Could you please take some crystals from the Ol Mahum Rangers and bring them to me?
Thank you! Here’s your reward! You brought me so many crystals that I might even have some spare ones to sell!

Did you come here to serve justice?! I am Mitchell, a humble soul delivering justice to Aden!

Vindictive Primas kill the weak and drain their life energy! I can’t let such evil beasts terrorize innocent people! Help me kill these monsters!
Yes, I knew it! I saw it in your eyes - you are also answering justice’s call!

Hey, you! You’re a mercenary, right? I’ll give you as much as you want, please help me! I’m exploring Aden and have recently become interested in necromancy!

But as I was studying necromancy, some mysterious creatures began interrupting my experiments! It’s tremendously bothersome - please defeat them for me!

Whew, hopefully, things will be a bit quieter now. Here’s your reward!

Why are you still here? I must concentrate on my experiment!

Hey, you! You’re a mercenary, right? I’ll give you as much as you want, please help me! I’m exploring Aden and have recently become interested in necromancy!!

I am researching the skeleton warriors around here, and I need someone to collect their skulls. Can you do that for me?

Wow, you got so man! I have a lot of research to do!

Woah! This one almost broke! Anyway, here’s your reward - I’m sure you’ll find it’s more than enough.

It’s surprising meeting someone in a ruin like this! I am an adventurer exploring Aden! I saw a good Dagger in the auction, but I’m short on funds!

Do you have any Vampire Bat Fangs? Sell them to me when you find them! I’ll give you a square deal, I promise!
Wow! You got so many! Vampire Bat Fangs are in high demand - here! Take everything I have!

It’s surprising meeting someone in a ruin like this! I am an adventurer exploring Aden! I saw a good Dagger in the auction, but I’m short on funds!

Do you have any Werewolf Claws? Sell them to me when you find them! I’ll give you a square deal, I promise!

All of these? For me? Let’s see. One... Two... Three...

I lost count! Here, take this, and hopefully, we’ll meet again!

Quick Foot? Now, that’s an interesting rumor. Adventurers say there’s an Ol Mahum faster than any other Ol Mahum around.

Supposedly, Quick Foot is fast thanks to boots it received from a wizard long ago.

I don’t care where the rumor started - I just want those boots!

Lots of Adventurers have tried to catch Quick Foot, but no one’s ever gotten close.

I have a plan! We’ll make it come to us! How? Heh heh, we’ll use bait!

We can catch some Ol Mahum and lock them up. When Quick Foot comes, we’ll spring a trap!

If you help me, I’ll make it worthwhile! What do you say? Don’t you want to see Quick Foot for yourself?

That’s enough hostages.
We’re ready.
Lock up the captured Ol Mahums in the cage.
