It’s all set. Quick Foot will be here soon.

The rumors were true! Quick Foot’s boots! Now, I can catch any monster I want! Thank you! Take this reward for your hard work!

Tell me whenever you need my help and I’ll be there in a flash!

I’d never expect to see anyone out here, but I guess I’m in luck! I need help.

One of my colleagues came here for an alchemy experiment, but I haven’t heard from him since.

I’ve investigating, but there are too many monsters here. Can you help?
How... How could this be... Fenril turned into a monster...? What happened here?

Hi! I needed help, and you’re here just in time! Could you lend me a hand?

I want to study how life forms survive in the desert environment.

That should help us understand how to deal with them! Do you think you could bring me their hearts?
What a mess! But... I’m alive thanks to you! I can pick my research up later - Please take this token of my gratitude!

Good, a mercenary!

We sent some scouts out a few days ago, but now they’re missing. Can you find them?

Oh, and if you take care of the Skeleton Sentinel while you’re at it, I’ll give you a bonus.
Whew, so that’s why they didn’t come back... I will report this at Gludio. This is your reward. Thank you.
By decree of Lord of Gludio, anyone who defeats the Ant General corrupting the barrens shall receive a special reward from my lord in addition to the bounty!
Good work! Never thought I’d see the end of the Ant General! Take this bounty for a job well done!

Greetings. I am Shane of the god Maphr. I’m a novice priest, and came here to complete my training.

I passed all the tests except for finding the Prayer of Maphr! Can you help me?

Whew... this... test... is killing me! But now I have the Prayer, so I can become a full Priest!

Oh - just between you and me, here’s a reward.

Greetings! I needed help, you showed up just in time! Could you lend me a hand?

I am a bit different than other archaeologists. I’m not just interested in relics, but creatures, too!

Did you know that this is basilisk territory? Can you bring me some of their flesh and eggs?

They’re dangerous, so be careful!
Wow! This is huge! Well done, well done! You brought me a very exotic ingredient! Thank you! Here is your reward as promised!

Greetings! You’re the famous Silverlight Mercenary! Good! I am Mitchell, the one who shall bring justice to the evil Ol Mahum! Join me!

Those Ol Mahum are attacking passing merchants! My plan is this: we will disguise ourselves as a caravan and use the cargo as a bait.

When they attack - and they certainly will - we’ll destroy the looters! Genius, right? Let’s do it!
Superb! We even killed the Raider Captain! This was a tremendous victory! Please take this small token of my gratitude. It was an honor to fight at your side!

I didn’t expect to see anyone here! Pleasure to meet you!

Did you come here to fight the Ol Mahum, too? We should team up!

There’s an evil here called Traman! It’s a real rascal and I aim to catch it. Looks like you’re along for the ride!
It’s... It’s dead! Wahoo! That was difficult, but definitely rewarding! I’m going to get even stronger and keep fighting the Ol Mahum!

Hello. I am Explorer Sheena Ringo. I am going to conduct a quite dangerous experiment, so I need someone to protect me. Can you help?

It’s quite simple. You need to guard me while I attempt to fuse mana.

The pay will be very good.

First, can you take out all those Saharas of the Desert? I can’t risk them attacking during my experiment.
I’m beginning the experiment. Be ready! The monsters will be merciless!

Whew... That was close. The fusion was unsuccessful, but I managed to accumulate some Mana in my staff. Dealing with Mana isn’t easy...

Thank you for protecting me. Here is your payment.

Shh! Quiet! I came to retrieve the Necklace of the Wind from inside the Ol Mahum base!

Think you could help me?

If we succeed, I’ll reward you!

Draw their attention while I sneak into their base!

Those Rangers seem like good targets! Let’s go.

Oh no! It’s a trap!
They’re coming! Help!

Please, help me!
Get that Ol Mahum right there!
Ah, hell! Let’s get out of here!
Thanks! I didn’t get the Necklace, but I did manage to pick up some items. Here’s your reward. Thank you!
I found Fenril’s clothes while I was deactivating the magic circle. Could it be connected...?
Whew! I managed to save most of my research equipment, thanks to you! This is your payment! See you later!
No Ant General, but you’ve killed enough ants today. It’s not the full bounty, but I’ll still give you something for your efforts.

Greetings. I am Shane of the god Maphr. I’m a novice priest, and I came here to complete my training.

During the test, I left my holy tome behind! There are a lot of monsters surrounding it - do you think you could come with me?
Whew! I would’ve died out there! But now that I have the tome back, I can return to the church! Thank you very much!
Whew! We’re lucky that this is it! Rumor has it that there’s a giant Basilisk around. If we ran into it, we’d be done for!
Ha ha! We caught a ton of stupid Ol Mahum! Good job! Let’s work together again sometime!

Greetings! My name is Mitchell. I’m an adventurer exploring Aden. I came when I heard that the evil Ol Mahums were here!

The Ol Mahum Looter Guards here have stolen food from each other - and killed their own kind! How could they turn against each other?

This is inhumane, even for Ol Mahum! Let’s show them the power of justice!

Great work! I hope we taught them the importance of loyalty!

Did you see them? They were in tears regretting their sins!

Hark! I came here after hearing that wicked Ol Mahums were picking on the weak near here!

It seems you’re here because of the news as well! Now, let’s bring justice to these Ol Mahum Looter Fighters!

I’ll take this side, and you can deal with that one!

Ol Mahum Looter Fighters raided the caravans and killed the travelers.

They deserve to die! Delivering justice gives me such joy! Hahahaha!

Greetings! My name is Mitchell. I’m an adventurer exploring Aden. I came when I heard that evil Ol Mahums were here!

Ol Mahum Looter Porters traded delirium plants here, even though they’re forbidden in Gludio Territory!

Delirium plants are very venomous! If we don’t stop them, there’s no telling what will happen!

We must defeat them and confiscate all of the delirium plants! Let’s go! There’s no time!

Ah, the sweet smell of justice! Hahaha!

I’ll give these delirium plants to the bailiff. Don’t worry - I’d never profit off injustice! Hahaha!

Huh? What brings you to this battlefield? Well, we could always use some extra hands.

Did you see any Gray Stone Golems around? Their cores have the power to attract stones! The potential of this magic is fabulous.

I’m collecting their cores, but they keep breaking. Bring any you find to me, and I’ll pay handsomely for them!
Thank you. Here’s your payment. I’m looking forward to using magic based on these now that I have some good specimens!

Huh? What brings you to this battlefield? Well, we could always use some extra hands.

Did you see any Saharas of the Desert around? Their cores have the power to attract stones! The potential of this magic is fabulous.

I’m collecting their cores, but they keep breaking. Bring any you find to me, and I’ll pay handsomely for them!
Thank you. I got some great specimens! I look forward to using them in my magic!

Greetings. I am Shane, a novice priest of the god Maphr. We must complete a set of missions before becoming full-fledged priests.

My third assignment is to defeat the Mutant Armored Ant Pages.

They take people as food for their Queen. They must be stopped!

The priests told me it would be simple, but the ant armor is thicker than I thought. Could you defeat them for me? I’ll go with you, and hopefully, I can learn some of your battle skills.

Thank you. It seems that they wanted to test how well can I find help as well. I can’t express my thanks enough.

Here is a small token of thanks. Unfortunately, a priest’s salary is not much... Thank you again.

Greetings. I am Shane, a novice priest of the god Maphr. We must complete a set of missions before becoming full-fledged priests

My second assignment is to defeat the Desert Skeleton Sentinel. They raid attack passersby and absorb their life energy. The church sent me to stop them.

The priests told me it would be simple, but I am having trouble reading their movements. Could you defeat them for me? I’ll go with you, and hopefully, I can learn how to deal with them by studying your methods.
Thank you! Now I know how to fight the Undead. Striking the joints is the key! Thank you very much.

By decree of the Lord of Gludio, I am gathering men to exterminate the Mutant Armored Ant Workers.

Anyone who defeats Mutant Armored Ant Workers shall be rewarded by my lord.
I hear that your work was extraordinary! Attacks from the desert have drastically decreased thanks to you!

By decree of the Lord of Gludio, I am gathering men to exterminate the Mutant Armored Ants.

Anyone who defeats the Mutant Armored Ant Warriors shall be rewarded by my lord.
You did splendidly during the extermination! I will be sure to report this to my lord.

Greetings! I believe there’s an ancient ruin around here - there must be some signs of it buried beneath the sand. I found something special while I was looking around.

It was a space similar to a cave, and I bet there’s something important inside!

I want to investigate it, but there are basilisks are blocking the entrance!

I am well aware of your skills. Could you defeat those basilisks for me? I’ll be sure to reward you.
Thank you! Now that the basilisks are out of the way, I can work in peace! Here’s your payment!

Greetings. My name is Arche. I’m an alchemist developing a combat potion, and I need to gather ingredients.

The Werewolves around here heal incredibly fast! If I could harness that, it would be invaluable in combat!

Bring me some werewolf blood - the more, the better!
This is Werewolf blood? It’s a lot gooier than I expected! Here’s your payment! I should start my experiments right away!

Greetings, I am Shane, a novice priest of the god Maphr. We must complete a set of missions before becoming full-fledged priests

My first assignment is to defeat the Mana Leeches around here. They have been absorbing energy from the ground, making the earth barren. The church sent me to stop them.

I wanted to complete my first assignment, but they stole my energy as well... Can you get my energy back by defeating them?
Thank you! There are far fewer Mana Leeches now, and I feel so much better. May Maphr bless you!

In response to the recent reports of Eroded Saharas attacking merchants, my lord has ordered a cull on Saharas!

Anyone who assists in repelling the Saharas will be rewarded!
Excellent work. I will be certain to deliver word of your accomplishments.

Greetings! I study monsters, and these ants here are really special.

Their exoskeletons are really well developed. Maybe it’s because of the environment? I want to investigate, but I’ll need your help.
I can really make something amazing from this carapace! Thanks!

Hey, I discovered something really special! Take a look!

What’s that face for? This is no normal relic! It must be several hundred years old, at least!

It’s an archaeological breakthrough! I got it from those Sahara. I think the relics are inside their bodies.

Can you catch them for me? I’ll find the relics. Haha!
Hell! Was that just a coincidence? Not a single one... D’oh! Ah, it’s not your fault! Here, your reward!

Greetings. My name is Arche. I’m an alchemist developing a combat potion, and I need to gather ingredients.

The Valley Watchers around here are very good at psychological combat! If I could harness that, it would be invaluable in combat!

Bring me their blood! I want a sample to use for my research.
Thanks! I wonder what kind of potion this will make! Here, your reward as promised!

Welcome, I am Arche, the alchemist. I gathered some ingredients for my experiment, but on my way to the lab, the Ol Mahum stole them...

The ingredients are irreplaceable - I really need them back! They’re in my bag. I think the Ol Mahum Carriers have it.
My bag! Whew, everything’s inside! Thank you. Thank you so much! This is a reward for your efforts. Thank you again!

Look at this... Innocent workers killed. Such meaningless slaughter... How will I tell their families...?

We already know the culprit. With footprints as large as these, only Thrush the Lizardman could have done this. I already sent my men to track him. Go south.

Yikes! Wh-who? Why are you looking for me? Ah, the bailiff sent you?

I found some footprints far larger than normal Lizardmen. It must be the Lizardman boss we’re looking for. Could you see for yourself?
There are Lizardmen in the direction of the footprints. They need to be defeated before the search can continue!
Wow! You beat them all by yourself? And here I was running to help you! Incredible! I’ll tell the bailiff right away!

We hope that Lizardmen will one day live in harmony with the townspeople. Not all Lizardmen are evil, and taking out the few troublesome Lizardmen should bring peace.

Could you defeat the Lizardman called Krush? Defeat his minions and he will appear.
May Eva bless you! Krush was responsible for at least 100 robberies. You did the right thing.

I am looking for ways to bring blessings to every being in this area. Punishing sins is one blessing I can offer.

Will you defeat Varash and his minions? They must pay for their sins.

Thank you! You saved my life! But I lost all of my goods, so I’m good as dead. What’s a trader without anything to trade?

They even took all of my money! Please, get my goods back from those Leto Lizardmen!
... ... ... (It seems Varash has killed the merchant.)

Great job.

What?! Merchants have been attacked by Lizardmen? Where?! I’ll take care of it.

A Lizardman called Screash is killing innocent people. We can’t let a lunatic like that run wild!

Please defeat Screash and his cronies - but watch out for their magical attacks!

You killed the shamans. Are you alright? I’ll tend to your wounds.

What? Something’s coming!
The sin of taking innocent lives is a heavy one. Though I am a servant of the Goddess Eva, it was difficult to show mercy this time...

I have a special announcement from the Cat Caravan! We’re looking for energetic adventurers and buying at high purr-ices!

Right meow, we’re purr-ticularly looking for Elven Red Bear tendon, a specialty of the Plains of Dion! The front paw tendon is purr-fur-ed! Bring them for a bonus!
Meow-velous! High quality deserves a high purr-ice! I’m looking fur-ward to doing business with you again!

We at the Cat Caravan place a special value on our clients’ trust! No trust, no trade! Trust us and lend us a paw, and in turn, we will always pay you well!

Right meow, we’re buying Blood Wasp stingers, a specialty of the Dion Meadows, for a high purr-ice! Bring them right meow for a bonus!

I know that this is Mr. Pann’s turf, but I’m here fur the caravan!

We are purr-chasing Prairie Blade Spider legs, specialty of the Plains of Dion! Bring them right meow for a bonus!

Are you fur-miliar with the Cat Caravan? If not, purr-haps you have seen cat merchant like us be-fur.

We are purr-chasing Red Bear Teeth, specialty of the Plains of Dion in a high purr-ice! Bring them right meow for a bonus!

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills Leto Lizardmen on the Plains of Dion, bring the evidence, and my lord shall reward you!

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills Leto Lizardmen Fighters on the Plains of Dion, bring the evidence, and my lord shall reward you!

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills Leto Lizardmen Archers on the Plains of Dion, bring the evidence, and my lord shall reward you!

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills Leto Lizardmen Looters on the Plains of Dion, bring the evidence, and my lord shall reward you!

The temple warned the Lizardmen about their aggression several times.

They have failed to change their ways, so we must now make an example of them.

While I obey orders... I am not fond of such methods. Will you defeat the Lizardman Shamans in my stead?
Thank you. This is a small token of appreciation. The Temple of Eva thanks you for your assistance.

The High Priests want to change the Lizardmen’s ways by force. I was sent to solve this problem.

I am not fond of using force... I’m hoping you could help me. Could you defeat the Leto Lizardmen Guards for me?
I am glad you’re alright. It was foolish of me to worry.

I’ve been sent here to arbitrate a dispute between the Lizardmen and the townspeople, but you could say that negotiations have... broken down

I was given orders to kill some Leto Lizardman Escorts to set an example, but blood makes me queasy. Could you take care of them for me?
I hope this will help us reach an understanding with the Lizardmen, and actions like this will no longer be necessary. Thank you.

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who vanquishes the Breka Orc Scouts, the scourge of the Dion Meadows, shall receive a reward from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!
Good work. I will pay you the bounty on behalf of the Archon.

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who vanquishes the Breka Orc Fighters, the scourge of the Dion Meadows, shall receive a reward from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who vanquishes the Breka Orc Suppliers, the scourge of the Dion Meadows, shall receive a reward from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Hey, you! Can you help me for a bit? I’m hunting Orcs. Those disgusting creatures don’t deserve to live!

But I can’t exact my vengeance while wounded. It makes me furious knowing that Orcs are running free while I’m stuck licking my wounds! Go and kill some Orcs for me. I’ll pay you, obviously!

Start with the Breka Orc Rangers! They’re the ones responsible for my wound - avenge me!
Whoa, you’re good! You were killing them twice as fast as I could! I’m jealous!

You look like a mercenary - care to kill some Orcs as exercise? I’ll pay you.

I was wounded in a recent battle. It’s not severe, but I need some time. I have Orcs to kill - I can’t die yet!

Could you kill some Breka Orc Troopers? Don’t hold back - make it hurt!
Good work. Your skills make this money well-earned. I admire your Orc-slaying prowess.

Everyone dies... but innocent people deserve better than a death at the hands of Orcs. I must avenge them...

...but my hand was injured, and I can’t hold a sword! I’d punch them, but that might make the wound worse. Still - revenge waits for no man!

Could you kill some Breka Orc Troopers? You look like you could really bring the pain!
The Orcs ruined my life! They must suffer as deeply as I have!

Hey, don’t sneak up on me! Wait - on second thought, perhaps it’s better not to disturb them.

I am Pavel, an entomologist. I am studying the Wasps native to the Plains of Dion, and my assistant just ran off after being stung.

Care to earn some Adena? I have to gather some Wasp specimens for my research... but be careful! My useless assistant might have made the Wasps angry!
Wow, back so soon? And with such good specimens! Hey, maybe you should become my assistant full-time!

Ah, this is troubling! Troubling indeed! I can’t stay here much longer, but my assistant’s nowhere to be found! I need to get Wasp Specimens, but I only have two hands!

Can you help me? I recently received a generous research grant, to there’s money in it for you! Please help me collect Wasp specimens!
Wow, look at these fine specimens! Why don’t you become an entomologist? I think you have the talent! Thanks! You saved me a lot of time!

We’re on the prowl for goods! This is the list of items the Cat Caravan will purr-chase! Bring them and I purr-omise a worthwhile reward.

Bring Prairie Antelope Hind-Legs! Meow!

We need helping paws to bring goods! This is the list of items Cat Caravan will purr-chase! Bring them and I purr-omise a worthwhile reward.

Bring Prairie Windsus livers! Meow!

We need helping paws to bring goods! This is the list of items Cat Caravan will purr-chase! Bring them and I purr-omise a worthwhile reward.

Bring Elder Antelope horns! Meow!

Dion Meadows is a wonderful place. The warm weather and fertile soil make food plentiful. The ingredients in this area are a premium dish on their own!

I am Chef Mechillen from the Gourmet Society. I was planning to gather ingredients here, but the hunter we hired is late. Ah, all this talk is making me hungry. Should we have a light snack?

Could you bring me an Elder Antelope flank? It’s the best meat for a steak.

If you do, I'll let you experience what a true chef's cooking tastes like. What do you say?
Oh, good timing! I just finished the necessary preparations. The meat is in premium condition. Let’s cook!

Taste is the gift of nature. We have an obligation to enjoy it. Oh, the world is full of flavors! A lifetime is too short.

I need an appetizer to prepare for the Gourmet Society’s feast tomorrow. I was hoping to look for some ingredients around here, but the hunter caught a cold and can't make it!

Tch! A cold. I saw him swimming in a wine barrel just yesterday!

Could you bring me the hind leg of an antelope for me? Ham made from it is the best appetizer to pair with drinks.
Oh, you’re back already. Unfortunately, I underestimated the time it will take to make this. I'll have to use this to trade for some proper ham. Money is always available, but ingredients are not.

The Gourmet Society is searching for the true meaning of life by eating... It seems like a tremendous task - but eating delicious food is a welcome challenge!

I plan to gather ingredients here today. The quality of the ingredients has a major impact on the quality of the dish, you know. But I haven't heard from the Hunter I hired. I would do it myself if I was any good at archery!

Could you bring me a Prairie Antelope? Of course, I don’t plan to eat it whole! But explaining the whole recipe would be a waste of time.
Wow, that was quick! This ingredient sure is fresh. Say... how about an exclusive contract with the Gourmet Society?

The Cat Caravan is supplying us with food, but their quality is all over the place. Pann is trusty, but he’s not always around.

I heard that a mercenary supplies Pann with goods, and I think the description matches you! Heh heh, can I ask you for your help?

Could you find some Vampire Bats? Their wing membrane is very tasty if you cook it just right! Oh, I’m drooling just thinking about it. Hurry, please!
Oh, it’s the Vampire Bat! Your decision to bring it as a whole was wise. Preparing the membrane requires a chef’s knife, not a warrior’s blade.

Greetings, [player]! We meet again. I’m patrolling the Cruma Swamp, and I have a job just right for you.

As long as the Marsh Queen, Zyrnna, is here, Cruma is not safe. Do you know how many people fled because of Zyrnna?

Please defeat Zyrnna! Defeating the Marsh Stakatos first will help weaken her. Don’t forget that Zyrnna leads a pack.

Ugh, I’m exhausted! I can’t hold my sword...

There! Zyrnna’s over there! Go get her!
Wow, you defeated Zyrnna! Your skills surprise me! I always trained myself, but... you’re out of my league. Good work, ha ha!

I have a target for you. Its name is Arcane - the leader of Wraiths. Arcane’s fate is sealed.

Arcane must be destroyed. I have placed a curse on it to force it to appear.

However, I’m missing some ingredients to activate the curse. Go collect dark essence from Shadow Choir Primas. I will use this summoning circle to send you to their location.
Impressive. You exceeded my expectations. You have a talent for destruction. Don’t fear your abilities.

I have a target for you: an Undead soldier named Liam. Once a valiant soldier, now he wanders aimlessly. You must destroy him.

I put a strong curse on him. Now, all we need to do is activate the summoning circle. But to do that, I'll need some ingredients.

I am proud of my curses, but there is something you must be aware of. A curse this powerful is bound to have side effects.

When my curse is active, it tends to also draw out entities similar to the target. Be prepared.

Does destruction necessitate pain? Not for me. It is a sweet temptation.

Hehehe... You’ve done well, Gran Kain shall be pleased.

You must destroy an Undead called Ronde. Ronde has always had a posse, and I expect it to be no different now. This task may prove to be difficult.

I will summon Ronde now, and I trust you will destroy him. Move to the magic circle.

My curse’s strength has a side effect; it will summon his minions along with him.

Did you expect this to be easy? There’s a reason it’s called a curse.
I will now close the summoning gate. Collect the cursed skulls from the Skeleton Scouts nearby.

Well done. The summoning gate is closed - and I’ll be keeping an eye on you.

If not for destruction, the world would be overwhelmed by chaos and agony. Destruction is necessary to maintain balance. May Gran Kain bless you. Follow his path.

This is a de-claw-ration from Cat Caravan. We are looking for paw-erful adventurers! We are willing to buy the following item for a high purr-ice!

We are purr-chasing the Swamp Assassin’s sharp hook, a specialty of Cruma Swamp, at a high purr-ice! Bring them right meow for a bonus!

We at the Cat Caravan place a special value on our clients’ trust! No trust, no trade! Trust us and lend us a paw, and in turn, we will always pay you well!

We are purr-chasing the Marsh Stakato Hassassin’s sharp blade, a specialty of Cruma Swamp at a high purr-ice! Bring them right meow for a bonus!

I know that this is Mr. Pann’s turf, but I’m here fur the Caravan!

We are purr-chasing leather wristbands, a specialty of the Cruma Swamp! I’ve heard you can take them from the Destructive Killer! Bring them right meow for a bonus!

Hey there! I knew we’d meet again someday! You think you could help me? Only if you’re not busy, of course!

There are Relic Fragments all over the place but I can’t do anything because of the monsters!

The Insane Killers have been particularly pesky - do you think you could get rid of them for me?
Heh heh, trusting you always pays off. You’re the best! You’ve done your work, and now I shall do mine!

What are you doing in Cruma Swamp, of all places? Me? I’m here because Feldheim asked me to collect Relic Fragments.

There are so many Relic Fragments here that all you have to do is pick them up - except the Killers are waiting to strike down innocent archaeologists like me!

Please defeat them. I can’t bear another sleepless night!
Hey, is that a scratch? No? Just some dust? Glad to hear it! You’re safe, and I’m safe to work! Thanks!

Excavation, excavation, excavation... and a glass of ale! Ah, the drink after work is nothing short of heaven itself! But I can’t even think about that right now. I haven’t gathered enough relics for Feldheim yet.

If not for that blasted Shadow Choir Prima, I’d be swimming in booze already! I’ll buy you a drink if you defeat them for me - what do you say?
Woohoo! Thanks. Now my work begins! Why don’t you get a head start on the drinking? This much won’t get you plastered, but it’ll at least turn your nose red!

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills Swamp Killers in Cruma Swamp, bring the evidence, and my lord shall reward you!

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills the Swamp Hassassin, my lord shall reward you!

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever can defeat the Marsh Stakato Slave of Cruma Swamp shall be handsomely rewarded by my lord!

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills the Marsh Stakato Envoys of Cruma Swamp, my lord shall reward you!

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills the Swamp Assassin, my lord shall reward you!

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who deals with the Maille Lizardmen Vanguard, the scourge of Cruma Swamp, shall receive a bounty from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who deals with the Maille Lizardmen Shamans, the scourge of Cruma Swamp, shall receive a bounty from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who deals with the Maille Lizardmen Pursuers, the scourge of Cruma Swamp, shall receive a bounty from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Excuse me... I have a favor to ask... Ah! Keep your voice down. We must speak without the bailiff noticing. It’s nothing illegal.

I lost the bailiff’s luggage. It must have been while I was napping earlier. I was able to find the bags, but the wine was missing.

It couldn’t have disappeared by itself! I think the Maille Lizardmen Patrol may have stolen it. Could you look for it?

The bailiff’s always thirsty after his shift. I’m dead if it’s still missing by then! My life is in your hands!

Oh wine! You found two bottles of it!

This should be fine! I’ll fill in the rest secretly! Thank you so much! This is such a relief!

[player]? [player]? Don’t move and just listen. I can’t speak any louder.

I noticed a few things disappeared while I was aslee- er, busy. I need to find them before the bailiff notices. I’ve already found some of the items, but I can’t seem to find the bailiff’s favorite pair of Greater Gloves.

They were brand new, and specially imported from Giran! If he finds out, I’ll lose my job!

Please help me. I’ve looked everywhere except for in the Swamp Ghouls’ lair. Could you defeat them? If you do, I’ll be able to look for the gloves.
I found them! I found them! they were, uh, at the bottom of the bag... Ugh. Sorry. This is so embarrassing...

I am a Priest of Gran Kain, redeeming the world through destruction. Join me in saving the world.

We must destroy the Cursed Seers. Gran Kain is not fond of the Undead. I will wait.
It was well worth the wait. Was it uplifting? Gran Kain is truth itself.

The world can be redeemed through destruction. Follow the will of Gran Kain.

The Horror Reapers must be destroyed. They should have met their deaths long ago and cannot be allowed to live again. I will wait.
Life must end at death. If not, life must be ended more forcefully.

Destruction is not the same as violence. The prejudice against it must be done away with

The Skeleton Scouts must be destroyed. Life must not continue after death. I will wait.
Your doubtless attitude is very good. Do not fear destruction.

Only fools turn their backs on destruction. Creation alone is imbalanced.

The Skeleton Pursuers must be destroyed. Life that does not respect death is worthless. I will wait.
Gran Kain smiles upon you. Thank you.

We need helping paws to bring goods! This is the list of items Cat Caravan will purr-chase! Bring them and I purr-omise a worthwhile reward.

Bring us Swamp Venomous Spider legs.
These are in purr-fect condition! You have a lot of tail-ent! Let’s work paw in hand again soon!

We need helping paws to bring goods! This is the list of items Cat Caravan will purr-chase! Bring them and I purr-omise a worthwhile reward.

Bring us venom sacks from Black Tiger Spiders!
Be claw-tious! The sacks need to be specially paw-ndled. Cat-ch you later!

Join paws with the Cat Caravan! We’re always on the prowl for goods! Bring good items for a good purr-ice!

Bring us Swamp Bat ears!
Won-fur-ful! The items you bring are always of the most su-purr-ior quality! Cat-ch you later!

Our temple received oracular orders to purify this land and put an end to the shadow creatures who reject the light of Einhasad.

Could you help me by defeating the Mist Horror Reapers?
The will of Einhasad leads to a greater good. Thank you.

I am here on the orders of the temple. The goddess has commanded purification of this land.

Will you help me defeat the Cursed Seer? Thank you.
Following the goddess’s will brings joy. You could be happy, too. Thank you.

By the will of Einhasad, will you join me in protecting everyone from the Undead?

You can help by defeating the Horror Reapers. Please lend us your aid.
A great temple begins from small bricks. Thank you.

Ol B’Khan, the leader of the Ol Mahum, is too aggressive. He is killing merchants left and right.

My people have found that Ol B’Khan has departed with a small squad of fighters to attack Tanor.

I am planning to strike from behind while Ol B’Khan is distracted, but first, we should improve our relationship with Tanor.

Could you kill some of the Ol Mahum Scouts over there?

Good work! It seems you’re famous in Tanor as well - along with a man named Durzel?

Anyway, we pinpointed the location of Ol B’Khan! Let’s make haste!
Good work killing Ol B’Khan single-handedly! Are all the Silverlight Mercenaries like you? Sir Hardin should be proud of his warriors!

I was sent here to investigate the robbery, and to deal proper punishment to the perpetrators. A wagon carrying cargo for our church was raided nearby.

I must bring in Tartan, the Guard Captain of Tanor, as a suspect in this robbery. I expect resistance, so it would be wise to suppress the local Tanor residents.
Good. Now let’s go get Tartan! I know his location.
Tartan! Have you no faith? How dare you touch a tribute to Maphr! I shall arrest you for robbery, theft, and sacrilege!
Curses! His spirit is strong! He’s resisting the spell!
Ah.. I can feel my legs again. I was paralyzed when the spell was broken. It was a hard battle. Well done.

I am a Priest of Maphr. A carriage carrying goods for our church was attacked and robbed near here.

It seems clear that the Tanor near here stole the goods. We must recover the missing tribute from them.
The Tanor holding the tribute is major evidence. Shall we investigate the wagon’s location?

Textbook behavior from the prime suspect. He’s back at the scene of the crime!

I’ll cast a spell to catch him.
Good work. Thaartan claims to be innocent, which I will believe until the court proves otherwise - but I cannot release him if he does not agree to cooperate.

A wagon carrying tribute for our church was robbed here. I suspect that Tutan, an advisor of Tanor, is responsible.

I must bring him to court. I ask for your help.
The time is now. I will overpower Tutan by casting a spell of immobilization. Please take care of his minions.

I appear to be cursed. I can’t hold Tutan in this state.

We need the Tanor Shaman’s talisman to lift the curse, but I doubt they will part with it easily.
You arrived just in time. A moment longer, and Tutan could have gone free. This will lift the curse on me. Now, I will take care of Tutan.

Oh, it’s you again! You’re more famous than I thought. I should buy more mana potions next time I visit the Silverlight Mercenaries. What brings you here?

I’m gathering ingredients because a woman claiming to be my rival challenged me. We’re going to have a cook-off!

The loser has to grant any wish for the winner. My pride’s on the line - I can’t lose!!!

People seldom come here, so there are lots of exotic ingredients around. I came here for a preliminary survey, but I can’t leave now that you’re here!

Fill my shopping list, and you’ll have permanent VIP status at my restaurant! First things first, I need Venomous Marsh Spider eyeballs.
Oh! I’m excited to get started on this dish. Thank you!

[player]? Remember me? You didn’t forget the master chef of the Gourmet Society, Mechillen, did you?

Ha ha! I have been challenged for the title of best chef. Why that woman regards me as her rival, I don’t know, but I must do my best to keep my pride.

I am going to gather special ingredients for this cook-off. This place is off the beaten path, so it’s full of rare ingredients, but...

It’s difficult for me to collect them myself. It’s a good thing I ran into you! Do you think you could help me with this list?

I need Shade Wasp wings. Haha! How I plan to use them is a secret!
Delicious food comes at a price. The chef’s talents and the ingredients both have to be the very best!

Huh? Have we met? I know you... Oh! You’re [player]! Welcome. You helped me a lot before!

I came here to prepare for a cook-off. A chef always has to defend their pride! Delicious dishes are always satisfying, but to tell the truth, I’m a bit nervous about this match!

The cook-off is a few days from now. If I’m going to show off my skills, I need the best ingredients!

I need Marsh Premo Keratin skins. Don’t worry, I would never serve them raw!
You look a little queasy. I told you, I’m not going to serve these plain! These skins have a special yeast on them that’s great for making bread. Are you satisfied now?

Oh, we meet again! What brings you here? I’m here for ingredients, of course. I have a cook-off coming up!

Most people don’t even know this place exists - that lady chef won’t stand a chance if I get my ingredients here!

I have to gather some Walking Fungus spore sacs. Could you help?
Thank you. Now I’m guaranteed to win!

We met again! I’m still grateful for your help. What brings you all the way out here? I’m preparing for an upcoming cook-off.

Since I can’t put this entire area in a pot, I need someone to collect the ingredients for me... and as luck would have it, here you are!

Do you think you could help me? I have to win this one! I need Red Fox meat, but I can’t kill them myself. Can you help a gourmand out?
It takes a very talented chef to cook Red Fox meat - otherwise, the stench will be unbearable! How do I do it? That’s a secret!

Hey there! You’re going to get mugged by Ol Mahum wandering around like that! No matter how confident you are, this is their turf.

It’s been a while since I last saw you! You seem to be stronger than before. I’m grateful for your help before - do you think you could help us out again?

I wonder where Mitchell is... I’m worried. He sure was bragging loudly about stealing that Soul Crystal from the Ol Mahum boss.

We should reduce the number of Ol Mahum before Mitchell returns. He can be a little careless, so I hope you can defeat the Ol Mahum Officers first.
That Mitchell! Can you believe him? A weapon is more important than a Soul Crystal! Anyways, thanks for your help!

Hey, long time no see! Look at you, with all this fancy armor! What brings to this place crawling with Ol Mahum?

I’m looking for Mitchell. He was saying something about an Ol Mahum Boss Soul Crystal before he disappeared, so I’m a bit worried.

If Mitchell is stranded somewhere, he’s probably hiding from the Ol Mahum. Defeating the Ol Mahum Recruits should make Mitchell’s return a little easier. Do you think you could do it?
Nothing in this world is free, so here’s your payment. Thank you.

Ah... Mitchell you rascal, where are you? This is practically Ol Mahum turf...

Huh? Good to see you! I bought a new dagger thanks to you. Can I ask for a favor again?

Sara Ra and I are looking for Mitchel, but we’ve had no luck so far. I’m trying to take out some of the Ol Mahum Suppliers to give Mitchell an easier path back.

Mitchell will probably think it’s his good luck that dealt with the Ol Mahum, but that’s fine by me as long as he’s safe.
Don’t look at me like that. I’ve been picking up after him for 3 years. If Mitchell is alright, then it doesn’t matter. Anyway, thanks for your help!

Hm? Have we met? I think we have... Well, in any case, can you help me?

I’m testing a new spell against the Ol Mahum, but I’m short on mana, and out of potions as well.

I promised to find Mitchell, but I can’t do anything right now. Mitchell will find his way, but Dorothy is too much of a worrywart! Hmm... While I replenish my mana...

Could you look for Mitchell? Be careful, this is Ol Mahum turf. Actually, it might be best to strike first. They’re not the friendliest, after all.
Wow, that was quick! My mana isn’t even half full yet! You’ve definitely become more powerful since last time!

Huh? I think I know you... Ah... where was it? Whatever, good to see you!

Dorothy told me to find Mitchell... You remember us, don’t you? Anyways, I don’t see why I have to look for him - he’ll come back when he feels like it.

I should probably defeat some Ol Mahum Sentries, but my mana is low. My new spell really soaks up mana.

Could you kill some Ol Mahum Sentries for me? You know that I pay well, right?
Wow! The Ol Mahum will go extinct at this rate. That’s enough. Mitchell should be back soon. Here’s your payment!

Uh... Your name... was... Ah! [player], right? I remember! Thank you for your help last time. Glad to see you again. Are you looking for some work?

You remember Mitchell, right? He’s somewhere among all those Ol Mahum out there, but I’m out of mana potions.

You don’t need to search for him yourself, just take out some of the Ol Mahum Sentries and he’ll come back. I’ll pay you for your time.
Mitchell’s still out there... don’t worry! I’m sure he’s alive and on his way back. Here’s your payment.

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who deals with the Kankoon Sentries, the scourge of the Summit of Dissonance, shall receive a bounty from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who deals with the Kankoon Elite Soldiers, the scourge of the Summit of Dissonance, shall receive a bounty from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who deals with the Kankoon Priests, the scourge of the Summit of Dissonance, shall receive a bounty from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who deals with the Tanor Fighters, the scourge of the Summit of Dissonance, shall receive a bounty from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Greetings, I am Rouen, a priest of the Maphr Church. I came to investigate the theft of my church’s tribute.

The High Priest suspects Tanor, but I believe the Ol Mahum are the culprits. Those cunning rascals manipulated the evidence to make Tanor the primary suspect.

I must arrest the Ol Mahum, but the High Priest will not allow it without more evidence. But leaving them like this makes me angry.

Can you bring justice to the Ol Mahum in my stead by destroying the Ol Mahum Patrol?
Oh, you’ve returned. That was justice well-served. Thank you.

Greetings, I am Rouen, servant of Maphr. I am investigating the theft of our church’s tribute. The High Priest suspects Tanor, but I think the Ol Mahum are behind it.

The Ol Mahum must have manipulated the evidence, so I have no proof that I can arrest them with.

If the law can’t serve justice, we must take things into our own hands. Please punish the Ol Mahum Scouts on my behalf.
The Tanor would never be so cunning. Since this was not a straightforward crime, this must be the work of the Ol Mahum. Good work.

Did you see the High Priest? He went to go arrest the Tanor?! But that evidence may have been manipulated! Ugh... he’s really inflexible.

I mean - I didn’t say anything! Don’t tell the High Priest I was badmouthing him.

I’m looking for the criminal who raided the wagon carrying our church’s tribute, and I think the Ol Mahum are responsible. The evidence shows that it’s Tanor, but that evidence is just too simple!

The evidence must have been tampered with. The Ol Mahum must have done it! There’s no official reason to attack them, but won’t you help me out?

It would be great if you could teach the Ol Mahum Sentries a lesson for their deception. I really want to do it myself, but I must ask your help instead.
I don’t think the High Priest’s methods are wrong, but this requires a more thorough investigation. Wrongdoers must be punished!

The Ol Mahum must have attacked the wagon carrying the tribute. Problem is, the evidence was manipulated to make Tanor the suspects!

It’s obvious the Tanor aren’t responsible to anyone with half a brain, but that being said, the High Priest is too stubborn.

I can’t strike the Ol Mahum without the authorization of the High Priest, But I can’t just let this go. Please punish the Ol Mahum Officers in my stead! Please!
Whew, that was so satisfying! It’s almost enough to make me break my vows! Thank you!

Hello? Adventurer? Could you move out of the way? I am a bit busy... Oh! Wait, do you think you could help me?

I’m Ashley, a master chef, and I’m preparing for a cook-off to prove myself as the best chef in Dion. I’m collecting ingredients, but my sous chefs are doing a terrible job.

I can pay you whatever you want, so could you collect some ingredients for me? It should be easy. Do we have a deal?

Bring me a Red-Tailed Fox. It needs to be all in one piece. Hurry!
Oh, good! It’s in good shape! If the hunt goes on too long, the ingredients get stressed and then they’re ruined! Its condition shows your skill!

Be careful! You don’t want to be eaten, do you? There’s very dangerous wildlife around here. I want to cook, not be cooked!

Have you ever heard the name Ashley? The master chef! The most popular chef in Dion! ...

...

No? How disappointing! You’re not interested in cuisine? Anyway, you look like someone that can hold their own in a fight. Can you hunt some Black Leopards for me? I’ll pay you well for them.
Wow, back so soon? You’re amazing! Here’s your payment! You should start studying food so your taste buds can understand how awesome I am!

Most Adventurers have poor taste - they’ll eat anything. Are you like that, too? I bet you’ll change your mind if you try a dish made by a master chef.

I’m Ashley, the top up-and-coming chef in Dion! Old guys like Mechillen are too old-fashioned! You’re interested in my dishes?

If you bring me some ingredients, I’ll invite you to my restaurant! An irresistible deal, don’t you think?

Alright, then bring me some Forest Fang Spiders. Bring them whole. I’ll cut them up myself! I’m tougher than I look, right?
Well, well! Bring them on! Oh, these look great! This should be enough! Here, I don’t skimp out on pay. I wonder what Mechillen is doing right now? He must be gathering ingredients somewhere...

Out of my way. Do you know that you’re hindering a master chef’s work? I’m collecting ingredients for an upcoming cook-off.

Where the hell are those hunters? Did they wind up getting poached? Ah, what’s a chef got to do to get capable help around here? Hey, wait, are you a mercenary?

Good! Here’s a chance to make up for getting in my way! I might even feed you if you do well!

Now, go and get some Sapping Wasps for me! Bring them whole if you can!

You’re back? You didn’t find the remains of those hunters, right? I’m joking!

I can’t cook right away, but you can visit my restaurant anytime. It’s easy to find. I think this is a wonderful start to a friendship! See you!

Hey, friend! Remember me? I’m Mitchell, the Aden explorer! I came here pursuing justice. Intel says the Ol Mahum here have a high-quality Soul Crystal! They might be using it for evil purposes!

I have to take the crystal to make sure it isn’t used for evil. I don’t know its exact location, so I’m attacking them one by one.

Can you take down the Ol Mahum Sentry over there? I’ll handle things here.
What? Done already? I knew I could count on you!

Monsters like this know nothing of justice - power only serves to feed their greed! I, Mitchell the Aden Explorer, shall defeat the Ol Mahum in the name of justice!

The Ol Mahum here have high-quality Soul Crystals. I’m concerned about what evil they might try to use it for.

I can’t let that happen! I’m pretty sure the Ol Mahum Suppliers have the crystals. Why don’t you check it out? I’ll go this way!
I guess it’s far-fetched to think the suppliers would have the Soul Crystals, but better safe than sorry!

Hey, glad to see you! It’s me, Mitchell, the Aden Explorer! Remember me? I’m delivering justice, as always. Why don’t you join me?

The Ol Mahum have gotten their hands on some high-quality Soul Crystals. I have no idea what kind of evil they’ll get up to with them, so we should destroy them.

I bet the commanders will be carrying the Soul Crystals. We should smash all of the Ol Mahum equipment to be safe!
Good! We can’t check them one by one, so this is the best solution! Great work!

I’m hunting Shrieking Treants, also known as Corpse Gatherers... However, it’s not going as I planned. I’ve sent soldiers to track them down, but they never returned.

Even more troubling, the soldiers I sent to look for the soldiers have not returned. There must be something going on. Do you think you could look for them?

Oh, and if you see any Screaming Treants or Black Willows on the way, kill them on the spot. They’re criminals responsible for numerous deaths of merchants and travelers in this area!

(Cough) ...who are you?

Th-the Archon sent you? Y-you’re... too... late... I’m... finished...

B-beware... of the trees... set them on fire... if it moves... it’s not... a normal tree... ugh...

Marvelous! You single-handedly did what the soldiers could not!

However, this tragedy is my responsibility. I didn’t assess the enemy’s power very well. Fortunately, your work with the Shrieking Treants gave their sacrifice meaning...

I have been assigned to purify this land, but it is as I feared - the Undead are already too numerous. There is a Fell Spirit called Balthazar among them.

It corrupts souls in such a way that they can never be cleansed. A terrible fate...

Balthazar is inside the Keep of Agony. Destroy the Fell Spirits, and it shall arrive to claim the souls lost by the Fell Spirits. Please defeat Balthazar.
Thank you. Your help has made Einhasad smile.

There is a specter named Cowboy, and it is desperately searching for something. Its soul is twisted, but full of sadness. We must put it to rest.

Specters tend to gather around, so look for Cowboy while you are killing the Tortured Specters.
This poor soul. I feel its sad longing... Now... It shall rest eternally in the arms of Einhasad.

The Shrieking Hallows are filled with of restless Undead. No matter what may have been unresolved in their former lives, they must now come to accept their deaths.

The Seamstress is the most spiteful of them all, but we do not need to know her story. For there is no death without a tale...

We can grant her eternal peace under Einhasad. Let us defeat Seamstress together.

We will summon the Seamstress against her will using a method preferred by the Priests of Gran Kain.

You must collect essence of tenacity from the Relentless Specters. It will be used as a catalyst for the summoning. I shall prepare the ritual.
The job makes us unwanted here. Did you gather them all? Good. Let’s begin.
Thank you. Death is the equalizer. A full death is required for a birth to have a meaning. May Einhasad bless you.

By the orders of the lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills the Bloodthirsty Specter in the Shrieking Hallows, bring the evidence, and my lord shall reward you!

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills the Resurrected Specter in the Shrieking Hallows, bring the evidence, and my lord shall reward you!

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills the Resurrected Merchants in the Shrieking Hallows, bring the evidence, and my lord shall reward you!

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills the Skeleton Troopers in the Shrieking Hallows, bring the evidence, and my lord shall reward you!

This land is truly unholy. It is crawling with wretches beyond redemption. May Einhasad bless you.

Please slay the Nerkas Necromancer. Do that, and I shall purge their foul and unholy souls permanently.
The soul of the Nerkas Necromancer has been destroyed. Good work. May the blessings of Einhasad be with you...

Our temple will purify this land that opposes the goddess. Please help us.

Please slay the Nerkas Soulharvester so I may destroy its wicked soul.
The Nerkas Soulharvester’s soul has been completely destroyed. You’ve done well. May Einhasad bless your path...

Zombie Lords are truly horrendous. I don’t want to even speak of them. I shall purify them even without the order of the temple.

Please defeat the Zombie Lord so I may destroy its soul.
The Zombie Lord is now no more. Thank you. May Einhasad bless you...

The Shrieking Hallows are a place that our church is closely monitoring. Our novice priests all visit here at least once. It is our mission to purify this land, no matter the cost.

Can you defeat the Relentless Specters? I hope you choose to lend us your strength.
Thank you. The Relentless Specters have been purified. Einhasad shall bless your path. May the light be with you, always...

We novice priests have a Rite of Passage which involves purging the souls of the Undead from the Shrieking Hallows. A dangerous task, but one that must be done.

Please don’t concern yourself with the specifics - it is the goddess’s will that I receive your aid. Will you destroy the Tortured Specters? Thank you so much.
Thank you. The Tortured Specters have been purified. Einhasad will bless your path. May the light guide you...

This is where Einhasad’s hand is really required. We novice priests must purify the souls of the Undead here.

Receiving help is the goddess’s will. Could you destroy the Dread Servants here?
Thank you. The Dread Servants have been purified. Einhasad will bless your path. May the light guide you...

All priests of Einhasad pass through this land. We are tirelessly working to purify the Undead. The obligation involves enlisting others’ help if needed.

Will you defeat the Fettered Souls for us? We would be grateful if you could lend us your strength.
Thank you. The Fettered Soul has been purified. Einhasad will bless your path. May the light guide you...

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who deals with the Innocent Spirits, the scourge of the Shrieking Hallows, shall receive a bounty from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who deals with the Death Reaper, the scourge of the Shrieking Hallows, shall receive a bounty from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who deals with the Ominous Willow, the scourge of the Shrieking Hallows, shall receive a bounty from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Listen here! Listen here! The Archon has an offer! Adventurers, Soldiers, Mercenaries! Lend me your ears!

Anyone who deals with the Doom Servant, the scourge of the Shrieking Hallows, shall receive a bounty from the Archon! Test your luck and valor!

Hi! I’m Yumaeri, a botanist studying the plants native to the Shrieking Hallows. I primarily focus on mobile ones like the Dicor or Mandragora. Static ones are boring, don’t you think?

I need to gather some samples, but the researchers here are nothing but a bunch of wimps. We need someone strong, like you! Will you gather some Dicor of Sorrows specimens? I have plenty of Adena and I’m willing to pay.
If I’d only met you sooner, I would have saved some time. The previous mercenaries all fled! Thank you.

Are you... an adventurer? Mercenary? You’re not a common worker, right? I’m not a common botanist, either!

I passed out for 3 days after hearing the scream of a Mandragora recently. I’m lucky to be alive, quite honestly. I’ve shifted the focus my research to directly studying specimens after that. So I’m looking for people who can gather specimens for me. Interested?

You look confident. I like that! Could you gather some Furious Mandragora specimens? I’ll reward you accordingly.
Nothing will prove your confidence better than field work! Great job. This will be a great help to my research - and I hope this Adena will help you.

I’m a botanist studying mobile plants like Dicors and Mandragoras. Plants that move like animals - fascinating, right?

Problem is, it’s hard to get them to cooperate with my research. I’m studying specimens, but even that’s difficult, and unfortunately, scientists aren’t great in combat.

You look rather skilled. Could you help me gather the Wailing Mandragora? I’ll pay you for your efforts.
Your skills are worth the money! Thank you.

Each Mandragora is all different, even if they look the same. You need a botanist’s eye to see the difference. I am studying specimens, but I’m having a hard time collecting them.

I hired some mercenaries for the job, but they all ran away. Hey, how about you? You seem confident - you think you could do it? I’ll pay you accordingly. Want to gather some Tortured Mandragora Specimens for me?
You meticulously gathered only Tortured Mandragoras. You’re more amazing than I thought! Why don’t you work as a botanist? There’s an opening in my lab. You’re always welcome!

Although they’re plants, Dicors are capable of complex emotions. Dicors of Despair, as their name suggests, are filled with dark feelings. I want to study them, but the mercenaries I hired all ran away.

I must have underestimated their strength. You... You look like you can handle them! Could you gather some Dicor of Despair Specimens for me? I’ll make it worth your time!
Wow, that was quick! The difficulty may be relative, but you’re really awesome!

We meet again. Gran Kain must have sent you here. There is a job just for you.

We must destroy the Vindictive Killers. A reason? Go listen to the lectures at the Temple of Einhasad. No? Then do the job without question. Go now.
Do you know Laurel from the temple of Einhasad? I wonder how those sentimental fools are getting by. I trust that you have defeated the Vindictive Killers.

The priests of Einhasad are not the only ones who visit here. We come here often because we can practice destruction without worrying about collateral damage.

Destruction is without guilt. Now, the Demented Reapers must meet their ends.
I feel it. So, you’ve succeeded. The shroud of Gran Kain suits you. When it comes to the Undead, we won’t be outdone.

Our temple will destroy the Undead in the Shrieking Hallows, and you shall help us do it. Gran Kain has chosen you. I know you will do the job.

Destroy the Black Willows. Burn them, crush them, it’s your call.
Do you feel it? The inner voice? Gran Kain will always watch over you. Destroying the Black Willows must have been a pleasure.

Hello? [player], I know you’re busy but could you stay a while and listen?

Sir Ancelotti assigned me a job. He wanted to concentrate on searching for the Shrieking Treants, so I have to cover his back.

I trained as a knight, but I barely passed. I won’t last very long out there. I think I’m going to cry. Could you slay the Maimed Killer for me? Please!
Thank you, thank you! I’ll double down on my combat training. Thank you again!

[player]! [player]! Please save me. The bailiff commanded me to watch the rear. How can I defeat the Exhausted Doom Servants?

Unless you want to see me as a corpse next time, please help me. My life is in your hands!
Thank you! I really thought I was done for. I’ll see another sunrise thanks to you!

Ah, [player]! Greetings! Uh, could you help me? Do you think you could defeat the Innocent Spirit over there?

The bailiff is not aware that I was bottom of my class in training. I don’t last long in combat. Please help a poor squire!
Oh, you’re a lifesaver, <YellowBold>[player]</>! Thank you! Now I feel safe! Whew, I thought I was going to die!

Welcome! I’m rescuing my comrades who were kidnapped by Zaken’s minions. I’d appreciate your assistance - what do you say?

I already saved some of them, but from what they tell me, there are others in different locations.

I can’t leave them behind. Please rescue them. Zaken’s minions are concentrated near the prisoners, so make sure to take them out first.
Thanks to you, many people were spared having their souls stolen by Zaken. Words cannot express how much I appreciate the help!

The Devil's Isle is full of treasures, but claiming them is quite difficult.

I’ve heard a lot about you and your Silverlight Mercenaries. Why don’t you join me in the treasure hunt? I already found a few, but it’s been difficult bringing them back because of monsters.

What do you say? If you bring them from the coordinates I give you, we can split the profits 50/50. Deal?

I’ll tell you the location. You’ll know I wasn’t lying when you get there.

The first treasure is just south of here. There’s a Red Treasure Chest near the treasure pile. Opening the chest will attract lots of monsters, so be on guard.

Huff... Huff... That was close!

Let’s see... sword with gemstones... golden goblet... and this diamond!

Why don’t you join me? We can be billionaires if we work together!

The difficult jobs are yours, of course!

I must be lucky meeting a Silverlight Mercenary in a place like this! I am Tark, Giran Vanguard!

I thought my comrades were all dead, but after investigating, I discovered that they’re alive.

They’re being held prisoner! Time is short! We must rescue them. Let’s deal with Zaken's Retinues and the Master Shooters first. Let’s go! I’ll make it worthwhile!

Great Job! You’ve done well! I’ll pay you handsomely when I return to Giran Castle.

I wonder why Zaken’s minions imprisoned people instead of killing them? Normal Undead shouldn’t have any free will...

Heh heh...

Did you come for me? Greetings. I was once Zaken’s second-in-command. Now I am a cursed man, something between living and dead.

Do you need money? I can give you lots of it if you grant my request.

It’s not so difficult. You will find a Black Treasure Chest on the edge of the Wharf over there. There’s a skull with a gemstone embedded in it. Please bring it to me.

Oh, the Zaken Pirates’ Navigator may get in your way. Please deal with them.

Heh heh... Well done. Bring me the skull, quick! Here’s your payment.

At last, I have the skull...

Heh heh heh...

I came all the way here to investigate the Giant Relic, but I didn’t expect to be studying skeletons.

Bones are stronger under the relic’s influence, but there must be some side effects. It will be difficult, but please check if there are any monsters experiencing side effects!

First, go check the Zaken Pirate Cutthroats! They may hold a clue!

Whew...I could have died out there. Thanks!

I must report this to Feldheim. The monsters with side effects will have to wait...

You should leave here while you have the chance - staying here means certain death! Oh, here’s your payment. I truly appreciate your work!

Meow, meow! I have a job fur you!

I’ve actually been here be-fur, but I came back because I need to purr-cure something!

When I came here in the past, I brought a friend named Shamong! Shamong and I tried to take the treasure by boat, but he was greedy and un-fur-tunately, it cost him the last of his 9 lives.

I was feline emotional and put the Necklace of Eva, the most im-purr-tant treasure, in his tomb! I must have been hiss-terical!

The tomb is crawling with monsters meow, you have to help meow-t! Find Shamong’s Grave and bring back the necklace!
Meow, meow! It’s been ages since I saw this necklace! Meow-nificent work! Here’s your reward! Thank you!

Here! Look at here!

Oh! Einhasad! Thank you for sending the Silverlight Mercenaries! I am Tark of the Giran Vanguard!

I thought all of my comrades were dead, but the investigation has revealed they are alive.

But we have to rescue them! They are in danger of being sacrificed to Zaken!

Zaken’s chamber is full of Master Shooters and Retinues. We’ll be dead long before we can rescue them if we don’t take care of the Master Shooters first. Please help me!
Thanks to you, my hope is restored. Knowing that even some of my comrades are alive brings me great joy. Thank you.

Here! Look at here!

Oh! Einhasad! Thank you for sending the Silverlight Mercenaries! I am Tark of the Giran Vanguard!

I thought all of my comrades were dead, but the investigation has revealed they are alive.

But we have to rescue them! They are in danger of being sacrificed to Zaken!

Zaken’s chamber is guarded by the Royal Guards. I think they have the key to the cage that my comrades are being held in. Please retrieve the key! I’m begging you!
Thank you! Now I can rescue my comrades!

Einhasad must be on my side for me to meet the Silverlight Mercenaries here!

I am Captain Tark, and am scouting this area. My comrades were either killed or taken by the Undead.

While I was planning the rescue operation, I noticed that some soldiers looked to be mind controlled by Zaken's Captain. I never imagined the Undead could use mind control...

If I’m going to rescue them, I must kill the captain. Who knows what could happen to the soldiers otherwise!

I’ll be sure to pay you well when I return to Giran. Please help me and defeat Zaken's Captain.
It seems the soldiers have all returned to normal. What a relief. It should be safe to free them from the cage.

Huff... Huff... Who are you? Not that it matters... As long as you’re not Zaken...

I was once the commander of a pirate ship, but I’ve been cursed to never die. Please, help me - I’ll give you whatever you want.

When Zaken was our captain, he gave us medals and claimed they would give us incredible power - but instead, they turned us into Zombies!

I think it was a form of insurance for Zaken... You should collect some medals so we can investigate them.

The Undead Navigators and Boatswains should still be holding them. Please, find the medals!

Hmm... They’re nothing special! Regardless, you’ve done a good job. Here’s your reward.

Hey, leave the medals. Even if they don’t do anything, they’re mine now.

Devil’s Isle is full of treasures, but taking them is another matter.

Did you see the those Zombie Pirates? Those ugly bastards really cling to their gemstones, even though they’re dead!

(Sara shows you a begemstoneed dagger)

I took this dagger from one of the pirates. Awesome, huh? Maybe the others have them, too.

I’m no good in combat, though... maybe you could get them for me! Please defeat the Zombie Pirates and bring me the begemstoneed daggers!
Wow, you really brought all of these? Now I can buy anything I want when I go back to town!

Devil’s Isle is full of treasures, but taking them is another matter.

See those piles of treasure? They’re cursed, so you can’t take them. But you know what?

Treasure that monsters are holding isn’t cursed at all!. Since the island is full of them, you can rack up a fortune just collecting treasure from the monsters.

Can you bring me some treasure from the Zaken’s Royal Guards? I’ll give you a great deal on it!
I knew I could count on you! These look pretty good. Here’s your payment - I promise I’m not ripping you off!

Devil’s Isle is full of treasures, but taking them is another matter.

See the marksmen over there? When they touch the treasure, they turn into minions of Zaken... The same would probably happen to us.

I ‘m looking for a way to cure this curse, so I need to study those Marksmen. Can you bring me their skulls?

I think investigating their heads might reveal something.
Hmm... these marks aren’t from a curse. These are traces of a Giant’s power! Yes! If I do this properly, the treasure will be all mine!

Devil’s Isle is full of treasures, but taking them is another matter.

I lost my precious ring while I was grabbing Eva’s Tears, one of the treasures here. With Eva’s Tears gone, the area is crawling with scorpions...

I caught some scorpions while I was looking for my ring, but more keep appearing... I think I have to put Eva’s Tears back in place to get rid of the scorpions.

I guess I have no choice but to give up Eva’s Tears... so I have a favor to ask.

I have to take it to the altar, so please distract the Scorpions. The ring is more important to me.
Whew... I found it. Seems the scorpions were holding the ring hostage. I should forget about Eva’s Tears and focus on different treasures instead...

Aw, crud! I was looking for the Giant’s Relic in the wrong place! The clues were right under my nose!

All of the monsters have been influenced by the relic - I should have been studying them, not trying to find it!

Hm... How should I do this... right! Could you help me out? I’ll pay you, of course!

The radius bone of that Zaken Pirate Lookout has developed strangely! Can you bring me the Lookout’s Radius? I want to start my research right away!
Oh, look at these sturdy bones! I should get them to my lab! Here, your payment!

Aw, crud! I was looking for the Giant’s Relic in the wrong place! The clues were right under my nose!

All of the monsters have been influenced by the relic - I should have been studying them, not trying to find it!

Hm... How should I do this... right! Could you help me out? I’ll pay you, of course!

The phalanx bone of that Zaken’s Marksman has developed strangely! Can you bring the Sniper’s Phalanx? I want to start by research right away!
Great, truly marvelous! This Phalanx is truly unique! It would be so wonderful if I could find the Giant’s Relic...

Aw, crud! I was looking for the Giant’s Relic in the wrong place! The clues were right under my nose!

All of the monsters have been influenced by the relic - I should have been studying them, not trying to find it!

Hm... How should I do this... right! Could you help me out? I’ll pay you, of course!

The tibia of that Zaken Pirate Cutthroat has developed strangely! Can you bring the Cutthroat’s Tibia? I want to start my research right away!
Wow, how did this tibia become so thick?! The relic’s power is incredible - if we find it, it could be an incredible help to humanity!

Greetings! I’m the first to venture here on behalf of the Cat Caravan! This is a dangerous area, but worth the risk!

Premos here have a habit of cat-lecting shiny things... and I found something great!

All of their treasures are piled in a specific location! There’s no time to waste - someone should claim their loot!

Please defeat the Premos! The more you slay, the more treasure we can take!
Meow all I have to do is tow the treasure! Here, your payment!

Have you heard the expression “the higher the risk, the greater the reward”?

Well, it doesn’t matter if you’ve heard it or not - this dangerous area is bursting with treasure! See the necklaces worn by the Succubi?

When you wear it, the Succubus’s Necklace can attract the person of your choosing! Nobles pay a fortune for these things!

Why are you still standing there? Bring me a necklace, and make sure it isn’t broken!

Thank you! I was afraid I heard the necklace shatter while you were fighting!

But I guess I heard wrong! Here, take this payment!

Greetings! I’m the first to venture here on behalf of the Cat Caravan! This is a dangerous area, but worth the risk!

I found something incredible! One Zaken’s slaves is wielding a golden sword!

A purr-recious weapon like that is wasted on a brainless Zombie! We have to find that sword, and fast!
Me-ow! A golden sword! Right here on the Devil’s Isle! I made the right call coming here - and here’s your payment!

Here! Over here!

Oh, thank Einhasad! How fortunate to find the Silverlight Mercenaries in this blasted land! I am Tark, one of the vanguards of Giran!

While looking for an escape route, I learned out that my comrades are imprisoned on the island. I want to rescue them, but it’s beyond my capabilities.

They’re guarded by Zaken’s Master Shooters and Retinues.

Please take them out! I have a duty to help my friends!
Thank you! You have my eternal gratitude - and now, I shall rescue my comrades!

Here! Over here!

Oh, thank Einhasad! How fortunate to find the Silverlight Mercenaries in this blasted land! I am Tark, one of the vanguards of Giran!

I saw some captains dragging wounded soldiers away. Perhaps some of my comrades are still alive!

But... I’ll never get past Zaken’s Royal Guards. Can you defeat them? I have to rescue my friends!
Thank you! Now I can go scout without being caught! Thank you! Thank you!

Here! Over here!

Oh, thank Einhasad! How fortunate to find the Silverlight Mercenaries in this blasted land! I am Tark, one of the vanguards of Giran!

I have a favor to ask. See Zaken’s Captain over there? He led the raid on my unit. If my comrades are still alive, he and his minions may have valuable clues!

I must save my comrades, even if only one of them is alive! Quick, help me find a trace of them!
Thanks a lot! There’s no sign of them, but I saw the captain dragging another body away! Maybe some of them are still alive!

Here! over here!

Oh, thank Einhasad! How fortunate to find the Silverlight Mercenaries in this blasted land! I am Tark, one of the vanguards of Giran! All the other vanguards have either been killed or taken prisoner...

I have a chance to escape, but I’d never forgive myself if I didn’t avenge my comrades. Could you help me get revenge? Kill Zaken’s Watcher for me, please!
Thank you! If my comrades are alive, they’ll be eternally grateful!

Here! Over here!

Oh, thank Einhasad! How fortunate to find the Silverlight Mercenaries in this blasted land! I am Tark, one of the vanguards of Giran!

All the other vanguards have either been killed or taken prisoner... Can you help me? If I escape, I’ll pay you when I get home to Giran!

We have to make it past Zaken’s Helmsmen to escape. Could you draw their attention? Killing them would be even better!
Thank you! There’s a lot fewer of them now. I should be able to get out of here!

Huff... Huff... Who are you? Not that it matters... As long as you’re not Zaken...

I was once the commander of a pirate ship, but I’ve been cursed to never die. Please, help me - I’ll give you whatever you want.

Those Zaken Pirate Boatswains over there were my men before Zaken’s curse transformed them. Will you put them to rest for me?

You just need to kill them. I’ll deal with their corpses myself...

Ah, these souls smell delicious...

Well done. I would have been glad to have you under my command... Here’s your payment... I hope we meet again.

Huff... Huff... Who are you? Not that it matters... As long as you’re not Zaken...

I was once the commander of a pirate ship, but I’ve been cursed to never die. Please, help me - I’ll give you whatever you want.

Will you bring peace to the Zaken Pirate Navigators for me? It saddens me to see them still lingering after death...

Please return their bones to me. They deserve a proper grave...
You did well... Here’s your payment. I hope we meet again.

I never expected to meet someone here! You look like a mercenary - could you help me?

Legend tells of a diamond on this island called “Eva’s Tears” that’s the size of an eyeball!

I found it, but there are tons of Skeleton Zombies guarding it!

What do you say? If you take care of the zombies, I’ll get the treasure! There’s Adena in it for you - after all, I’m gonna be a billionaire soon! Let’s go!
Good! Finally, I’ve got my hands on a real treasure! Here’s your payment!

I never expected to meet someone here! You look like a mercenary - could you help me?

When I first got here, I found a pile of treasure and dove right in - but when I came up for air, I was surrounded by Skeletons!

I had to run so fast that I left everything behind, even my pack! Going there without my gear is suicide, so I was hoping you could help.

You can? Thanks! I think Zaken’s Royal Guards have my equipment. You can probably get it from them!
Thanks! Now I can keep exploring. Be careful out there - don’t let the gold get you distracted!

I never expected to meet someone here! You look like a mercenary - could you help me?

See that golden goblet over there? It’s worth a fortune! But if I try to grab it, I’ll be a sitting duck for Zaken’s Marksmen!

Could you draw their attention for me? I’ll be back with the goblet in a jiffy!
Whew, that was close, but with your help, I managed to grab it! Thanks! We make a good team.

I never expected to meet someone here! You look like a mercenary - could you help me?

As soon as I grabbed the giant diamond, a huge swarm of Devilrock Scorpions attacked me! I managed to escape, but I lost my precious ring.

I came back to look for it, but there are way too many scorpions. If you want to help, please deal with the Scorpions while I look for the ring.

Oh, no! They just keep coming...

Well, you did your best, so here’s something for your time. I’ll have to find another way...

Greetings! According to Feldheim, there are signs of the Giant’s Relic over here! Do you know anything about it?

No? Well, I guess...

I searched the whole beach and didn’t turn anything up, so now I have to head inland..

But there are too many wraiths there. Can you kill some of them for me? I don’t want to be stabbed while I search!
Thank you! When I discover the Giant’s Relic and uncover its secrets, it will be partly thanks to you!

Greetings! According to Feldheim, there are signs of the Giant’s Relic here! Do you know anything about it?

Heh heh! Don’t worry, you’re not an archaeologist! My Mana Detector is picking up huge readings!

The Giant’s Mana has transformed the Undead around here!

I want to search further in, but there are way too many Lookouts! Can you help me out and kill some of them?
Thought so! The Giant’s Mana turned the men into Zombies... but who would have done something like this? And what did the Giant’s Mana do to them...?

Greetings! According to Feldheim, there are signs of the Giant’s Relic here! Do you know anything about it?

Hmm, I guess it’s rather cutting-edge archaeology... There’s somewhere I want to investigate, but it’s guarded by Zaken’s Marksmen. Could you defeat them?
I had a safe investigation thanks to you! My Mana Detector is going wild - we must be close to the Giant’s Relic!

Greetings! According to Feldheim, there are signs of the Giant’s Relic here! Do you know anything about it?

That’s alright, no one does... Maybe if you defeat that Cutthroat, it’ll drop some clues?
Huh? Nothing? Well... At least there are fewer monsters! That should make my investigation easier. Here’s your payment.
