Greetings! I’m the first to venture here on behalf of the Cat Caravan! This is a dangerous area, but worth the risk!

Did you see the Shadow Choir Prima? They’re rare here, but their horns are very expensive in the market!

Go get their horns!
Meow! This horn has many uses! Thank you, here’s your purr-omised reward!

Greetings! I’m the first to venture here on behalf of the Cat Caravan! This is a dangerous area, but worth the risk!

Zaken’s Slaves here wield quite good weapons! Slay them and take their equipment!
Meow, look at all these useful weapons. The sea breeze made them a bit rusty, but a blacksmith can make them shiny again! Here, your purr-omised payment!

Greetings! I’m the first to venture here on behalf of the Cat Caravan! This is a dangerous area, but worth the risk!

The Bornestings around here are highly venomous! But! Risk means more value! Its tail is a renowned delicacy among the connoisseurs.

It may be a bit dangerous, but please go get the tails of those Scorpions! I’ll make it worthwhile.
Oh, thank you! Fur-tunately, you’re unharmed! That means I can hire you again...anyway, I’ll roast one right now if you want to try it. Oh, here’s your payment!

Greetings! I’m the first to venture here on behalf of the Cat Caravan! This is a dangerous area, but worth the risk!

One of the famous monsters around here is the Succubus. Their beautiful hair cat-ches a high purr-ice in the market!

Can you collect me some of their hair? I can’t pass on a product like this!
Meow! Just look at this smooth, shiny hair! Of course, my fur is nicer... No, you can’t pet me!

Greetings! I’m the first to venture here on behalf of the Cat Caravan! This is a dangerous area, but worth the risk!

The Premos around here collect all kinds of shiny things. Slay them, and steal their collections!
Quick, give it to me! Twinkle, twinkle, twinkle... aw, these are worthless, all of them! But here’s the payment as purr-romised... better luck next time!

Welcome. To come all this way, you must be an adventurer as well. If I’m correct, a great battle is due to begin inside the Dragon’s cave.

When the Dragon is resurrected, we have to defeat it faster than anyone else so we can claim its treasure.

According to my research, there’s a spellbook that can kill a dragon. It’s called Dragon Slave... or something. I need more information.

According to the Giran Library, the Grand Wizard Erucion first used the spellbook in a battle against the Draconians. Maybe if we fight the Draconians, we’ll learn something.

I didn’t think we’d have competition for the Spellbook! Hurry! That wizard was clearly heading Veremus’s lair.

The Giran Intel Trader said the spellbook might be in there - we have to follow him!
Whew, Veremus isn’t here! Let’s look for the spellbook!
Damn, they just keep coming! Let’s find the spellbook and make a run for it!

Whew... I don’t want to ever have to go into a Draconian lair again... Look! Look! Is this it? Wow, it is!

Such a powerful spell in my hands!

Huh? Aw, shoot!

The most important page has been torn out!

Damn Draconians, ruining such a priceless treasure...

Sorry... I’d like to be alone for a bit.

Interesting, meeting someone in a place like this.

A Silverlight Mercenary? Ha. Perhaps the heavens are enabling my revenge...

I’m Nithos, a captain of the Giran’s Blood Rangers.

I’m here on orders to investigate the movements of monsters in Dragon Valley, but on my way here, I was attacked by the Dark Brotherhood.

They were strong; they summoned a demon and commanded monsters...

My men fought valiantly, but I am the sole survivor... My shame means I cannot return home.

Could you help me recover their corpses?

Their bodies should be near their lair. I’m dead if I go alone, but with your company... Please, help me. I’ve heard the Silverlight Mercenaries never turn their back on a soul in need... Please...
This is the place! Collect the soldiers’ corpses!

Stealing our Lord Beleth? You ignorant fools!

You shall join the dead!
I’m back for my revenge! I’ll kill you myself!
Ha ha ha! The coward captain who fled while his men were slaughtered, back for more... I’ll make sure you rejoin your troops!

Huff... Huff... I am truly grateful.
My men have been avenged, and I can return home.
Thank you.

"Are you here to hunt the Wyrm Guardian?

Good! I was looking for someone to find dragon hearts for me.

I spent my whole fortune in Giran on a Grima’s Bracelet that turned out to be fake! They said that it would raise my mana by 200%...

But guess what? You have to fill it with Mana yourself! Can you believe it? And they wouldn’t take returns, either!

Well, what can I do? I guess I have to gather it myself. Dragon hearts are the best source of Mana around here.

If you’re hunting the Wyrm Guardians anyway, can you bring me their hearts? I’ll pay you!

Wow, these are in good shape! Thanks!

Hm... One more thing. If I start to charge the bracelet here, the Mana will probably attract monsters.

These hearts are losing Mana by the second, so I can’t wait.

What do you say? Can you help me? I’ll pay you extra!
Woohoo! This is a lot more powerful than I expected! Thanks! Now, I have thrice the mana I did before! Here’s your payment! Great work!

Hello there! Did you come to serve justice as well?

From what I heard at the Giran tavern, there’s an Evil Summoning Stone near here!

If there’s truly an Evil Summoning Stone here, I can’t just turn a blind eye! Will you look for it with me?

Killing the monsters nearby should reveal its whereabouts. It’s said that when a monster summoned from the stone dies, its corpse returns to it! If we follow the corpses, we’ll find the stone!
Here! The Evil Summoning Stone is here!
Damn! The last demon to be summoned is Velkir! We have to defeat him right away!
Whew, sometimes rumors are true! If we were even a second later, more demons would have been summoned. We had good timing!

Oh! Thank Einhasad! Meeting the Silverlight Mercenaries here!

Please... Please help me. The Death Binds are desecrating my men’s corpses...

Their worthless captain has lost his sword and is helpless but to watch...

Could you please help me?
Now that I found my sword, I can avenge my men myself! Thanks!

[player]! What brings you here? Have you come to hunt as well?

You see, I acquired a ring of the Guardian, which protects me from Flame attacks.

But while on my way to show it to Sara Ra, minions of Beremoth, lord of the Dragonkind, stole it from me! I called Ringo and Mitchell, but they’re preoccupied with something.

Can you help me? Their lair is in the North!

Woohoo, I found it! Thank you!
It’s been nothing but trouble, though... maybe I should sell it.

Greetings! We’ve met a few times before, right?

As you know, there’s a rumor spreading in Giran that an Adventurer defeated a Headless Knight and found a sword called “Soulbringer”. Ever since, more Adventurers have been hunting the Headless Knights.

But... no one’s been able to find another sword.

I don’t think the first Adventurer fought a Headless Knight at all, but a Death Headless Knight. Do you think you could test my theory? Let me know what you find!

Welcome. We Guardian Elves are focused on restoring the wounded Guardian Tree.

However, I disagree with my colleagues. We do not know if the Guardian Tree is meant to be immortal.

Rather than restoring it, we should be focused on finding a way for our race to survive without the Guardian Tree!

I am researching leads. Can you help me?

The Death Werewolves become very strong at night. Their strength is inexhaustible! It’s immense!

I must learn how they become so powerful. Please hunt some Death Werewolves for me - as many as you can!

Ah! Finally, I can conduct my experiment!

A werewolf test-subject at last! Splendid!

Here, the promised payment! See you next time!

Greetings. I am Lawrence the Vendor. You look like a mercenary; would you do me a favor?

There’s money in it for you, of course.

Have you seen the Saharas of Barren Land? They stole my precious diamonds just a while ago!

There were... 40 diamonds, I think. A lot of monsters took them. Please get them back for me!
Thank you. I’m planning to travel to Orren to sell these! My friend knows the way through the forest.

Have you seen the Fettered Souls? They move about with their arms strapped behind them. Please bring me some of their torture implements.

Don’t ask me what for. I have a client...
Here’s your payment. I’m impressed by your work. Perhaps we could do this again sometime?

Wait! Hold on a moment...

Good! I discovered something very important!

You know the Death Headless Knights? Their souls are special! Just the right kind of special - normal Headless Knights would never survive my experiment.

Can you bring me some Death Headless Knights? Once I have them, things will get really interesting!

Good, you brought them. I’ll put these to good use, and when the spell is complete, I’ll share it with you.

Here’s a reward for your hard work - don’t spend it all in one place.
A sword fragment? Hmm... are these fragments meant to be a clue? When I meet the rat who spread this rumor... Anyway, thanks for your help!

Have you seen the Grandis Dragon Slayer? Ringo, Mitchell, and I were going to hunt together, but I lost my Ring of the Wind and couldn’t keep up with them.

If you can find my ring, I’ll give you all of my Adena in return!

If I can’t hunt, I’m useless!
What? It’s not here? I’m screwed. Hunting around here is really hard without the Ring of the Wind!

Huh? You’re here today, too? Did you come here to hunt?

In that case, I’ll tell you a secret. That Wyrm Guardian there has the Ring of the Guardian, which protects from flame attacks!

That’s what they told me in the Giran tavern. Do you want to join me in hunting for the Ring of the Guardian?

Oh! Finally! It wasn’t as easy to get as I thought it would be.

We have to check if it works! I’m not going to die just because I didn’t test it. I need a flame spell... I’ll ask Ringo to help me.

I’ll let you know how it turns out!

Mana flows strangely here - do you feel it? I think we should investigate the monsters.

I need to gather Mana from Monster Eyes, but the progress is slow because I need so many.

Will you help me hunt? Please bring me 40 Monster Eyes.

So Mana is flowing rapidly toward the dragon’s cave... how unusual!

You saved me a lot of time - here’s your payment!

Hi there! Rumors are spreading in the taverns in Giran that the Maelstrom Dustwinds around here can drop the Bracelet of the Wizard, so everyone’s hunting Dustwinds!

The Bracelet of the Wizard amplifies Mana, so it’s a must for all Wizards! What do you say - if you find it for me, I’ll pay you handsomely!

Hm...I guess finding a full bracelet is going to be harder than I expected. Anyone who finds even a piece must be lucky!

You did a lot of work, so here’s your payment! I’ll deal with the pieces!

Oh, no... I was traveling with Sara Ra and Dorothy, but I got lost. Have you seen them?

We’d teamed up to hunt together, but that’s meaningless when we’re all split up!

I guess I’ll have to find them myself!

Huh? Where’s my bag? I thought I put it over there... who took it... not you, not me... then who?!

Those Dustwind Gargoyles! Let’s get them and look for my bag!

Thank you! Grabbing my things the moment I look away... they are really fast!

Thanks anyway. I owe you a reward.

Hey! There’s are Deathly Monster Eyes here! Dorothy told me that Deathly Monster Eyes drop very a very expensive spellbook.

Let’s work together and get that spellbook for ourselves! I’ll pay you for your trouble!
Wow, looking for the spellbook is a real pain. I’m exhausted. Let’s call it a day. Here’s your payment - I’m gonna take a nap.

Ha ha ha! I got separated from my friends, and when I tried to meet back up with them, those Wyrm Guardians were blocking my way!

When we’re all together, they don’t stand a chance... but I can’t fight them alone!

Can you deal with those Wyrm Guardians for me? I’m low on Mana, or else I’d help!
Thanks! Now I can rejoin my friends! Someday, I’ll be able to repay you!

Interesting, finding someone in a place like this. What brings you here?

I’m here slaying Death Binds of Death.

They killed my men... and if I kill them in return, I can ease my guilt.

Will you join me? The more we kill, the fewer people will share my comrades’ fate.
Thank you. You remind me of my old comrades. Being sole survivor is far harder than I expected it to be...

Turn back! This is a dangerous area.

Oh! You’re from the Silverlight Mercenaries. If only my men were as strong as you...

Forgive me for being nostalgic. My men died in combat against the Wyrm Guardians here... They were about your age...

Can you help me? Please slay the Wyrm Guardians over there. I can’t finish the job myself.

Please. I’ll pay you for it.
Thank you. Your actions have eased my guilt.

You must have great combat skills to be here! I’m a merchant headed for Giran. On my way, my caravan was raided by Orcs!

I would be drinking in a tavern in Giran already if not for the Orcs... Can you help me? If you recover my cargo and help me escape, I’ll make it worthwhile!

Good! First, let’s make sure the path ahead is clear. I think those sentries are guarding it. You deal with them, and I’ll look for my cargo.

Thanks for finding the way out, but my cargo is still here somewhere... Where did those Orcs put my things?!

They didn’t eat everything, did they?!

You must have great combat skills to be here! I’m a merchant headed for Giran. On my way, my caravan was raided by Orcs!

I would be drinking in a tavern in Giran already if not for the Orcs... Can you help me? If you recover my cargo and help me escape, I’ll make it worthwhile!

Those Shamans stole my cargo to use in a ritual! Kill them and recover my goods, then bring them back to me!
Wow, thank you! There are even items here that weren’t mine in the first place! Ha! I’ll be sure to put them to good use! Ha ha!

You must have great combat skills to be here! I’m a merchant headed for Giran. On my way, my caravan was raided by Orcs!

I would be drinking in a tavern in Giran already if not for the Orcs... Can you help me? If you recover my cargo and help me escape, I’ll make it worthwhile!

Will you help me recover my cargo? If I show up in Giran with nothing to sell, I’m sunk! Those Rearguards ran off with my goods. Kill them, and it’ll lead you to my missing products!
One of the Rearguards squawked about where the Shamans took my cargo! The intel’s good! Thank you, thank you!

You must have great combat skills to be here!

Ah, you’re one of the Silverlight Mercenaries! Great! I need someone to avenge me! I was on my way to Giran when those Orcs attacked me!

Those blasted Orc Fighters smashed my wagon and stranded me! I wouldn’t mind if they’d killed me, but they damaged my sweet ride!

What’s the expression? Oh! I’ll make it worthwhile! Please kill those Breka Orc Fighters! Pulverize them!
Hahaha! Watching you kill those Orcs almost made up for the loss of my poor wagon! Thank you!

The Orcs here raid passing caravans, taking the passengers as prisoners to sacrifice to their bloody gods. They got my wife and kids... I can’t leave without avenging them!

I already killed lots of them, but they are too many. Can you slay the Patrols for me? When Patrols are alerted, they call in the horde...

Thank you! With Patrols out of the way, I can kill the rest more easily!

It’s time to arm myself!

Just look at them! Those Cruel Orcs! Did you see that?! Those Breka Orc Warchiefs are butchering their captives!

Can you slay those Warchiefs for me? I’d do it myself, but my legs are wounded!

Hurry, before someone else is sacrificed!
I’m so grateful. You saved many lives from the Orcs. Thank you!

The Orcs have begun using witchcraft, leading to more Human deaths. If I could go back in time, I’d kill the person who taught Black Magic to the Orcs.

Please kill the Shamans. With them gone, our soldiers will stand a chance in battle against the Orcs.

Ah, the Silverlight Mercenaries save the day! Good, good!

You guys give me hope for the future!

Greetings. Did the lord of Orren send you here, too?

I came to scout the area on the lord’s orders, and I’ve learned that the Orcs have far more sentries than we anticipated.

If we leave their numbers unchecked, the Orcs may detect Orren’s troop movements or even send raids to attack our soldiers.

I think we can handle this ourselves. Will you help deal with the sentries?

Ha! I love the smell of Orcs dying in the morning!

The more we kill, the safer our people are!

Welcome. We Guardian Elves are focused on restoring the wounded Guardian Tree.

However, I disagree with my colleagues. We do not know if the Guardian Tree is meant to be immortal.

Rather than restoring it, we should be focused on finding a way for our race to survive without the Guardian Tree!

I’m researching some items. Would you help me?

It is said that the Guardian Basilisk’s heart keeps beating even after death. I would love to see this property for myself. Can you collect some Basilisk hearts and bring them to me?
Thank you! I’ll get to work on my experiment right away. I hope this Basilisk heart holds the answers I need!

Guardian Tree.

However, I disagree with my colleagues. We do not know if the Guardian Tree is meant to be immortal.

Rather than restoring it, we should be focused on finding a way for our race to survive without the Guardian Tree!

I’m researching some items. Would you help me?

It is said that Reapers absorb souls from other lifeforms in order to sustain themselves. I must understand how the process works. Please kill some Reapers and bring me their remains.
Thank you! This material comes from the Underworld, so perhaps it holds an answer!

Welcome. We Guardian Elves are focused on restoring the wounded Guardian Tree.

However, I disagree with my colleagues. We do not know if the Guardian Tree is meant to be immortal.

Rather than restoring it, we should be focused on finding a way for our race to survive without the Guardian Tree!

I’m researching some items. Would you help me?

No matter how many Ravine Windsus we kill, there are always more. Their breeding potential is outstanding! Don’t they ever get tired?

I must study their reproductive power. Please slay some Ravine Windsus and bring me their bodies.
Incredible! Loot at the strength of these cells! I must start the analysis immediately! Thank you, I will put this to good use!

Hello! I am Lawrence the Vendor. You look like a mercenary; would you do me a favor?

Oh! I’ll pay you, of course.

The black land here is famous for its pristine sands. Because of the war in Gludio, sand from here is in high demand as a building material.

I can’t pass on an opportunity like this! I can transport the sand, but can you hunt some Twilight Saharas in order to secure the sand?
Whew! Look at all this sand! Here’s your payment - I even gave you a bonus! Thank you.

Hello! I am Lawrence the Vendor. You look like a mercenary; would you do me a favor?

Oh, for a price, of course.

In Orren, the tails of Soul Devourer Primas are in high demand as a piece of interior decor! It shows that whoever lives there is a great warrior.

Of course, many prefer just to buy them. What do you say? If you bring them, I’ll pay.

Hello! I am Lawrence the Vendor. You look like a mercenary; would you do me a favor?

I’ll pay you, of course.

Are you familiar with the Amber Basilisk? Its meat is very tender and delicious! Add a beer, and you’re in heaven!

If you bring me some of that meat, I’ll cook dinner for us and sell the rest in Giran for top coin! What do you say?
Ha! Delicious! Here’s your payment - you’ve made me a very wealthy man!

Heh heh... What brings you here?

You must be wondering what I’m doing in a place like this.

I’m not a regular merchant - I’m a cool merchant. Do I have your attention?

Then bring me 5 black Diamonds from the Saharas over there.

Do that, and I’ll tell you more about me.

What? Back already?!

I’m in the business of discreetly supplying special products to special people. These diamonds will make one of the lords of Giran very pleased.

I like your style. Why don’t we work together more?

Heh heh... What brings you here?

You’re just in time. Care to work for me a bit? It’ll be worthwhile.

I have an easy task for you. Hunt the Headless Knights over yonder, and I’ll pay you for their armor.

Thank you for bringing it in such good condition. This armor will be put to good use.

Don’t ask how. That’s none of your concern.

Here’s your payment - I assure you it’s plenty.

Here to see me?

That’s alright - I was just about to hire someone.

It’s said that the Sahara of Barren Land create a Rain Gemstone when they die, but it disappears so quickly that few have ever seen it.

If you collect the Rain Gemstones from those Saharas, I’ll pay you an excellent price for them.

Marvelous! These Sahara Rain Gemstones are in peak condition!

Quick, give them to me. Here’s your payment!

Greetings. Today’s weather is better than I expected.

I need some Headless Knights. Can you bring them to me?

I would do it myself, but Headless Knights are resistant to Black Magic.

Your power should be sufficient to fight them. I’ll make it worthwhile.
Heh heh... I’ve seen mercenaries like you a few times before. As I expected, your work is impeccable.

Did you see the Wandering Fettered Souls lingering here? They look like people who died in agony.

For whatever reason, they’re full of dark energy. Will you hunt them down for me? They’re fascinating research subjects.

Thank you. My pulse is racing just thinking about the experiments I’m going to do!

Woohoo!

You’re quite something, conversing with me normally. Most people either strike me or run away.

Meeting in you is part of Destiny’s plan. Could you help me with something?

Please catch some Grandis Bonecrushers from around here. Their strength makes them a prime experiment subject, but it also makes them difficult to catch using Mana.

Wow, even the violent Grandis are no match for you. My Black Magic will develop faster thanks to you.

If I can control this one, it’ll be like having an army at my fingertips!

Greetings! Care to make some money?!

Do you know Venga, lord of the plains? It’s the king of the Cougars around here! Many have tried to hunt Venga, and many have failed.

Gludin has set a bounty on it, and its skin would sell for a high purr-ice if someone could catch it!

What do you say? Hunt Venga, and we can split the paw-fits fifty-fifty! I deserve a cut for giving you the info.

Deal with the normal Cougars, and I’ll track Venga down.
Great work! I knew you could do it! Here’s your reward! Half of the bounty and leather purr-ice!

Welcome! I’ve heard great stories of your feats from the Cat Caravan!

I am a merchant, but also a paw-tron! As you know, people here are suffering from the Ol Mahum raids!

I want to take back what they stole. What do you say? Will you help me?
That was close! Things should be quiet for a while since we defeated Katcha! Great job!

Greetings. I feel the light surrounding you. The Goddess commanded we purge the evil here.

Dear Adventurer, please help us. The Undead can be purged with the light, but Bugbears are difficult to deal with. Would you help us?
Thanks to you, my fellows escaped safely.

Greetings. Einhasad told me you’d come.

The Undead here have been behaving strangely. They’ve been gathering in a single spot. Can you investigate?

First, please deal with the Shade Reaper and the skeletons. I will get the exact location for you.
The Chest of Darkness! We were lucky. Gathering the dark energy like this... You did well. This is your payment.

Listen up! The Lord of Gludio shall reward anyone who will slays the notorious Ol Mahum Cutthroats!

Catching the serial killer Jackal will fetch an even higher bounty!

Happy hunting!
Great work! Gludio Territory is safer thanks to your efforts. On behalf of the Lord of Gludio, thank you. This is the promised reward!
Well done! Jackal escaped, but you defeated enough Cutthroats to make us safe! Here’s your reward!

Hey, stop! Stop! Stop!

Can you help me?

I was on my way to Gludio when Lizardmen stole my luggage!

Can you get it back? I’ll pay you!

Those Maille Lizardman Pillagers have my bags!
Thank you! I never thought it would be so hard to get my possessions back! Here, take this payment!

Greetings! Did you see the bounty as well?

The monsters are a problem, but so are those strangely-powerful Red Bears.

Thus! The lord shall reward anyone who slays the Red Bears and Kaba, their king!

Be sure to bring me evidence of your deeds.

Well done! Your skills are extraordinary! I shall personally report this to my lord!

Here’s your reward! Please work for Gludio again!

Help me! I am Hamon, a soldier from the 1st Platoon. Most of my comrades are dead, and reinforcements aren’t coming.

Damn the chancellor! I can’t die like here! Please take me with you!

But first, kill the Bugbears, or we’ll never make it out alive!
Whew... We’re out! I made it out alive! Thank you so much - I’ll repay you someday!

Welcome! I heard the townspeople of Gludio are suffering because of the Lizardmen Troopers!

They multiply as fast as we can kill them - it’s no use!

It’ll be better to burn their weapons and kill their Training Captain! Will you join me?
Great work! The people of Gludio will be safe for now. Well done!

Hey, are you a mercenary?

Good! It’s said that the Lizardman Shamans here can use ancestral Flame magic.

I want to investigate the spell - can you look for his spellbook?

I don’t know for sure where it would be... maybe one of the Shamans will have it?
Whew, that was hard. This one should be the real spellbook. It’s weird how many fakes there are lying around! Thanks for your help.

Welcome! So you’re the famous mercenary!

Glad to have you here! We’re about to sweep the Turek Orc Bowmen; join us!

Let’s see your skills first. Will you slay the Scouts and Patrols?
You killed Kariana the Sharpshooter! Wow. I’ll be sending word of your talent to my lord.

I am Faute, bailiff of Gludio. I came here on the orders of the Lord of Gludio!

We subdued the Turek Orcs several times before, but they’ve recovered quickly.

The Orc called Tukan is the most rambunctious of them all!

The scouts make it difficult to infiltrate the area right now. Deal with those scouts first!

Great!

Now we have the foundation to defeat Tukan! Thank you!

We are having trouble due to the increased number of Turek War Hounds! We have to get rid of them.

The soldiers are on it, but it is taking longer than expected. Could you help us?

We have a problem! Soldiers out for surveillance haven’t come back yet!

Please find them!

I never expected to meet someone here... I am Hamon, a soldier from the 1st Platoon. I had abandoned all hope, but meeting you gives me a glimmer of hope...

I need to avenge my comrades - will you help me?

Thank you. The Bugbears and Dark Weavers killed my comrades. Please slay them for me.
Thank you. You have avenged my comrades, and someday I will repay your debt.

Welcome! I heard the townspeople of Gludio are suffering because of the Lizardmen Troopers!

Those Lizardman Troopers are under training over that way!

I shall burn their weapons to weaken them!

You go defeat them for me!

Well done! Kaba escaped, but you killed lots of Red Bears, so we’ll be safe for now!

Here’s your reward. Kill Kaba next time!

Hey, Adventurer! I’ve got an offer for you! It’s dangerous - still interested?

A bounty has been placed on the Breka Orc Fighters and their leader, Garlok! Sending rookies would just strengthen their defenses,

so the bailiff says the job’s for veterans only. I’ve got confidence in you!

Visitors to the temple are complaining about Lizardmen in the farmland.

We aim to foster peace between the Lizardmen and the townspeople - perhaps taking out the most troublesome Lizardmen will help bring peace.

Will you defeat a Lizardman called Krush? Defeat his minions and he will appear.

May Eva bless you! Krush was responsible for at least 100 robberies. You did the right thing.

Embrace the will of the water. May peace be with you!

Hello? I am Evna, a follower of the Goddess Eva. I am looking for ways to foster harmony here.

Will you defeat a Lizardman named Varash? Defeat his minions and he’ll appear. Be wary, though - they are skilled archers.

Varash paid for his sins. The merciful Goddess Eva will give him an opportunity to be reborn.

The Temple of Eva thinks highly of your feats and valor. May peace be with you!

The Lizardmen have done too much harm lately. Will you deal with a Lizardman called Screash?

He used witchcraft to kill numerous people, and his behavior cannot be tolerated.

Killing innocents is a terrible sin. May Screash’s valor be used for good under Eva’s guidance.

May Eva’s blessings bring peace to you.

Dion Meadows is a wonderful place. The warm weather and fertile soil make food plentiful. The ingredients in this area are a premium dish on their own!

I am Chef Mechillen from the Gourmet Society. I was planning to gather ingredients here, but the hunter we hired is late. Ah, all this talk is making me hungry. Should we have a light snack?

Could you bring me the inside round of an Elder Antelope? It’s the best meat for a steak.

If you do, I’ll make us a tasty snack. What do you say?

Oh, you’re back just in time! My preparations for cooking are complete. The meat of most males is too tough... perhaps from the stress of competing for mates?

Wow, the Alpha Male is incredible! The meat is in pristine condition. Now, let’s get cooking!

The Gourmet Society is searching for the true meaning of life by eating... It seems like a tremendous task - but eating delicious food is a welcome challenge!

I plan to gather ingredients here today. The quality of the ingredients has a major impact on the quality of the dish, you know. But I haven't heard from the Hunter I hired. I would do it myself if I was any good at archery!

Could you bring me a Surly Vampire Bat? Of course, I don’t plan to eat it whole! But explaining the whole recipe would be a waste of time.

Hey, you! Can you help me for a bit? I’m hunting Orcs. Those disgusting creatures don’t deserve to live!

But I can’t exact my vengeance while wounded. It makes me furious knowing that Orcs are running free while I’m stuck licking my wounds! Go and kill some Orcs for me. I’ll pay you, obviously!

Start with the Breka Orc Rangers! They’re the ones responsible for my wound - avenge me!
Whoa, you’re good! You were killing them twice as fast as I could! I’m jealous! Hey, have we met before? You look familiar...

Hey, Adventurer! I’ve got an offer for you! It’s dangerous - still interested?

A bounty has been placed on the Breka Orc Fighters! Sending rookies would just strengthen their defenses,

so the bailiff says the job’s for veterans only. I’ve got confidence in you!

Visitors to the temple are complaining about Lizardmen in the farmland.

We aim to foster peace between the Lizardmen and the townspeople - perhaps taking out the most troublesome Lizardmen will help bring peace.
Well done. Embrace the will of the water. May peace be with you!

Hello? I am Evna, a follower of the Goddess Eva. I am looking for ways to foster harmony here.

Will you defeat the Lizardman Archers? They’ve been using townspeople as target practice!
The Temple of Eva thinks highly of your feats and valor. May peace be with you!

The Lizardmen have done too much harm lately.

Will you deal with the Lizardman Shamans? They’re abusing their magic and that cannot be tolerated.
Eva is a merciful goddess, but... whew, but they were too cruel.
Oh, you’re back just in time! My preparations for cooking are complete. The meat of most males is too tough... perhaps from the stress of competing for mates?
Wow, you defeated Zyrnna! Your skills surprise me! I always trained myself, but... you’re out of my league. Good work, ha ha!

I have a target for you. Its name is Arcane - the leader of Wraiths. Arcane’s fate is sealed.

Arcane must be destroyed. I have placed a curse on it to force it to appear.

However, I’m missing some ingredients to activate the curse. Go collect dark essence from Shadow Choir Primas.
Let us summon Arcane. We will have to deal with its minions, first.

The preparations are complete.
We are ready to summon Arcane.

Go to the summoning circle. 
Liam will be summoned soon.

You must destroy an Undead called Ronde. Ronde has always had a horde, and I expect it to be no different now. This task may prove to be difficult.

We should begin by destroying some of its minions. Please collect their cursed skulls while you’re at it - we’ll need them later.
If not for destruction, the world would be overwhelmed by chaos and agony. Destruction is necessary to maintain balance. May Gran Kain bless you. Follow his path.

Our temple received oracular orders to purify this land and put an end to the shadow creatures who reject the light of Einhasad.

Could you help me by defeating the Mist Horror Reapers? After you defeat them, purify their souls in the holy brazier.
The will of Einhasad leads to a greater good. The fact that they oppose us is proof. Thank you.

Ah! One of our usual suppliers is severely wounded! I need some product right meow, but it’s hard to find anyone up to the task!

Can you do it? Bring me venom sacks from Black Tiger Spiders and I’ll be waiting with lots of Adena!

Wow! This is incredible! It was a dangerous job, but you’re safe meow!

I’ll be very careful with these venom sacks. See you later!

When you work for the Cat Caravan, you meet some very strange clients. I understand needing a hook... but why does it have to be from these things?

But how can I refuse when they’re offering such a high purr-ice? I’ll pass the earnings on to you! Go meow!
Thank you! These are in purr-fect condition. Thanks for taking such a ridiculous job!

Greetings, [player]! We meet again. I’m patrolling the Cruma Swamp, and I have a job just right for you.

As long as the Marsh Queen, Zyrnna, is here, Cruma is not safe. Do you know how many people fled because of Zyrnna?

Please defeat Zyrnna! Defeating the Marsh Stakatos first will help weaken her. We must prepare before we confront her!
Well done! You’re worth more than ten soldiers!

I have a target for you, and I’ve prepared a summoning circle to draw it out.

However, I’m missing some ingredients to activate the curse. Go collect dark essence from Shadow Choir Primas.
I have a target for you: once valiant soldiers, the Skeleton Pursuers now wander aimlessly. It’s your destiny to guide them to Gran Kain.
Hmm... You’ve done well. Gran Kain shall be pleased.

It would be beneficial for you to collect cursed skulls from the Skeleton Scouts. They are useful for opening and closing the Summoning Gate. There will be a large-scale summoning soon, and we need to prepare.
I shall only summon the minions of Ronde from among the Skeleton Scouts.
Today, we freed the poor souls following Ronde. We will soon set Ronde on the same path.

Ah! One of our usual suppliers is severely wounded! I need some product right meow, but it’s hard to find anyone up to the task!

Can you do it? Bring me venom sacks from Black Tiger Spiders!

You worked so hard to help me, but I couldn’t find it. Ah... where the hell is it?!

Please, go away. I need to be alone for a while...
Whew, good work out there! I’m safe to work now, right? Thanks!

Be careful! You don’t want to be eaten, do you? There’s very dangerous wildlife around here. I want to cook, not be cooked!

Have you ever heard the name Ashley? The master chef! The most popular chef in Dion! ...

...

No? How disappointing! You’re not interested in cuisine? Anyway, you look like someone that can hold their own in a fight. Can you hunt some Black Leopards for me? I’ll pay you well for them! Here - this bait will help lure them out!
You’re amazing! Here’s your payment! You should start studying food so your taste buds can understand how awesome I am!
You caught him! Well done. I’ll take it from here.

I am a Priest of Maphr. A carriage carrying goods for our church was attacked and robbed near here. I suspect that it’s the work of Thaartan, a minion of Tanor.

It seems clear that the Tanor near here stole the goods. We must recover the missing tribute from them.

A wagon carrying tribute for our church was robbed here. I suspect that Tutan, an advisor of Tanor, is responsible.

I must bring him to court, but Tutan managed to curse me. Will you bring me a Tanor Shaman talisman to cure me?
Thank you. I didn’t go down easily. I cast a spell to Tutan, and I’ll summon him using that spell. Prepare for combat!
The resistance was formidable, but we triumphed. Well done. I shall bring Tutan to court.

I’m gathering ingredients because a woman claiming to be my rival challenged me. We’re going to have a cook-off!

The loser has to grant any wish for the winner. My pride’s on the line - I can’t lose!!!

People seldom come here, so there are lots of exotic ingredients around. I came here for a preliminary survey, but I can’t leave now that you’re here!

Fill my shopping list, and you’ll have permanent VIP status at my restaurant! First things first, I need Venomous Marsh Spider eyeballs.

Hey there! You’re going to get mugged by Ol Mahum wandering around like that! No matter how confident you are, this is their turf.

It’s been a while since I last saw you! You seem to be stronger than before. I’m grateful for your help before - do you think you could help us out again?

I wonder where Mitchell is... I’m worried. He sure was bragging loudly about stealing that Soul Crystal from the Ol Mahum boss.

We should reduce the number of Ol Mahum before Mitchell returns. He can be a little careless, so I hope you can defeat the Ol Mahum Officers first.
I never expected their boss to show up! Sorry about that - are you hurt?

Hey, glad to see you! It’s me, Mitchell, the Aden Explorer! Remember me? I’m delivering justice, as always. Why don’t you join me?

The Ol Mahum have gotten their hands on some high-quality Soul Crystals, and I need to find them.

I bet the commanders will be carrying the Soul Crystals. We should smash all of the Ol Mahum equipment to be safe!
Good! We can’t check them one by one, so this is the best solution! Great work! And slaying their first officer - superb!

You look like a mercenary; can you hunt some Black Leopards for me? I’ll pay you well for them.

Here - this bait will help lure them out!

I’m Ashley, a master chef, and I’m preparing for a cook-off to prove myself as the best chef in Dion. I’m collecting ingredients, but my sous chefs are doing a terrible job.

I can pay you whatever you want, so could you collect some ingredients for me? It should be easy. Do we have a deal?

Bring me a Red-Tailed Fox. It needs to be all in one piece. Hurry!

A wagon carrying cargo for our church was raided nearby. I suspect Tanor are responsible for this robbery.

I expect resistance, so it would be wise to suppress the local Tanor residents.
There must be someone leading the Tanor Knight Recruits... I must find them. The intel from the Ol Mahum is quite useful.

A carriage carrying goods for our church was attacked and robbed near here.

It seems clear that the Tanor near here stole the goods. We must recover the missing tribute from them.
These guys are sly old foxes. They act innocent, but don’t believe their lies.

A wagon carrying tribute for our church was raided here. The Tanor Shamans are the prime suspects. There’s a witchcraft talisman included in the evidence we received from the Ol Mahum.

We need to compare the talisman to the ones carried by the Tanor Shamans. here. I’d appreciate your help.
Case closed! It’s a perfect match to the sample I have! They’re prime suspects - there’s no time to waste!
The resistance was formidable, but we triumphed. Now, I’ll find the person behind all this!

People seldom come here, so there are lots of exotic ingredients around. I came here for a preliminary survey, but I can’t leave now that you’re here!

Can you fill my list? First things first, I need Venomous Marsh Spider eyeballs.

Ol B’Khan, the leader of the Ol Mahum, is too aggressive. He is killing merchants left and right.

My people have found that Ol B’Khan has departed with a small squad of fighters to attack Tanor.

This is the perfect chance to take out some of his minions. Could you kill some of the Ol Mahum Scouts over there?
Good work. No matter how strong Ol B’Khan is, he’s weaker without his minions.

I wonder where Mitchell is... I’m worried. He sure was bragging loudly about stealing that Soul Crystal from the Ol Mahum boss.

We should reduce the number of Ol Mahum before Mitchell returns. He can be a little careless, so I hope you can defeat the Ol Mahum Officers first.
Are you okay? Good. I was worried I asked you for something too hard, but as long as you’re safe, it’s okay.

Hey, glad to see you! It’s me, Mitchell, the Aden Explorer! Remember me? I’m delivering justice, as always. Why don’t you join me?<

There’s no telling what kind of evil the Ol Mahum have planned, so we should destroy their equipment! Let’s target their commanders first!
Good! We can’t check them one by one, so this is the best solution!

The Shrieking Hallows are filled with restless Undead. No matter what may have been unresolved in their former lives, they must now come to accept their deaths.

The Seamstress is the most spiteful of them all, but we do not need to know her story. For there is no death without a tale...

We can grant her eternal peace under Einhasad. Let us defeat Seamstress together.

We will summon the Seamstress against her will using a method preferred by the Priests of Gran Kain.

You must collect essence of tenacity from the Relentless Specters. It will be used as a catalyst for the summoning. I shall prepare the ritual.

By decree of the Lord of Dion, I announce this bounty. Anyone who completes this feat shall be rewarded accordingly.

Whoever kills the Resurrected Specter in the Shrieking Hallows, bring the evidence, and my lord shall reward you!

I survived thanks to you! I should ask to be transferred to another post, or I might really die out here...

Here’s the bounty, as promised by the Lord of Gludio... along with a bonus for saving my life.

Aw, rats! Why did I have to get such a dangerous Post? I should have suspected something was up when they offered me hazard pay, but... why here, of all places?!

Why does anyone even come out here? If you’d all just stay away, I could be safe and sound and posted somewhere nice! Argh!

Let’s get this over with, shall we? Slay the Doom Servant!

I still have a few hours left in my shift... if I survive that long. Don’t go too far! Ugh. I’m never coming back here again!

Claim your reward from the lord! I’ll pay the bounty on behalf of the bailiff... Ugh... I sound like a damn parrot, but it’s a living...

An Adventurer? Greetings. I am Yumaeri the botanist. I’ve been looking for mercenaries like you.

While I was studying the plants here, I discovered a plant spreading sorrow to the monsters. I want to investigate further, so what do you say? Will you help me?
Let’s go to where the sorrowful plant grows.
Whew! Thanks. I could have died before completing my research. Here’s your payment! Let’s work together again sometime!

Greetings. The lord told me to expect you. We are following his orders and purifying this location.

There’s a monster spreading despair here. Destroy it, and it will be purified and reborn.
Manipulating Dicor... the Dark Mystics research crazy things. I must report this to the church. Ah, I almost forgot your reward!

Greetings! I asked the Silverlight Mercenaries for help, and you’re a sight for sore eyes.

My soldiers have all fallen unconscious, and a Wizard told me the Reapers have stolen their souls.

I beg you! Slay the Reapers and return my troops’ souls!
Thank you! When you killed Repus, my soldiers began to awaken one by one! Here - this payment is a token of my thanks.

Hello. [player]? I know you’re busy, but can you help me out?

Before coming here, I promised the townspeople that I would defeat their archenemy, Kamel the Slayer.

But I was drunk! There’s no way I can actually defeat him.

I know the Silverlight Mercenaries could make quick work of him - can you help me? I can pay.

Whew... I can’t believe I almost died over a bar bet!

Here’s your payment, and can you keep this a secret? Heh heh... Thanks!

I have an offer from the bailiff! Before commencing the siege of the Keep of Despair, he shall reward anyone who defeats the Innocent Spirit and its minions, the Rampaging Toats.

[player], he’s counting on your valor. Please destroy the evil!
Incredible as always. The insidious Rampaging Toats have been slain! Here is your reward.

I am on a mission to purify this land, but as I feared, there are far too many Undead here. They may seem mindless but they have a leader.

I’m not sure who they follow, but I am confident I will discover their identity over the course of my mission. Today’s target is the Nerkas Necromancer.

These souls are twisted and full of sadness. We must put them to rest.

I do not think it will be difficult to find the Tortured Specter.
Poor souls. They shall rest eternally in the arms of Einhasad.
The Shrieking Hallows are filled with restless Undead. No matter what may have been unresolved in their former lives, they must now come to accept their deaths.
Whoever is responsible, they used this device to manipulate Dicor on purpose... I shall find its maker.

Greetings! I asked the Silverlight Mercenaries for help, and you’re a sight for sore eyes.

My soldiers have all fallen unconscious, and a Wizard told me the Reapers have stolen their souls.

I beg you! Slay the Reapers and return my troops’ souls!
You saved my men’s lives! Thank you so much!

Hello. [player]? I know you’re busy, but can you help me out?

Before coming here, I might have told the townspeople that I would avenge the people killed by the Innocent Spirits.

But I can’t even slay a single Wraith! I barely passed the knighthood test. Can you deal with the Innocent Spirits for me?

Thank you... You saved my life! This place is so dangerous - why does anyone even live here?!

Oh! Did you take the Spirits’ chains?

Help us! We were supposed to receive supplies to aid the siege of the Keep of Despair, but the convoy was attacked and killed by Innocent Spirits!

Dion can’t send more supplies - we have to recover what the Innocent Spirits took!

I’m begging you - please retrieve the supplies from Dion!
Wow! You recovered the supplies from the monsters’ lair! Incredible! This is but a humble token of our appreciation. Thank you.

I was defeating Medusae, but doing it alone is quite difficult. If you assist me in carrying out the bailiff’s orders, I will reward you.

Gather the hair from the Medusae. It will be used to lure other Medusae.
As for Ellen... I tried to fight together... But you did it alone. Ellen was formidable... You’re a great warrior.

Bears expanded their dwellings near the town entrance. We can’t live with this!

Normally, dealing with a few of them would drive them out, but these bears are thick skinned.

We will reduce their numbers this time. Why don’t you sign up for the job?

Did the mission go well? The bears have been driven out, yes?
Wait, what’s that sound?

Wow! You really did it! Did you see the other bears running away?

Now I have a tale to tell my daughter! That’s if I can even get married first! Ha ha...

Ah... it’s... you. Uhh... I am not feeling well... A common side effect when using black magic, but... Today is more severe than usual.

Use this black orb while attacking the succubus, it will absorb their mana.

Hurry... My body feels as if it will crumble.

I’m so sorry... You could have died because of me.

It’s a fate awaiting all who embrace dark powers... That demon is really tenacious...

What the hell is the shepherd doing? The Antelopes are all over the place! I’m going to die from the smell of their manure!

I heard the Antelopes were chased over here by the Windsus. I can’t leave my post, so I need someone else to fix this!

Kill the Antelopes or kill the Windsus - I don’t care as long as the stench is gone!
The antelopes are gone. How did you do it? I should ask Jean. Thanks anyway! Now I can breathe comfortably!

Hey, Mickey! Weather is bad today, don’t you think? But it’s good enough to munch on the grass, I say! Hey Doris, you just stepped in some poop, ha ha!

Huh? Who are you? Ah, welcome! I have a habit of talking to myself. Mickey and Doris are the antelopes over there, I have to change their names every day since they all look the same! Ha ha!

I am the shepherd here. Everything was fine, but now I have a problem! The archon commanded me to reduce the number of Windsus!

The archon must not like me, what do I have to do? I can’t stand the blood... Will you help me?

Thank you, the crisis has been solved! A story worthy of a master bard’s tale!

That genius being me, of course. Not everyone needs to be a warrior, ha ha!

To complete my mission, I need a lot of preparation. I don’t know how adept you are with magic, but being diligent is essential for mystics.

Gather some petals from the Elder Dicor. I will make a temporary spell catalyst from it. Since it’s likely that I will have to fight for a whole day, I shall conserve my energy for now.
I was able to conserve my energy thanks to you. If I succeed in something dramatic and important, know that you contributed to half of it!

Wh...who’s that? Whew, you’re not a lizardman! Why are you in such a dangerous area! Well, not that I can fend for myself here anyway, ha!

Sorry to ask you this, but can you help me? I can’t die just because I lost the battle. I shall return home.

But so long as those Langk Lizardman Rangers are there, I can’t leave. They caught a number of people already! Can you deal with them? Is this pouch of Adena enough for the job?
Huh? You really defeated all of them? I didn’t expect that... Damn... Here’s the promised reward...

The Blood Ranger operation has failed... Lots of soldiers have died. Few of them escaped, but it will be difficult for most of the survivors.

I think drawing their attention would help the surviving soldiers escape. I don’t plan on dying, of course. So can you help me?

Defeat the Langk Lizardman Elder Shaman. If they realize they’re under attack, they will be disrupted. I will create a diversion myself! Please!
The shamans are really a pain in the ass. We should have hired mystic mercenaries in the first place. Or brought you with us... Well done.

Why would an adventurer like you look for me? If you know who I am, my apologies. I’m not here to sell anything, but can offer a job instead.

It’s a job that can bring plenty of Adena. Bringing the wyrm’s head would be easy for a heavily-armed friend like you...

The real objective is inside the head, but they don’t understand that. Just bring the head for me. Now hurry, I can’t stay here for long.
You don’t look interested in why I’m after the wyrm’s head. Not that I intended to explain it anyway. Here, Adena for you!
Bring the Ruin Snipe Leather to me, I will buy it at a special price! It’s an offer higher than others, an opportunity you should not miss!
Well done. Here’s your payment. Everyone! Look here! Someone has just earned a small fortune! See this? You can be rich too!

I was defeating Medusae, but doing it alone is quite difficult. If you assist me in carrying out the bailiff’s orders, I will reward you.

Gather the hair from the Medusae. It will be used to lure other Medusae.
Thank you! I'm surprised they can be lured with a strand of hair. Maybe I will try it again later.

Wow! You really took them down! Did you see the others scatter?

This is a story I’ll tell my kids someday! I mean, assuming I ever have any... Ha!

Are you a mercenary? Even if you have work to do, will you do my job first? The military has been sent to defeat the lizardmen here, but it looks like they failed.

Surveillance with my magic reveals that the force has been obliterated. The surviving soldiers must be scattered, and if the lizardmen find them, they will all die.

Please defeat the Langk Lizardman Sentries to ensure the safety of the surviving soldiers!
Thanks! I’ve heard that the sentries were very nimble, but you handled them well.

Hey, do you have a death wish? If the lizardmen find you here, you’re done for!

Will you help me? As you can see, I’m a lone soldier now. All of my comrades are dead, but I can’t die here!

That way, where recruits are, is a bit easier to go, but since I can’t clear the way, will you go deal with them for me? Please!
Wow! You’ll drive them to extinction at this rate. I don’t even need to hide, thanks to you! I didn’t expect much, but you’re incredible!

Hey, you! You look like a mercenary, what brings you here? If you don’t have a job right now, could I hire you?

My name is MacNahan, I’m a Blood Ranger Captain and, right now, a straggler... But I can’t leave the soldiers to die.

Please defeat the Langk Lizardman Troopers for me. If you distract them, the soldiers on the other side should be able to escape safely.
The troopers were a real pain... If there was a soldier like you, things might have been different... But the army would never have a capable soldier like you... Well done.

Wh-who... Ah! I thought you’re a lizardman! I’m saved! Hey, get down, quick! Don’t let them spot you, so they won’t spot me! They will roast me when they get me!

I can’t die here like that! Help me. Please get rid of as many of them as you can... I must return alive.

Defeat the Langk Lizardman Fighters. They’re really nasty!
Did you even fight them? What? You already defeated them?! Hey, you’re... not... lying?! Wow! I should get going! Thank you!

Listen, you could be rich in Giran! The Giran Merchant Guild buys leather and pelts in large quantities! This is your opportunity to get rich! Earn a small fortune right now!

Bring the Alpine Cougar leather to me! I will buy it at a special price!

You already know my name? I don’t recall ever having told you... Alright. Let’s just say I can trust you. But I always test people before I can trust them.

To improve our relationship, our needs must be matched. I have the Adena and you have the means to bring goods I need.

Bring me the weapons of bugbears. The easiest way is to kill them. They’re not exactly chatty creatures...

I don’t like people who talk too much. I also hate people who ask too many questions. And people who don’t keep their word. You are none of those.

So rest easy now. I don’t hate you. We had a deal. I shall look forward to our next business...

Can you lower your voice? I hate noisy people. There’s nothing to sell, but you can sell me something instead.

If you bring me the Deluded Bugbears’ weapons, I will pay you for your time and effort.

Don’t try to take their weapons, just kill them. That makes it easy and I don’t need to wait longer.
I prefer the shade because of my business. Staying in one place for a long time makes me uneasy. Here’s your Adena. I shall go where I feel more comfortable.

Have we met before? You look familiar. I am Yumaeri.

I have been researching the Dicors recently. I acquired most of my specimens from mercenaries and merchants, but there were a couple that I forgot.

Will you bring me the Dicor of the Forest specimens? I will pay you accordingly.
Oh! Such pristine condition of the specimens makes me remember who you are. No one was as perfect as you. Sorry for not remembering. Thank you, and see you later!

It’s a good day, isn’t it? Being able to say hello to anyone passing by like this. Will you come here for a moment? I have something to ask you.

It’s simple. I offer some work, and you will be paid with Adena in return. What do you say?

I need the Ruin Dicor’s petals. I’m not accustomed to such delicate work. If I use my spells against the Dicors, there will be only ashes left. Please.

I admire your surgical work. Perhaps I will be able to control my powers as delicately someday...

But I somehow doubt it. It’s not easy to shave with an axe, to say the least...

Talking with a Dark Mystic is difficult. Only a few people like you can talk to me normally. I may not be an entirely good man, but I’m not an evil man.

I simply require a mercenary who can bring me Forest Werewolf claws. Can you do this, no questions asked? Of course, it will be worthwhile.
That’s okay. Just take it. The story about a Dark Mystic conjuring up some fake Adena is just a joke. I paid for your work. So long.

Ah! What was that? Who are you? You’re a mercenary? Did someone send you to look for me?

No? Damn... Whatever, I will return to my home when I get out of here! I can’t die like this!

Will you help me? If you defeat the Langk Lizardman Shaman it should be easy to escape...

Great! No wait, did you really defeat all of them? That’s incredible!

Oh, there’s no time for this! Here, your reward! I’m going now, you should do the same!

You! Aren’t you afraid of the lizardmen? What are you doing here? You look like a mercenary... Did the castle send you to find me? I’m Blood Ranger Captain MacNahan.

Looks like I was wrong... I am responsible for the failure of this operation. A defeated officer is as good as dead, but I must do what I can for my soldiers before I die.

Will you defeat the Langk Lizardman Soldiers? If you bring mayhem here, the soldiers hiding on the other side should be able to escape. I beg you!
I hope at least one person escaped safely. I can’t die like this. Well done! Can I ask for your help later again?

Hey, did you see any Giran Soldiers here? I came right after receiving the message calling for reinforcements, but there are only corpses.

I’m trying to search using magic, but the area is larger than I thought. I need more catalysts for the spell. I need ashes from burning the Elder Dicor stalk.

Bring the Elder Dicor stalk to me! Can I count on you? I would really appreciate it if you could do it quickly. The lives of the soldiers are at stake!
Bring it here! Keep that pouch of money. Now, shall I begin the search?

Hey! Shh, don’t look this way, just listen! Keep down! If the lizardmen find me, I will be roasted!

I’m a Giran Army soldier sent here for a Blood Ranger operation. Most of my comrades are either dead or ended up roasted as Lizardmen food.

I can’t die like that! Please help me. Reduce the number of Langk Lizardman Warriors. I will find my way out after that!
Wow, if the army had anyone like you, things would have been different! I should do my part! Escape should be easy now!

Listen, you could be rich in Giran! The Giran Merchant Guild buys leather and pelts in large quantities! This is your opportunity to get rich! Earn a small fortune right now!

Bring the Hungry Red Bear leather to me! I will buy it at a special price!

Listen, you could be rich in Giran! The Giran Merchant Guild buys leather and pelts in large quantities! This is your opportunity to get rich! Earn a small fortune right now!

Bring the Stout Cougar leather to me! I will buy it at a special price!

Hmm... Have we met before? Most people who come to me are either looking for a favor, or wanting to buy something. But you’re different, yes?

Good. A meeting with a purpose saves time, no need for setting up business. I want the Wyrm Warden’s head. You want Adena?

Please respect my occupation. I can’t wait here long, go bring it to me.
Bringing the Wyrm Warden’s head so quickly! Your speed is one of your virtues; not asking too many questions is the best among them.

Ah, I think I met you before... I can distinguish plants very well, but have a hard time with people. But I do remember that you’re a very capable mercenary.

Will you gather some Dicor of Hallucination specimens for me? It’s all that’s left on the list. I can return to my research if I get it.

Please, I will make it worthwhile.
Wow, that was quick. Now I can return to the lab thanks to you. Here, your payment. Please say hello to me when we meet again!

Normally, when I mention my occupation, people don’t talk with me unless I do something to them. But you don’t fear me, and I appreciate that.

I only want the succubus wings, no harm to anyone. My spells can only kill succubi, not get their wings.
Black magic is like a double-edged sword. It destroys the practitioner as well... So a delicate technique to control the destruction is not possible. Thank you.

You look like a capable adventurer. Do you need any work? I need someone to hunt some snipes, specifically the Swift Snipes.

I’m researching the differences between them. It’s for my research, not for mere curiosity. I can’t hunt them while preserving their condition.

My powers are far from delicate work. The corpses should be damaged as little as possible. Would Adena suit you for a reward?
Here, take the Adena. Marvelous work, worthy of the Adena. Thank you.

This area was pretty good in the past. I had no worries of making a living here, but not too long ago, it started getting pretty bad.

The harbor will be shut down at this rate. Who would want to trade and travel in such a dangerous harbor? As the port master, I can’t just watch this happen.

I was waiting for a specialist like you! Please defeat the one-eyed Alfonso for our harbor! He’s wandering around the southeastern wharf!
Really? You really defeated him? You’re amazing! You’re really amazing!

I had various issues while working as the Port Master for 30 years... but it has never been this hard. I wonder the harbor could recover from this...

I hired some mercenaries, but they were no use. You look different, however... can you help us? I can’t leave the harbor like this!

It will be a great help if you just deal with the most powerful evils here. Do you know about holsts? They’re a frequent sight in the southwest wharf, at the end of the harbor. Please defeat them!
That troublemaker has gone! The future of our harbor is brighter!

Hey, hey! I was looking for you! I found something marvelous! Not sure who did it, but someone sealed the Lesser Giant with a powerful spell!

Help me remove the seal, there are guardians in a seal like this. Defeat the Creations of the Lesser Giant and bring the spell stone from them!

Perhaps the long duration of the seal had a bad effect... or it was sealed in the first place because it was dangerous.

Well, we did what we can. Aw, I’m too old for this!

Oh, who is this? Am I still drunk? Is that really you? Welcome! I rarely drink, but I made a mistake yesterday.

I can’t shake hands with an arm like this... I had emergency treatment but I can’t fight. There’s an offer I accepted with a down payment, so I’m in a tight spot.

Hiring you out of my own pocket will be better than to pay the liquidated damage and harm my reputation.

Can you hunt some Forgotten Lesser Giants and gather their cores? I will give you the amount I’ve been contracted.
Even the Degenerated Lesser Giants are formidable, aren’t they? But I knew you would pull it off. My honor still stands, and you get the money! It’s a win-win game!

This harbor became like this recently. It’s only getting worse. My job seems to be at stake.

Dealing with the Death Flyers won’t suddenly make the harbor quiet, but I should at least do something. Can I hire you for it?

You can’t fight all of them, but if you go for their leader, it could make a difference. Good luck!
I knew you could do it! My instincts are still sharp! Assigning the right person to the right job is what makes a manager!

Ah, where did you get that awesome equipment? I had something like that at home, but after dad passed, mom sold it. That was 10 years ago!

With equipment like that, I could defeat the Wandering Dead and become a hero. You’re well dressed already, so may I offer you a job worthy of that equipment?

Or you can just lend it to me and I can do it! Ha ha, just kidding. I’m just a vigilante.

Never thought to use that incense! That was a gamble, but it worked fine. A big success!

This money is not mine. Townspeople entrusted it for times like this. On behalf of the vigilantes here, I thank you.

Wow! [player]?! Welcome! I almost didn’t recognize you. You look amazing now! Can we chat for a moment? Just a second, let me finish the calculation.

Now! Shall we check the offer list again? Done, done, assigned this to other... and... what’s this? Collecting the Rabid Coastal Cougar fangs? Why is it here?

Mitchell should have done this, that’s what Dorothy and I agreed on... right. Mitchell... Mitchell forgot again!

Eh... [player]... I wanted to chat... but may I ask for a favor? Can you collect the Rabid Coastal Cougar fangs?

Hungry Red Bear fangs would also be okay. Just collect either of them. I used up all of my mana potions, I can’t do anything right now.

Oh, last time, Mitchell got extremely lucky with the Enchantment Scrolls he bought with all of his money! He bragged about it to everyone he could find, so someone stole it while he was drunk!

He went back to the auction and bought the enchant scrolls again, but now his equipment is in ruins!

Ah, it still pisses me off just thinking about it! Do you know how hard it was to get just the minimum equipment? Oh! That not all! ... Sara Ra has so many things to say.

Mitchell. Mitchell. Mitchell! A fool! A justice wannabe! A feather brain! Where the hell is he! How many times have I told him not to move alone! Hey! You! Did you see a man like this

... ... Huh? ... ... Have... I see you before? Right! [player]! It’s been a while! You’ve become so awesome! You’ve accomplished so much...

But why! Am I still finding Mitchell like this! Ah, who cares! I’m going to start without him! [player] can take Mitchell’s role.

What do you say? All you have to do is defeat the Ol Mahum Bandits Pillagers and their boss, Nagash the Ruthless. Please!
I don’t like Ol Mahum related jobs, but I really need the money! It’s because that stupid Mitchell got ripped off in the auction!

This is bad! Even heroes can be in a tight spot sometimes! Especially when one forgot to bring his bag! Ah, think, Mitchell, think! Where did you put it?

Ugh... Dorothy and Sara Ra nagging at me... that would be scary! Ugh... I can’t think of anything like this! Hey, friend! Now is the time for you to rescue a hero!

The Ol Mahum Bandit Suppliers must have taken my bag during combat! So greedy with the supply items! There’s a ration for Dorothy inside the bag!

Save me! Go find the Ol Mahum Bandits Suppliers and bring back my bag. Crack them until they cough up the bag! Damn them!

Ha ha ha ha... ...

Forgive me, my friend... the bag was on my back...

Hey, don’t get mad! Hah!

The bag is strangely light... No, it’s getting lighter. Did I level up? Am I getting stronger? Hah, being a hero is so tedious. Ha ha ha.

Huh? That looks like the ration I have to deliver to Dorothy... what’s happening? Huh?!

Waughh! (The bag is ripped off.)

... ... ...

Argh! What is wrong with my bag?! Hey, friend! Your hero is in danger! See there! Those Ol Mahum are eating my rations! Please bring them back to me!

I was sewing my bag! Delivering this ration is very important!

You... you’ve never seen Dorothy’s eyes when she’s upset... Eek...

This area was pretty good in the past. I had no worries of making a living here, but not too long ago, it started getting pretty bad.

The harbor will be shut down at this rate. Who would want to trade and travel in such a dangerous harbor? As the port master, I can’t just watch this happen.

I was waiting for a specialist like you! Please help our harbor! Defeat the evils here!
Thank you! Thank you! There are still lots of evils in the harbor, but you’ve reduced their numbers!

I had various issues while working as the port master for 30 years... but it has never been this hard. I wonder if the harbor could recover from this...

I hired some mercenaries, but they were no use. But you look promising... Could you help us? I can’t leave the harbor like this!
Thanks! That's awesome! If there's any chance, I hope you can get rid of Holst next time…
That’s strange. Nothing’s happening? We’re missing something or something’s gone wrong. It’s not what I expected... I have to think about this.

Oh, who is this? Am I still drunk? Is that really you? Welcome! I can’t shake hands with an arm like this... I had emergency treatment but I can’t fight.

There’s an offer I accepted with a down payment, so I’m in a tight spot. Hiring you out of my own pocket will be better than to pay the liquidated damage and harm my reputation.

Can you hunt some Forgotten Lesser Giants and gather their cores? I will give you the amount I’ve been contracted.

This harbor became like this recently. It’s only getting worse. My job seems to be at stake.

Dealing with the Death Flyers won’t suddenly make the harbor quiet, but I should at least do something. Can I count on you?

Never thought to use that incense! That was a gamble, but it worked fine. A big success! Well done.

This money is not mine. Townspeople entrusted it for times like this. On behalf of the vigilantes here, I thank you.

[player]... I wanted to chat... but may I ask for a favor? Can you collect the Rabid Coastal Cougar fangs?

Hungry Red Bear fangs would also be okay. Just collect either of them. I used up all of my mana potions, so I can’t do anything right now.
I wasn’t going to ask you for this... but I have no choice. It must be completed today... And you’re trusty as always! Unlike someone else I know...

Have I seen you before? Ah! [player], right? Welcome! You’re getting even more awesome as time goes by!

Do you have a bit of time? There’s a job to defeat Ol Mahum Bandits Pillagers. I have other jobs to do, so will you do it for me, please?
If not for a certain fool, I wouldn’t accept Ol Mahum related jobs... Ugh! Thanks anyway! That really helped a lot.

The Ol Mahum Bandit Suppliers must have taken my bag during combat! So greedy with the supply items! There’s a ration for Dorothy inside the bag!

Save me! Go find the Ol Mahum Bandits Suppliers and bring back my bag. Crack them until they cough up the bag! Damn them!

Argh! When did my bag become like this?!

Hey, friend! Your hero is in danger! See there! Those Ol Mahum are eating my rations! Please bring them back to me!

There’s a job to defeat the Bugbear Fighters. Are you interested? I am recruiting mercenaries on the bailiff’s orders.

[player] will make other mercenaries obsolete.
I didn’t recruit any mercenaries after you. I knew you’d finish the job quickly.

Did they run away, or are they dead? Time is running out! ...Huh? Who’s this? [player]!

Welcome! I am truly happy to see you, but I have to finish a job with my wounded arm.

I sent some of the juniors, but they’ve gone silent! This is frustrating! I think you’d do it in no time! Could you gather the cores from the Forgotten Lesser Giants? What do you say?
So you succeeded! The juniors returned without anything. Being a treasure hunter requires more combat skills, I guess.

So you’re here too. Are you interested in archaeology? You’re a friend of Feldheim, so I guess you have a special relationship with us.

I need someone to defeat the Grandis Shredder for me, and you’re right here! Go defeat them for me!
Great! You’ve done your job, now it’s time to do mine!

It’s been a long time since I was a port master, and this is something I’ve never seen before! I recommended this job to my son, but maybe I was wrong.

But I still have to do anything I can as the port master. You look like a seasoned veteran, please lend me your hand.

Will you defeat the Dismal Shout? That shriek makes me consider suicide!
I’m a changed man. With a friend like you, this job is manageable. Let’s be good friends from now on. I brought lots of Adena for our friendship!

It’s already been two hours without any contact... Ugh! How many times have I told you not to move alone, stupid Mitchell! I can’t wait any longer, I’ll have to hire someone else! But where can I find someone... ...

Wait, you there! Have we met before? Are you... [player]? Oh, so glad to see you, [player]! What a coincidence!

You see, I’m under a lot of stress right now... Could you defeat the Ol Mahum Bandit Workers for me? I would appreciate if you didn’t ask me why!
If you work with Mitchell, you will understand me. He’s driving me crazy!

[player]! It’s been a while! You look far stronger than you did before! Have you ever collected cougar claws before? The idiot who was supposed to bring them is not coming!

The idiot is Mitchell, of course. I swear, the stress is going to kill me one day! It’s a job we have to finish by tonight! Mitchell didn’t complete anything!

I have my own work to do... Can you help me with this? All you have to do is collect Starving Cougar claws.
Whew! Thank you! Jobs like this are very time sensitive. Losing credibility is a disaster in my field of work. I owe you!

Let’s see... Most of the work is done... Ah! A bear hunt? I don’t have many mana potions left... This could be difficult...

Will you defeat the Hungry Red Bear for me? I took the job, but it would be better to offer it to you, rather than pay the liquidated damage.

Well, none of this would have happened if stupid Mitchell didn’t lose all the money! Then, I wouldn’t have to worry about the price of mana potions! Ahh... I need to calm down... Inner peace... Inner peace...

Whew... Inner peace... Whew... Ah! You’re here! You shouldn’t sneak around like that. I try to meditate a lot these days. I may end up like Dorothy if I don’t.

Here! It’s yours. It’s not much, but it’s a win-win for us.

Welcome, my friend! Came here looking for justice? I am about to deliver it by defeating the Ol Mahum!

Are you with me? Ha ha! Defeat the Ol Mahum Bandit Warriors! I bet you can’t eliminate them as fast as I can! Ha ha ha!
Yes! You’re on the side of justice! I can gladly spend my money on friends like you! Here!

My job is hiring mercenaries on behalf of the vigilantes of this town. We have no choice but to hire specialists against the undead.

If my skills were higher, I would have bought some equipment, defeated those Shipwrecked Pirate Zombies in style and saved our town! For now, I should probably ask for your help instead.
...As long as the town is safe, it doesn’t matter who does it! Better than increasing the casualties! There are many ways we can protect the town.
Buying leather! Buying leather! Buying cougar leather. Bonus for Insatiable Cougar leather! Offering the best price you could sell your leather for. Act now!

Why is it insatiable? It’s only a name. They are known to be particularly hungry. That’s why I risk coming here to obtain their leather.

Here, your Adena. There’s my leather, bring it here.

We meet again, [player]. Are you traveling? I am hiring mercenaries under the order of the bailiff. Are you looking for work?

There’s a job to defeat Bugbear Warriors. They are aggressive, but if it’s you, [player], you should have no problem with that. Would you like to take it?
No problem, I presume? Today must be the worst day of those Bugbear Warriors’ lives.

Wow, look who’s here! It’s been ages since I’ve last seen you! Ah, I would like to shake hands, but please forgive me.

If my arm was hurt while fighting monsters, I would brag about it... But I got drunk and fell down!

I received an offer, which has not been completed yet. You think you could help me gather the Lesser Giant's Creations’ cores?
So that’s what a Lesser Giant's Creation’s core looks like.

Hello everyone, please stay awhile and listen!

The lord of Giran has offered a bounty. Anyone who defeats the Zaken Pirates will be rewarded, regardless of their status or gender!

Fight for the Giran Harbor! Fight for Giran and all of us! Defeat the Zaken Pirate Shooters!

Thank you! Thank you! [player] is a hero of Giran!

On behalf of my lord, I reward you for defeating the Zaken Pirates.

Hello everyone, please stay awhile and listen!

The lord of Giran has offered a bounty. Anyone who defeats the Zaken Pirates will be rewarded, regardless of their status or gender!

Fight for the Giran Harbor! Fight for Giran and all of us! Defeat the Zaken Pirate Infantry!

Look here, it’s [player]! The hero who defeated the Zaken Pirates!

On behalf of my lord, I reward you! Well done.

Hello everyone, please stay awhile and listen!

The lord of Giran has offered a bounty. Anyone who defeats the Zaken Pirates will be rewarded, regardless of their status or gender!

Fight for the Giran Harbor! Fight for Giran and all of us! Defeat the Zaken Pirate Vanguard!
Look here, the hero who defeated the Zaken Pirates has returned! On behalf of my lord, I shall reward you!

Ah... Whew... Hi there,[player].

You’ve become even more powerful... But here I am still tending to this idiot...

Will you gather some Savage Red Bear meat? The idiot who was supposed to bring it is not coming... This is frustrating...
It’s not that the Red Bear meat is delicious... Anything tasting better must be sold for money... How did I end up like this! Argh!

Hello? Remember me? Are you here to find some work? Well, I already accepted all the offers available here...

Will you deal with the Ol Mahum in my stead? It’s a job to deal with the Ol Mahum Bandit Sentries, but I don’t want to touch any Ol Mahum...

We’re planning to leave as soon as we have the money to get moving. All of this because of an idiot who lost our money in an auction...

Wow, done already? You’re amazing as ever!

Hmm... Earning money like this isn’t bad, maybe I should become a commission agent? Ah, what am I thinking? I’m getting lame!

Strangely, there was a hole in my bag. But I figured out why! It’s because I used this bag to shield myself from arrows!

The bag had a lot of rations that Dorothy asked for... If I don’t bring them... I don’t even want to imagine what would happen...

I must get the rations back! I recovered everything I could see here, but it’s not enough! The Ol Mahum Bandit Archers over there must have picked up some rations!
Waugh! You have no idea how happy I am! If I didn’t recover those rations... Dorothy would have punched me- Er... I mean... Would have been very sad... Thank you!
Buying leather! Buying leather! Bring the whole leather of Starving Cougars! I will buy them for a better price than the Giran Castle Merchant Guild!
Oh! Such quality! This is why I have to go to dangerous areas! It was worth the risk! Here, your Adena!

That Dismal Shout gives me nightmares. Oh, just thinking about their shrieks makes me shiver!

I would purge them if I could! But since I don’t have any equipment like you, could you do it for me? Please?
I know that equipment is not the only factor in combat, but still... it is the most important.

Greetings! You’re just who I wanted to see, meow!

I arrived here with other merchants from the caravan, but they scattered as soon as we arrived, meow!

Something bad could happen to them! Please find them, meow!
Hermes went out to sniff out treasure? Looks like I was worried for nothing, meow! Now I can sit tight thanks to you!

Greetings! You’re just who I wanted to see, meow!

During my investigation here, I found a collection of trans-purr-ts from wrecked ships!

They like shiny things, I bet there are shiny things inside the supplies! I want you to find them for me, meow!
Meow, what is this?! It was silverware! Meow! It wasn’t worth risking even one of my nine lives for it! This sucks, meow!

Greetings! You’re just who I wanted to see, meow! Nesca, one of my com-paw-nions have been out there for a long time!
