This place is filled with dark energy that should have already dissipated. That's what's affecting the Stone Golems. It's not pleasant, but we should put them out of their misery.

Something is influencing the monsters nearby. The ones we're seeking are trying to delay us.

We must be quick. First, let’s destroy the source of the dark energy.

A Monster Summoning Stone. If we leave it here, its corruption will seep into the land.

We must remove its magic. Be on your guard.

Talking Island has four barriers. [player] has purified two of them, so only two remain.

No one knows their exact location, but Feldheim should be able to give you a heading. Let’s explain the situation and ask him for help.

Hmm... so the archaeologists were involved in this for a reason.

The barrier entrance? Let’s see...

The western part of Talking Island has some areas I’d suggest. Follow me.

Entering that light? You will need this.

It's the Elven bracelet Niah found. If you’re right, this must be the key.

I can’t hold out much longer...

Hurry, I must fulfill my mission. Follow me.
There are a lot of guards here... I can only hope that the purification device is still there. We'd better deal with those brutes.
I feel the presence of a powerful monster here. Prepare for combat.

Dexter had an Enchant Scroll. I will give this to you, [player].

Wait... a minute... very well. As a reward for helping me, I will teach you how to Enchant using that Enchant Scroll.

Now, we shall activate the purification device. Alas, I am incapable of operating it.

I have been influenced by the dark energy for too long.

[player]! Please follow my instructions and activate the device.
Thank you. Now, only one remains. It will not be easy... I am sorry to trouble you with such a burden. Thank you for bringing peace to the townsfolk and spirits of this island.

There’s a problem. While you were gone, monsters rallied and Russel was wounded in combat.

It’s worse than it looks... Russel is not well at all, even though it’s a small wound.

It’s a light scratch, but I feel like my energy is being drained.

Healers tell me that it’s a curse. The monsters must have cursed me.

Elven Flowers should undo the curse... please. Get some for me.

Did you see werewolves around here? They wounded me.

Please destroy them to save others from my fate.

I wouldn't wish this curse on anyone. After you’re done, please go find the Ranger Captain and warn him about the danger.

We didn't find anything, but we know they must be headed to the ruins since they targeted the Elven Relic.

Please join us. There are Skeleton Soldiers on the path to the ruins.

Their bones will block the path if you don't stop them!

The Decrepit Forest of Spirits has been designated as a conservation site since the Spirits have been weakened... what could they be doing there?

Since the Ranger Captain and Silverlight Mercenaries are tracking them, they must be a serious threat. I’ll guide you to the forest!

There’s something strange here. It looks like a crystal... do you know what it is?

A M-Monster Summoning Stone? What should we do?

Hm... perhaps it’s time. We are tracking one of the members of the Dark Brotherhood.

They are causing problems all around the continent with their sinister, dark powers. They're old adversaries of the Silverlight Mercenaries...

Sorry to involve a new recruit in such a serious conflict. You can still follow your own path if you want.

But if you’re with us, I will teach you how to use Soul Crystals. It will give you an edge in the upcoming battle.

The black magic is growing more powerful. They must be nearby.

The archaeologists must be here, too. Hurry!
This is bad... using magic will harm them... but spider venom should melt the cage!
Open the cage to rescue them! Be on guard - the Dark Brotherhood may be watching!

They threatened to kill me if I didn't hand over my Elven Relics... they killed some of the other archaeologists as an example. Their corpses disappeared so quickly...

I hid the bracelet with the bag, but I had to give them the Elven Necklace... I'm so sorry. They took the necklace and went that way.

The last purification device is nearby. We must hurry - the dark energy is stronger than ever!

If they know we have the Relic, they will attack us right away. Looks like Feldheim knows the location of the barrier. Go meet him!

The entrance to the ruins is that way, but there's a problem.

The ruins are infested with Red Rouses. The Dark Mystics must have summoned them.

Slay the Red Rouses to secure the ruins.

Huh? That’s a Monster Core!

Monsters sometimes drop them which contain important information about them. Gather those Monster Cores to raise your stats.

Oh, silly me! Of course, there's more you can do with them! Here, I'll tell you what you can do if you collect enough.

This must be the entrance to the last barrier.
The fate of this island rests with you. Good luck!
Oh...thank goodness. I thought... this was the end... Follow me... I’ll guide you...
The monsters are desperate, too. We have a lot of distance to cover, but there are guards here already. Deal with them first.

I feel a strong dark energy. It’s different from powers we’ve encountered before.

We need more power to overcome it. It’s time to teach you the ancient magic, [player].
The dark energy is overwhelming me. I can’t hold out much longer. Hurry, before it’s too late.
Th-there’s a Wizard... a Dark Mystic... it must have cracked the barrier and sent the monsters!

Heh heh, can you feel it? The lord is back - the lord who shall claim this realm!

Now, it’s time to say goodbye to this pathetic island. Are you sad? Too bad.

I have a gift for you - a farewell present. Try to survive it! If you can.
Please... I fear I can’t fulfill my role... please activate the last device...

At last, it's complete. I... it’s time for me to sleep once more. I hope there's no need for me to reawaken.

Thank you. May Eva guide your path.

Thanks to the feats of [player], the threat against Talking Island has been neutralized. Most of the islanders will never know they were in any danger.

And the people who do know will likely forget it in time. But the Silverlight Mercenaries and I shall remember your Achievements.

Can you spare a minute? There’s someone you should meet.

I don’t like long introductions, so let me get to the point. You're invited to join the Silverlight Mercenaries.

There’s a darkness far larger than what you’ve seen on Talking Island. Our mission is to defeat that darkness.

The Silverlight Mercenaries are in need of your strength. More tests and struggles await you.

The Silverlight Mercenaries shall be there for you when you need us - but I will not force your decision. Tell Theodore when you have made your choice.

You made the right choice. I congratulate you on your wise decision. As you may have suspected, the last mission was only partially successful.

While we saved Talking Island, we didn’t stop the Dark Brotherhood. The Dark Brotherhood must have larger plans, and we must thwart them.

Now, let’s leave Talking Island and prepare for your first journey into the larger world.
The harbor is infested with the Undead! Get rid of them, and then we’ll talk!
This is a disaster! The Guard Captain is protecting the townspeople, but he needs reinforcements. We’ll handle things here - go gather some lumber!
Good! Now, deliver the lumber to the Guard Captain, and let him know we’re almost done cleaning up here.

The Undead onslaught is slowing down our work on the walls!

Hey! Over there! Something’s coming. Get ready!

That ship looks like it’ll sink any second.

Once you clear the path, can you go join the lieutenant’s investigation?

I think that ghost ship’s the cause of all this. The Undead started attacking when it sailed into the harbor!

We have to destroy that ship - but first, we need to clear out some of the Undead and secure the perimeter.

The hardest thing about fighting the Undead is that they keep getting back up - using holy power should make them stay down.

However, we aren’t able to wield holy powers, so we’ll need a holy bomb.

We’ll hold the line - you go find the cardinal and get some Holy Water.
Greetings. The Holy Water is ready. This will exorcise the Undead. Please deliver it to the soldiers.
We received a message from the cardinal while you were away. You should go see him.

Greetings. I’ve been waiting for you. Your selfless actions to save the harbor impressed me.

I hope it is not too much to request another favor.

Will you please deliver this Einhasad Holy Artifact to the mayor of Gludin Harbor?
Please deliver this artifact safely to the mayor’s hands.

Did you say you’re a mercenary? Good. I have a job for you.

Townsfolk are vanishing near the Windmill Plains. We can’t find any leads... can you take a look?

Oh! And I heard Aida the merchant wanted to thank you for saving her from the pirates. She’s by the East Gate.

Hey, thanks for what you did out there! You probably didn’t notice me because you were busy fighting!

But I wanted to repay you somehow!

Wait, where did I put that equipment?

Damn cat! Must’ve taken the sword, too... I should have noticed when he added a bonus...

Ah - I know! I’ll tell you about a dungeon where you can find equipment!

Huh? Do I know anything about townsfolk vanishing? Well... not much. People don’t want to talk about anything bad these days...

Oh, that cat merchant!

Go through the east gate. He set up shop there- he must’ve heard something.

Hurry, though - I wouldn’t count on him to stick around for long.

As a matter of fact, I did hear something about the Windmill Plains! I was about to go there!

I’ll show you the way - follow me!

I dealt with Werewolves along the way, but I couldn’t get enough of their claws!

Werewolf claws are an expensive magic ingredient. I’d be looking at a huge payday if someone were to collect some for me...

Werewolves are a huge problem for the farms around here, so you’d be helping a lot of people!

Hey! I spy Cougars! Their leather is even more expensive than Werewolf claws!

Don’t just stand there, get some Cougar leather, too! We can’t pass on this!

Whew, this should be enough. Deal’s a deal!

You’ll want to talk to the farm manager over by that windmill.

See you later, meow!

Now, I’m not sure if this is connected to the other missing people, but...

There’s this young farmer next door named Li-el. One day, there was this big commotion over by Li-el’s windmill, and then Li-el was gone!

It’s that windmill over there. I’d go with you, but I’m too chicken!

Hm... perhaps Augel could help with the plant.

Augel’s an herbalist who lives by the windmill up near the fork in the road.

Oh, you surprised me! Sorry, everyone’s jumpy these days.

That plant is a common weed... but it’s rare to see one die like that.

Sometimes, plants near graveyards or battlefields die like this due to the presence of death.

Hey, did you hear that?

Well, Ol Mahum are seen frequently these days...

Gives me the willies! Please take them out!

Oh! Come to think of it, I saw some shadowy figures leading a wagon full of people up the road.

The weight of it must have left tracks. You should take a look.

As for me, I’m getting out of here. Thank you!

The Guards keep telling me to leave because it’s dangerous. Bollocks! I can’t leave my home! Then where would I see my customers?

Though... I did see some Orcs recently... Who am I? Oh! I’m Helena the Fortune Teller. It’s a pleasure.

Oh - you can deal with the Orcs? I’ll tell you everything I can about them.
You’re looking for the missing people? Go to the abandoned shack to the north. You may find what you’re seeking.
Get... men... bring... east. Fail... this... end...

Oh! After a shadowy man visited the abandoned shack east of here, Orcs appeared.

He seems to be gone now... but I’m curious! Let’s go!

Don’t worry, I can protect myself.

Hey, what are these markings? There are strange letters on the wall!

Hm... looks like a spell...

Let’s see... Orcish Order... Ol Mahum... dried black weed... that reminds me of this place.

If you take the path over the river, you’ll get to the Silent Graveyard. That’s where we have to go!

Alert the guards? I don’t like them, and this is fun... Ugh. Fine.

The grave keeper’s name is Kadol. He’ll be out by the entrance - you should talk to him first.

Are you here about the missing people? This big, muscular guy with lots of hair pushed his way through a while ago.

Say, what’s going on? You’ve made me nervous!

Ha ha ha! Looks like I found the clue first this time.

Well, shall we begin from the inside?
The Silverlight Mercenaries are here to investigate the abduction. That reassuring.
Yes, it is! What brings you here, lady?
I lost something precious... Will you please find it for me?

We should spread out. I’ll go this way, you take the upper part. We’ll meet up in front of that abandoned shack.

Ugh! Bats! Let’s deal with them first!
Wait - what’s this cauldron doing here? And ugh, it stinks! Someone used it recently. Let’s investigate!

I can’t be sure... but this looks like black magic. Who did this, and why?

We need to know, but first, we should dispose of the cauldron - we should bury it in that open grave.

This is bad. Something terrible is happening, just like on Talking Island.

Eleanor! We shouldn’t leave her alone!

She’s gone! Ah, this is bad.

Right, she was looking for something. She must be near. Let’s look for her!

What? You think I’m trying to impress her?

You’re completely misreading the situation!
D-don’t lie to me! Was that a ghost?!

A g-ghost? I never said anything about a ghost! Don’t say that.

I just found a piece of her bracelet during the search. Look! Her name’s on it.
My Lord... <YellowBold>[player]</>! We must spread out. This guard is untrustworthy. Will you check over where the reapers are?

Russel? Ah, the hairy mercenary! He’s not back yet.

I saw him headed towards the Bugbear nest... It’s west of here.
If she really was a ghost, she must have been asking for help.

There are many abandoned shacks around here. We should search them. After dealing with these bats! Ugh, they’re very annoying!

I heard there’s this crazy guy on Talking Island who likes eating these things grilled - maybe we should bring him here!
Hey, Russel is signaling us! I’ll bring you to him. Let’s go!

I can hear something coming from the basement. Maybe it’s the missing townspeople!

It’s locked tight. We have to force it open. Help me!
There! Inside! It’s the townsfolk! They’ve been locked in there the whole time... Come on!

That Undead dropped this piece of a bracelet. It matches the other... That must have been Eleanor!

What’s going on?

I’ll help Russel recover the remains. They were our neighbors once.

[player], you should head to the Looter Camp. Please give Captain Jackson the news of what happened here.

My intel says some of the townsfolk were headed to the Ol Mahum camp. They might be sacrificed for black magic. We must hurry.

Are you one of the Silverlight Mercenaries? Hmm! So, the Silverlight Mercenaries are truly as resourceful as rumored.

I don’t know what brings you here, but please help us.

The Scout reported that there’s another Ol Mahum post in the north. Please search it.

Beware of the Cutthroats blocking the path... I hope we find something this time.
I can’t leave by myself. Please take me somewhere safe!

Aymel... Aymel... Aymel...

Hm...I don’t know who Aymel is, but someone was captured trying to rescue us.

She might be in the stronghold with the others - hurry!

That’s too risky! I know you want to solve this fast, but we have to be smart about this.

Clear the path by slaying the warriors guarding the Stronghold entrance. Once you do that, I’ll lead the main force for an assault.

They’re stronger than I thought!
Help the soldiers fight the Guards!

My Scout found their base! Follow the road and turn to the left! Maybe that’s where your comrade is.

Go! We’ll hold the line.

Human female? Hm... no idea!

Anyway, the damn Ol Mahum took all of my precious goods! Please get it back! I bet those Loot Guards have it!

I thought after passing the Windmill Plains it would be safe, but it seems the entire Gludin Highway is swarming with bandits.

Get me out of here!

Wait... hm... hm...

Ah! I remember! A woman was taken north along this road!

Search near the northern Ol Mahum post... The Ol Mahum are sure to talk if you apply enough pressure!

They took my sword! Wait, you rascals, I’ll whip you like an ox!

I’m not going anywhere unarmed. Let’s look for my sword!

Let’s move! No time to waste!

That Dark Mystic is next.

We’ll sweep the rest. Aymel and [player] should go to the heart of the Stronghold.

Captain Jackson is there already. Oh, and take out the Ol Mahum Shooters on the way. They’re a huge threat to the townspeople.
I will look for the Dark Mystic. Meet me inside the Ol Mahum Stronghold!
We’re losing a lot of men to those Ol Mahum Fighters. Please clear a path for us.

There’s another pressing matter. The Einhasad Holy Artifact you delivered to the mayor of Gludin Harbor was stolen.

Searching for the missing townsfolk is important, but finding the Holy Artifact takes precedence. Without it, the harbor could be invaded again.

I dispatched scouts with the details - meet with them to be briefed. And be careful out there!
First, let’s search that storage. We should take out the Loot Guards to stop them from sounding the alarm.
Let’s investigate the chests here. Spread out!
Damn... not here. Let’s try that way. There’s more Ol Mahum storage over there.

I’ll stay here and investigate. [player], you should go check the last bit of storage over there.

I saw a suspicious woman heading that way - hurry!

Huh? What happened? I’ve been imprisoned here this whole time... Oh! I saw a Dark Mystic. She was commanding the Ol Mahum.

Maybe she knows about the holy artifact. But first, let’s invite these Ol Mahum to dance!

Normally, killing all these guards would make the Guard Captain show up...

Where the hell is it? Do I just have to keep looking?

Hey, [player]. Search that way. Tell me if you find anything.

Let’s spread out and look for the mystic. Signal when you find her! She should feel our power.

Well, I guess you can deal with her yourself if you feel up to it. I like your enthusiasm!

Don’t go alone - what if it’s a trap?
I’ll go with you!

Hey, I was kidding! We’ve got to look on the bright side. If it’s a trap, someone’s gotta be watching us! Textbook villain.

So, we’ll be the textbook heroes. Let’s go!

Heh heh heh... Confused? Black magic can create new worlds!

But I have something even more exciting in store. Prepare to die!

Damn... you spoiled my experiments. I must take my leave.

But you shall rot here for eternity.

What a chicken, running off like that! Next time we see her, I’ll roast her!

Anyway, let’s look for a way out. If the dark mage was able to leave, there has to be a way out for us, too.

Eh? Really? No kidding? Wow!

You don’t know what elixirs are? Wow...

Alright. See that flowering plant? Pick some of those.

It would be irresponsible if I let you leave here without explaining what elixirs are.
Now, listen up - I’ll only explain this once.
Hurry! We don’t know what’s going on out there.
Urgh, I’m okay! Let’s get out of here! Meet me outside the Ol Mahum Stronghold!

I’ve been thinking... the place we just left. I think it was the cave beneath the Ivory Tower.

We should revisit it from time to time to gather elixir ingredients. I’ll tell you how to get there - we did it once, so it’ll be easy to find our way back.

Aw, we totally missed this one. I’ll have to report back to my master.

By the way, this cat keeps asking for you, [player].

I’m about to leave for Gludio, but having you along would be helpful, [player].

I heard it’s dangerous there lately, and I’m a ‘fraidy-cat!

Oh! Of course, I’ll make it worthwhile. I always pay!

Mrrow?! Th... that’s a Crazed Black Wolf! Oh no!

Sniffing around with his toothy snout! Hiss!!!

[player], kill it! Kill it right now!

For both our sakes!

Hey! You didn’t come back with empty hands after killing those wolves, did you?

Whew, listen! Crazed Black Wolves have valuable leather and fangs!

Got it?

Ah! It’s a jungle out there. See those Red Foxes? Kill them too!

They’re cunning, unreliable, and their snouts are just awful! Hiss! Kill them right meow!

Whew, now listen to me... see their tails? Full of fur? Doesn’t that smell like money? No?

Ah, where do I have to start? You’re just not merchant material. I guess we can’t all be!

Just trust me. Gather the Red Fox Tail Fur!

Oh! That must be a Black Wolf! He’s bristling with high-quality leather! A merchant’s instinct is always right!

We’ve struck gold! Hunt them and bring me their hides!

Hey, have you ever seen Humans playing hide-and-seek with Lizardmen?

Wait... no! It looks more like tag!

Wait... why are they coming this way?! [player], do something!

A group of Lizardmen attacked our town and kidnapped people! Their bounty hunters are still hunting the townsfolk - that’s what happened to me.

I beg you, please stop them!

Slay the Lizardman Goalseeker. The hunters abduct any townsfolk they see.

If we’re going to stop this, we have to deal with the Lizardman Goalseekers.

Ah! There! Someone’s surrounded by Lizardmen.

That must be Melina! Please, rescue her!

I always dreamed of lying in the arms of a knight... so cruel that it should happen only at the end...

My vision is fading... is this it? Will you give this necklace to my brother?

His name is...

... ...

... (She dies.)

We can’t let this stand. Please avenge Melina and the townsfolk.

I’m too weak to do anything on my own.

Please, take out the Lizardman!

I am forever in your debt.

You saved my life and granted my wish. I will remember your name and the Silverlight Mercenaries forever.

If I may, let me guide you to town.

You want to fulfill Melina’s dying wish? You’ll have to find Heath. He’s a soldier in Gludio.

The Gludio Conscript Officer would know where he’s stationed. You should meet him first.

Heath? The name sounds familiar, but it’s not my job to remember every single man’s posting.

I just enlist people. The guard at the East Gate might know more.

Heath? Yeah, I know him, but why should I tell you anything? What’s in it for me?

You don’t look wealthy... wait, I know how you can pay me...

See that Red Bear? Its leather would grease my palm quite nicely.

To my knowledge, Heath is stationed at the monster extermination site. They say it’s awful up there these days...

I pay through the nose to keep away from there - a man’s gotta live, eh?

Do I know a soldier named Heath? Don’t be absurd.

Being posted in the middle of a war zone is bad enough - how would I keep track of all those footmen? Ask the lieutenant and stop bothering me.

Heath? He’s with the 3rd Platoon, but... they’ve been decimated. He might not even be alive.

We were about to send a search & rescue, but we need to deal with these Red Bears and secure the perimeter first. If you want to help Heath, help us first.
Rats! Bugbears on the path. My soldiers can’t handle them alone. Please help my men - I’ll join you!

I have good news and bad news. The good news is there is a survivor from the 3rd Platoon.

The bad news is that he’s surrounded by monsters and needs us to rescue him.

Argh! They just keep coming. We must defeat them all!

They killed everyone! Everyone but me!

Ah! I don’t want to die! No!

Not like this! Argh!

We were on the mission as planned, but we lost our flank support during combat.

We were completely surrounded by monsters... oh no! More Bugbears!

I can’t count how many times you saved me. I’m going to go far away from here - if I report back in, I’ll just be sent here again and again until I die.

Heath? He was there until the last battle. Not sure what happened - if he’s lucky, he moved north and joined the 2nd Platoon.

Corporal Heath joined the 2nd Platoon as the sole survivor of the 3rd Platoon. He volunteered for a scouting mission. If you want to meet him, wait here.

So, you’re a mercenary? Good. While you wait for Heath, why don’t you help us hold the line? You look like you can handle yourself.

The enemy is well-coordinated - not something you’d expect from monsters. Something’s commanding them.

In a situation like this, it’s best to cut off their head. The ranger reported the location of their commander.

We’re headed there now - join us. We’ll rendezvous with the ranger first.

While we were scouting, we found the one commanding the Bugbears.

We tried to flee but were surrounded. Only I managed to escape.

The others might still be fighting! Please. Check if they’re still alive.

And if they are... please help them...

I’ll report back to my platoon, but I want to recover my comrades’ bodies first.

I can’t let them get eaten by the monsters.

Please! Help me collect them.
Please collect their equipment, too - we need it for the surviving soldiers.

I’m going back to my platoon now - please follow me.

Oh no! We have to hurry! The Bugbears are on the move!
Hey! Look over there! The chancellor! The chancellor brought reinforcements at last!

You’re a Silverlight Mercenary? I shall submit a formal complaint. The Silverlight Mercenaries shall be banned from Gludio in the future.

You, platoon leader, will die before you return to town.

Oh! While you were dealing with the Bugbears, Corporal Heath contacted me. He found an Evil Summoning Stone during his scouting mission.

Corporal Heath is calling for reinforcements while he investigates the Evil Summoning Stone.

Since you have business with Corporal Heath, you should go meet him.

... ... ...

Okay. Melina is... but... now is not the time. I have a mission.

Please help me slay these monsters to avenge my fallen comrades.

We should start by targeting the Dark Weavers. That will help clear a path to the Evil Summoning Stone.

Now there’s just the Summoning Stone left. Let’s go! We have to finish this!

When this is over, I’ll ask Melina for forgiveness. I failed to protect her...

Let’s finish this before the Demons return!

Hey... wait! There’s someone coming!

[player]... a puny little adventurer hindering our plans?

You spoiled our plan, so I shall kill you in return.

Space is distorting again!

I have a Teleportation Stone. I don’t know if it’ll work, but we have to try!

Look around, so many sacrifices. The soldiers here are all heroes of Gludio.

We can’t leave them here. Please help me recover their bodies.

I’ll report back now. [player]... uh...

If my eyes aren’t mistaken, there’s a mysterious figure in dark clothes waving at you!

We were investigating this area for signs of the Dark Brotherhood. Seems you found them first.

We’re not sure, but the Archon of Gludio seems connected to the Dark Brotherhood. I shall investigate further.

You must return to the town and meet a Silverlight Mercenary named Lonna. She has important information for you.
You’re ready. Let’s go into town.

The monster infestation is somewhat under control here, but the Lizardmen are still prowling the west.

Their town chief is trying to contain it, but since most of the forces have been sent elsewhere, it’s not working.

Go meet the chief, and I’ll join you later.

Oh! I almost forgot. You’ll see some Black Wolves near the entrance to the town. Please deal with them.

As you can see, the entire town’s been overrun with Lizardmen. Those Lizardman Pillagers are taking anything that’s not nailed down!

Forks, knives, stoves, frying pans - any metal they see. It’s not funny! Our survival is at stake!

Please slay those Lizardman Pillagers!

Good. We need to deal with the Lizardman Seekers next - they’re the brains of this operation.

They observe the town, then direct the actions of the looters and kidnappers. Killing the Seekers will hinder their activities!

Now, it’s time to take back the stolen supplies. Food and cooking ware are the most important things. We can’t fight them if we’re not fed.

They say that a general failing a mission can be forgiven, but failing to feed their troops can’t be.

You ready? Let’s go! For our grumbling stomachs!

Karin, one of the townspeople, may be trapped inside her house.

Please rescue her before those lizards notice. Her house is west of here.

Thank you for saving me. I saw Lizardmen taking people, so I hid in my house.

The Lizardmen were taking their prisoners south. Please rescue them, too!

I’ve never wielded a sword... One day, I’m conscripted, and the next, I’m imprisoned!

Hey, those are the Lizardmen who imprisoned me! Please do something about those Lizardman Assault Soldiers!

Oh! I saw something strange while I was locked up.

Do you know the Gludio Archon? That sneaky bastard was doing something funny in an abandoned shack to the south.

Even stranger, the Lizardmen didn’t touch the Archon!

You should investigate the shack right away!
What? A Black Magic Tome? Shouldn’t we report this right away?

I have so many questions... About a year ago, the chancellor declared war against the monsters.

After troops took the monsters out, the Lizardmen rose, and their conflict with the Turek Orcs ended...

You should cooperate with soldiers of Gludio to defeat the Lizardmen. I’ll look for the chancellor.

Forget what you learned about Lizardmen on the homestead.

We’re dealing with far stronger warriors here, and they’re much better coordinated.

You’d never expect a bunch of reptiles to be so cunning and intelligent, huh?

First, slay the Maille Lizardman Scouts. Cutting off their intel is key to victory.

Maille Lizardmen are different from other Lizardmen. They’re well-coordinated. You can’t fight them head-on, so we’ll have to be crafty.

Let’s start by killing their leader. How will we lure him out? Well, they say that Lizardmen are very sensitive to the scent of their own blood.

And their leaders are the most sensitive of all. Let’s kill some nearby Lizardmen and burn their blood.

Good. Now, let’s try Theodore’s plan - burning the blood was just the first step.

Theodore’s plan is simple. There’s a Lizardman altar southwest of here. Burn the totem at its entrance. That should lure the leader out.

Oh! I almost forgot! Aymel is rescuing hostages near the altar.

Me? I’m rescuing hostages! These damn lizards are a pain in my rear, but now I have you!

Let’s do this together. I’ll draw attention to the altar while you rescue the hostages.

Once you’re done, report back to that meat head.

The Maille Lizardmen have 3 powerful leaders. One of them was the Vanguard Captain you just killed.

Put down the remaining two and our problem will be solved. We just have to lure them out...

Let’s start by collecting more Lizardman blood.

Burn the totem at the entrance, just like before. Remember how I said there are 3 leaders? We need more blood to lure the third one.

Collect blood from the Shamans while you make your way to the altar.

Now we’ll draw out the High Shaman.

He’s the Maille Lizardmen’s ultimate leader, so he’s very powerful - not to mention adept at necromancy. Do your best.

Burn the other leaders’ and the shamans’ blood on the brazier when you’re ready.

Heh heh... my mission is complete.

The Orcs should already be on their way to Gludio by now.

Ha ha ha...
There’s no time! We must defend Gludio! Russel, come to Gludio with me. <YellowBold>[player]</>! Go with Aymel and attack the Turek Orc Campsite!

If not for Theodore, I wouldn’t have come here. Consider yourself lucky!

Let’s get started - I’m going to tell you about the Adena Dungeon.

You can never have too much money, so make sure to visit the Adena Dungeon every day!

Now, go to the west gate of the town. A friend of yours is waiting there!

Anyway, it’s always good to see you - I’ll catch you around.
Agh... The Advance Party already passed through here... I’ve got to stop following the troops...

I... I’m done for.

Please hold back the Orcs. Please defend Gludio. Urgh...

Don’t worry. We’ll take it from here...

Whew... So many people dying...

Let’s deal with the scouts first. Spread out and rendezvous in the lower intersection - Deal?

Hey! Those War Hounds will make it hard to sneak in.

Let’s take the War Hounds out first. I’ll go on ahead - meet me at the base entrance.

Shh! There are sentinels in the watchtower out front. Looks like we have to go around... Let’s split up and flank them! Meet me inside!

Kill anyone who gets in your way!
Over there! See the soldiers imprisoned by the Orcs? They’ll be useful in our mission.

The Orcs stripped us down to our nethers. We can’t fight like this!

Please find my men’s armor. It can’t be far!

We’ll hit the left flank. You strike the right.

We must either annihilate the Orcs or at the very least slay their Chieftain.

You hold them off - I’ll scout out their facilities and look for the Chieftain.

Meet me at the south rock as soon as you can.

See there? That’s the Orcs’ forge. They must be producing combat supplies.

Smash the forge, and you smash their dreams of war. Kill the Orc Blacksmiths!
He’s near the altar below. The coward is hiding behind his guards. Let’s smash them!

Huh? It can’t be this easy... Something’s wrong.

Hey, over there!

Now, now... You know what? I am royally pissed off.

All of my efforts and careful planning are up in smoke thanks to you!

You worms need to know your place. Why continue your futile efforts?

Now, you’ll pay!

Uh... Wh-what’s happening?

I can’t see anything... or hear anything... or feel anything either!

I’m scared!

What a sinister curse! Aymel’s senses are completely blocked.

It’s not fatal, but if we don’t do something, she’ll go out of her mind with fear!

I’ll take Aymel to my master and leave a Teleportation Stone behind. Rest here with Russel for a while, and then join the Blood Ranger at Windawood Manor. It seems something terrible is happening there.

I’m worried about Aymel, but Hardin should be able to help her.

Oh! Thanks to your valor, the Silverlight Mercenaries’ fame has grown even greater. I heard that the Lord has prepared a reward for us.

The Lord seems oblivious to the corruption, but observant enough to not ignore such a great feat.

You should visit the Deputy Archon on behalf of the mercenaries. I should check on Aymel!

Oh, before I forget - someone named Lonna was looking for you. Meet with Lonna after you visit the Archon. There seems to be something you need to know!

Looks like the work in this area is wrapping up! You won’t die easily now that you know about the Exp. Dungeon!

Oops! I should get going! I have more mercenaries to teach. Good luck!

Greetings! Don’t worry about Aymel - she’s a tough one! She’ll be right as rain soon!

Your next mission will take you to Windawood Manor, right?

The foes you meet at Windawood are bound to be stronger than any you’ve faced so far!

I can’t send my favorite recruit to suffer at Windawood unprepared!

Here, check out the Exp. Dungeon - you’ll be able to level up fast there!

I-I am Shayne. A su-supplier. The Undead suddenly emerged in the old ruins of the Windawood Manor, cutting off the supply line with Gludio Castle.

I am assigned to investigate the situation, but I can’t enter ruins full of Undead.

Y-you have great timing. C-could you deal with those werewolves over there?

Th-there, do you see those vampire bats eating that corpse? It’s shameful of me to ask this, but please drive out the bats for me.

I can’t watch a soldier’s corpse being desecrated.

A-ah! Blood in here?! It looks like a recent injury. It must be from some other soldiers.

The Undead around here can’t have such fresh blood. Will you follow the blood and help the Soldiers?

I-I will wait here for support. Urgh, just looking at the blood makes me dizzy.

Ugh! You saved my life, so I won’t blame you if you say no... but perhaps you could help me.

While I am resting here, take out those Skeleton Warriors.

Looks like you’re going to join Gludio’s Southern Garrison... so, you should be able to do this.

Oh! There are Skeleton Bowmen over there. You should finish them off too.

What, no?

Ugh! Why is my body so hot? Can it be, that the water in the well was poisoned? Help! Somebody!

Ah... Sorry for pulling off that ruse with the well water. Were you surprised?

You’ve come this far, can’t you help me one more time? The hounds over there need to be defeated...

Th-thank you. Truly. I don’t know which god you believe in, but may they bless you.

Wait, you’re a Silverlight Mercenary?

Some of the troopers have gone missing during the Windawood Ruins investigation. I was searching for them...

Will you let me know when you find any fallen soldiers or deserted equipment?
Rescue the soldiers before skeletons arrive! Hurry! There’s no time!
Skeletons are already here! Oh no! Argh! All is lost...

So, you’re the one the Silverlight Mercenaries sent.

Some of my comrades were here when I was taken. I hope they’re still alive... Please find out.

If my comrades’ corpses become the Undead, we may have to fight against them...

I don’t think I could do that. We must cremate them.
Thank you for helping me. Now, we must regroup with the main force. Please follow me.

You’re [player] from the Silverlight Mercenaries? I heard of your feats in Gludio. Looks like you helped the other soldiers a lot.

Let me keep it simple. The Southern Garrison in my command has been working to drive out the Turek Orcs in Windawood Manor.

We were increasing our numbers while holding the line, and we were almost ready to take the offensive until the Undead broke out.

That cut off the supply line from Gludio, and now we’re pinned down. Securing the supply line is paramount.

The Undead couldn’t have appeared from nowhere, there must be a source around here. Until we find out what it is, we need to slay any we find.

Well done. But it’s only the beginning. Hmm... Perhaps things around here are connected to the Dark Brotherhood as well.

A brilliant warrior like you makes me feel safe. We’re going to save more soldiers.

Now drive out the Cursed Hunters.
You killed a lot of the Undead! Thank you! But, they keep coming. Can you really defeat them?

That wasn’t easy. If those things come in large enough numbers, it will be too difficult. Please, defend against the Undead until the seekers bring additional intel.

Understand that I can’t mobilize my troops without proper information on the area.

Oh, and your companion is looking for you over there.

I was gathering intel here alone. Unfortunately, there’s nothing I could find. Ha!

Well, if I keep at it, something should come up.

I found just the right monsters to warm up with. Do you see the Mysterious Subjects wandering there?

They are rare, so soldiers have a hard time dealing with them. We should take them out first.

Truly hideous. Soldiers will be frightened on sight.

Good! Now let’s deal with those Soul Slashers over there. You ready?

Now, now... you’re the ones killing my precious subjects!

I shall take your life as payment!

Thanks for revealing yourselves!

This day shall be your last!

The Southern Commander’s message has arrived.

The seekers found a strange black cauldron north of here. Haven’t we heard this before?

Yes, the cauldron on Talking Island! The Dark Brotherhood is involved in this as well!

It seems the Southern Commander is already on his way. Let’s join him and destroy the black cauldron!

So [player] and Russel saw a cauldron like this before?

A black magic cauldron... if Dark Mystics are involved, that would explain the Undead. There were other cauldrons spotted in the area.

They must also be destroyed. [player], please help us.

The Ranger Captain who found this cauldron is missing.

He’s a formidable ally... our actions must have alerted the enemy.

[player] find the Ranger Captain. And when you spot a cauldron, destroy it.

Whoever you are, thanks! Without you, I would be stew in that cauldron! Curse the Undead!

There was a battle between the Rangers and the Undead nearby. We were on the brink of victory when some guys with black robes and Soul Slashers appeared.

After that, all of my men were killed and I ended up in this bone cauldron.

They say that people killed by Reaper Undead, like Soul Slashers, can’t rest because their souls are bound by the reaper.

Will you defeat the Soul Slashers and let my men rest in peace?
One more thing! Please help me recover the belongings of my men.

The location of the cauldron was identified right before fighting the Undead. It’s the last we’ve found after scouring all of Windawood Ruins, so, it should be the last cauldron.

Report this to the commander and destroy the final cauldron.
Seems the Undead are rampaging towards the final cauldron. <YellowBold>[player]</>! Eliminate the Vindictive Prima to clear the way!

I will thank you after you destroy the cauldron. When we take out that cauldron, it will drive out the Undead.

The Undead will surely come to defend it! The last one will have the most resistance! Be ready!

Heh heh heh!

Joyful, are you? Do you think it’s over?

As long as the Lord gives us mana! Skeletons shall rise again!

Rise, army of the dead!
What? A giant skeleton?! Prepare for battle!

That was some battle. Good to see you’re all alive! Now we can start the war against the Turek Orc properly!

Just a bit longer, people. The day to reclaim Windawood Manor is almost upon us!

The Southern Commander was valiant.

But, Windawood Manor is a wasteland...

I wonder if it’s really worth saving.

Huh? The Silverlight Mercenary didn’t tell you who I am?

I am Vaughn Windawood, head of House Windawood. Most of the Soldiers here are part of the private forces of House Windawood.

Our mission is to restore Windawood’s manor and valor. We’ve wandered for a long time, but this is the only place we could return to.

Thankfully, the Silverlight Mercenaries are helping us.
Ah! We didn’t know. P-please, forgive us if we were rude. I’m not very bright! Ha ha!

Ha ha! Well, that’s possible. Living on the battlefield makes me disregard manners.

Hmm... now that it’s done, I’d like to offer you another mission.

I sent an investigator to the battlefield because of an incident that occurred at the Windawood Manor.

Escort her to the guard post on the battlefield. She’s a very capable magical engineer but still young and inexperienced.

Her name is Angie. You should be able to spot her right away.

The name’s Angie! A magical engineer contracted to help restore the Windawood Manor.

You’re [player] from the Silverlight Mercenaries? I’m a Silverlight Mercenary, too.

I called the Silverlight Mercenaries for help. I think the Dark Brotherhood is connected to the incidents here.

Oh! Vaughn Windawood doesn’t know that I am a Silverlight Mercenary. Let’s keep it that way.

Now! Escort me! That’s why you’re here, right?

Angie? A remarkable girl, considering her age. She’s truly a great help to Sir Windawood. Now, shall we talk about business?

Maybe you’ve heard from Sir Windawood, but the Southern Garrison is practically his private army.

Lord of Gludio agreed to allow independent operations, but there will be no support.

So, the army is on its own in terms of logistics. Fortunately, we can mine the nearby crystals to make Soulshot.

Curious? Better to try it yourself! Go mine some crystals.

Yeah, that’s the crystal used to make Soulshot. Some call them elemental stones, but we just call them crystals.

The commander didn’t receive the report yet and the Ol Mahum are making trouble.

I didn’t intervene, as it wasn’t serious yet, but while you were gathering crystals, the Ol Mahum bastards stole the stored crystals.

I can’t spare men while the main force is out, so please deal with them and bring back the crystals.

Thank you! Without you, who knows how long it would have taken to recover from the pillaging! Could you check the other crystal storages northeast of here?

The other crystal storage is under the command of a lieutenant called Reinheim. Please take out any Ol Mahum you see along the way.

I shall slay the wretched Ol Mahum around here as well.

Truth is, the crystals here have already been taken by Ol Mahum. If the commander hears of this, heads will roll. Please save me.

I picked some quick soldiers to pursue the crystal thieves. All you need to do is take out any Ol Mahum while they give chase.

Good. While you were watching the rear, I found out where the Ol Mahum ran away to.

A bit northeast of here, there’s a box inside a ruined elven structure.

We have to guard the storage from the Ol Mahum, so you should recover the crystals.

Did you retrieve the crystals? Good. Actually, there was another Silverlight Mercenary who came before you. His name was Russel, I think.

He went to find out why the Ol Mahum were on a rampage, but there’s been no contact so far. I am a bit worried, why don’t you go find him?

This is just an observation, but the Ol Mahum here are strange.

They’re acting as if they’ve lost their minds. Perhaps someone’s controlling them.

They have no reason to expand into the Orc’s territory.

If we fight the Ol Mahum Vanguard over there, we may find something. What do you say?

Have you seen a dwarf girl named Angie? Ah, so you’ve already met! Good. I reckon that it would be better for a specialist to deliver the message rather than myself.

Go find Angie, tell her everything that has happened here. She will be able to analyze the situation better than anyone else.

Hmm... I think the Ol Mahum are under some kind of a mind control.

Magic with as large an effect as this is great indeed.

I came here by following the power influencing the Ol Mahum and ended up finding these strange, purple crystals!

Now, It’s your turn. Gather those crystals! What are you waiting for? You’re not thinking a poor fellow like me should do it, are you?

Hmm... This is indeed contaminated by dark powers! Whew, if I touched it, we’d be in trouble.

See this? This corrupted crystal is connected to the interior of the elven sanctuary. We should investigate further.

Let’s go! You’re not thinking about sending a lady like me alone out there, are you?

This is strange. These crystals are not contaminated yet.

I should take a look. [player], gather some crystals for me.

What are you doing? Are you going to wait until I nag again? You asked for it...

Over there!

Someone’s collapsed!

Let’s go!

No wait! Lookout!
Look out! Demons gathering! Something’s not right!

The Dark Brotherhood? What’s that? I don’t even remember my name... ugh!

Oh! My name’s Valter! That must be it.

And... something is pulling me.

What happened to these trees? It looks as if they are holding rotted blood.

Please, peel their bark so that I can examine them.

The tree bark is dying because of the powerful dark energy. What kind of entity would wield such dark powers?

H-how do I know all these things? Argh! Something’s calling me from over there.

It can’t be resisted! Please clear the path by dealing with the spiders. We must go that way!

What happened here? And who is that man?

[player], please investigate the area. Look for any clues.

Hey, wait!

[player], what’s wrong? Your eyes are strange! Could it be that the man is using mind control?

No! [player], stay with me! Are you so weak you’d be taken by Black Magic? Damn!

Those items...?

Argh! My head’s cracking! I think I remember something...

Here...!

A familiar view!!! Yes!!! It’s here!!! Ha ha ha!!!

Ha ha ha! Valter, was it? Bringing me here. How foolish!

Thank you! Now I can be resurrected!

No one shall stand in my way! Heh heh...

I shall awaken myself now! If you want to see, break through my minions and reach the center of the ruins! If you can, that is! Heh heh.

Finally! Outside at last! Ha ha ha!

Don’t get in the way!

Whew, finally...! How fortunate...

Ugh, it hurts... I think a succubus hit me...

So-sorry... Even if under mind control... It’s still my fault... I’m truly sorry.

Why don’t we move to a safe place using the other teleportation stone?
The commander is looking for <YellowBold>[player]</>. The two of you shouldn’t worry. Go meet the Guard Captain first.

[player]! Just in time! Where have you been?

Defending crystals from Ol Mahum? Your feats keep impressing me, just as in Windawood Ruins.

Good! Now everything is ready. After reporting to the commander, the Turek Orc assault will begin.

Welcome, [player]! Now I shall brief you the operation. Your mission is to join the assault and infiltrate the Orc Camp, taking out their main facilities and forces.

The main force of the Southern Garrison will annihilate the remaining Turek Orcs during the chaos.

1st Special Ops Squad leader Kail will be preparing. Meet him for the details. He’s a man of few words, so don’t take it personally.
Go go go! Be wary of the tight entrance and traps!

Entry complete.

Take out that shooter for the following units!
Enemy war machine found! Destroy it at once!

Orc War Hound! And War Hound Mother Riley must be removed!

Special Ops Captain Duvalte is also standing by over there, so get rid of them all.

Thank you for helping me!

Duvalte? Duvalte will be inside!

See those Orc Troopers over there? Yeah, those bluish thugs!

When in battle, they have no regard for their lives. That’s when they inflict the most damage.

Let’s reduce their numbers while they’re off guard.

While you were hitting the Orc Troopers, I found their weapon stash.

No matter how strong Orcs are, they are nothing without proper weapons.

Let’s burn them all.

Hell! They noticed! They’re coming! No choice but a direct assault now!

Hey! [player]! Don’t die on me! Ha ha!

Ugh, damn Orcs, they keep coming no matter how many we kill.

Are they Undead? Or do they hatch from eggs?

Damn! It’s pointless to keep talking! Let’s do this, [player]!

Oh! When you see anything that looks like a Captain, slay it right away! That will teach them.

Ha ha ha! Good. Now that their leader’s taken care of, the remaining units should be easy to deal with.

Good, let’s take out the other leaders as well. Only a few lieutenants should be there with the Warchief.

They are likely to be in the core of the horde, so let’s get inside.

Damn, Orc Shooters. [player]! Take them out while I find the leaders.

Look, over there! See that one with two minions? It’s their defense captain leading the archers. Let’s take them out.

Why are you still here? Of course, you should be the one to do it.

Wait! There’s a problem. Rangers were discovered by Orcs while on their way to destroy the signal fire. Idiots! I ‘ll court martial them after all this.

I must lead the forces here, so you go help them. Meet Aurora who is in command of the Ranger team.

Now go and don’t die out there!

You’re from the Silverlight Mercenaries? Let’s get to it then, it’s a war zone here.

The Turek Orc’s turf is large, and their forces are spread thin. They seem to communicate using signal fires.

Destroy the signal fire, and their communication will collapse.

Before taking out the signal fire, let’s deal with the guards nearby.

While you were dealing with the guards, I contacted the main force! Destroy the signal fires and they will come to us!

We must take out that signal fire!

The Blood Rangers have taken the outpost thanks to the destruction of the signal fires! The time to liberate Windawood is now!

Our last mission is to defeat the Decanus here!

Kill them and the Turek Orcs will lose their chain of command. Help me, [player]!

The backup forces are cutting down the Orcs!

[player] should defeat the Orc Warchief with Miles.

Look around, there will be Orc Captains giving orders.

I heard that you already killed two. The remaining ones must be the Patrol and Protector Captains.

Take them out and their chain of command will collapse.

Th-there! The Townsfolk are imprisoned there. I was wondering where the missing townsfolk from Gludio went. Seems we found them.

We can’t leave them like that. Let’s take out the Elite Soldiers around the cage first!
Now please rescue the prisoners! Hurry!

Looks like the prisoners are safe.

Now, it’s time to put an end to their evil deeds. Our forces are fighting at the altar. Join Aurora in front of the altar and slay the Orcs!

Thanks to [player], the operation is almost complete. Now is the time to liberate Windawood!

Orcs are still on the offensive though, do not relent!
We must quickly destroy that Black Soulstone! Hurry!

Hmm... the awakening of the darkness is also happening in the Wasteland.

The Wasteland... No, it’d be better to tell you about it next time.

Theodore should already be in the Wasteland, go meet him there.

Going to the Wasteland? Right down that road. Visit me sometime.

Drinks are on me!
You don’t know the details, right? I will brief you on the way.

The Silverlight Mercenaries think the turmoil caused by the Dark Brotherhood is related to the Dark Wizard Beleth.

The situation in the Wasteland, where Beleth was sealed, is also under surveillance.

The Ivory Tower sent some mystics to investigate the Wasteland as well. Your mission is to help them.

The Silverlight Mercenaries have an alliance with the Ivory Tower, so cooperation with them will be a pleasant experience. Maybe you could find their tracks around here.

Seems the Ivory Tower’s Mystics are already inside the Wasteland.

Before beginning the mission, why don’t you prove yourself?

Yes, you’ve accomplished great things before, but the Wasteland is a different place. The evils in the Wasteland are of an entirely different sort.

Hmm... Maybe those Ol Mahum in front would suffice.

Good. Now find the mystics sent by the Ivory Tower. I will go alone, to assess the situation in the Wasteland.

Take care, and don’t you dare taint the name of the Silverlight Mercenaries.

Argh! Wh-what are you!? You scared me!

Of course, you’re scary! What kind of nut would wander this Wasteland!

Oh, here’s another one! Augh! Don’t sneak up on me or you’ll be roasted by my fireball!

Wait... You’re part of the Silverlight Mercenaries? I heard of you guys. They sent you, what the hell are they thinking? Just don’t get in the way.

First, look for something with dark energy. I can feel it nearby.

Huh? What? What did you find?

... A bag? What... what the hell? What kind of thing would emit such foul energy?

Huh? What is this? The bag is opening!

Hey! Hand over that bag. What?! I’ve been a fool! We can’t have it like this!

There’s nothing we can do but you should take it and keep your distance from me.

Let’s go to a safe spot first. I’m almost out of my mana.
We can camp here, so secure the perimeter! I don’t want to spend the night with those Ol Mahum.

What’s this cloak doing here with the Ol Mahum? This... it’s the cloak of an Ivory Tower Wizard! I wonder who… this is bad.

Let’s move! We can’t stay here.
This should be safe. I need to rest and recover my mana. The Wasteland is cold at night, can you gather some firewood?

The werewolf dropped an Ivory Tower seal... This belongs to my friend Edin. He studied with me... Ugh, I hate this place!

I’m not going to become like him, I’m not going to involve myself with this any further! I will use the teleportation stone right now! Go find the mystic named Emon. Should be wandering nearby.

Go now! That bag must be attracting evil! Stay far away from me!

I was supposed to get the teleportation stone from Edina, but she left! So, I’ve been wandering the Wasteland for three days!

It’s been 2 days since I’ve eaten anything. I’ve never had to go without food for this long... Do you have anything to eat?

If not, can you get basilisk eggs? I’ve wanted to try them for some time...

An Ivory Tower Mystic begging for food... how pitiful...

I forgot to tell you something important. Basilisks are very aggressive and vicious during breeding season.

They will crush anything around the eggs with their powerful jaws. Be careful.

Wow, I’m full. Now I can concentrate on the mission.

I didn’t wander around for three days for nothing. I was in bad shape, but now I have the energy to move again.

Now, I can show you how an Ivory Tower Wizard really works! We must leave here quickly. Looks like the basilisk is very angry at you for stealing its eggs.

I will tell you the truth since you’re a Silverlight Mercenary. I came here to investigate if the changes here were connected to Beleth.

Also, my comrade that was sent here first is missing. I was supposed to be here with Edina, but now I am alone.

The missing comrade and Edina ran away... Looks like surviving for three days was a miracle.

This is where Beleth was sealed away several centuries ago. Where we’re standing should have a statue of Gran Kain...

I don’t know why, but there’s nothing remotely resembling the statue. We must investigate the ruins nearby. Please search with me.

Looks like the stones scattered on the floor are from the Gran Kain Statue. The Gran Kain statue of sealing has been destroyed...

Beleth may be resurrected after all. Did the people involved with its resurrection kill my companions to silence them?

Anyways, you seem to have a very interesting item. A bag full of dark energy...

Planning to keep it? I would recommend throwing it away... but it is also as evidence of what happened here.

Hmm... Let me examine it. It... has a curse for a specific target. It should be properly dealt with. Luckily, this is my specialty.

I require some ingredients. Could you bring me basilisk blood?

Basilisk blood also has dark energy inside. You just apply it like this. Hmm... Smells like rotting fish.

Now I need one more thing. The essence of the mutant ant. I don’t think I have to explain it, do I?

Now I’ve completed the temporary treatment. Holding the bag will not activate the curse.

We should head to the campsite where a merchant named Staris is staying. Staris knows the area very well. He can deliver the message to the Ivory Tower in no time.

Ah... please stay away from me. The odor is too much to bear. I may cough up the red bear steak I had 3 years ago.
A little bit further and Staris’s Campsite will be in sight. Ugh, will you please keep some distance?
Ah! Someone’s in danger. I usually don’t meddle in the business of strangers, but this sparks my curiosity.
Ugh, this is bad. It must be the basilisk poison. My body is paralyzed...

Huh? Staris? Apart from the poisoned mouth, it looks like the Staris I know! What the...

If you want to help him, will you get some mutant ant saliva?

It can neutralize the paralyzing basilisk poison . It’s the best we can do for now.

Ugh, this smell...

Well, thanks. There’s a campsite nearby, let’s move.

The young loud mouth Elf, Emon, should be with us shortly as well.

Thank you. If not for you, I would have been dead in the desert.

I want to give you a small gift... but my gift is mixed with all those adventurer’s belongings. It’s inside that box, take it.
Okay, that’s that, but it seems you have some other business with me. What is it?

There’s an urgent message for the Ivory Tower. Do you have a teleportation stone?

If not, can you deliver the message personally?

Come on! Can’t you communicate using spells? You live in the Ivory Tower, for Einhasad’s sake! And you call yourselves mystics?

The Silverlight Mercenaries use teleportation stones every day, but the Ivory Tower can't?

Ugh... You know the price of a teleportation stone? And distance is the main factor when communicating with magic. I told you before!

From here to the Ivory Tower, only the grand mystic can do it.

Okay! Okay, old elf. It’s my specialty, trust me!

But... I have something to request as well. Your friend from the Ivory Tower is missing. I can’t go to the Ivory Tower like this...

Will you find your friend? Last I heard, they were heading north.

Losing contact with our comrade here is the reason Edina and I were sent to the Wasteland.

With our comrade’s powers, most threats would be easy to deal with... Something powerful must be involved.

We must investigate this. Will you search the corpse?

Did you see where the demons came from? The north? In that case, they must have come from that way...

Hmm... I should investigate this area a bit more. [player] should head for the north. I heard that one of Staris’s caravans is over there. Meet me there.

You’re the Caravan Master Staris’s friend! That bag belonged to one of the seekers in this region. A standard issue item for the caravan.

I was worried about him since we lost contact, and to think, he ended up like this?

He was hunting Sahara. Seemed like he was looking for something... Why don’t you follow his tracks?
He also caught a Giant Leech to study. I think I heard him going on and on about dark energy...

Oh! That adventurer was lingering around the mystic’s grave.

It looked like they were meeting someone... I was about to report it to Staris, as it was very suspicious.

There’s really nothing but tombstones there. The mystic’s grave is west of here.

They seemed to be investigating this area. And what’s the tablet you’re holding?

That’s what my comrade tried to obtain by hunting the evil? Can I see it?

This tablet emits dark energy. Seems the evils consumed this.

We should see if other evils have this too. Let’s start with the Giant Leech!
Now let’s defeat the Eroded Sahara.

There are Tablet Fragments everywhere. Can you gather them? It’s a guess but...

This tablet must have been used for sealing Beleth. Combining the pieces will tell us the truth.

Let’s see... Let’s combine the Fragmented Tablet.

Hmm... So this goes here... And... Should this mark be here?

What? Am I right?

You’re going to die soon anyway, heh heh.
You will soon join your companions!

Ugh, what?! M-mana is draining!
Ugh... Help...! Help!

Who are they? If they struck my comrades like this, they wouldn’t have had a chance.

What my comrade found out is also connected with Beleth. Did they attack because of the intel related to the resurrection of Beleth?

Let me rest a bit.

[player] should notify Staris. We must let the Ivory Tower know at once.

Hey, a little help here? I was on my way to the campsite, but that black robed woman summoned evil and wrecked my wagon.

The wheels especially. Could you pick up the wheel parts that the evil took?

Huh? On your way to Staris? You’re the Caravan Master’s guest?

You should be on your way, right? But... could you get back the shaft of the wagon from the Mutant Armored Ant Fighters?

With it, I can leave here on my own!

Thanks to you, we should be able to get to the Campsite. Oh, you will need to be careful about the girl wearing dark clothing. She sure makes things tough on us!

She headed south so you should see her as you head towards the south barracks! Be careful and thanks for your help!

Oh, hold on! You match the description of the person Feldheim was looking for a few days back. Do you know Feldheim?

I knew it! He was in a rush to find you! I believe he was heading to a Summoning Stone Dungeon in Mount Eborga.

How about you pay him a visit? In the Summoning Stone Dungeon, you will probably be able to get some Summoning Stones that can be used to strengthen your mount.
You’re just in time. Why don’t we have a chat on the way to the Southern Barracks? I am Tiana, a merchant.

Whew, it’s farther than I thought. If the wagon wasn’t broken... Well, this is destiny, right? I met you.

You look capable, may I offer you a job? Of course, it will be paid.

So you’re accepting it? I need... condensed mana... there’s a good source. Bring some Mana Leech blood.
We’ve come this far, I wish to make some other requests. There are Skeleton Soldiers nearby, please gather the mana filled skeleton powder.

I will make a powerful explosion spell using the skeleton powder, but I need some liquid to mix it up... Oh, that will do?

Please get the blood from those mutant ants.
Well done. But do you realize that some very angry ants are still on your back?

Now, it’s time to part ways. I have something important to do.

May we meet again in good fate. Goodbye! Shall I make those bombs for my mortal enemy?

The evils of the Wasteland are strange these days. They are more aggressive and vicious than before.

Maybe they’re on alert, or maybe they are under someone’s control.

We should investigate the area.
We need to look around. Help me.

God forbid, but we should prepare for the worst.

The resurrection of Beleth seems to be real now.

I will report this to the master. [player] should keep helping Staris.

Must be Tiana! If she’s targeting our caravan, she must be trying to interrupt the negotiation. If it were me, I’d do the same.

If this negotiation happens, a trade route directly to the Ivory Tower will be opened. We’re passing the canyon... Watch your head.
Hah! Staris! How tenacious! Still alive!

You! Wretched hag! Did you think you would be safe after wrecking my caravan?

Killing people, and then blowing up the Southern Barracks!
The only one I want to kill is you! Don’t mistake my intentions, you bastard!

They said that the culprit was wearing a black robe! Deny it in front of Gran Kain! This is your day!

[player]! There’s the culprit! Tiana is here!

Huh? You? What?

You... You’re one of them!

Staris! You greedy pig! Your greed destroyed my house! Die!
Argh! This is unfair! I will bring my own next time! We shall meet again, Staris!

Welcome, Staris! I’ve been waiting for you! Mew! The Ol Mahum Chief is demanding that you show your negotiation terms.

I wrote down its demands, mew! First... defeat the Sahara of the Desert. Send your troops right now! Mew!

The second requirement! Mew! Defeat the Gray Stone Golem!

At this rate, we’re going to end up catching all monsters in this area, mew.
Staris went ahead saying that the Ol Mahum are having some sort of internal conflict! Mew! <YellowBold>[player]</> should help him.

See there? Ol Mahum fighting amongst themselves! Looks like the Ol Mahum have been divided into two factions.

The Chief’s faction which wants to trade with us, and those Ol Mahum Looters who are rebelling against it.

We’re on the Chief’s side, of course! Or all of my work could be gone!

Unlike most Ol Mahum, the Ol Mahum here are sustained by mining rather than pillaging. Their largest customer is us, the Staris caravan.

The Ol Mahum here value minerals more than their lives.

We should retake the minerals from the looters out there.
I must meet the Ol Mahum Chief. Follow me!

We can’t pass like this. You should reduce the number of Ol Mahum Pillage Warriors.

While you draw their attention, I will infiltrate the Chief’s house.

Don’t worry, I will not be seen!

Damn! Looks like one of my men tried to sneak inside the Ol Mahum Stronghold.

Now the situation is beyond control. Staying here will not solve anything.

If you find him, tell him to return to the campsite.

Okay! I shall return to the campsite!

The Ol Mahum Chief’s tent is northwest from here! Staris should be there already! Mew!

Whew... It’s you. Is he safe?

This is the tent of the Red Fur Ol Mahum Chief. I finished talking with the Chief.

Since the Ol Mahum have been fighting each other, it’s difficult to see who’s side they’re on. See there, they don’t have red fur. Hard to tell the difference... Huh?

Hey, they are drawing weapons! Those Ol Mahum are acting strange! Look over there!

I heard the situation. The ones against trading with us revolted.

What makes it strange is that the rebel acted as if it was under someone else’s orders.

Whatever it is, the Staris Caravan agreed to cooperate in suppressing the rebellion. First, they are asking us to clear this area. Recover the Ol Mahum corpses.

Seems that looters are occupying the mine right now.

Seems the Chief of the Ol Mahum here had to retake the mines to show his power.

I told you, right? The Ol Mahum here have a special interest in minerals.

Now, let’s go to the entrance.
To retake the mine, we should first deal with the looters all over the area.

Good! Now it’s time to finish off the Ol Mahum rebellion.

Move this way and the Looter Stronghold will be there. Their captain will be there. We must kill it.

There will be a familiar face near the Looter Camp entrance. We should leave the combat for specialists, don’t you think?

Now! Hurry. Oh, and give this memo to the mercenary. It’s an order of sorts.

What was next? Ah, dealing with the Rangers! Seems Ol Mahum Looter Escorts are guarding the leader.

It will be wise to clear them out before dealing with the captain.

Now! The Weapon Box is next! The most effective way to weaken their strength!

This Staris guy, he doesn’t look like a simple merchant. Okay, let’s do this quickly!

What was next? Ah, dealing with the Rangers!

Seems Ol Mahum Looter Rangers are guarding the leader.

It will be wise to clear them out first.
Only the leader remains! Let’s do this!
Now, let’s report this to Staris!
Help me! Save me! Please help me!
That sounded like Staris. I will go first, follow me.
I heard something out there, but Ol Mahum Looter Rangers are stopping us! Let’s get rid of them!
I thought I heard something around here...
And you! <YellowBold>[player]</>, right? Are you really going to do this? Do you know what they’ve done to me?
Huh? So you know each other? Looks like that black robed woman has locked up Staris!
Yes! That black-robed woman is the culprit! This woman attacked our caravan and killed the Ivory Tower Mystics!

Trickster! Full of lies! You’re really low! I brought my own people this time! It won’t be easy!

Ol Mahum! Here’s the Adena I promised! Slay any who stand in our way! I will give you twice of what I promised!

Wow! She knows how to handle a mercenary!

Look at those Ol Mahum eyes! Brace yourself!

Hah... Have I...failed...

[player]! I will remember you! You’re worse than Staris!
Hell! Staris is locked up! Let’s rescue him.

Hell, running away like that! Why is everyone just looking around!

That woman is the daughter of a Caravan Master I competed with. I reckon that after the Caravan went bankrupt, her life would have been difficult. I understand that she may hold a grudge... but!

This is an outright crime! How can the Silverlight Mercenaries let this woman go! Hey! Say something!

Whew... This is going nowhere. Let’s return to the campsite.

And I want to ask for some understanding. I should head to the Ivory Tower myself, but the Southern Barracks is gone, and I must organize the caravan.

I will send one of my men instead. Please deliver this letter.

I owe you much. Next time, drinks on me! Send my regards to Hardin!
But... some people with dark robes keep looking this way. I don’t have a good feeling about this, mew. Let’s get out of here! Mew!

Hey, will the merchant cough up the letter?

I expected Staris to come alone, but the silver goon is also here. As if it will make any difference.
What... what are you doing! Mew! B-black robe? Y-you’re one of Tiana’s minions, mew?

Ha ha ha! Right.

We’re working for that poor woman! We came here to make you fools suffer!

Doesn’t matter if you refuse to hand over the letter, we were going to burn it anyway. Now you shall be burned with it.
Meeeeeew! <YellowBold>[player]</>! Save me! Mew! What are we going to do?
There! Another person in black! Those eyes! A total villain! Mew!

...Sorry for being such a menace!

Took me some time! [player]! Don’t lower your guard! It’s only the beginning!

Ugh...

Damn Silverlight Mercenaries! Don’t feast on this brief victory! You shall die soon! Wait and see, Theodore!
I will head for the Ivory Tower, mew! I will deliver this letter and get myself out of this madness! Mew!
Merchant of Staris, did you say you have a letter for the Ivory Tower? Please send my letter too.

Okay, mew! Sorry for calling you a villain. Never thought the famous Theodore would be so handsome, mew!

Mew mew! Then, I shall be on my way, mew!

The Ivory Tower must be notified that the Dark Brotherhood killed Ivory Tower Mystics...

And the resurrection of Beleth...

[player]. Did the Staris caravan mission go well?

While you were solving the problem of the Staris Caravan, I completed my investigation over the incident at the Wasteland.

My research shows that Beleth has been resurrected. No activity so far, but I am certain of it.

My master seems calm... but the resurrection and the Dark Brotherhood will be our top priority.

Expect orders related to these issues. First, we shall head to the Dion Manor? There is word that the Orcs are moving now.

Welcome. You must be the one Theodore sent. Our mission is to eliminate the Breka Orcs, but the Orc Scouts have us pinned down.

Their keen observation over our movements makes any planning difficult. Reports indicate that they came here to search for something.

Whatever it is... Oh, there’s another Orc Scout out there! Show me your skills!

There was no time to tell you, but the number of Orcs here is tremendous. Increasing every day, at this point, it even rivals the Orc Dwellings.

If the Orcs go for a frontal assault as they are, we won’t be able to stop them.

Lead the way and slay the Breka Orc Fighters!

A few days ago, the supply unit transporting the weapons was ambushed by the Orcs. The recruits have nothing to fight with but sticks.

Go retrieve the Weapon Boxes.
Will you deliver the Weapon Box to Lieutenant Vacen? Vacen will assume command from now on.

Welcome. Recruits would have fought with clubs if it wasn’t for you!

But what we need right now is veterans, like you. The Orcs will be here soon. Get ready!

If we keep on the defensive, there will be no chance of winning. We will strike their Supply Items instead of the Orcs themselves.

To do that, we should deal with the guards first.

As you know, Orcs handle weapons carelessly. No matter how good their weapons are, they get trashed within a day.

It would be pretty detrimental to them if we burn their extra weapons! Let’s see them try to fight with weapons without handles.

Burn their Weapon Boxes to burn their morale!

Seems the Orcs have noticed us, so let’s hurry. We should burn the Supply Items!

Oh! Deliver the retreat order to the remaining men after starting the fire!
O-One of our men is missing! He’s the only surviving one among 5 brothers! Please save him, his name is Mike!

Retreat? No! All of my brothers were killed by the Orc Captain, I am the sole survivor!

Without slaying him, I can’t leave! If you want me back alive, help me!
Guess who escorts the escort? The Orc Captain. Slay that Decanus over there, and we can kill the Orc Captain!
I know the captain’s location. Let’s move!
I see the Orc Captain there. The Orcs would definitely go wild if we defeat him, right?

I picked up this one while looking for anything important. Is this an order?

Orcs can read?! Why don’t we look around more?
Let’s leave this place. Was it... that... way?

The Orc offensive has been weakened thanks to you. We should gather medicine for the wounded soldiers.

I’m going to send anyone who can move. You should help. We need the wasp wings first.
Will you bring some Enraged Wasps? Their organs have a liquid which can neutralize poison. It will be used to make an antidote.

One more thing. We need transparent tree sap. Enraged Wasps’ liquid is too strong to use directly.

Normal water can’t dilute it, so find some weathered trees nearby.

Someone is looking for you. You should go that way.

Oh! I heard from Mike. Did you cut off the Orc Captain’s head? With that head in your possession, they might follow you around. Be careful.

Th-this is... a painting of a girl? You found this... from the Orc Captain? So the “key” really left the tower...

Hmm? Sounds like Orcs! Look out!!

I will take this letter. Seems the Dark Brotherhood is searching for the same thing as me. I must find this girl.

You shall prioritize the Lord of Dion’s quest. Meet the Guard Captain sent to the Agricultural Area. I already told them about you.

I heard that the Silverlight Mercenaries would come for support... But that was you? I came here on the orders of my lord, but I am sick of the stench of those Lizardmen.

Why don’t we get started with the Lizardman around here.

The lizardmen are abducting townspeople left and right.

We must find the townspeople, but there aren’t any clues yet. In these cases, we should take a crack at the culprits first!

Ah, if I were to make anything from this job, shouldn’t I earn some money at least? I know an alchemist who collects strange items.

I have a request, could you help me? The lizardman’s rake goes for a high price these days, why don’t you gather some?

We have to slay lizardmen anyways, so why not? It will probably be best to go for those Lizardman Archers.

Among the list, there’s a lizardman tail. What would anyone do with those stinking tails...

If it wasn’t for the mission, I wouldn’t accept it, but I have you! I will share some of the profit.

Don’t forget that our official mission is to find clues of missing townspeople by defeating the lizardmen!

While fighting the lizardmen, there could be some things pillaged from the townspeople, like gemstones.

If you find anything like that, bring it to me. It will be an important clue in finding the townspeople.

Hey, wait. This looks familiar... This is my wife’s ring!

He-hey, where did you find this? Go back and search the area!

Thano sent you? So it was my ring. Thank you for returning it. The lizardmen took it from me...

We should leave the area first. I will tell the others, will you wait for a moment?
There are no townspeople around here. Let’s get out of here!
Wait! There’s a kid over there! What should we do? There are too many lizardmen! We have to save them!

We came out of the house, but got abducted...

Please help me! It’s too scary here...

She has the same necklace as mine. The necklaces identify each other with magic.

The Lizardman Guard took my necklace... We have to get it back. Only the necklace can find my sister.

The gemstone of the necklace has been taken by the leader... Without it, the necklace has no purpose.

Could those escorts still have it?
It’s not there? Oh no... I need the gemstone to find my sister using the necklace... Please find the gemstone...

The gemstone! Yes! This is the one! Now I will wear it with the gemstone inside the necklace...

Oh! I feel my sister’s necklace! It’s not far from here. I will look for my sister. Thank you.

I caught this kid trying to leave town. She says she was looking for her sister. Claimed to know you. So, you’re going together?

If you don’t have to go right now, could you slay some more lizardmen? They seem to strike the town when there are few people inside.

If I move out, the townspeople will be in danger. If you reduce their numbers, it will be a great help for the townspeople.

That kid is not one of our own... Sorry, but there are no men to spare.

Why don’t you ask the archon about it?

Will the archon help me?
There! A lizardman is coming! Why are they following me?
Seems the lizardmen remnants have followed us! We can’t let them inside, we have to kill them all!

I was gathering food for the refugees, but when I go hunting, those lizardmen strike the town like this.

We can’t move like this, can you bring some Windsus meat for us?

The one called Pamba is the leader of this area, it will be large enough to feed lots of people.

Lizardmen drove out the people from the Agricultural Area, so the town lacks food right now. Everyone is worried.

Here’s what we have gathered. Deliver it to the archon. Sorry for the inconvenience.

Looking for a kid named Elie? Hmm... There weren’t any outsiders among the refugees...

Maybe the merchants know something? Go to the plains to meet the merchants.

Never saw any outsiders except you. Poor kid... Did you feed her?
