Being hungry in situations like this is truly miserable. Can you get the Prairie Antelope meat? I can’t cook very well, but I can prepare the meat for you.

Meow! The animals around here are more aggressive and vicious these days. It’s hard to get any leather or horns. Even with the purr-emium offered to the hunters!

Elven Windsus leather is very popular, but there’s no supply. Can you bring it for me, meow?

The wasp’s sting can be used to make an anesthetic. A gift for patients under surgery!

Could you bring the Prickly Wasp’s sting?

Here! Give this cloth to the kid. It’s a reward for your hard work.

It pains me, reminding me of the lost brother of mine. Send the kid my regards.

The animals around here... have a strange energy. The Elder Antelope’s horn has the most suspicious energy inside.

Could you gather some Elder Antelope horn? I need to check something.

The remains over there are responding to my necklace. I almost thought it was my sister’s necklace.

Why don’t we move the remains over to one side?

But the remains near those spiders are not responding.

The strange energy from the spiders must be dark energy!

The necklace is weak near dark energy. I can’t find my sister like this.

Can you drive out the bats over there? I feel the dark energy coming from the bats.
Now that the monsters are away, it’s working again. I think the Elven Ruins are emitting an energy similar to my sister’s. Will you clear the Ruin Remnants for me?
I think I know which direction my sister is in... But the dark energy makes it hard to tell exactly. The Surly Vampire Bat over there emits strong dark energy! Please, drive it away!
Wait! There! A wizard! D-Do we have to run? No? It’s not a Dark Mystic? There’s a difference?

I was looking for the mercenary sent from the Silverlight Mercenaries. I am sent by the lord to inspect the Silverlight Mercenaries’ mission.

Cultivation of the plains is slow due to the rampaging monsters. If it gets any slower, my lord will be rampaging as well.

Now hurry, let’s start with the Ferocious Red Bear.

Did you see it? A Tullan Bugbear is here. There were no Tullan Bugbears on the plains before...

Nevertheless, we shall slay it.

Monsters are increasing at an unnatural rate... The answer is obvious. Someone is summoning monsters.

Summoning at this scale requires a summoning stone. Let’s spread out and look for it.

How persistent Dark Mystics they are. This is a pretty powerful summoning stone.

I can deactivate summoning spells but it won’t have any effect for something of this strength. Better to smash it instead. It should be easy for you.

I received a report that the scouts have gone missing. Traces of black magic like this...

I shall alert the forces. There, a fallen scout who’s still breathing. Go!
Let’s clear out the Red Bears nearby before saving the wounded.

Poisoned? This is... spider venom corrupted by black magic!

There’s no time! I must request the lord summon Ivory Tower Mystics. Spiders corrupted by Black Magic can’t be dealt with by normal soldiers.

Can you apply some first aid? You need to find the Antidote Mushroom! I’ll go on ahead!

M..meat! Whew, I was about to die... thank you. How long have I been down? I have to report to my base!

Will you help me? I can’t move properly yet.

According to a wounded soldier, there’s a Dark Mystic controlling the spiders! The soldier said he escaped from an egg sack.

The townspeople were probably looking for land to cultivate! We must save them!
While you were on the mission, I met Theodore. If the spiders are being controlled by black magic, the spider eggs should be full of energy. He said you need to destroy the eggs.
A Prairie Blade Spider. Spiders already corrupted by black magic must be killed. Defeat it!
The enemy knows our movements. As long as the culprit remains, this area will not be safe. Search the area!

Did you think you could protect this kid with some goons? My expectations were too high.

I accept your silly challenge. And the reward? Death! Hahaha!

Hahaha! Welcome to my grave. No one can save you now! Without precious Theodore or Zaab by your side, can you defeat me?

If you want the kid, come on!
Wh-where is this place? I-I’m scared... There are evils summoned by the bad wizard here... I... can’t move...

We... we can’t stop... We must find Elie...

Ah! I feel familiar energy there! Hurry!
This is it! I feel a familiar energy from this crystal! Now we can return to where we came from!
We’re out! But... Elie wasn’t there even with those bad wizards... Perhaps the guards saw her?

Now dealing with the spiders should be much easier. Of course, we can’t let the townspeople enter the area until then.

Also, Theodore has been waiting for you. Go now.

You found one of the keys I’ve been looking for. It’s Leia. It’s appearance and thinking resembles a child, but it’s actually a relic, thousands of years old.

It’s not an ordinary girl. Her twin Elie has the same powers.

With both twins, the giant’s relic, dormant in the Cruma Tower, can be activated. Now, do you understand why the twins are the key?

The Dark Brotherhood is looking for the twins. We have Leia, so let’s concentrate on finding Leia’s sister.

I asked around, and one of the townspeople who was abducted think Leia has been abducted as well. I think they saw the other twin.

When we were caught in the spider egg sack, Orcs came in and took out a kid.

I thought it was Leia, but it must have been the twin! They went towards the shortcut to Cruma.

If Leia is alright, then the kid must have been Leia’s twin!

I can return to the town on my own. Let Leia know the news!

The Orc Captain’s letter was about the Dark Brotherhood offering a bounty to Orcs and lizardmen for the twins.

Orcs must have been looking for the twins. If they went as far as to open the spider egg sack, it must have been Elie.

We need to hurry. Leia must go too, so clear the way of any monsters.

[player]! The Dark Brotherhood is heading to Cruma Swamp with Leia’s sister. Catch them!

I will go first! Meet me in Cruma!

You’re from the Silverlight Mercenaries? Welcome to Cruma. Theodore already passed by.

I was about to light the beacon. Without the beacon’s fire, we can’t see anything. Could I leave the other beacon to you?

With the lights on, spiders can be spotted easily. Defeating the Swamp Venomous Spiders is my job.

I had a vacation for a few days and their numbers increased. It would be much faster with your help.

The Black Tiger Spiders are more aggressive these days. They are quite difficult to handle.

Could you help me kill some more?

Now I must return to my guard post. If a traveler gets bitten while I’m away, things can get messy.

There seems to be a person over there, you should head that way. Now if you will excuse me...

My companion has been poisoned! I think a spider did it, but I need an exact sample to make an antidote.

Gather some Swamp Venomous Spider venom sacs! Then I will know what should I use.

I will stay with my friend.

Hans has been taken by the spiders. It’s unlikely he will survive, but... could you look for him?

I will protect Mitereu, so look for Hans! Oh, and if you see their queen, please avenge us!

I can’t tend to the two patients here, so I must return to the research camp.

Oh no! Spiders are out to hunt. I... I can’t fight! Can you hold your own?

...That’s unfortunate. My heart is heavy for Hans, however, we must save Mitereu while we can!

But going to the research camp would be difficult... Ah! Is that a researcher? Horace?

Laris! Bring Mitereu to the infirmary! Hey kid, why don’t you come over here, it’s dangerous!

Thank you for helping us researchers. We will tend to the wounded, so if you have time, please help the archaeologist.

He came to find the research notes, but he’ll need an escort and assistant. I can’t be an escort, but maybe you can.

Glad to meet again! Horace is not usually so diligent, but I guess I made him that way! He tossed you the job when he had the chance. Well, I’m not complaining!

Cruma is a very special area, with the giant’s relic and all. The wave that comes out of the relic neutralizes dark energy.

The monsters around here have dark energy, which is what I’ve been investigating. The dark energy’s influence over the monsters is very interesting...

In any case, I need your help right now. I lost my research notes. The carrier I hired ran away because of the spiders... could you find my notes?
I can’t find the notes about the Horror Reapers... Maybe I should research Horror Reaper samples again. Could you bring some for me, meow?

Cruma is a very special area, with the giant’s relic and all. The wave that comes out of the relic neutralizes dark energy.

Ah! A Swamp Bat! Go get some of them, they will be useful research specimens!
There’s the Horror Mist Reaper! I never even tried them, but I should while you’re around.

Oh! The Cursed Seer and Danthalion, prime specimens! They’re a rare sight!

They have strong magical energy, worthy of research.

I’d think someone actually sent these monsters just for us! What luck!

Over there... isn’t that the wizard you’ve been traveling with? No? Oh! I took too much of your time. Sorry.

This area is dangerous, so I will head for camp soon. I’ll be sure to pay you back for helping me!

You left the kid with the researcher?! Damn! Did you forget what I told you before? We must return quickly. We can’t leave her alone.

There’s a dark energy fluctuating around with traces of a powerful Dark Mystic summoning dark ones.

That Horror Reaper is the result. Let’s deal with it quickly,

This chaotic dark energy... leaving a trail on purpose... A provocation, perhaps?

Let’s investigate this pile of sheaves. Why in the world would sheaves be emitting dark energy?

This mark... Where have I seen this...

Ah, I know who it is.

Oh, my. A pleasure to meet you. Did you have a good time with my minions?

I had no plans to meet you. Why are you here? Where’s the one who’s supposed to be here?

Woah! That scared me! Why are you doing that?!

Research camp? The camp’s that way! Hey, wait! Why are you in such a rush?
Feldheim! Did you see any suspicious people passing by here?
Suspicious people, you say... I only saw Horace with Mitereu and Laris. If you move quickly, you can catch up with them.
What’s that?! That looks like a fire in the north!
That’s... the research camp! Damn! Niah is over there! Let’s go!
The supply items in the camp are on fire! Extinguish the fire first!
<YellowBold>[player]</>, I will pursue the traitor, you take care of things here.

Leia? The kid who came with Horace?

Huh? She’s gone! Where is she? Sorry, you should ask the guards. Skeletons are still around, so be careful.

Horace must have set the fire in this camp. Absolutely crazy! He also took the girl you were with!

Let’s follow Horace while getting rid of Skeleton Pursuers!
We found Horace! They cornered him! That way!
Huh? Is that Horace? Why is he wearing such dark clothes?
Horace took the girl, so she must be nearby. Let’s find her.

Horace tried to take me by force. It was like he was possessed. I can’t move, I was so shocked.

Why is everyone so mean to me! The Orcs, and people... Look! Even Lizardmen are after me now!
Could you gather the crystals over there? They’re similar to what I had at home, I think that will restore my energy.
This crystal is not enough... I feel a strong crystal nearby. I think that the Lizardman Leader has it!

[player], this crystal looks like a giant's crystal. This should not be here. It should only be in the... Cruma Tower where I’m from.

How are these crystals here? Would one of the researchers know?

Interesting. I don’t know the entire story, but this crystal really is the giant's crystal.

One of my researchers was able to enter Cruma Tower, its doors suddenly opened.

Cruma Tower doesn’t normally open like that, so it seemed suspicious but scholars couldn’t have passed such opportunity. We brought back some crystals and relic fragments.

But we didn’t bring all of them. There were a lot of people entering the tower, even Orcs and lizardmen.

They must have brought them expecting to make a fortune, but threw them out when they realized there was no one buying. Why don’t we look for more?
We need more giants' relic fragments, but the Skeleton Scouts are nearby. Please slay those Skeleton Scouts so that we can collect them.
Deliver this to my researcher, Bruin. He should be organizing and storing the relics. Our research will have some progress thanks to you!
Welcome. Looking for Bruin? I think... I saw Bruin over there. He shouldn’t be far.

Ah! So the head researcher sent you! Oh no! What should I do? They took the giant’s relic. I was ambushed by suspicious people.

Urk! My wounds are still fresh. Will you bring the Medicine Box?

Ah, those relics were hard to get... I can’t go back to Cruma Tower...

Over there! They’re Lizardman Scouts. When I collapsed, they came in and took the remaining relics and supplies. Please avenge me!

Now I have to report that I lost the relic, right? Oh, I’m dead... let’s go somewhere safe first. I must heal my wounds.

Wait, why are they still here? Swamp Ghouls! I can’t move fast enough yet! Help!

Thank you for saving Bruin. I have to protect the researchers, but it’s been more than I can handle on my own. I can’t deal with the increased monsters.

Seems the ones that ambushed Bruin know what these relics are. Why the hell are these stones so important... They were in such a rush, they even dropped some of them...

To save Bruin, we must reclaim the relic fragments. Will you help me? Let’s save Bruin again.
Huh? Do you feel that chill? Thought so! The Swamp Ghouls are increasing. They’re about to attack us! Incoming!

[player]! The movement of these monsters is... not normal. The Dark Brotherhood is rampaging.

Elizabeth! That witch must have released the Marsh Stakato Slaves to interrupt our pursuit... Kill them!

Why do you think the Dark Brotherhood wants Leia? The twins are the keys for activating the Cruma Tower’s giant relic...

They want to discover the secret of the giant’s power using the relic. That’s what Beleth always wanted. The Dark Brotherhood must be desperate.

Don’t let Leia out of your sight... They probably have Elie already. If Leia is taken, I can only imagine the worst.

The Swamp Hassassins over there were released by Elizabeth. They will strike when they have the chance. It’s best we strike them first.

I didn’t fully hear from Theodore. What in the world is going on? I was pursuing Elizabeth, but our missions seem to be the same...

Gathering the giant's crystals? What use are these? Why is Theodore ordering these things around? Can you do this yourself?
Now is not the time! The soldiers scouting have gone missing, all of them! This kind of scale could only be the work of the Dark Brotherhood!

Oh, we meet again! Your stalking skills are quite impressive. It’s so nice to see you but this is quite the pickle.

I’m a bit busy, so can’t play with you right now!

Hell! Damn summoning magic! The fact that it keeps working is ticking me right off! Did you say the tower? Cruma Tower?

Let’s head there first. One of them must have the key.
Over there! Did you see the light? That must be them! Go go go!

Found it! The key! But... why is it like this? Shoot!! The key’s broken! Damn sadists!

Maybe one of the Dark Brotherhood’s minions have the keys! Yeah, let’s crack that Swamp Assassin!
Hey, <YellowBold>[player]</>! Where’s Leia? I was concentrating on fighting! I’m no nanny!

The Dark Mystics took the key, but I can sense its location.

The second key is near that Marsh Stakato Envoy.

Now I feel it... those robed people... with the key...

Go down south and we can catch them!

So the one with Theodore is tracking us.

Heh heh, you shall have the glory of being the first victim of my newly trained Stakato mother!
I see you’re still alive! I’ll personally get rid of you! I can’t let you live, knowing that you’ll stand in the way of the Dark Brotherhood!
U-ugh... This isn’t over! There’s no way I would be defeated by you! I’ll show you the incredible power of darkness that Elizabeth gave me!
We have to find the third key, right? Leia! Do you feel anything? Defeat that Marsh Stakato Hassassin to let Leia concentrate!
Hey! Is that the giant's crystal? <YellowBold>[player]</>! What are you waiting for? Remember what Theodore ordered? Gather those giant's crystals!

Ha ha! I’m quite cool, you know! Leia, you’re pretty cool yourself! Now we must find the third key...

Hey, it’s an ambush!

Fortunately, no one’s been poisoned. The swamp venom inflicts an endless hemorrhage and eventually brings death. We must be prepared.

Bring the Poisonous Mushrooms. This mushroom blood stops blood from flowing.

I need the Destructive Killer blood as well. Only a small amount should do.

Aymel told me that I should go to a safe place. Meet me by the tree over there.
Ah! There! Don’t let them get away! A wizard is running over there!!

So we needed three of them? I’m a little surprised we got them all so easily. Leia! We’re heading to the Cruma Tower. You okay with that?

We can’t move all at once because of the dark energy here, so Aymel can’t go with us. Let’s move!

[player]! We’re such a good match, don’t you think?

Elie’s fine, but who knows how long will she stay fine! Do you want to play a game? Find Elie, the clock is ticking!
Shit... we must find Elie before it’s too late!

Elie!!! It’s me, Leia!
What happened! Answer me, Elie!

That wizard’s words are troubling. If it’s really the swamp venom... We must find her quickly. It should be alright as long as it’s not too late, right?

Huh? There! Elie’s over there!

Wait! It could be another trap!
I will protect Leia. <YellowBold>[player]</> should go there and check!

That’s Elie! It’s really Elie this time! That wizard’s holding her!

Save Elie! There’s no time!
Now the area will be full of evils. Let’s leave this place now... With the seal of Cruma Tower gone, it’s no longer safe...

Leia and Elie may look like kids, but they are relics that protected Cruma Tower for thousands of years...

This is disturbing. The seal of the Cruma Tower gone, Elizabeth taking away the giant’s research files...

I must go meet the master. He will be disappointed... This is bad. Let’s meet again near the Summit of Dissonance.

And... help that cat merchant over there!
Meow.. H-help... Thirst... Water in my bag... The Destructive Killer took it... Meow...

Water! Water! Slurp, slurp! Cough, cough! I really thought I was going to die! Meow! Thanks!

I dropped my bag! I almost drowned in the swamp while running away fur-om the monsters, it must have been then! Please avenge me, meow!

I, Peddler Pan, always pay my fur-iends back. I shall let you know the secrets of a merchant, meow.

The Shadow Choir Prima’s tail makes very expensive medicine! Now go get them, meow!
Where are you heading now? To the Summit of Dissonance, meow? In that case, you will pass through the Serene Woods. I have business there, I shall allow you to accompany me!
Is this the inside of Cruma Tower? Familiar energy inside an unfamiliar site... Get ready, it’s headed this way!

Theo, Theo, Theodore, I’ve been waiting for you. Leia’s here too? Leia, come to me. Ah, stubborn. But Elie is waiting for you.

Can’t be helped then. My minions, bring Leia to me!
Oh, stronger than I thought. I should have removed you from the tower... I won’t go easy on your anymore!

Meow, now that’s... not done yet! I forgot the items Hardin asked for!

Help me once more, meow! Always good to lend each other a paw, no?

This area is full of great purr-oducts! There’s the brown bear, meow!

The color of this season of fashion in Giran is brown, meow! It should fetch a good purr-ice! Go get them!
Sales require good sense, meow! You don’t have it! I told you the fashion trend! You should bring the leather! Go, bring me the leather!
I saw someone staggering over the bridge, meow! Check what’s going on!
I... I’m starving. I could eat anything right now...

The hunter becomes the hunted, funny right? Laugh all you want, but it’s better than dying.

Look! It’s the ones who’ve been hunting me! Help me!!

Why are you helping him, meow? You’re burning daylight! Now let’s get back to the road!

Meow, the Black Leopard! Their leather is worth a fur-tune! Don’t stay there, go get their leather!
The Leopard King’s leather is hot in Giran. We must make sure the leather is not harmed! Let’s set a trap, meow.

Wait! What is that stupid hunter doing now, meow? Why is he being hunted by spiders? Well, let’s be on our way.

What? Let’s go, meow!

Meow, alright! Go help him! You’re hopeless in being a merchant!
No way! I don’t want to hunt spiders! I was chasing a big, juicy rabbit, when all of a sudden, a spider appeared out of nowhere!

Now I have all I need, meow! You truly have a potential to be a great adventurer! Ha ha! It’s been some time since I’ve had a good fur-iend in the Silverlight Mercenaries!

I don’t trade here, there’s a war going on between the Ol Mahum and Tanor, you see, meow.

Meow, is that Theodore? You’re meeting Theodore? I don’t go where Theodore is. So long!

If Elizabeth discovered the secret of the giant’s relic, the situation is dire. It also means that Beleth will be able to use the power of the giants soon.

We must make more allies to fight the Dark Brotherhood... The Tanor here are fighting the Ol Mahum, and the Ol Mahum receives the Dark Brotherhood’s support.

We must end this war by helping the Tanor. But for the Tanor... making friends requires a bit of force.

Don’t lower your guard, we’re just about to begin now.
There’s no retreat. The Tanor Fighters don’t respect the weak.

We have to go meet the Tanor Highchief, but the road is rough already. Only the toughest may become Tanor Fighter.

Trouble is that such toughness is heading toward us. We have no choice but to fight...

Since the Ol Mahum is with the Dark Brotherhood, we should negotiate using that information.

My master is coming personally for this alliance, so be ready.

It looks you’ve grown much. It’s rare to see Theodore commend someone.

Let’s spare the pleasantries. If we can’t evade war, then we should end it quickly.

There will be no Tanor left at this rate.
Should we open up the way using other tactics?
Tanor are coming. Get ready, do your best!

Must be lost somewhere. Ugh, will you go find Durzel, [player]?

He keeps his promise, but in terms of time and place, he is very remote.

Thank you for coming, but I was on my way. I was making friends with the Tanor.

There, we must pass here, so let’s defeat those shamans. If we’re not careful, their curse will turn us into Training Dummies.
Now let’s negotiate with the troopers! They are true warriors. They will use their hammers until their death.
See those sentries over there? They can hear even the smallest noises. We’ll be discovered no matter what, so let’s go to the front!
Hardin sent a signal from the eastern barracks. Now it’s my turn! Don’t be too surprised and follow me!

Will you let me talk to Durzel privately?

You have to handle those Tanor anyway.
I have some doubts about Durzel’s methods, but gaining respect with military power seems to be the best way. Shall we keep going?
Durzel will infiltrate the Tanor camp while we create a diversion here. First, let’s set fire to this wagon.
It was a success. Tanors are coming. Get ready!

Seems the chief is on the inside.

Can you deal with those sentries by the watchtower?
Theodore will be waiting inside the watchtower, can you find Theodore for me?
The master may look like a good person... But sometimes he’s ruthless. I hope this works. Let’s defeat those suppliers.

Looks like Tanor Priests are preparing a ritual before the battle. Hurry, they must be preparing for combat against the Ol Mahum.

If the ritual begins, it will be harder to meet the chief. Slay those priests!

Since the master has decided, there’s no option for the Tanor now...

Since he must talk to the chief, slay the Knight Recruits nearby and help the master.
We need to further demonstrate our strength to force the chief to make his decision.

I shall talk to the chief now. Meow, here comes some Tanor. So they don’t want us to talk to the chief.

Please keep them from interrupting the talk. Sometimes we need to communicate with our paws... Thanks, meow.

Looks like the chief has been persuaded. We have a common enemy after all. It was easy to communicate for a Tanor.

The chief has requested to recover his men’s corpses, make sure they are well tended too.

What? Hardin’s already gone? He had something from the chief... What was it...

Okay. Now let’s teach those Ol Mahum a lesson!

Prepare for combat! Tanor’s Warchief is rebelling! Damn! Who’s on our side?! They all look the same!

Just think anyone attacking us is one of the Tribal Chief’s minions!
Please find traces of the ones who ambushed us. I must find where Kankoon is!

Deputy Chief Kankoon’s group does not recognize us as their friends. I thought dealing with the chief would be enough!

We can’t back off from this fight. First, defeat Kankoon’s sentry!
We have to fight the Ol Mahum, what are we doing here! Now let’s defeat the Elite Soldiers. They’re the most powerful warriors.
Those Elite Soldiers look like recruits when they’re compared to you. Now we’re ready to get this going! Ready? Let’s go.

Hell, Kankoon’s group keeps coming even after their leader is dead. Let’s defeat them quickly and leave this place. There’s no time.

Defeat the priests. Their curse can be a major threat.
The sentries found us. Take them out before they alert the others.
Whew! There’s Theodore. What a peaceful chap he is.
By the looks of it, the negotiation was not completed. There’s no time, we must move now. I will explain on the way.

The Tanor here are all the chief’s forces. They are not influenced by the rebellion, so they will fight with us.

Let’s start with that patrol over there.
Next are the Ol Mahum Scouts. Scouts can call in more troops, so you must defeat them quickly!

There should be an envoy sent by the Tanor Highchief. It will officially recognize us as friends of the chief.

But to be real friends, we should solve few of their problems.

Not all Tanor respect you as their friends. But help me a bit, and they will, so don’t worry.

On behalf of the chief, I shall request something. Some of our friends have gone missing. If they’re dead, we need to find their corpses.
Seems the Ol Mahum are using something strange. Will you investigate it with me? First, we should infiltrate the Ol Mahum base while slaying the scouts.

Your friend Durzel went that way, yelling “War!”. I will follow you after looking for Tanor.

Join Durzel first. Please defeat the Ol Mahum Sentry while you’re at it.
Now, this is war! Don’t go easy, kill them all. Start with those weak recruits!
Another important thing in war is logistics. Burn their Supply Items! It will wreck their morale!
Slay the ones extinguishing the fire! Prepare for combat!
There! Captains are over there! Strong monsters are more fun, don’t you think? Now let’s exercise a bit!
Oh, during the fight with the captains, Borys ran inside. I wonder what’s going on? Why don’t you check it out?
Shh! Quiet. I think the abducted Silenos are here. Some are not Tanor, but please rescue them.
More cages inside. Not only Tanor but Silenos as well... Let’s rescue them.
Some of them have been dragged inside. We must check that way too. Can you defeat the suppliers first?
What the hell are they doing here! Damn Ol Mahum! We can’t stop here! Let’s find the traces of the Tanor!
Th-there, a survivor! Let’s move! This way! Hurry!
This way! We need to rescue them quickly!
Ol Mahum and the Dark Brotherhood, I will never forgive them! I must report this to the chief. But before I go back... I must cremate my friends...
I will join you shortly. This is shocking to me. I have arranged it with Theodore already, you should go on ahead.

Since the Dark Brotherhood is mobilizing, we must hurry.

We can’t wait until Borys returns. Let’s go defeat the Ol Mahum Chief. Start with the snipers.
Good, there’s the chief. A direct assault will be a suicide. Let’s take out the troopers first.
Time to kill the chief! Let’s attack before they find us!

Durzel went first to find the Soulstone. The Soulstone should be where the chief retreated to.

We must recover the Soulstone. Let no one stand in your way!
Reclaim it? The Soulstone must be destroyed! That’s the only way to make sure they don’t return!

The master ordered us to reclaim the Soulstone, Durzel! Ah... Are you really going to disobey the master?

The chief is dead, so their chain of command will collapse soon. This war is finished. Let’s leave using the teleportation stone.

Our mission was quite a success. The master will be pleased. I shall report to the master and go to the Shrieking Hallows. Meet me there.

The master will likely work with us when we get there. The opponent is formidable... make preparations before you go.
Did you rest well? You must be curious why we’re here. Follow me, I will tell you while moving.

He has been sealed but the increasing dark energy will release him soon.

Hmm... There’s always been a lot of Mandragora here... Let’s clear this area.

There’s a cenotaph nearby. This land has had many needless deaths. The cenotaph is here to calm their souls.

Even still, there are a few that turn into demons.

The Dicors nearby are attacking the cenotaph. Go defeat the Dicors.
We can’t go without a tribute. There are a lot of flowers that have the color of the blood spilled on the ground. Bring those flowers.

Since this land is full of specters, the land itself emits the dark energy... a perfect spot for Beleth and the Dark Brotherhood.

Also, there’s a great demon called Guillotine who is dormant here, so anomalies caused by dark energy happen pretty frequently.

This way! I have something to show you.
This tree wasn’t here before. It must have appeared along with the dark energy. You should investigate it.

The dark energy brings new monsters, releasing sealed evils. Leaving the area like this won’t be good.

Meet me at the cenotaph. It will be west.
Good job with the bouquet. You should try paying the tribute yourself.
Let’s remove some weeds before we leave.

Master told me that there’s something we have to do. The master can be ruthless sometimes, like what we saw with Tanor...

If you feel that you have a different view than he does, think of this cenotaph here. Ultimately, the path we take is of our own volition.

I must go now. I’m too busy to help Peddler Pan. You’re not the only one he has working for him. See you later.

Had a good time in the Summit of Dissonance, meow? I actually need an adventurer to test new purr-oducts. You would fit purr-fectly!

Now, apply this... and fight the Mandragora! They’ll run away, meow! If this experiment is successful, it will be officially supplied to the Silverlight Mercenaries!

Th-this can’t be! Now try this one, meow! Not Mandragora, but Dicor! It’s a Dicor repellent!

Test it with the Dicor of Sorrow over there! Meow, it will work this time!

How can this be, meow! I failed... how shocking! I have to do the experiment again...

I need more Mandragora, but I used them all... Meow, please go get me some...

No... No! Normal Mandragora can’t make great products, meow!

Let’s go find some special Mandragoras! I came here all the way to make the repellent, meow!
Meow! A Mandragora with colors I’ve never seen! Quick! Dig it up!

Business requires humor and wits! Thank you, meow. I will make the repellent. If I succeeded, I would have signed the contract with Hardin right now! It’s too bad!

I’m done asking for help for now. Meow. Meow!

Did Theodore tell you that you would meet me here? Did he tell you what will you do? I received intel that a demon from the past may wake soon.

Guillotine... If it is awoken, then everything shall be going towards what Beleth desires... No one can produce the dark energy like Guillotine does...

Even if the Shrieking Hallows has a dark history, monsters have never been more active. I have to investigate this.

The flow of dark energy is distorted, which is suspicious. The Dark Brotherhood’s involvement is obvious.

What are you doing? Prepare to fight the undead.
Good. Now let’s begin. I will lead the way, follow me. Once we go up the stairs, it’s undead territory, so be careful.

That was close... It was as if they were waiting for us.

The undead making a coordinated ambush... the Dark Brotherhood are here.

Kill them! They’re a source of dark energy.

They hunger for the warmth of the living. If we don’t hide our warmth, there will be many more ahead.

Get some cloth pieces from reapers.

Their cloth contains their grudge and even the land itself overflows with it. The living can’t harbor such a grudge.

Go get weeds grown from the blood of the dead. They should be nearby.

Let me introduce you to Valter, a new member of the Silverlight Mercenaries. Continue your investigation with Valter. I will go meet Peddler Pan for a moment.

I forgot that I had some items to order. I’ll see you again soon.

What we have to do is light Einhasad’s furnace. It can stop Guillotine from breaking the seal.

Lighting up the furnace requires crystallized pure souls, but Hardin told me that the crystallized grudge of the undead could also work.

We’ll need lots of them. Let’s spread out.

Hardin told us to check for any remaining corpses at the cemetery. If the corpses at the cemetery are moving, that means Guillotine’s resurrection is imminent.

I will go first, meet me in the graveyard.

The seal containing Guillotine’s power must be weakening. Something is not right...

Did you hear that? Sounds like a tree is moving...

Whew! Let’s resume our work. I found a location for the furnace.

Just follow that road. I will wait for you there.

Einhasad’s fire is a death sentence to the undead.

They will frantically attack us to survive, so get ready.

We need more time for Einhasad’s fire to mature...

But the nearby undead won’t be waiting. The killers are too close, let’s defeat them.

They’re still here even with the Einhasad’s fire... Something’s clearly wrong.

The furnace’s now mature, so the undead can’t touch it. Let’s go investigate the area.

My god! Is this a Soulstone of sorts? Never seen one like it... I think this is preventing the souls from moving on.

This Soulstone must be destroyed.

There are several incinerators nearby... We should check them all.

In the past, there were many deaths due to the tyranny and many were cremated.

Corpses deserted near the incinerator had been left behind after Guillotine was resurrected as a demon.

There will be strong undead wandering near the incinerator because of that. It’s dangerous, but it would be best to spread since we don’t have a lot of time. Take care.

There are 2 incinerators along the way. I can see that the Soulstone is absorbing the souls of the dead and dark energy.

Please defeat the Doom Servants nearby before destroying the Soulstone.

Wait... you see that? That’s Koma, a collective of souls.

The Restless Spirits are gathering... They are feeding off each others’ darkness, just waiting for death...

Leave them and they will be a huge threat later on. Let’s defeat them.

Now let’s destroy the Soulstone in front of the two incinerators.

I will go and report this to Hardin. The situation is entirely different from our expectations.

[player]... Meow meow... What should I do... I was almost killed by skeletons. Will I become a zombie cat if I die?

I don’t want to become a zombie... I have to stop the bleeding... Meow, I need herbs... I sold all of the herbs I had when I was passing Dion...

Meow! Herbs! Oh, I feel better already! It’s a rare herb, thank you!

Ugh... It still hurts... but... Meow... Wait... I want... to have that... expensive-looking chain! I shall use that Innocent Spirit’s chain to make a splint...

Hiss!! Hardin has gone too far this time, calling me to such a dangerous place like this! Deliver this reagent to him, meow. It’s very expensive, be careful!

I will wait somewhere safe, meow. Let’s move together after you’re done! I used my teleportation stone twice to bring that!

Who would install the Soulstone here other than the Dark Brotherhood? Collecting the dark energy like that... We can’t allow it.

If you try to destroy a Soulstone that is already full of souls, you can get hurt. We need something safer.

Use the reagent Peddler Pan gave you on the Soulstone. It will release the souls inside.

Meow that Soulstone is just an ordinary stone. Let’s light up the fur-nace again.

Fur-st, we must gather crystals of grudge. Let’s gather the Ominous Willow’s crystals fur-st, meow.
Well done. But it’s far from over. The Death Reaper is next. Go to the castle entrance after you’re done. I will wait for you there.
Einhasad’s fire can suppress the power of the undead. If this furnace works well, then we can prevent Guillotine from breaking the seal.
Valter should have returned by now... It’s been a while since I last heard from him. Will you go find him?
I dropped my reserve sword while fighting the surrounding undead. Could you find it for me?

What I think is, the Dark Brotherhood has something else in mind other than gathering the dark energy in this castle.

I should investigate further before making a conclusion.

Help! I came here... Because it’s a shortcut to Giran...

My companions... Please find my companions... They were scattered between the specters...
This wound is severe... I must tend to it. Could you find traces of the other merchant?

...passed on. The wound was too severe. Too late... Will you look around while I recover the merchant’s corpse?

Check the upper side of the stairs. I found this merchant while investigating that area.

Ah... Who is this? Hardin’s goon, I see. Came to sacrifice yourself like those merchants? Heh.

The contract with the lord of this castle must be finished... Don’t you think it’s about time you die?

You look bleak. What did you find?!

The Dark Brotherhood turning the merchants into undead? We can’t let them suffer like this. We must slay them all.

So what is the Dark Brotherhood plotting with the lord of the castle?

Let’s investigate further. Let’s spread out and meet after it’s done. Beware of the skeletons along the way.

There are demons upstairs... It must be the demons that signed the contract with the lord of the castle.

We can’t leave them like that. People who lose their souls to demons will suffer even after death.

We can’t let them play with human souls. Let’s defeat them and meet in front of the room next door.
Oh no... These merchants have already lost their souls to the demons. We must defeat them release the souls!
Demons can’t be summoned to this realm automatically. There must be an evil summoning stone nearby. Destroy it when you see it.
Now let’s find the Dark Brotherhood! Meet me below the next staircase!
There’s a Zombie Lord blocking our way. I will take the rear, could you slay the Dark Brotherhood?
Oh, I will give you what you want. Are you ready to meet the one you’ve been looking for? Now you shall die!
G-Guillotine of Death? So he was the awakened lord? We... must find Hardin right now. We will die if we stay here!

Get back! This furnace can’t stop Guillotine!

I will count to three, then run away! You must escape while the furnace and seal buys some time!

There won’t be enough time even if you leave this castle right now and light up the last furnace.

I will light up a furnace here to buy more time. Gather as many crystals from specters as you can!

Good work. With these, there will be plenty for the last seal!

Light up the furnace! Now Guillotine must be headed this way from the Ruined Keep!
Oh no... We have to get out, but there are too many specters here! Let’s spread out and meet at the entrance!
Yes, Hardin! <YellowBold>[player]</>, see you at the exit!

Why is your fur all rustled! What is happening, meow?

G-Guillotine is back? Really, meow? Why are you telling me this now?! Let’s go! Follow me!
We can’t escape because I have only short ranged teleportation stone! Let’s just go back to Hardin instead! It will be safer, meow!

Let’s light up the last furnace. The previous furnace probably has been destroyed by now.

We must stop Guillotine... if he comes out of the castle, Giran will be in danger!

[player], we owe Peddler Pan very much this time. Calling him here was quite dangerous.

Will you escort him on my behalf? Take him to Giran.

Whew... That was quite some work. I will return to the HQ now. There must be more work waiting for me from the lords...

Never thought I would see Guillotine in person. It’s a miracle we survived.

I have so much room for progress. I will be a different person when we meet again.

See you later, [player].

That was close, meow! Average merchants can’t trade with the Silverlight Mercenaries because of these dangers. Only my caravan can handle it!

Meow? Didn’t you know? The Cat Caravan and the Silverlight Mercenaries are very close! I’ve worked with Theodore too!

Now let’s get back to work! The Dicor’s petals over there are worth some money! Go get them, meow!

Meow! Let’s head to Giran! You want to trade, go to Giran! If you’ve never been be-fur, remember who got you there!

But you must gather more items to sell in Giran. Now gather the nails hammered to the hands of the servants around here, meow!
Giran is this way. Just follow the road, meow! I will go first, meet me in the Giran Dominion!

Meow, I almost forgot! Hardin asked fur something when we were leaving!

The merchants in the Keep of Agony were transporting an important relic, meow!

But Hardin couldn’t sniff it out, so he asked me to bring the accountant’s ledger, meow!

What are you doing? Get mew-ving!

Come quick, meow! Aden is a continent full of war and evils! So, it has highly developed medical science... especially in herbalism!

Herbs are always short on demand, meow, so it brings high purr-ofit. What we’re going to gather here is Dicor buds, meow.

There are only a few per Dicor, they have no toxin and make people healthy, meow. Now, mew-ve!

Did you think becoming rich would be easy, meow? Even I didn’t know what to find at fur-st.

Meow... Do you see that shining, blue plant? My hyper cat senses are tingling... That’s a blue mana plant! ...

It’s a rare herb containing mana. It increases the mana of magic users if applied long enough, meow. It’s extremely expensive. Now get it!

Mrrow? You see those herbs? They’re rare, special herb only found here! It may look like an ordinary thorn, but its sap can be used as an anesthetic.

Go get it! Right now, meow!
Snipe claws are used for polishing. Grab as many as you can, meow.

Wait! Now concentrate, meow! The way we’re going has rare Flat Mushrooms.

The Flat Mushroom is known to make kittens grow taller, meow!

It’s not an official fact, but its rumor makes it popular among mothers, meow! The wealthy mothers of Giran do not care about the purr-ice. Gather any you see!

Red Bears around here have a special organ called a strength sack, meow. It is popular among knights and young men.

But they are most wanted by wives who are dissatisfied with their husbands, meow! Let the bear hunt begin!

The bear paws at the Wagon Wheels Restaurant of Giran is rated 5 stars! I’ve been there once... I am already drooling, meow.

The bear paw is the purr-ime ingredient, but few people can hunt the Red Bear. Meow, we can sell it for a high purr-ice!

Meow! My friends live near here. I always give gifts when I pass by, and I will do the same this time.

The clothing made of snipe’s leather is the best item for fashion leaders, meow. There are more than ten designer brands using snipe leather in Giran!

But snipes are usually the hunters, not the hunted! That means it’s rare, and rare means money, meow!

A good gift! Meow! Go get it!

Meow, is that Dicor sap on your cloth?

Oh my meow! I made a huge mistake! Alchemists love Dicor sap, meow! Go get it!

Now, look carefully, meow! The leather you just brought has its tailfur shed off. Tailfur is key for high quality.

I can’t give this as a gift, meow. Take special care and bring me one with the tailfur intact!
Me-ow! Very good! Do you know how it feels when exchanging a full bag for Adena? Meow ha ha ha! Let’s head to Giran!

Alice! Where’s the payment? You know that Vehin will be punished if you don’t do your work.

Or perhaps you can do something for me? Bring the girl.
Ugh... I’ll go back for now. I’ll find you again, Alice! I will take you next time!

When I was a new merchant, Alice and her brother Vehin once saved my life. Meow, I will pay my debt.

Meow! They need money, so we need to earn money! Help meow-t and I will be sure to repay you! There’s a Red Bear over there, go get it!

Meow! You can pay taxes with leather instead of money. Hunters like Alice and Vehin do so.

Go gather some Red Bear leathers, meow!
Alpine Cougar fangs can also be used to pay taxes. I am ever grateful.
Cougar leather is also money, meow. Gather them for me to sell.
There are some crops I raised to sell. Will you harvest them for me?
Let’s return to the town for now! I want to show you around. But first, I’m going to go pay my taxes with the leather you got for me.
Will you wait in front of the central statue? I will be there after paying my taxes. I am supposed to meet the elder there. See you soon!

Wait! Shh! Quiet!

That dark, black leather! Spiral markings! Long fang and claw! It must be!

Rugal, king of the snipe! What a purr-fect day!

A monster you could never find in a hundred years, meow!

Sneak up on it and bring back its leather, meow! Its leather is purr-actically gold!
Oh no... Looks like the cougars and Red Bears regards us as their food source! This has never happened before... Take care!

I lost some documents that were for Alice.

There are four of them!

You know Alice? In that case...

Will you deliver these to her? It’s urgent.

Damn! The Gorgon Flower Garden, of all places! Hunters shouldn’t be conscripted like this!

Can you believe it? I can’t just let my brother turn into stone! I will bring my brother out of the garden!

What can you do even if you reach Gorgon Flower Garden? Want to turn into stone?

If you keep doing this, I have no choice but to arrest you!
So many Medusas out there... Is my brother inside? I must get in! He might be getting hurt as we speak!
There are lots of things on the ground here! I have to check if there are traces of my brother!

If you meet a Medusa’s gaze, you will turn into stone. Has my brother already been turned to stone?

Hey! Those wyrms are about to destroy that stone! No! It could be my brother!
Doesn’t look like a soldier... I should ask for where my brother or other soldiers are!

If this girl’s brother is a soldier, then he has no choice but to fight Medusa. Why the hell are they continuing the operation without countermeasures for the curse?

My son had the same fate! After losing my son to those Medusae, I have been researching ways to stop their curse.

I completed the research for blocking the curse, but I need more ingredients. Help me gather them. If you bring enough, I can share my invention.

First, I need wyrm eggs! Can you do it?

Let’s see... I need a bugbear heart. Since I’m a botanist, I can’t bring such things by myself.

Other ingredients can be replaced with plants, but these are irreplaceable. Please.
Now I need Medusa eyes. This ingredient and the next one are the most important. Could you get the Medusa eyes?
Last one! It’s as vital as the Medusa eyes. Gather the moss from the victim’s stones.

Here, drink this! And these are for Alice and her brother.

Go and make sure no one else suffers from their family turning into stone! Slay the Medusae!

This place is too dangerous. Leave at once, before you turn into stone! Hey, what’s that!

Medusa! Look out!
There! I saw some adventurers break the curse using those flowers. It can’t prevent the curse, but it can break it after.
There, those are my comrades turned into stone.

They’re destroying the stones! What a heinous act!

If the curse is lifted, they can return to normal people but that won’t be possible if they’re destroyed! Stop them!
My comrades are fighting over there! Let’s help them!
Is everyone okay? That was too reckless, <YellowBold>[player]</>. I thought I was going to lose you forever.
Alice! I was worried about you!

Brother! I thought I was going to die!
Thank you, everyone! Thank you, wizard.

You must be Alice and Vehin! People are waiting for you.

Don’t worry, they sent me to help you. Let’s go using the teleportation stone.
Don’t worry, they sent me to help you. Let’s go use the teleportation stone.
Vehin! Alice! Meow! You’re all right!
So it was you who requested assistance for us! You saved us!
Good to see you alive, meow!! I thought I will never see you again!!
Now I will guide my fur-iends to a safe place! Thanks for your help, meow! See you later!

Peddler Pan asked to find you.

Ugh... You have no idea how much he whined. I had to come here just to stop listening to it.

Pan will take care of Alice and Vehin.

We have somewhere else to go. Follow me.

Dicors swarming here... This never happened before. It’s quite disturbing.

Can you eliminate those Dicors?
Those Dicors looks suspicious. Is that a cloak on the ground? We have to check it out.

Now I am curious who the cloak’s owner is. I don’t have any urgent business anyway.

Look! Dicors were gathered because of dark energy from this cloak.
I always had a strange feeling in this forest, even though it’s by my hometown... I should find out why.

This tree is part of a seal of a something. I don’t have a clue as to who it could be... but the method used here... Whoever it is is far from average...

I will decipher the seal... Hmm? What is this?
Ah, I made a mistake! Get ready! The Seal Sentry will come out!
This tree should be investigated too. It’s hollow inside. There must something there.

These are elven records... They’re a bit difficult to read due to the condition.

There may be other documents. Could you find them for me?

This is almost a puzzle. It will take time for me to decipher it. The succubus over there is making it difficult for me to concentrate...

Clear the area for me!

The one who taught black magic to the Woodland Elves... it’s probably Dasparion.

Could you bring me some succubus wings?
Those werewolves seem to be enhanced by the power of black magic. Can you gather their claws? I need to check it out more closely.

The designer of this seal is using the life force of the trees nearby. If I’m right, trees closer to the seal should be weak.

Look for other trees. Some of them should be unnaturally drained.

A demon! A demon has been sealed here!

Watch out! The seal is weak! The demon’s on the loose.
So the Blood Queen has been sealed here. We should strike now, when it’s not fully recovered!

<YellowBold>[player]</>!

The monster should come. thinking it’s a soul. We shall slay it when it comes out.

Then primas will come.
