People think they arrive in dead lands, but it’s the opposite. The land becomes barren because of the sahara.

And you know the stone that looks like a heart when you kill saharas? Plant it in the ground and you can return the nutrients to the land. If you want to restore the land, plant the hearts in the ground!

Now I will be on my way! I still have to look for items Hardin ordered! I will gather what I can gather alone for now!

Now let’s bury this heart into the ground and go to the hunter shelter.

It’s only a personal guess, but I think the Blood King has an adverse effect on the Protection Tree.

Hunters always work around here, so they may know something about the Blood King.
Look out! Enraged Saharas are coming!
Look out! Wyrms! Coming this way!
Wyrms moving like this... What is happening here? Let’s go to the hunter shelter for now.
People here may know something about the Blood King. Let’s spread out and ask around!

Came to buy something? Here’s some fine wyrm leather. Hunters risked their lives for it.

You don’t look like a merchant. People coming here are either merchants or hunters. What brings you here?

Do I know anything about the Blood King? What is a Blood King? A new cocktail? Ha ha...

You saved my life. Thank you. Did you say Blood King?

Come to think of it, I met someone a while ago... A dwarf talking something similar. He was excavating things along with his daughter, but I don’t remember his name..

Damn. They left a few days ago.

There are basilisks in the south, maybe they went there. Be careful, if you look around you just might find them...

They haven’t returned, so something bad must be going on.

They could be still alive, but I don’t recommend looking out for them.

I owe you again! You should wait until I repay my debt next time, ha ha! My business here? There’s so much to dig up here!

See that Fettered Souls over there? I had to run away because of them! Those damn monsters, will you defeat them for me?

Well, it’s not a simple excavation this time. The Silverlight Mercenaries requested this.

Or, should I say Hardin requested this one? It’s dangerous, so let’s go to my post first.

There are so many evils... Could you clear the path? Fighting the Headless Knights could turn me headless.

Do you have anything to eat? I have been starving for so long. Windsus jerky? Great! Ah...

Looks like the Headless Knights have followed us! No wonder I can’t eat these days! And I am still overweight, would you believe that?

I have you, so I refuse to run this time! Defeat them for me!
Hm... I have a request for the elf you’re with... there’s an ancient elven written on this tablet. Could I ask to have it deciphered?

The ancient elf? Ha ha, do you think all elves can read ancient elf text? What simple logic!

Show it to me. Just in case you don’t know, these ancient letters require mana when reading. If something interferes during reading, it will erase the contents and harm me as well.

So make sure the evils around do not bother me.

So that was what it is? I have to look for other tablets soon! Thank you!

I finished this one, so let’s move. Now Fettered Souls are blocking our way. We are almost there, so keep it up!

[player]! It’s been a long time. Thank you for saving my dad, I never expected to see you here.

Oh! Head Archaeologist!

I found two more of the tablets you told me to find.

Huh? Ask the elf?

Please, will you decipher these tablets?
I’m also interested in what it says. Give it to me.
That’s was close. Let’s decipher it before they come again!

Hmm... That explains why the excavation is so slow. The evils around are harassing you, right?

I need clues on the Blood King anyway, so we should reduce the number of evils here to help the excavation. Let’s defeat the Headless Knights around.
Seems like the evils have been rapidly increasing under the Draconian rule... there are so many of them here... the Fettered Souls are no exception. Let’s deal with them too.

I want to investigate the inner area, but that’s where the grandis are. It’s also where a number of tablets are. I want to concentrate here.

Will you drive out the grandis? Be careful, their blunt weapons will crush your bones.

Hey! There is a pile of tablets here! I think what Hardin’s looking for may be here as well.

I can’t follow you, since I have to recover these.

If you want to really drive out the Grandis, you should kill their leader. That will make then think twice before attacking us!
We defeated the leader. Let’s leave.
The leader will not be easy. Let’s go together!

Help me... Why did Hardin order dragon eggs from me... Dragon eggs are really difficult to obtain! I tried to steal one, but I failed.

I gave up after such a long chase. Please go get the dragon eggs for me.
But... the peddler cat also want to taste the dragon egg... They say it’s a true delicacy. Bring lots of it!

After this, I will not accept Hardin’s personal orders for a while! He is really exotic!

The list goes on! I left anything requires combat! See those gargoyles! They’re used for stuffing, and looks like Hardin has a new hobby! Go get them!
Next up, see those grandis? Their blunt weapons are very good to use as steel frames! Why are you still here?

Oh! See those dragon bones?! I was wondering how could I get those!

Pick them up right now! Er... I mean please pick them up for me! I am exhausted!
We must get those Heavy Dustwind Gargoyles! They are more vicious and more expensive than ordinary Dustwind Gargoyles! Go!
Agh, those Monster Eyes are gazing on us. Wait, I think they’re also on the list... and here it is! Defeat them!
There’s a torch over there. Let’s head that way.

We restored the shelter quickly, thanks to you. I found out who was behind the attack by checking the corpses.

It’s Veremus. He rules this region. I don’t know why he’s doing this, but we can’t let him get away with attacking hunters.

Ha, that cat merchant seems happy. Must have heard that Veremus piled up lots of treasure.

We need your skills, so please help me. Start by dealing with Veremus' minions.
Ah, I’m tired of talking. Go get the wyrm leather!
We have enough eggs... so we can sell those! Let’s regroup after picking up those wyrm eggs!
If you had enough, follow me.
That Deathly Monster Eye is Veremus' minion. Let’s deal with it too!
The Wyrm Guardian resistance is formidable. Maybe Veremus already knows that we’re coming for him. Let’s move.

Someone’s fighting the Wyrm over there! Ooh, beat it!

It’s an elf! What’s an elf doing here? Let’s see.

I found a tablet while I was alone. It’s an important clue. Listen!

The Blood King is healing his wounds in the dimensional rift, thanks to Veremus.

If he is hit even just once more by the spirit sword, he will die. But the dragon knight, Cager took the sword... Damn it...

Burnsting is Randol’s sword. It’s as famous as Randol himself. No wonder the Blood King would be heavily wounded.

With the sword, it should be easy to fight the Blood King. But the sword is in Cager’s hands...

Did you say, Cager? Good! Do you know how many of my comrades died because of him? I will join you!

Let’s defeat the watchers nearby first! We don’t need them knowing what we’re up to!
According to the tablet, Veremus knows the location of the dimensional rift. But I don’t think Veremus will so easily tell us of the location... let’s hurry up!
That’s where Veremus lives. Let’s remove its younglings before Veremus returns!
The Protection Tree is about to die... There’s no time... Find the treasure of Veremus... If Veremus is right, there should be a gemstone that will take you to the dimensional rift...
The Protection Tree is weakening. I can’t hold on much longer.

Wyrms are swarming here. So this is where the dragon knights are? We need to be careful, one wrong move and we’ll be surrounded by those wyrms.

Let’s deal with them before they decide to eat us!
There are the eggs! If those eggs hatch, us elves will be in trouble! We should destroy them while we can!
According to Hammon, there are dragon whelps inside! We must destroy them all! Are you with me?
Huh? There are some eggs left! Let’s destroy them!
How can this be... our relics are here! We must bring them back! With these, I can save my people!
Do you see those dragon knights? They’re formidable minions of Cager. Be prepared!
If we can’t go there, we can make it come to us instead! Burn those wyrm corpses! They have a strong connection to their kind, so it will surely come here!
There’s Burnsting! Finally! We have Burnsting! Now, we can defeat the Blood King!
Damn! Death Binds in here?! We can’t leave them. They will surely follow us! Defeat them right now!
I think the tablets are guiding us... Good. Let me take a look at this. Please protect me while I decipher this.

Hmm? I heard something strange over there, could you check it out?

I will deliver the tablets to Feldheim.
Huh? I felt the ground shuddering. Is this an earthquake? Or... is this Antharas waking up?
Veremus knows we’re here. Be careful, he will be very angry because we killed a lot of wyrms!

You can’t stop us with this.
Veremus! Tell us everything you know about the Blood King!
I shall go with you instead. Cara is only a dead weight in such condition. Hurry, there’s no time.
I would like to help, but I don’t think I’m capable of doing so...
Why are you going in such a dangerous place! You think you have nine lives or what?! Help me here instead!
We have the teleportation stone. We must destroy the Blood King. Time is running out.

There, there’s the Blood King.

No one’s leaving unless the other’s dead.
I’m... done... take the essence... and leave now... save the Protection Tree...

Oh no... Celin... we must head to the Protection Tree now. It won’t last much longer.
Let’s use this teleportation stone.
I can’t let Celin’s sacrifice go to waste. Use the essence on the Protection Tree!
Return the essence to its rightful place...
The Protection Tree has been restored... Wow... Our mission is finally complete... Thank you... We are truly grateful, <YellowBold>[player]</>...
The Goddess Eva must have guided us to meet <YellowBold>[player]</>. It is truly a blessing. The elves who left here and the land will both return soon. Thank you.
Celin!! You’re alive? I thought you were dead...
Wh-what is happening? I... was dead...

Meow! This is all very touching, but I must be on my way to gather the supplies Hardin ordered.

I’m heading to Oren. [player], would you join me? Follow me if you will. So long, elves!
Saving me from the Orc Stronghold was one thing, but the salvation of our people... I am truly grateful! It’s sad that we have to part ways, but I hope we will meet again!

Outsider... No, I mean... [player].

My life is yours from now on. My bow is always ready, waiting for your call.

And... thank you.
<YellowBold>[player]</>, when you need our help, please call us. If it’s you, <YellowBold>[player]</>, we will be there. Thank you.
Let’s cross the road! This area is practically a maze, so don’t get distracted! Let’s go, a hunter I know is waiting.

I heard from the secret merchant about you. An adventurer, right? I was an adventurer once...

I am gathering capable people, you think you fit that description? Can you deal with the cougars?

I will be at the post, come to me when you defeat them.
You’re more than capable. Good! You need a job? I will offer you one. We should clear the area. There are too many Rabid Cougars here.
Ah, pesky beasts! Ha! No matter how many you kill, they keep coming. It’s fine by me, because they taste okay. Come to think of it, shall we gather some cougar meat?

Oh! The secret merchant is waiting in front of the bridge.

I owe the secret merchant a lot, will you deliver cougar leather to the merchant as a gift? Thanks!

I will be across the bridge, I have things to do!
Wow, how nice of him! I shall sell this one too! There’s a problem. Var’s herb box has been taken by the spiders. We have to get it back!

Did the secret merchant like the leather? Good!

I am gathering weapons that hunters deserted. There are many useful items here. Will you help me?
Save money, and money will save you! Anyway, since hunters are busy these days, there are a lot of prey just wandering about. We should hunt them for money!
I’m short on energy these days, that spider should help me a bit... a young person like you would not understand, ha ha! Oh, I may look young, but I’m old... My bones are cold!
The secret merchant has been wounded by a cougar ambush. My box of herbs should be near the merchant, go find the herb box and the secret merchant.
Thank you for coming. I could have died out here! I must have my revenge against those cougars. Make sure to bring the cougar claws while avenging me!
Now there’s nothing worthy here anymore! Let’s cross the bridge and head to the hunter campsite!
Why is this place like this? Looks like hunters had a fight here... where’s the hunter who guided us? How rude!
I have to investigate the Giran hunters, but they are not cooperating. Will you help me?
Hah! Is everyone from Giran a spy? Since when were hunters discriminated by their hometowns? Act like this and I’ll leave! Tell that to that hunter!
I have no choice... It’s very bad out there. People get arrested when they are from Giran! It’s for the good of all! Please continue with the investigation!
Trust me! Are you doing this because I’m a hunter from Giran?
Look at that... there really is a spy out there. We can trust no one! This is bad... Less hunters mean more monsters... Hey! Bugbears are coming again! Quick, come here!
We must stop them! If they cross the bridge, they will ruin everything!

There were too many hunters in the past, we were almost out of prey! Ha ha, those were the good old days. The merchant? He left a minute ago, said that he’s heading to Oren. I will take you to him, follow me.
This reminds me of the past. There were tons of prey when the campsite was just beginning, just like today! Everyone was competing for a larger prize! What do you say? Will you challenge me?
I can’t beat a young fellow, ha ha! Most of the young lads have gone to the town, since townspeople have been offering escort jobs. Hey, why are they gathered like that over there?
That violent bugbear is a perfect protein supply for hunters! Since we’re here, might as well grab some! Help me, ha ha!
There! The merchant you’ve been looking for seems to be stuck! Always clumsy like that. Alright, go on now. Hunters always travel around, so I’m sure we will meet again somewhere! Ha ha!
I can’t miss an opportunity like this! See the weapons the bugbears are wielding? Those are very expensive maces! Go get them!
Trouble! Bugbears are very angry! We could lose all of our goods! <YellowBold>[player]</>, let’s go! Protect me!
See that castle over there? We must be quick. If not for the business in that castle, I would not be here! Ugh, what use is money when I die?! Deal with these Dicors!
Hey, wait... Why are you not bringing the Dicor petals? You did all the work, but didn’t care to bring the petals? You can’t be rich like that! Go! Bring them!
Get in! Products should be sold in good timing to maximize profits!
A Silverlight Mercenary. You may pass. Martial law has been issued, so make sure to receive your pass from the archon!

The Silverlight Mercenaries guarantee your status. That’s the best you could hope for these days. Fortunately, peace will soon be upon us. The cardinal will announce the contents of a peace treaty soon.

Oh, I have a request. A merchant has been distributing fake passes in the town. Please find and deal with the merchant.
Good job! Trusty as I’ve expected! Now, I shall show you something. It’s where only few people can enter. Deliver this to the Cardinal, Krovis.
Now the atmosphere of battle shall be gone. Townspeople shall no longer fear for war, you’ve helped to lift a great burden.
Ha ha, it is. You’re going to announce it today?
Yes. News of the peace treaty should be shared with the public quickly to make the townspeople remain calm. Meet me in Giran next time.
It’s an honor to have such a noble one as <YellowBold>[player]</> deliver this important document. It is a document containing the peace treaty. Now the harsh atmosphere with Giran will be gone.
The Southern Barracks is on fire! Use the canteen near you to extinguish it!
Pursue them! Pursue the Giran assassins who killed Caranese! Giran! It’s Giran’s ploy!
The man with the bandanna went west. Please get him! He must have been from Giran! Damn you, Giran!
West! He went through the west gate! The cardinal has been assassinated, how can this be?!
What? I don’t know, never saw a man with a bandanna, I only saw that guy come out.
Why do I feel like I’m going to the evil stronghold whenever I’m with you? Ha ha, let’s go now. I’m sure there are quiet evils there too.
Why do I call them silent and evil? They expand their control silently! The entrance is already full of people. You ready? Let’s go!
Those shamans are very important for lizardmen morale. We shall defeat them first.
Ugh, archers are always unpredictable. Defeat the archers before they inflict heavy damage.
Wait, is someone there? Those pesky wizards again? Let’s go find out.
Hey, you came? This tree is what the lizards regard as the chief’s tree. Hey, see those shamans escorting the chief? Please eliminate them, ha ha ha!
Well, someone asked me for this chief’s tail for lots of money. It’s not just one of those small jobs from the townspeople! Will you help me with this? Ha ha ha! Good!
We should leave soon. We’re not here to fight every lizardman inside... Hell, we’re a bit late. Still, we should find our way out.

We secured the escape route. Theodore will be here to neutralize the Orc base. I will take it from here, you find Theodore in front of the Orc base.

There will be Orc Scouts while on the way. It’d be better if you deal with them while moving.

Orcs are quite aggressive, but they seem to be dumbfounded by the Tanor counterattack. We must stop this war in order to stabilize Oren.

Defeat the sentinel on the watchtower and join Aymel inside. She is already fighting on her own.

Hey, if you’re late again you will do my work for me! This begins now!

Go defeat those Timak Orc Fighters!
Take those Orc Archers. I can’t move because of them!

Over there, [player]. Look wayyyyyyyyy over there, you see it? The evil summoning stone. And a shaman.

There’s a simple solution. Destroy it promptly.

The Dark Brotherhood must be involved. There’s no reason Orcs would act like that otherwise. The Dark Brotherhood must have their own dirty reason, right?

Ooh, that Timak Orc Warchief is coming for you! He looks pretty strong!

Hey! [player]! A Soulstone! There’s a Soulstone!

Destroy that Soulstone! If the Warchief revives, I will take him!
Now only the minions remain. Let’s sweep them fast!
Damn, Silenos were here. When did such a battle happen... Please examine the Silenos corpses! If the clash was recent, then they could be aware that the Orc Leader is gone...
Let’s go, I arranged to meet the Tanor Herald over there to end this war. I hope we can stop fighting this time.
I wonder why heralds prefer places like that... I hate these high Bridges... Why the hell is this area full of high bridges... I really hate high grounds...
Hey, what are you doing? Are you mad? Why did you kill the herald?! You... you... ugh, there’s no choice now. Peace is not an option, we must storm inside!
Theodore is supposed to help us from the inside. Find Theodore.

Silenos are thorough with their vengeance. They’ve been training in this warrior training ground. They didn’t plan to stop until all Orcs were annihilated. We have no choice but to defeat the warriors.
This is the first time I feel sorry for the Orcs. There are Orc corpses inside the training grounds. Let’s cremate them.
I didn’t want this to happen with the Silenos, but sometimes things happen regardless of intentions. They think we’re siding with the Orcs. Get ready, and survive this one!
Ah, I should rest here. The sentries must be observing us in the post. Defeat them. Also, I dispatched Aymel, so finish this war along with her. Make sure she is unharmed.

Ugh, these guys are too simple. Do they even care about their own lives when fighting?

Did the Dark Brotherhood use mind tricks on them or are they always like this? Let’s defeat those Elite Soldiers before they get us first.
Do you know these simple brutes are peaceful farmers? Check those crops if you don’t believe me.
Now we reached where the Tanor Highchief is. You reckon he’ll talk to us? I think he will draw his sword... But let’s try it since Theodore ordered us to.
Damn! Swords drawn! At least we tried.
Fortunately, they will not kill us because we have the Breka Orc Chief’s head. But will the shamans do the same? We should be ready just in case.
Wow, Hardin?! Hardin is here! Let’s go!
Welcome. Looks like you solved the dispute in this area. Great work. I came here because the situation is shifting very quickly. We will move quickly, time is running out.
Are you ready to enter the land where time has stopped? I shall leave first, there’s an urgent mission for me. Theodore will be waiting.

This land feels like it’s floating in the middle of time, without life or death.

Quiet and static... at least it should be that way, but it’s changing. Those dead reapers wandering here, at least this area seems alright for now.
Only things which are neither dead or alive wander here. People who head for the Ivory Tower sometimes end up here, so we should eliminate these things for the people.
You will feel it when you’re near. Will you catch the Walking Fungus? It will spill its spores and die, gather the spores.
The land is already full of the dead. Could you defeat them?
It’s not supposed to move, but for whatever reason, it is now. I don’t interact well with things like that, but it’s probably near us...
I wonder if you’re really as good as they say. Soul Collectors are a fitting opponent, so defeat them. I will be the one to determine whether or not to take you.

Did you see the land of the dead? It looks vastly different from the land that is dead because of a dragon. The idea that elves are a symbol of life is something to laugh at.

This land is dead because of the elves. When they were going to be expelled from the continent, they poured magical energy disregarding the consequences, and the result is this mess.
The only benefactors from destroying the barrier device are monsters... Then who are the Barrier Watchman here transmitting our information to?
What the hell! I really hate Weavers. I defeated a bunch of them before you arrived, but there are still so many left. It wasn’t like this before... Well, act now, think later!
The Ivory Tower Wizards would not leave it like this... there must be something wrong with the barrier device.
Master told me that the continent is in danger. So is that what this is about? Hmm...
I came here because Theodore was coming! What an elusive guy... Did he leave already?

Anyways, this area is supposed to control the barrier maintenance device, but the wizards managing it are all gone.

No traces of any attack, only the lack of wizards. We should investigate the area for clues.

So the wizards have left... Then, no one is tending to the device.

But even still, the device should not be damaged... I feel a familiar energy nearby. Search for it!
Oel Mahum...? This isn’t their territory... Defeat them all. They should not be here. I must inform Karen of this.

I should check the condition of the devices. I can’t even see because of those Oel Mahum!

Why are they making things difficult for Theodore! I’ll get rid of these Oel Mahum.
The collapsed barrier device is being destroyed even faster because of the Oel Mahum. It’s not just Theodore’s problem anymore, at this rate, the entire continent will be in danger!
We must preserve as much as possible! Defeat those Oel Mahum Workers and reclaim the barrier device fragments!

We should prevent this from further damage.

We need to watch out for the Oel Mahum especially... they tend to steal anything they can.

Evils and monsters are increasing, this land is near death. It’s not a real solution, but defeat anything you see.

Grandis Destroyers... are not a huge threat, but let’s get rid of then for now. We don’t have time to think.
This is not Theodore’s energy. Not black magic either.. but we should check.
Don’t worry. Wizards have been dispatched to rebuild the barrier, they will be here soon. I am clearing the area, will you help me?

I made the contact go around in order to mask our identity. The contact shouldn’t have arrived at Ivory Tower yet... Someone’s been watching the barrier device.

I don’t want to help the Ivory Tower Wizards, but if this goes down everyone’s done for, so we should help until real help arrives. Defeat the Oel Mahum.
They’re rather persistent, aren’t they? Where the hell is Karen? Find her for me.
I want to keep it as a souvenir, could you fetch them for me? It’s been a while I received a gift, and I like flowers... Theodore never brings any gifts...
What is this? Someone dropped this!
What is this!! Ugh, it’s not dangerous, but what a nuisance! Let’s get rid of them!

Let’s see... the wizards are all leaving. I should guard the area since Theodore told me to...

I have no idea what’s going on, but it looks like there’s a witness. Let’s follow them. Theodore told us to help the Ivory Tower Wizards but... let’s just get rid of these guys and get moving!
See what the arrogant elves have done here. Kill anything you lay your eyes on. They are not lifeforms.

If Karen asks for something stupid, refuse it. You saw the dead land earlier, right? This is the true dead land. There are no lifeforms here.

It’s full of Spore Fungus which are only useful for Karen’s potions. Let’s take their spores.
Calm down, they’re just monsters. They’re not people, but monsters surrounded by dark energy. Do you think you can handle it?
Karen must be wandering around, gathering her potion ingredients. Must have forgot that we’re looking for the witness. I really want to just leave her here.

Do you know why this area has become such a strange place? War. Elves and humans fighting for the continent.

Now only monsters remain here. That’s the truth behind this place. Those monsters are the remnants of greed. Let’s remove them, they don’t belong here.
Makes sense that dragons wouldn’t have a problem staying here. Offspring of the goddess of destruction. The beginning of a disaster. They should be gone. The master would have wanted it too.

The elves and humans killed the land while battling for it. And the winner, the humans, did their best to hide this land.

Take a good look. This is the true face of greed. I want to erase this entire area.
I told you, it’s full of magical energy. It may sound avaricious, but let’s take some Grotesque Mushrooms...
Looks like the owner of the diary dropped something else!
Since I don’t know the destination, I can’t use teleportation... Soul Eater... Soul Eaters are biting the clothes!
I’m not good at finding traps... What should we do? Since Theodore is reliable... shall we ask him?

Destroying the barrier device is a large risk, but why inform the Ivory Tower right away?

It would have been better to wait until the situation got serious. I am looking for the witness here, join me. Defeat the Water Seers to preserve any evidence.

Oddly, time is not right.

Damn, the Obsidian Golems just gobbled up a bag. It could belong to the witness, so we have to get it.

Being able to check the status Ivory Tower Wizard’s barrier device means that someone has been observing the device for a long time.

There, a cloak similar to what the Soul Eater had!
We must hurry. You think you’ll be able to follow along alright? Be wary of the Spore Spiders!
Not sure what’s ahead, but there’s no time. And someone’s waiting for us at the bridge.

What pleasure to see a familiar face. Is the great Hardin alright?

It’s too bad you won’t be able to send my regards. You’ll die here.

The witness is here.

What’s this? It’s a magic stone, but I don’t know what it does. Have you seen anything like this?
Since it’s right beside the bridge, the spell may be connected with the location. Did a wizard release lycanthrope here?
Why should someone head here instead of the Ivory Tower? That stone seems intact.
Someone must have destroyed it with purpose, but it couldn’t be the spell caster... The Dark Brotherhood is still here. Monsters are rampant with black magic. Defeat them.

I saw one of the Dark Brotherhood fallen on the way. Looks like the owner of the diary is here somewhere. There are too many monsters considering there’s no death energy here.

They have been released on purpose. No idea why, but they are obstacles which must be defeated.
There’s only the Dark Brotherhood... None of these look like the owner of the diary. Let’s get rid of them all.
Then all we have to do is follow the stones. We don’t know how many of them are here, so hurry up. They have too much dark energy to have been released by a wizard.
Looks just like a flower, right? It would be pretty if combined with the other flowers I have! What do you think?
I need to be more careful! A Phantom Spirit...? In a place like this? I think we’re almost there!!
We should give her some water. She needs to calm down first.
Promised to come for help... but... didn’t. I trusted... but monster... monsters!
That’s... not the monster... I released... can’t... control...

The witness is too unstable, and the Dark Brotherhood has been shaken off too easily.

There’s definitely something else... I will take the witness, you take care of the Soul Slashers.

The plan has been thwarted because the Ivory Tower noticed too quickly.

What do you say? Shall we kill the rat, or let it go?

Her condition is getting bad. She may fall into panic soon. We must leave at once.

Defeat the Vampire Bats, I will protect her on the way.
This... this is not the place I arranged for! This can’t be... there! Someone’s over there!

You had some cute tricks, but we had some too... What do you think? Were you surprised?

That kid is going to die, shivering like that... So allow me to kill her myself!

Do you know why I always spare you? Your activities are useful sometimes.

Even now. Hoho. I shall kill you the next time I feel like it!

Did that stone activate a teleport spell here?

Whatever, let’s get out of here. Damn bats, I defeated tons of them and there’s still so many left!
A precious... grave... gave me ingredients... give it some... flowers... to make it comfortable...
I heard that some potion ingredients can only be found near the grave. We should gather herbs while we’re here. The witch looks like she needs it, and we should also be prepared.
We can’t stay much longer. Shade Attackers can be a threat to the panicked witness. Defeat them.
I don’t want to do this, but we have to head for Ivory Tower. Let’s contact the master while moving.
I shall report to the master that we’re heading to the Ivory Tower. While I’m doing that, could you gather Ruin Basilisks poison?

The Dark Brotherhood may be tracking us. Since we have an unstable witness, we should minimize combat.

I have to report our exact location to the master, will you investigate the flag near the castle to determine our location?

The Elmoreden Empire’s flag... we’re in the direction of the Ivory Tower, but not inside Oren Territory. If this is an old ruin, there could be Oel Mahum bandits here.

Let Karen calm the witness down, we should look for supply items nearby.
Where the hell is Karen? She really never stays in once place. I guess she took Molly somewhere...

This is near the Oel Mahum Bandits, right? The ones that wandered near the barrier device. We can’t leave them here.

The master would agree with me! There are Bandit Rookies over there, we must remove the sprouts!

We can’t compare them to the Dark Brotherhood, but these guys are evil too! Leave them here, and the dark energy will grow!

Now let’s get to it!
Where’s Molly? Hey? She was with me a few minutes ago!
We must head to the Ivory Tower... Something’s happening! That must be why no one came to me!!

There’s an Oren soldier. Oren soldiers usually don’t go near Ivory Tower...

What is happening there? There really may be something going on... What should we do?

Ah... a Silverlight Mercenary. The captain will allow you to join the operation.

If you defeat the bandits and bring their heads to the captain, it should make things easier.

The guys you’ve defeated outside of the castle were a threat, but the main force is elsewhere. We must defeat the ones inside this castle as well.

The soldiers are ready, so let’s begin the operation!
Don’t stop, keep attacking! Don’t allow them to recover!
The enemies out front are not aware of us yet We shall strike now, don’t let them escape. The mission is to annihilate the bandits.
I leaked a false information of the merchants’ movements, so a traitor would be here to deliver the news. We must find the traitor!
What? I’ve been compromised? Ha! Do you think you can hold your own against all these bandits?

The bandits drove off the merchants passing here. Parasites feeding on Oren’s economy!

The order is to retrieve pillaged items. Some of them will be retrieved right now, and the remaining items will be processed after reporting to the lord.

The bandit boss is still on the loose! If we lose the boss, the operation is a failure!

Search anywhere the boss might be hiding!
Whew, I thought we lost the boss! That was close! Let’s get him before he runs away!!
Theodore should be taking Molly, right? I like Theodore, but he’s very thick skinned... I should check on Molly.
I was looking for a prisoner. The prisoners are missing merchants, they must be imprisoned somewhere since there are no corpses. We must rescue the prisoners.
Karen said we should get rid of the bandits while getting out of here... I think we’d better get going.
Wait! I heard... an explosion! It’s where Karen and Theodore were headed! Let’s go!

This is Forest of Evil. Only monsters should be here, but the explosion... Karen’s looking for the source.

Plants have been altered, it must not be an ordinary bomb. Orc corpses... There may be surviving Orcs here, approach with caution!

Only corpses around here... Did the Orcs make the bomb? Orcs capable of making a bomb with such strong magical energy...

Shh. Did you hear that? Something... Something’s coming!!
Did Karen find the location? I hope Orcs didn’t attack her...

The Orcs... I saw them. I defeated some of them. Isn’t this black magic? How can it be possible when the Ivory Tower is so close...

Now there are evils? What the hell?!
Shh! Don’t make any sound... Move silently. There was a battle in the front. That’s where the explosion took place.
First, we must notify the Blood Ranger Captain that those wizards are bad guys. We can’t do this without backup.
Hm... the Dark Mystics involved with the Orcs can’t be the ones we’re rescuing. Defeat those Dark Mystics first!
How could we not know of the Orcs set up here... We lost so much information due to the bandits. We shall strike the Orc camp right away. Start with the area around us.
What are you doing, I can’t even call you Oren soldiers. Some of the Orcs are still alive.
That bomb still active. We must show it to the master. Bring it here! The black magic is one thing, but that bomb is something else.. It should be investigated.
Trouble! Orc Seekers! They came after the explosion! At this rate, the Orcs are going to find us first!
There seems to be an Orc camp, but Oren can’t allow Orcs here. Let’s get in. Deal with the sentries quickly, would you like to join us?
Deal with the archers first. With them around, casualties are inevitable. Defeat them quickly!
Never forget that Orc Warriors are the most dangerous of all Orcs. Defeat them first!
What the.. the Orcs really made the bombs using black magic... Defeat the ones making the bombs!
Show no mercy! Destroy the bomb wagons! Don’t let them attempt to start a war again!
Where’s Karen? We must leave! Tell Karen!
Fool! Why did you detonate the black magic bomb?! Do you think Orcs are deaf? They’re going to swarm in here!

Wait, Timak Orc Shamans are doing something here... a black magic ritual? Damn... it really is black magic! No! We must defeat those shamans.

There are escorts over there... hurry!

Our stars are just not aligning, are they? We seem to be slowly getting closer over time though, don’t you think? You see, they had this large nebulite fragment, so I taught them how to use it!

But they refuse to hand me the bombs! Well, we can’t trust any bipedal entities, can we? Same goes for you. It’s time for you to go!

Hm... It’s really unfortunate, but since you have no intention to join me... It’s time for us to part ways.

I have a very very important mission, so play with my kids instead!
<YellowBold>[player]</>! Come here! Molly is panicking, help me!

Nebulite? The ancient meteor that fell in the Ivory Tower crater? The Orcs had it?

Ah, but we have to leave anyway! Molly’s not the only one in danger right now. The dark energy is increasing here.
The Orcs are following us! Wait, Orcs are in the front too!
Let’s head to the Ivory Tower... This area is so full of bleak energy and scary people.. and I fear for the Ivory Tower.

The post is deserted and ruined...

Something must have happened here...

This looks like it was done by a monster. They shouldn’t be able to enter the Ivory Tower’s post...

Too many suspicious things are going on... We must hurry. If Karen was half as gentle as Molly, we would be already there! Where the hell is she now?

Hey, look at these purple flowers! How pretty! Let’s gather these purple flowers and give them to Molly!

She must have been terrified, she has been trying to hide her fears...

According to Theodore, the master will never come near the Ivory Tower. So all we have to do is to make sure that the Ivory Tower is alright.

That’s what I want too. I will gather my strength. Let’s defeat those golems and get going!

The monsters are powerful here. It’s likely because of the nebulite. I read it in the books...

Karen wanted to study the bombs; do you think she would like it if we gathered the nebulite fragments for her?

I want to meet someone in the Ivory Tower... I have to ask why didn’t he come for me.

Hey, isn’t that Monster Eye looking at us? Urk... We have to hurry and give this to Karen...

Monsters are strangely rampaging here. This is abnormal even with the nebulite...

Some of them look similar to the ones in the Wasteland. We should defeat them before they threaten us, but be sure to check for black magic.
L-look out! Monsters! Monsters are coming! Argh!!!

Normally, evils would fight over the center of the crater where the nebulite energy is high, but all of sudden they came straight to the post...

There are civilians near the Ivory Tower, it worries me. We must head that way! There are evils remaining here, please defeat them!
Trouble! Combat in the front! That campsite’s where the civilian envoy is staying!
Whew, that would do for now. What is happening... I have to report the Sentry Post ambush, so I should find an Ivory Tower Wizard. Will you help me?

The wounded are Oren’s envoy. I told them that they can’t go inside, but since they were under attack while waiting here, the tower’s in a tight position now.

There are too many that are wounded here, I can’t use the healing magic on all of them. Will you help me find the medicine box?

Are you... with Molly?

It’s good to know that Molly is still alive... tell her that I’m glad to know that she’s okay...

So he knew that I was in danger. I thought there was a reason for his absence...

I risked my life... But mere words of concern... If I wasn’t okay, that would have left me an idiot. Ah, I don’t want to think about this...
Black magic... What the?! Molly is under the effect of black magic! No!

You’re going to kill Molly? No, there’s got to be a way! We’re not sure, but it must be because of the Ivory Tower Wizard!

Theodore may know something!

It requires massive magical energy, and I can’t guarantee that she will be restored...

Wait, so you left her there alone? Their target is not us, but the Ivory Tower!

I will contact my master, you defend the Ivory Tower with the Ivory Tower Wizards!

I hate their twisted pride, but what they are guarding is important.

There must be a Soul Fragment. Defeating the transformed evil won’t kill it, but defeating it several times will damage it.

We must find and retrieve the Soul Fragment while doing it. That’s how we can restore it. If the Dark Brotherhood takes it, there’s no way we can do it.
The Soul Fragment must not be destroyed, it is irreversible! Bring the Soul Fragment and Molly to the master!

Looks like Karen’s shocked. But wasn’t Elizabeth around the Soul Fragment? That’s strange... She normally guards important items personally...

Wait! I thought the Ivory Tower would be safe without Molly... Check! Right now!
It’s not all of it, but it is still dangerous enough. Saying that should be enough. I’m not only sending the Ivory Tower Wizard, but I will officially request help from the Silverlight Mercenaries.

Our mission was a complete failure... the nebulite stored in the Ivory Tower has been taken.

I will contact the master immediately. We will head to Dragon Valley. The master told me that that is the most dangerous area, so if anything happens it will be there.

Let’s go to Dragon Valley using the teleportation stone.

There’s no time to think now.
Dragon Valley is near, we must hurry.
Venetor was the first human to defeat draconians. As a symbol of human supremacy, his tomb has been placed here. That merchant’s selling a special powder, go get it.
This? It’s a powder made of dragon bones! Burn this powder in front of the great hunter Venetor’s grave! He will watch over you, adventurer!
Not sure it’s because of Venetor, or the wish of Humans, but Draconian descendants and evils do not come here. But cross that bridge and we will immediately be met with Draconic Minions.
After battling with the gods, Antharas has been resting here with severe wounds. The dragon is sucking up the energy from the land, cursing it. There are cursed entities over there. Defeat them.
An evil summoning stone is here! So the Dark Brotherhood have passed here. Destroy the evil summoning stone and pursue them!
It’s horrible, but that’s why we can’t give up. Defeat that Dark Knight!
There seems to be too many strange entities around here. Do they wish to stall us like this? Huh? Is that the master over there?
The Dark Brotherhood craves magical energy they can’t even control. Giant’s relics, elven crystals, and even nebulite... When I found out what that means, it was too late. Help me, please.
It’s bad. The draconian descendants are rampant as if they are demons. We must put down the worst ones first. Be careful, they are dangerous even in a normal state.
Theodore is already there. While I deal with issues here, you go help Theodore. Hurry!
I already told the master, but this place has been searched by someone else already. We’ll catch them soon. We shall deal with Demon's Handmaidens easily.
It’s getting worse. Demon's Handmaidens... Rumor of Antharas summoning demons to guard while it rests was true... They must not stay in this realm... Defeat them.
I need to check if a mind control spell was used on the evils, like back at the Ivory Tower crater. Defeat the Drake and bring its heart.
No traces of black magic... There’s only one who can influence the evils like this. We must hurry... come closer.
Draw their attention with my apprentice while I go forward. I can’t deal with the draconian descendants here right now. I will use the dark energy they’re drawn to, so get ready.
Looks like the master is very adept at handling the dark energy... Wait! Did the ground shudder? What is happening? Damn, you take on the Draconic Minions!
Everything is going berserk, we must evacuate! Meet me north of here!
Something’s happening. Is the master running late... I hope he’s alright. Get ready, the monsters are coming... I hope that we may survive.
It’s over... For now. We must catch up soon... Or we’ll end up as Drake food... Hah...
Over there, a fortress. So humans were here... Let’s hide inside for a while... I need to rest a bit.
This is bigger than I expected... What is this place? Ugh... Are there any medicine boxes here?
The supply boxes are almost empty? Soldiers must have left here pretty recently. They must have been stranded here for a long time, why were they staying here? Wait, is that a Giran flag?
Oren’s army inside Giran Territory, stranded and dying here... Ugh, I have to use a healing spell on myself, can you deal with that Kaim Vanul?
Giran must have been aware that there were Oren forces here, but they were left here to rot. No reinforcements ever came. Is that a corpse? Stop those evils from eating it!
An Oren soldier dying in Giran land. I don’t know the whole story, but his only sin was following orders. And that’s how he was deserted. Let’s cremate the corpse.

Before we go, remember what I’m telling you. Trust no one but yourself. Never forget that. The only one you could trust in the end is only yourself. That’s all I can tell you. The master is up ahead. Let’s go.
I tried to hurry, but I ended up late. Half success and half failure... First, defeat the ones going for the scattered nebulite fragments.
We can’t give up yet. During the ritual, it looks like they couldn’t contain the powerful energy and it resulted in an explosion. I have to recover the nebulite, will you clear the pests for me?
There was a giant’s altar here. Now I know why they were obsessed with the giant’s ruins. Damn them! Recover the remaining nebulite fragments on the altar. We can’t leave those any longer.
Oh, but you’re already too late! Destroying the nebulite, stopping the ritual, your puny efforts were meaningless. He will be resurrected and you won’t live to see it!
To commend your efforts so far, I shall personally fight you!
Right, they’ve woken Antharas. Fortunately, Antharas is not fully awake, but they will wait for another opportunity. First, we must defeat the Dark Brotherhood before they escape. This way.
That way! Let no one escape! Beleth must not know that the ritual has been even partially successful! Go stop them, right now!
There are rifts in the land. This is not normal... It’s dangerous but I have to examine them closely.
No! It’s dangerous! This is a zone where Antharas summoned the demons to guard its rest! And that zone’s floor is rupturing!
Demons are coming out! We must stop them! Even if the ritual has been stopped in the middle, Antharas will be awake if it’s stimulated like this!

I’ve received news that the Dark Brotherhood are still here.

We must defeat them all to make the ones on the outside believe that they’ve failed. To buy more time, make sure they are truly dead.
If Antharas is awake, the demons guarding the dragon will become more powerful. We should defeat them now.
More Dark Brotherhood over there! Defeat them quickly, before they start another ritual.

Hm... If the demons keep coming, the world will fall into chaos even before Antharas is revived. I should carve a rune in the rift to block them. Runes require demon blood. Bring me blood from the demons.
Well done. I’ve set a magic gem to stop the rift. Help me activate it.
The draconians are coming for the rift. Defeat them.
Damn! When Elizabeth was dying, she must have cast a curse on Theodore. To lift the curse, we need both blue and red essence from the demons. First, defeat the Blood Queen for the blue essence.
There’s no time. Bring the red essence from nerkas and Headless Knights. I will be in front of Venetor’s grave.
We’re lucky the makeshift reagent weakened the curse... We’ve done everything we could here.

Draconian descendants going berserk, and demons coming out are evidence enough. This battle dealt heavy damage to us too. Let’s return now and find a way to stop Antharas from resurrecting.

Stand in front of me, and I will send you to Giran Town.
How may I help you? Did the Port Master send you?
Back so soon? You’re better than I thought.
We’ve got trouble! An Orc raiding party is attacking the port!

Who? Ah! You must be the one sent by the Guard Captain.

Thank you for coming.

You say you found this equipment from bats? There shouldn't be any bats out here!

Hmmm, I wonder what pushed the bats out of their natural habitat...
So, it was the Orcs! And they've locked up my colleagues?! Oh, you got the key!
Thank you for freeing me! My work brought me out here. I didn't expect to be almost killed by those filthy Orcs!

The Guards are just about to finish mopping up.

You've saved my colleagues and this excavation! Thank you!

Hey, what are you doing to those Vampire Bats?

What? Feldheim asked you to kill them? He should reduce the workload instead of killing those silly things!

Oh, you don't know- Feldheim is my dad. He’s worried more about me than about the excavation.
Welcome, trusted one. I’ve been waiting for you. I am the Purifying Fairy guarding the barrier.

A monster like Gorsaur inside the barrier?! This shouldn’t have happened.

Something big is going on. We must activate the purification device with haste.
Up for some fishing? Huh? A favor for Niah? Ah, another sucker falls for her tricks. Don’t feel bad, it’s what she’s good at.

Oh, that’s a lot. Now let’s begin!

Hey, why don’t you try fishing for yourself? There may be a fishing contest here, maybe take a look around.

I am Terre. Niah went that way- said she had some urgent business.

You might find Niah if you hurry.
Th...thank you. I got my wagon back!

That does it. Where was I? Right, when I regained my conscious, I was on a wagon, going somewhere...

I escaped by rolling off of it as hard as I could. Seems being fat has some uses...
Suspicious people? Too many people move through here to pay attention to “suspicious people.” We only have time to look for wanted people.
Abduction? Hmm, there are some Adventurers who’ve gone missing, perhaps it’s related. I’ll order an investigation.
That was incredible! No wonder they’re calling you the Hero of Talking Island Harbor!
Huh? You? Welcome back! I saw your feats on the port.

This is a rare opportunity, so don’t miss out!

You can’t be a mercenary with bad equipment!

That was a true monstrosity. Without your help, casualties would have been very high.

My men are all grateful for this.
Marvelous. I knew you’d do it. Try the <YellowBold>Arena</> when you have some time. It’s one of the best ways to gain fame in Aden.

You’re [player]? I heard about you from Russel. Can you assist me while waiting here?

Talking Island has several incidents going on, so we’re short on hands.

Okay, this will do.

Have you heard of the Ivory Tower? Believe or not, we’re right under it right now.

Einhovant Arcane Academy is connected to the Ivory Tower’s basement.

Good, now let’s go after the prize.

I guess I can’t keep the secret from you anymore. We’re looking for the Elven Coronet.

It has the power to allow one to pass through the barriers of Talking Island.

Huh? You brought the supplies? Did the soldiers ask you? They should be disciplined.

Ah, the message from the Archon. Well done.

I have been watching you.

I am Theodore of the Silverlight Mercenaries.
As I thought, you still need some training... but you have the gift.
Oh, thank Einhasad that you’re here. I lost Niah!
Argh! Hey! I don’t want to stay here any longer!

You’re [player]? First, I’d like to thank you for taking care of the bodies of those fallen soldiers.

Looks like you’ve done a great deal in the East. Incredible.
Whew, I’m okay now. That was close.
Burning the cape summoned monsters, eh? Then they may be the ones I’m after.

Th-thank you! I thought I was going to die!

I was paralyzed, unable to move because of those foxes. I hate foxes!

This is the mark of an Orcish axe... If Orcs are suddenly appearing in the East with these kind of axes...

Orcs only cut down trees to build base camps. They must be somewhere nearby.
We meet again, <YellowBold>[player]</>. Seems these Orcs are related to the ones I am looking for. We should work together.
I’m okay... the defensive magic kicked in...

Oh, it’s you! You’re the one meddling with our plans. I was beginning to suspect I’d have to look for you, but here you are.

You may call me Elizabeth - you’ll die with my name on your lips!

I felt tremendous Mana. What happened? Did you meet someone?

A Dark Elf woman?

Hmm... It can’t be...

I found everyone but Niah.

I can’t wait around like this. Will you join me in searching for her?

This is Niah’s hat and bag. Looks like the Kidnappers took her somewhere else.

Oh, Niah! Please stay alive!

Einhasad, why are you doing this to me!
Welcome. I’ve been waiting for you.
A Monster Summoning Stone. It’s a rare thing... they must be more powerful than we thought.

Here we are.

Look, there’s a light!

We found it.
A curse...I shall alert the Rangers. Thank you for the info.
Oh, my head! I tried to stop the black robed ones entering the spirit forest... but I can’t remember anything after that...
So the skeletons here are the result of that Monster Summoning Stone. With the Elven presence here, monsters shouldn’t be able to spring up without any reason.
Oh my gosh... I really thought I was going to die... never seeing my dad again...
Now, we have the key for the last purification device. Hurry.
Welcome, I’ve been waiting for you! You have a talent of entertaining me!
You’ve returned. Well done. The dark energy is disappearing.
I’ve been watching you, <YellowBold>[player]</>! The name’s Hardin. I am the master who taught Theodore.

So the harbor is almost stabilized?

As you can see, we are barely holding the line here, there were only a few men to spare.

I should see this through before I thank you.

Who are you? A mercenary? The Guard Captain sent you?!

Good! Let’s deal with the situation first.

You brought the Einhasad Holy Artifact on behalf of the cardinal? Great! Now I can rest.

The old Holy Artifact in the Einhasad temple had been defiled. I filed a request to the Church of Einhasad to send a new one...

The Undead attack came when the new Holy Artifact was being delivered... it can’t be a coincidence.

Oh, did I say thank you?

Hey, that’s a total rip-off!

Damn cat! If not for the pirates!

Oh, you’ve come! Welcome!

Hi! Have we met before?

Missing? Are you talking about the Windmill Plains?

Whew. This is it! Meeting when we need each other, it’s destiny! You escort me, I give you info!

Come to think of it, there was an important witness.

What do you say? I’ll introduce you to the witness. I owe you, after all!

Hello, knight! I am Hamel, the manager of this windmill farm.

Oh! you’re a mercenary. Knights, mercenaries, they are all welcome to us farmers. Heh heh.
My lord, what happened to that plant?! I’ve been a farmer my whole life, never seen a plant die like that.

No! I won’t go!

Oh... I thought you were one of the Guards.

How did I know? This is a no-brainer.

People coming around these days, they’re either Guards or others related to the case. And strange things began in the north.

I was only observing the incidents.
Huh? Hey, are you really going in there?
Hey, it’s been a long time!
Well, what brings you to this land of sorrows?
Did you find something? Or nothing so far?
...Eleanor? That can’t be right. She recently vanished!
That piece of the bracelet... it fits with what I’ve found. Do you believe me now?
You found the bracelet? So did we see a ghost? No... I can’t believe it.

Byron sent you?

Hm... very unfortunate.

It seems the missing townspeople were sacrificed by Black Magic...

You came to rescue me. Oh! Thank you.

I thought I was going to die. Oh, my!
Are you going into the Stronghold by yourself?
Thanks for the rescue! The dark ones captured me while passing through the graveyard!

Thank you for saving me. Who are you?

Huh? [player]?

You’re the new Silverlight Mercenary? Welcome. I am Aymel.
We meet again, <YellowBold>[player]</>! Who’s that with you? Oh, she’s who Russel has been talking about!
Just in time! I’m having trouble entering the interior. Ol Mahum’s resistance is very strong here...

So Captain Jackson sent you. It turns out the group that took the Einhasad Holy Artifact headed to Ol Mahum Stronghold.

For some reason, they never hid their tracks, taking the opportunity when soldiers moved out for search and rescue.

The remaining forces were no match for them.

What took you so long?

What? Einhasad Holy Artifact? How should I know? Why are you asking me?
Hey, a Black Magic Tome? Maybe it’s a connection. We should investigate further.

Hey, [player]! What brings you here?

But where am I? This is not the nether world, right?

Oh, damn. I have so many things to do.
Hey, do you see this? It’s an <YellowBold>elixir</> ingredient!

Seems it escaped. Aw!

Wait till I catch it! Just wait!

Just take them.

What? Why, you ask? Well, they call me “Aymel the friendly” for a reason!

Oh, greetings! I’ve been waiting for you. I wanted to thank you for recovering my goods.

Also, I have something to ask.
These are the Gludio Plains! We must pass through here if we are going to the Town of Gludio!
Thank you! I thought I was done for.

Whew... who are you? A knight?

Thank you, but it is too late for me.

Is she dead?

She was a sweet girl, dreaming about marrying a knight...
This is the Town of Gludio. Thank you. Now, I feel safe.

Fight to your dying breath! We can’t let these monsters break through our lines!

Huh? Who are you? A Silverlight Mercenary? Ah... what brings the famous Silverlight Mercenaries here?
You alright? One minute later and the lieutenant would have died. He’s being evacuated so I’m sure he’ll be fine.
Ah... I had some hallucinations. But I think I’m okay now. Thank you.
This is the middle of the battle. You look like a mercenary, what brings you here?
Did the platoon leader send you? Shhh, quiet!
Th..thank you. I owe you a lot, saving the lives of my men...
Uh, I’m okay. How are my men?

Don’t worry, no matter how corrupt the Gludio Territory is, they won’t touch me under these circumstances.

These fools can’t do anything against the Silverlight Mercenaries either.

Even claiming to be on behalf of the lord is suspicious.
Did Platoon Leader Melbourne send you? Huh? You’ve been looking for me?

Whew, we could have been stuck there. No wonder why they were so aggressive.

A place like that would make anyone crazy. Having a teleportation stone was very lucky.

They were brothers and sisters, sons and daughters- just like me and Melina.

Not sure if I’m qualified, but on behalf of the townspeople of Gludio I wish to express my gratitude to you, [player].

And thank you for being there when my sister Melina was dying.
Hi there! So you’re the new recruit everyone’s been talking about!
Finally! No matter how many times I ask for help, they never answer. It’s up to the mercenaries after all...
Hey, thank you! I thought I was done for.

Found something, [player]?

Hm... The chancellor and a Black Magic Tome...

Everything happening in Gludio is connected to the chancellor.
Time is short, so I will keep it simple.
Looks like I’m not too late!
Hey, <YellowBold>[player]</>? Didn’t expected to see you here.
Did you meet Aymel? Let’s get started!
As you suspected, this is one of the Dark Brotherhood. Seems it was disguised as the Archon to raise chaos in Gludio.
Hey, it’s been a long time, <YellowBold>[player]</>! Seems you’ve done great work here! Rumors are already spreading.

Thank you! We came here on the lord’s orders, ended up as prisoners after encountering large forces!

Never expected forces of this scale... we were blindsided... It won’t happen again. I will prepare for a counter attack.
Great job! I found the chieftain while you were smashing the forge.

Hey- [player]! You’re alive.

What? Aymel was cursed by a witch?

It is an honor to meet you, [player]. Please accept this reward from my lord. Thank you for saving Gludio.

Oh, did you meet Lonna? She’s been looking for you for some time.

Argh! I thought you were a ghost, sneaking up on me like that!
