It already chills my bones...
So there are only traces of the Advance Party, and they are not here?
The slave’s bones have traces of combat, so they must have passed here.
With a Dark Mystic involved, it makes me worry for the Advance Party.
Another trace of the Advance Party here!
A worthless shell! How dare it attack Aymel!
So... This place is called Devil's Isle with reason. It’s full of monsters...
The Advance Party! But something doesn’t look right...
Th-this is a rightful measure of defense! What the hell is going on!
What are you saying? The Advance Party attacked you?
Now it’s safer. But still far from a proper camp.
If Aiden got lost, he should be able to find us with this fire.
Aiden is still not coming. This is getting worrisome...
There was a stone enchanted by black magic?
Look at this! Another Advance Party camp! But this one looks like it’s been deserted for some time.
Is this another Advance Party soldier's diary?
Traces of the black magic, a black pattern resembling a snake... It must be! The pattern from the contract with Elizabeth!
Why are you running like that? Did you find something?
Are you alright? Looks like I made it in good time.
Did you see a succubus during combat? Hmm... A succubus in a place like this...
So... a Dark Mystic is here. We must be careful.
Whew... I can’t drop my guard even for a moment...
Just where... the hell are they coming from! I can’t concentrate on the investigation!
Not these... Could it be snipers then?
Aiden! I was looking for you, what are you doing out here! Talk to me!

So, according to you, Zaken is behind all of this? The Dark Brotherhood revived him?

Zaken... I thought it was just a legend... I can’t believe this.
Wait! I feel a strange energy.
Did you hear what they just said? Aiden and our soldier are imprisoned!
What the... Aiden... Aiden has disappeared... He was right in front of me... he vanished!
You’re awake! Do you know how worried I was?
A tremendous treasure. These must be another trap like the one before.
Now I can move around without worrying. Moving makes you feel better, no?
The area is full of treasures and traps.
If Zaken embraced the power of giants, then even I’d be no match for him...
I felt someone’s gaze after coming here... Looks like we were under surveillance.

Where did that come from? Looks like there are many secrets here.

Is this a navigation log of the pirates?
No one’s here. Where did they go?
You’re here? I saw someone like Ashear running there, but they vanished into thin air like a ghost. All that was left was this corpse...
Are there... any survivors from the Advance Party?
Damn... Why is the place where Aiden should rest so dirty?
Now... Aiden will rest in peace...
Th-this is not enough. I will find Ashear, and defeat the remaining pirates.
I will never forget the Soldier who died here. Pirates shall meet a worse fate than them.
Here! Traces of the Advance Party!
Well, I was right... but it’s been torn into small pieces, it’s difficult to read.
Done! Now I can read it!

This is the box!
The Lesser Giant's crystal is inside!
Ugh, that was good for the Silverlight Mercenaries.
Th-there is no time! Ashear is in danger! Ugh...
Now, this should be a safe place.
That was lucky. The bleeding will stop soon.
I’m alright. The cave is empty, so Ashear must have left the cave already. Are we still far from the exit?
The exit of this cave! I hear the waves splashing on the beach!
So... Everyone is dead... Captain Frederick must have seen this as well... Whew...
Are you alright? We came here before they arrived.
We can’t be emotional. Let’s find the navigation log Ashear mentioned.
Did you find anything? The navigation log?
Found it! Let’s check its contents and regroup with Captain Frederick and Theodore!

Alright, calm down, Frederick! They returned now, so wait for a moment!

[player], did you find the navigation log?
Whew, we can’t lower our guard!
Damn! I will do it my way!
It’s not enough... the Advance Party and the soldiers... I must defeat more of them!
Is this not enough? How arrogant!
Zaken’s not coming, but the Dark Brotherhood is! Is Zaken already with the Dark Brotherhood?
That giant hole over there... Looks like a byproduct of Zaken’s transformation.
Frederick doesn’t look good... It must be the wounds from the combat with the high priest.
Ugh... Not yet... I can’t die before I get my revenge!
Damn... Lost him! This is Zaken’s lair. We can’t leave him!
Good! Let’s go! It may not be too late!
Frederick’s condition... It’s too late... He doesn’t have much time left...
We must complete our mission to ensure their sacrifice was not in vain.
S-success! We entered the abyss with our bodies!
Whew... That was close. Is everyone alright?
You’re <YellowBold>[player]</> from the Silverlight Mercenaries. What brings you here?

Well done.
Such a young daughter... This is sad...
That’s strange. We were supposed to meet here... Perhaps something happened.
This is... Oren’s pattern. We were late, not the envoy!
They have the Oren soldier markings, they must be responsible for this!
Wow, I’m alive! Will you forget what I said before? Thank you for coming here!
Hurry. They will feast upon the hostages soon.
Good. Anyone who ate these shouldn’t be a problem. Take a good bite, you pigs!
That was good. We did it without being seen.

Thank you. You look like you came here for the envoy, not me...

I never thought the Orcs would get me. And I could have been sacrificed for their bloody festival, but now I’m safe.
If you’re trying to save the one called Caranese, it will be very dangerous. He’s imprisoned by the High Warchief.
Keep your head down! The High Warchief is right over there!
That will do. They won’t notice for a while even if we assassinate the High Warchief.

We actually got out of there!
We’re alive!
<YellowBold>[player]</>, go assist the elves with Cara. Let’s meet in Oren after we finish our work.
Good job. I didn’t come here to fight the Orcs... Things got complicated.
Evils came all the way here... This is very disturbing.
They were abundant in the past, now only a few of them remain...
Hey! <YellowBold>[player]</>, fancy meeting you here, meow!

The Stone Golem’s Core is used in special orders, meow, especially for sealing powerful entities.

I’m sure you have one right now, meow.

Cat got your tongue?!
Paw-fect! Now let’s go for the next item, meow!
A guest? Is this a joke? There’s no reservation. It’s only a personal friendship of yours.
Greetings. I’ve heard from Cara about you. On behalf of the guardian elves, I thank you.
Thank you. Now sick elves can be treated.
Thank you. Basilisks are no longer harassing us.
But that was not the end of our misfortunes.

They’re the Blood King’s minions, trying to take the remaining Protection Tree’s essence. The Blood King is the cause of all this...

Our Protection Tree is immortal, but the Blood King backstabbed us during the war against the draconians and stole the Protection Tree’s essence.

Protector Randol was able to secure some of it, but the Protection Tree has been weakening since.
Prepare for a long journey. We should be ready for anything.
Good, that will do! Wait, where’s that cat? It’s difficult to hide from Celin...
Wow, we really struggled against that one, but you finished it off so easily!
You’re incredible. Dealing with all those primas single-handedly...
Wow! Did you see them running after their leader died? Now we can rest easy!
I hope this will return some of the essence.
E...Elf! An elf! Gotta run, meow!
Wow! Found it at last! Thanks!
How did it know that I wanted to restore this land?

It’s dangerous to move further east from here. Let’s return to the hunters’ retreat...

Wh-what’s that? That black cloud...
Is everyone okay? What the hell is this... Why did the draconians attack this area!
If it’s not in the south, then it’s the Chasm of Oblivion... It’s a place far more dangerous.
Look who it is, it’s <YellowBold>[player]</>! Never expected to see you here!
Ha, look at them! Did I tell you how much I like you? Thank you, ha ha ha!
Huff huff... Let’s rest for a while.
In times like this, I can’t really eat in comfort.

I finished deciphering the tablet, but the contents are partial. It won’t do much by itself, but I will read it anyway.

The Chasm of Oblivion has a dimensional rift connected to the netherworld. And inside of it...

That’s it. We need more fragments to understand what it means.

I’m Guardian Elf Knight Randol... I leave this message to my descendants...

The draconians didn’t intend to start a war with the elves... Those who bleed black blood...

Wait... Guardian Elf Randol? He’s a legendary figure among us. He went missing in the chasm while pursuing the Blood King! The tablet is about him!
Thank you! But there are still a lot of evils out there.

I heard from Cara. You decided to help our excavation?

Thanks, although it’s a job offered by Hardin, your help will be appreciated.

Where?! Do you have any broken bones?

Dealing with such a monstrosity like that! You’re really awesome!
M-meow!!!! How delicious!!! Meow!!! What an exquisite and exotic taste!
It would have been better if there were no scars. Good, meow! This will still be a high-quality product.
Mrrow... This one was actually not on the list, but more for me to sell, meow!
This one is really on Hardin’s list, meow! Don’t you believe me?
You must have heard me earlier, meow. This one is very clean, it should go for a handsome purr-ice!
Meow, that was scary. Eyes that big fur-ighten me!
Meow? The leather? The leather? The leather? Did you forget the leather?!
You work well, but any thoughts on working alone, meow?
This sweet and delicious wyrm egg is the best ingredient, meow. I shall bring some of them when heading to Oren.
Very swift! You’re even faster than the hunters!
Wyrms are getting more aggressive as we get closer to Veremus’ nest.
Veremus must have noticed us. Watch out, they will go on the offensive from now on.
Where have you been! Leaving a lady in such a dangerous area... I’ve been looking for you!
Well done! Now let’s enter the enemy post. Get ready!
What a weakling... Even though the Protection Tree is dying, she shouldn’t collapse like this!
So many dragons!! What were they preparing here?
Good, we should be alright now! It would have been better if I brought all of my companions and destroyed these eggs together!
Thank you! Our Protection Tree will be safe thanks to you!
Whew... We’re alive... Even the draconians protect their younglings.
Huff... Huff... What a battle. I scouted ahead, but Cager is not inside the post! He must be in the sky...
That was truly powerful. We would be impaled if not for you! Thanks!
That will do! Let’s head to Veremus’s nest!

Veremus cooperated with him to receive the power. We were cut off by Veremus from escaping...That’s all it says.

Oh, there’s something else... Could this be the part about the Blood King? We don’t have much time.

This tablet is talking about Veremus. Let’s find its nest first.
That was... an epic battle... Ugh...
We’re here. Watch out! I don’t know much about this place either.
No... the Protection Tree restored her life... How fortunate!
This way! Come quickly, you sloth!
So you’re the friend the secret merchant mentioned!
You’re better than I thought! You look slender and weak, ha ha!
Thanks. Now I can roam around the canyon more freely.
Oh, never expected you to bring that much! We will be stuffed thanks to you, ha ha!
Such fine leather, meow! You know I like you, right?
Thanks. It would have been difficult without the herb box.
Thank you! Hunters have left so many items!
The venom sac is an expensive product. Ha ha.
Although it looks bad, the spider meat is actually full of nutrients. You should try one.
Meow! Nice of you to come!
Good! This won’t be enough, but it will do for now!
Oh, sorry! I remembered something urgent, ha ha!
There you have it... There really is a spy among us.
Never expected the bugbears to pour in like this.
The secret merchant always leaves without a proper farewell.
Ha ha, was that manageable? No matter how aggressive the bugbears are, they are just prey for us hunters.
Whew, I could have been dead. What took you so long?
Well done. Would you like to work with me?
Never lower your guard against those Dicors.
If you brought it in the first place, I wouldn’t have had to do this!
Stop! We’re searching for a spy from Giran.
Ah! I’m too old for this.
Welcome. I heard of your arrival. Please give me the peace treaty documents.
They are after us! Fend them off!
Damn... Lost them. They were here... but we lost them...
This is only the beginning. Beware of the lizardmen.
The sentinels are relatively weak, but don’t lower your guard.
Always be careful of the shaman’s curse.
The archers are no problem once you get near them.
Working in such a dangerous area... This is why I hate hunters...
Whew, that was a difficult battle.

Just in time, I see. There were no Orcs here before. They must have arrived and harassed Tanor Silenos, of all species. That started this never-ending battle. Let’s talk while dealing with the aggressive Orcs.
You’re here? We’re almost done here, good timing! Ha!
Good, good! I acknowledge your strength!
Whew, that’s better. If you see them again, crush them all!
Orcs are always a problem. And now they’re trying witchcraft!
Whew, the Warchief is formidable. It fought well.
Done? Good! Now we’re almost finished!
Did you see the traces all around here?
Hm... I have a bad feeling about this.
I hope the negotiation goes well.
Welcome. I’ve been waiting for you.
I can’t believe that they are a peaceful species.
Whew, I hope there won’t be any more conflict...
You always manage to survive somehow.
You’re late, I was wondering when you’d come.
These Elite Soldiers are pretty good.
They should have stayed at the farm.
So... there’s no choice but to defeat them.
Then let’s meet in the land where time has stopped.
This area is not influenced by time.
Did you see the land without life? Why would such a land exist? Think about it.
There’s another apprentice of the master you never met before. She’s waiting for you.
Hi there! I heard a lot about you.
So the barrier is gone because the device is broken.
There are too many monsters here. And evils too.
Karen’s here. I don’t question her skills, but she has quite the personality...
Return immediately... The Ivory Tower has recalled the mystics. The Ivory Tower has something very urgent and all mystics have been called for.
I thought so. Even without a warden, one of the barrier devices that supports the continent’s pillar can’t be destroyed like this.
The Oel Mahum is here too? This can’t be...
Wait, the Oel Mahum Workers are stealing the barrier device fragments.
One of the barrier devices being completely knocked out is a serious matter! Where’s Theodore? We must notify the Ivory Tower.
Keep watching, anything can happen now.
An unidentified wizard is near us.
Thanks for notifying me about the broken barrier.
The Ivory Tower Wizard has arrived?
Wow, there’s a flower here too. Is this because of the barrier device?
There’s something other than flowers here.
Ready to enter the horrifying lands?
Hurry, if the Dark Brotherhood already knows there’s a witness, it will be dangerous.
Why are you so surprised? Ah! Oh no...
Do you think I could get lost here? Don’t worry.
The descendant of the dragon is here.
Pay close attention to this land and the monsters.
To tell the truth, this area was the home of a horrific war, but it’s also the perfect site to gather magical ingredients.
There’s blood, just as Theodore predicted. We don’t have much time!
Wait, what if it’s a trap?
The witness can’t be a fake.
The witness notified the Ivory Tower of the device’s destruction, but seeing that she left the diary, she must have been chased by something.
There are lots of suspicious things, but the witness seems to be true.
Witness, the Dark Brotherhood, whoever it is must have passed here before us...
There’s a way out with that bridge.
A rat... Now I know who are we looking for.
No... I never saw a tombstone like this before.
One of the enchanted stones is down, the other one intact...
Where have you been? I’ve been looking for you!
I knew there would be others.
It means that this stone is hindering the Dark Brotherhood.
But these purple plants all around here... They’re so beautiful...
Ah, now is not the time... If Theodore finds out, he will nag at me.
Let’s hurry, the witness’ house is just over there.
Why... Why did you leave me alone...
A rat could have ruined everything.
Did they want to spread the Sea of Spores all over the continent or what? If we were late, everything would have been lost! Fools!
We know how to cast spells...
As always, you’re a pesky one.
Do you know how surprised I was when you suddenly disappeared?
The status of the witness is troubling, and Karen’s getting tired too.
So everything is connected to the Ivory Tower.
It’s this way, move with care.
Well done. Now this will remove our trace.
The master allowed us to head for the Ivory Tower. This is the first time... There must be an omen of something happening there.
Looks like some usable supply items are here. Let’s use it while moving to the Ivory Tower.
Shh! Quiet. You know that there are lots of bandits around here, don’t you?
Good. If we tell the Ivory Tower that we defeated them, they will treat us better.
Good. That should hurt the Dark Brotherhood.
Hmm... This is strange. It won’t work.
I wasn’t trying to escape. I suddenly thought I must head for the Ivory Tower immediately...
This is a restricted area. We are neutralizing the Oel Mahum bandits here. Do you want to join the operation as a mercenary?
The Silverlight Mercenary... Your identity is clear, and your ability to defeat the Oel Bandits is reliable too.
Good work out there. I heard about you, but seeing your skills personally is truly remarkable.
The battle is not over yet.
They knew precisely when and where the merchant was moving. There must be a spy.
Damn, caught in a place like this...
Well done. We will safely transport these goods.
I thought we were going to fail. I’m delighted!
Theodore taught me how to control the magic effectively... So I was doing some work... I don’t want to be a burden.
It’s fortunate that the prisoners are still alive.
You came here after the explosion too?
This is strange. Don’t lower your guard.
Orcs using the power of black magic... It’s as if the monsters are evolving...
Worried about me? You’re wasting your brain power.
Whew... I’ve never been here, but I didn't expect anything like this would happen near the Ivory Tower.
See the Dark Brotherhood? I thought they were looking for us, but they’re not.
The Dark Mystics are suspiciously moving around the manors...
Watch out, it may blow up.
You saved us from danger. Thanks. The soldiers were not aware of it.
We should quickly finish any combat in this area. I have a bad feeling about this place.
Don’t stop. There are plenty of them left.
The power of the Orcs still surprises me.
Since when did the Orcs become so intelligent...
Destroying that?! The Blood Ranger Captain is out of mind. Now this area will be soon taken over by black magic too!
What? Blew up all those bombs? Why?!
Whew, this is what happens when you do something without thinking. I thought I was going to die here.
You again? Can’t you live quietly, for a change?
Oh, hey, if you get in my way, you’re getting in Beleth’s way. You’re more stupid than you look!
Because the Dark Brotherhood is so close, Molly tried to run away. I barely calmed her down... Ugh...
Welcome. I just arrived here too.
The ambush happened only a moment ago.
Oh, everyone is worried about me... Thank you. This flower is so beautiful.
We’re almost there, keep your pace.
It’s remarkable that such tiny gemstones contain tremendous mana.
That’s better. Those watchers are monsters summoned for surveillance. Someone could be watching us.
We must reach the Ivory Tower at once and check this phenomenon.
The evils... suddenly raided the Sentry Post... I barely escaped but passed out... Thank you...
Whew... Looks like someone is controlling the evils on purpose...
We’re lucky. <YellowBold>[player]</> protected us from further damage.
You’re the one who helped us a moment ago. Thank you. I will report about the Sentry Post to the Ivory Tower.
The wounded are critical... They must be treated inside the Ivory Tower.
He said that it was good to know that I’m alright?
Molly... had a tremendous amount of dark energy...
It’s almost impossible to restore a human that was turned into a monster because of black magic...
The master said a nebulite fragment will be enough for the magical energy, so we must send Molly to the master!
Because the Dark Brotherhood controlling the Soul Fragment is gone, Molly didn’t turn into an evil again. Karen should bring her to the master.
The moment we were content after defeating the Blood Queen, the Dark Brotherhood ambushed us... There were few casualties, but they took some of the stored items.

This is the Haunted Necropolis.
Did my spell have errors in its calculation? Or did someone deliberately disrupt my spell?
Surprised to see such a wasteland? This is Dragon Valley. It’s Antharas’ territory. But even this land is a symbol of human supremacy. This way, there is a place we should stop at.
They say that holding this special powder helps when fighting draconians. It could be a myth, though.
How are you holding up? Don’t underestimate them.
The Headless Knight is a soul that inhibits a valiant knight’s armor.
Looks like we are pretty late. Let’s hurry.
Your power truly shines here. I remember when you were a rookie adventurer.
Welcome. I knew you’d be here. Let’s pursue them quickly.
These Boreas are normally not here. Is Antharas really about to wake up?
This all implies that Antharas is about to awaken.
Did you meet with Theodore? I want to join you, but there’s simply no time.
Are they going to revive Antharas... We must stop them!
Hm... So it’s not a mind control...
Is Antharas really about to come back to life?
I saw you and the master in combat. It’s good that you’re protecting the master.
We must not allow them to leave this canyon.
Whew. No matter how powerful you are, you must be careful here.
The evil’s attack is getting fiercer.
The best defense is offense. We either eat them or they eat us.
So this area has been destroyed too?
Isn’t this the flag of Oren? Something’s wrong.
It must have been a difficult monster. You protected me well.
Trying to eat the corpses... A monster is still a monster.
Sorry I couldn’t build a proper grave.
Now, we are all together. Prepare for the worst from now on.
Nebulite fragments spread all over the place...
The evils feel the power of nebulite and gather.
No. Was nebulite used in the giant’s altar?
Heh, came all the way here? Pesky flies!
So even Elizabeth was merely a tool.
The Dark Brotherhood are getting stronger, perhaps the nebulite is empowering them...
Well done. You bought us some time.
Good. We must eliminate anyone we can.
We can deal with them right now, but after Antharas is back it will be far more difficult to handle.
There are still so many left... Just how many are there...
Endless combat since we arrived at Dragon Valley... Let’s seal it before we get tired.
Whew, blocking the rift is only a temporary measure. It may reopen some day.
You did well. Even the draconians are strongly resisting.
A curse on Theodore... You brought the blue essence. Now bring the red essence!
The red essence. Good. I shall revive Theodore.
But, Antharas will return... The ritual has stopped, but the explosion of the altar shook the land with tremendous magical energy, and Antharas felt it too.
Antharas is awakening?! This is going to be a huge problem.
Countess of Blood’s Boudoir: Very Hard
Take the bomb from the Grenadier
Eliminate the Corrupted Golem in the cave

Oh, you’re part of the Silverlight Mercenaries! Thank god you’re here... I have no idea what’s going on.

The last I heard from our friend, Laenis, was that the atrocious Orcs invaded the Timak Orc Shaman Village and were destroying it.

I have no idea why they’re attacking their own people. I haven’t been able to talk to Laenis since.

The village is over there. Follow me.

I got rid of the barricade that was in our way, so you should be able to take that path to the village.

Once you enter the village, ignite the Signal Fires. There will be Orcs guarding the Signal Fires, so be very careful.

Also, take extra care around the guards. If they find you, they’ll bring a horde of enemies along with them. Good luck.

That was terrifying! The agonized cries of the Orc Shamans were driving me crazy!

The Orc Shamans used to live in this village... But the new Timak Orc leader, Ramog, reduced it to rubble.

Ramog wants the power of the god, Paagrio. To achieve that, he killed all the Shamans who opposed him. The remaining few were dragged off for some ritual.

Paagrio is the god of fire. He is also the god of the Orcs. It is recorded that the Shamans sacrificed their blood and accepted Paagrio as their god.

If the ritual Ramog is trying to perform is to acquire Paagrio’s power, this isn’t just about one Orc trying to become stronger - this is something that puts the entire continent in danger!

I need to get this message to the Ivory Tower as soon as possible! Someone there must know. Please, be safe! Please stop the ritual!

Are you alright? Did that scare you? Hehe.

I was worried about you, so I used the fastest teleport scroll I could find and got here with my friends from the Ivory Tower as quickly as possible!

I’m glad you’re safe. Silverlight Mercenaries, your help was vital in helping to stop the madness of the Orcs. On top of that, we were able to recover some of the Nebulite Shards that we lost.

On behalf of the Ivory Tower, I am ever so grateful. We only wish the best for the Silverlight Mercenaries.

Oh... you’re from the...Silverlight Mercenaries…

I’m so happy that you responded to my request for help…Ergh…

Captain Tark and some of my other comrades were dragged off into some hole by a guy called Boatswain.

I was able to run away, but it looks like this is the end for me... urghh... please... find the captain and save my group...!

Thank you so much! I’m so grateful for your help!

We have no time to waste here. We’ll talk details as we walk! Follow me!

What are these shiny yellow eggs?

Wait... could Countess Trisha be trapped in here? I need to crack this egg right away!

Are you all safe? That was close!

Hmm? Look up there! I see something! Let’s hurry over!

Augh... I feel like I broke a couple ribs. It hurts so much that I can’t move.

I’m sorry to tell you this, but... I don’t think I can keep going with you... I have no hope but to wait here for support.

Leonard… he’s the Countess’s Guardian Knight.

The disappearance of Countess Trisha may have been his plan, but whatever happened to her, we need to find her.

I will not upset my Lord... At the very least, I need a corpse... Please...

I clenched my fists, ignored the pain, and hurried to follow you, but what did I run into?! The Countess, where is Countess Trisha!

Wh... what?! Countess Trisha and Zaken are lovers…? And now the Countess is dead, and he has vowed to get revenge?

Sh... shit! This is bad! If he’s that angry, he’ll attack with everything he’s got! We must notify our Lord and Hardin, and prepare for war!
Grendel leather would be fine too!
I’ll Collect Your Money for You!

Set Fire to the Bugbear Barracks

Keeping Wary of the Dark Brotherhood

Where the heck were you?! It’s dangerous for a cat to be alone in these mountains, meow!

We need to go to the hunters’ town to do some business!

Goods are sold at a higher price in the hunters’ town because it is so isolated!

To top it off, we can buy good quality leather for cheap! Let’s get going!

Woah, Grendels! Their fangs sell at a high price! I’ll pay you well for them!

Meow! The quality of Grendel fangs in the Northwind Plateau are fantastic!

Bring me some of their leather while you are at it! Waste not, want not!

I think you can do it, meow! There is a guy called John who makes a living hunting in Northwind Plateau.

That guy bought 10 fishes from me but has yet to pay!

Can you go and collect for me? I’ll pay you a fee!
I’ll pay you to help me out! Bring me as many Windsus livers as you can!
You brought so much! Well, leave them there and bug off before I kill you!

Wait a sec! This windy path with the Grendels and Ravine Windsus seem familiar!

This must be the place where rare “truffle” mushrooms grow, meow!

They are very valuable and expensive goods! The only way to find these, which grow underground, are by having Windsus track them!

The female Windsus are known to have a better sense of smell than their male counterparts. Look for a female one!

Oh, try attacking the male Windsus. The males are known to gather around female Windsus if they sense any danger!
It’s here!!! I found a female Windsus! Come over here, meow!
Do you see that? The males are protecting the female. Get the female!

I’m headed to find some truffles after preparations are complete, meow! The problem is that I’m sure there will be many Starving Grendel on the way. Better to be safe than sorry!

Defeat the Starving Grendel nearby so that I can look for truffles in peace!

I’ll be in your care then! I’m sure there will be male Windsus trying to mate with Coocoo!

Make sure to keep us well protected, meow! Let’s get going girl!
Meow meow! I smell something fragrant, meow! Protect us, <YellowBold>[player]</>! This is a crucial moment!

Meow? What is that?

There seem to be someone fighting a spider in front of the waterfall. We can’t have Coocoo getting hurt, you should go check it out!

I’ll follow after I see Coocoo return safely.
There seems to be more spiders. Could you take care of them? They’re poisonous... Ugh!!!
I have a favor to ask. Would you gather some White Herbs nearby? The poison will metastasize quicker if I move around.

The Northwind Plateau was once a beautiful and tranquil place... I can’t believe monsters now run rampant here... I don’t want my hometown to continue being overrun with monsters.

Could you clean up the spiders in the area? I am feeling better, but far from any condition to be fighting.
My goodness! I knew the spider population was massive, but I didn’t expect this many eggs! Scramble those eggs!
It’s about time we return. Those darn spiders delayed the trip to my hometown! Pan, come along with me! I’ll introduce you to a good buddy of mine, a trader. Hahaha.

I remember this place was rampant with Red Bears. Why are there so many spider webs? I see no Red Bears but loads of Atroxes!

This is scaring me, meow! No matter... Atrox poison pouches sell for a high price...

Get me some, will ya?

I had no idea this place would be so overrun with Atroxes. Let this go any longer and we could be eliminated just as the Red Bears were.

We have no time to waste. Help me get rid of as many Atroxes as possible!
O-over there, meow! You see the corpses? There seems to be more that way. It’s frightening me. We have to check it out, don’t we?
O-over there! A giant Atrox! Isn’t that the Poricule from earlier? We gotta run!!!
We were this close to being eaten by spiders! Let’s go to town! I don’t want to be here any longer, meow!
Are those Razorwind Bugbears? Get ready! They spotted us.
The hunters told me that Bugbears have invaded! We need to hurry to the town meeting hall and fight them off!
I would love to catch up with you but the Bugbears have set fire to the tent. Let’s extinguish that first. Hey! Help us out, will ya?

Uh oh! The scouts have reports of Bugbears gathering. They are definitely scheming to invade soon!

We must prepare! Would you look around for supplies? We are low on swords and bows as a result of the last battle.
They’re coming!!! Take your defensive positions! We must stop them at this bridge!!!
Seems we’ve wrapped up the situation. Let’s go ask the town chief what this was all about.
Sigh. It will be some time before the town is restored to its former glory. We successfully defended against their attack, but I fear the worst is yet to come.
Hmm... How exactly did the Bugbears happen to reach this far in?

Hmm... I’m not too sure of the cause, but I do have a theory.

(The chief brings out a strange skull.)

One day the hunters went hunting and brought this back. Our wizards said it was a skull with mana.

The Bugbears began attacking us a few days after... It’s been nothing but a burden to us.
Well, how about entrusting Hardin with it? I’m sure he would be able to control the mana within the <GreenBold>skull</>.
Good idea. The problem is that the Bugbears will continue to assume that we have possession of it. How would we solve that issue?
I’m close with Hardin, I’ll ask him for help. I wouldn’t want my hometown being overrun with those damn Bugbears.
Would you do that? Thank you so much! We’ll redirect our efforts to restoring our town and trust you to deal with the Bugbears.

I’ll use this teleportation stone to ask Hardin for help. Could you defeat the Bugbear Tyrant in the meantime?

I’ll ask for reinforcements as well as a safe measure.
Ah, I’m going to sell some leather here. I’ll see you next time, meow!
They seem to have set up camp and reinforced it like it’s an outpost. Well, let’s take out as many of them as possible.

The infamous insatiable gluttony of Bugbears should drive them mad when they run out of rations. We’ll take advantage of that!

Burn their rations!
We must take out the Bugbears while they’re sleeping. Let’s make sure they never wake up!

I heard about the situation on my way here. Is it true that there are hunters taken captive by Bugbears?

Seeing as there is a cage over there, we should check it out. We might even be able to find some clues.

We need to hurry! This may be our last chance to save the hunters! Defeating those swine should reveal something about where we can find the hunters!

Well? Get to it! I’ll be collaborating with Durzel to decide on our plan of action!

Well, here is our plan of action! Through discussion with Aymel, we have decided to lure out and eliminate the Bugbears! It is too dangerous for us to fight on their turf.

Lucky for us, I thought of the perfect plan. I just happen to be in possession of Windsus meat, which the Bugbears would die for. They’ll come running for sure if we cook some!
Now’s the time! The group of Bugbears we defeated should’ve been the bulk of them! The rest should be easy!
Great! Let’s rescue the others. I’m glad the operation has been successful. I’ll stand watch!

Phew. The situation seems to be all wrapped up. The hunters should be able to deal with the remaining Bugbears. Hmm, I wonder where Russel is. I was supposed to meet him here.

Something must’ve happened to him. We should look for him.

Haha. Welcome. Ah, I see you’ve come as well, Aymel.

I can’t believe I’ve been done in by Nymphs...
Tsk tsk. All that muscle was of no use! No wonder everyone calls him a meathead!
Haha. Be careful of the Nymphs around here. They were evading my axe with ease, I had no choice but to run. Be careful if you encounter them.

There’s no time, [player]!

That idiot may be acting like he’s fine, but he’s gravely injured! We need some hemostatic herbs, quick.

I need your help because I have to take care of this meathead.

The herb has a white coloring. I’m quite sure that I’ve seen them around here!

I made sure to ensure Russel is getting his rest.

I think being defeated by the Nymphs was a huge hit to his pride. I’m sure the Nymphs did something to Russel. Look for something suspicious about the Nymphs.

Ah, I’ve heard about this pollen... Something about Nymphs and hallucinations...

It must be those Nymphs. We may be in danger if we inhale the pollen.

Let’s defeat them quickly! Oh, and make sure not to inhale too much pollen!

Luckily, they don’t seem seriously addicted to pollen! The hunters told me that the Nymphs use pollen to cause hallucinations.

It seems they were responsible for the Bugbears acting up. We should take care of the Nymph Queen to calm down the Bugbears!
Be careful! Dark smoke is coming from the Nymph Queen’s corpse!!!
Ah! There are the hunters who were taken captive! Let’s rescue them!
Thanks! I won’t forget this. Visit me at the inn in the forest and I’ll treat you to a fantastic glass of beer!
Thanks! I thought I would be eaten by those Bugbears! Come visit the town and I’ll treat you to some awesome grub.

No wonder you are a member of the Silverlight Mercenaries! It was impressive how you didn’t even bat an eye while fighting that demon.

Perhaps we were meant to cross paths. Where are you headed to next?
I need to escort the hunters to town, as well as handing this <GreenBold>skull</> to Hardin and aiding in the restoration of the town.
Well, I should make sure that meathead receives some treatment. The nearest metropolis is Oren Castle, right?
If it’s Oren Castle you are looking for, I can take you there. I also know of a talented healer there.
Well, it’s decided! Let’s get moving.

I think they trapped Aymel in another room because she’s a girl!

We need to find Aymel before something bad happens to her! Let’s look for a way out!
Are you guys alright? We came running as soon as we heard about you guys. Shhh! Quiet down!
Let’s escape quickly. Any longer and the guards will come running!
I can’t leave like this! I can’t leave Aymel here!
Forget about Aymel! We don’t have time to look for her!
I won’t leave without her! You go ahead if you want to go!
You are so stubborn! Ugh! Steiner, would you accompany me? <YellowBold>[player]</>, what do you plan on doing?
Thanks for agreeing to accompany me!
Best of luck to you! Let us go, Steiner!
Sigh. We must rescue Aymel even if it means turning our backs on Oren! Let’s defeat the guards and find out where she is being kept.

They knew nothing!

Perhaps the prisoners know something! Let’s ask!
How shameless, a criminal asking to be saved!
We’re not criminals! We’re innocent citizens!

Yes! We’re citizens! The majority of us have done nothing wrong... Maybe one late tax payment, but that’s all...

The lord hasn’t been the same ever since the first lady Salein disappeared and Christine was taken in as a concubine.

Innocent citizens like us are being imprisoned! Any longer and this area will become Christine’s playground. We don’t want to die here! Please set us free!
Have you seen a girl with brown hair and half of her face covered with a mask?
I’ll tell you if you set me free!

The citizens will surely die if the Guards catch them! Could you knock the Guards out long enough for them to escape?

In return, I’ll lead you to the brown haired girl.
Christine took the brown haired girl inside! I’ve heard nasty rumors that happen to girls who go there. We need to hurry!!!
Embrion will be here soon. Hurry up.
What shall we do with this girl?
Send her to the chief! It is time for us to claim Oren for ourselves!
Aymel has been sent to the chief? Who is that? We need to rescue Aymel!
The ruckus from earlier caught the Guards’ attention. Why couldn’t you have rescued me quietly? Deal with those Guards, quick!
The Guards are coming. Quick, this way!
We’ll be caught immediately if we try to escape looking like this. We should steal the soldiers’ gear and disguise ourselves!

I know a weapon merchant in Oren Castle.

He would probably agree to hide us. Let’s go!
Halt! You thought we wouldn’t recognize you if you don some disguise?
Phew. That was dangerous. Good thing we secured some meds when we escaped. The girl called Aymel seemed to be heavily injured. Here, use these meds to heal up and get some rest.

When I was held captive, I remember seeing them order around a merchant for a delivery. That merchant must be in cahoots with Christine! We should be able to gain some clues if we capture him!

How about we find the merchant?
I’ll come along. Let’s scatter and look around.

Hmm... A suspicious merchant. The local merchants are bothered by the recent arrival of a foreign merchant...

I don’t know why since I haven’t conducted any business directly. Oh! Merchant Rhias should know something!

A foreign merchant? Oh, you must be talking about Creezaro!

He does look suspicious, wearing a dark turban and hiding his face. But, he offers his goods at a good price, so I like that.

I heard that he was going somewhere else to conduct a trade...

Maybe you can catch him if you leave now!
He’s setting off! Let’s tail them so that they don’t notice.
Hehehe... Humans. Thought we wouldn’t notice you tailing us?

Creezaro seems to have taken humans to the Swampland. I wonder why they did that...

I’ll have to investigate the Swampland, but first, we need to defeat the Guards.
See those Sentinels? They seem to be guarding something. The security has gotten tighter! Let’s investigate there first.
Hurry! We must save these people before the Lizardmen notice!

You came to see Salein?

I’m the wizard who was in charge of guarding Salein. That is until she was taken south by the Lizardmen. We need to hurry if we want to rescue her!

Wait! We should destroy their totems so they can’t draw strength from them!
I’ll take these two people to town. Go on ahead. I’ll follow afterward.
Do you see those weakened lizards in dismay? Now is our chance to defeat them!
Huh? Are those soldiers? Let’s rescue them and have them join us!
Hehe. Foolish humans. You acted just as Grunky predicted you would!

Seeing as how the Lizardmen are disguised with Oren Soldiers’ outfits, I think the situation is a lot worse than expected.

Regardless of their intentions, I’m sure they will be a great danger to Oren. We must dispose of them.

Through my years of experience with the Lizardmen Marsh, I know they aren’t capable of using such impeccable transformation magic.

I’m sure they are being aided by someone. Could you burn the Oren supplies being used for their disguises?

Aisa and I will look for who is behind this.

This is the reason why those lizards were able to disguise as humans! Dark Mystics...

They can’t be ordinary people. It must be the Dark Brotherhood’s doing!

Be careful not to touch this crystal. Please stand guard while I use magic to destroy it.

The Shamans will surely come rushing once they notice the crystal is in danger.

Earlier, Steiner said this has to do with the Dark Brotherhood, right?

I guess that assumption has turned out to be fact. Let us defeat the Lizardmen and look for clues about the Dark Brotherhood.

It may prove useful in looking for Salein.
Seeing as how there are marks on the Lizardmen’s tongues, the Dark Brotherhood must have been controlling them since birth! Let us go to their nesting location. I’m sure we can find something there!
The Lizardmen eggs are tainted by darkness! Let’s destroy them to prevent future enemies!

Things aren’t over yet. Peace will not return to Oren until we defeat the queen Crokyle!

Uh oh! Crokyle is here! We need to defeat her in order to escape!
We must stop Crokyle’s minions from the Priest! Defeat the Lizardmen Guardian that block our path and we can stop the minions if we hurry up!
Sigh. Nothing is ever simple. Give it all you’ve got! As long as I draw breath, I will fight!
Hey! Cut him open and pull Salein out before we’re too late!

W-who’s there? Is that you, Steiner?

Huff... Huff... I thought I was done for...

Oh no! The lord is in trouble! Christine is not human, she’s a Lizardman!!!

A Lizardman transformed to approach the lord and abducted me to this place when I found out its identity.

I think I was abducted with plans of being used as a sacrifice.

We don’t have any time to waste... We need to rescue the lord!!!
I brought a Teleportation Stone to use for rescuing Salein. Let’s use it.
Uh oh. We’ve been teleported to the wrong location. This is... in front of Oren Castle. We could be noticed by the Guards. Let’s move, only take out Guards as necessary.
Are you prepared to for the journey to the lord? Well, let us set off!

Steiner? I thought you died! Well, I guess I was wrong.

Salein is here too? Wow, this is my lucky day!

Christine? What is this about?

Steiner? Salein? What in the world is going on?!
My lord! Step away from that girl... I mean, lizard!
You’re stupid to the end, David! You’re too late! All soldiers in this castle are under our command. Kill them all!

Oh, my love, Salein! I thought you had died. I am so thankful that you are still alive.

I hear the Silverlight Mercenaries helped in your rescue. I am greatly indebted to them. Oren and I will offer our assistance if you are ever in need.
Thank you for saving our lord. I am forever grateful.
Meeting you folk has been the greatest fortune of my life. Thanks to you, I was able to be exonerated from my involvement with Christine.
I was able to be a part of this incredible experience thanks to you!
I hear Theodore has come to town looking for you. You should go see him. Now I can devote everything to ensure Salein recovers.

I received the Bugbear relic from Russel. A skull with mana...

My apologies for assigning you to another job without a break.

Did you know Timak Orcs occupy this area? They are quite an aggressive race. I hear an internal strife over is occurring.

Rumor has it that a Tribal Chief has a relic holding powerful mana. I would like your help investigating that rumor.

Russel should be there so join up with him.

From what I could see, they seemed to be preparing for battle. They were gathering weapons and storing extra food.

Let’s burn their weapons and food to buy some time!
It is crucial for us to defeat the Sentinels if we are to find out what exactly the enemy situation is. Let’s defeat them quickly!
Do you see that? I see a captive... I wonder why the Orcs haven’t killed that person. No matter, let’s rescue them quickly.
Oh no! Here come the Orcs! Prepare for battle!

I am Rakum! The right-hand to the chief!

My original, glorious appearance as an Orc was taken away by a strange spell. Now, I look like an ugly human!

I have a request to make of you, human! Defeat those traitors! I, Rakum, will repay the debt.

Kazan, the Tribal Chief of this area, went hunting a few days ago and came back different. A strange magic overwhelmed and trapped our chief.

We need to rescue him! But Kazan has many minions... You can help us by starting a fire and distracting them! I’ll look for the chief in the meantime!

Oh, don’t set a fire to the food! We need to eat it.

There are many soldiers who guard Caraku’s cage!

Defeat Kazan’s Seekers who guard it!
It’s Caraku! He’s gravely injured! It must’ve been the Warden! Let’s rescue Caraku!
We’ll follow after we confirm the Seekers aren’t chasing us. Go and rescue Caraku!

I never thought I would live to see the day when I would be helped by other races. Thanks a bunch.

Ugh... That damn Kazan! I can’t believe he’s taken over my position.

Hey, calm down, Orcs. Go in like this and we’ll be killed off!

It seems there are already Orcs like Rakum and Caraku who are being held captive. We should rescue them and have them join us.
You are smarter than you look, human! Let’s defeat that traitor and get the keys first!

Nice. Now set my minions free!

They saw Rakum and I being transformed into humans so they shouldn’t attack you!
I can’t stand them anymore! I’ll rip them to shreds!

There are still many minions who aren’t free yet. We should defeat Karok and also set the slaves free.

Let’s meet up at the chief’s place after we take care of business!

Kazan has become aware of our attacks. I expect him to attack soon.

My minions are already fighting valiantly. Aid them to defeat Kazan’s Elite Soldiers!
Let’s hurry and set my remaining minions free!
We’ve cut a path through to Kazan’s Barracks. Let’s go! You will pay the price for your betrayal, Kazan!
The green stone Kazan is holding has a strange power! Be careful!
That seems to be what Theodore spoke of. We did encounter trouble, but I believe we took the best possible choice of action. Let us retrieve the stone.
Can’t you do anything about this human body? I don’t want to live the rest of my life in this feeble body...
I’ll look for a way to turn you back into an Orc.

I am very thankful as well. Contact us if you ever need our tribe’s aid.

The powerful Timak Orcs will stand by your side.

Having Orcs as allies is very reassuring!

I received an urgent message from Theodore, asking to meet in front of the Tanor Outpost.

I don’t know what it’s about, but we should hurry.
We don’t have any time. Let us set off and talk on the way.
Hmm. Seeing as there are so many Recruits, they must’ve been prepared for us. This many can’t hold us back. Defeat them all!
We need to find out exactly where Durzel is! Oh, the Sentry Captain should know. Capture him and make him spit out Durzel’s location!

That damn Chit! I can’t believe he didn’t disclose any information, even as he died!

It’s okay. Let’s try out Training Captain Charto. I’m sure he knows!

Find him! We must find out where Durzel is!
The Tanor Royal Guards are closing in! Defeat them before more gather!
I’ll have a talk with the Tribal Chief. Just in case, I’d like you to keep me protected!
She doesn’t seem to be here. Does this mean that we have to go to the Chief’s post? Aymel seems to have gone ahead. Why don’t you meet up with her? I’ll follow after cleaning up the situation here!
The Dark Brotherhood and Elizabeth!!! Today will be the day I put an end to that wench! Let’s go! Only deal with the Tanor who charge at us!
I feel Durzel’s energy nearby, but I also feel another energy, a suspicious one... We don’t have time to concern ourselves with that. Defeat any Tanor Tribe Guardians who get in our way!
Ah, this is where Durzel was! I have the key, so let’s hurry and rescue him!
Thanks! Didn’t you guys see the Dark Brotherhood?
Yup! We saw them on our way here and made sure to teach them a lesson! What business do they have here anyway?

This girl here was being chased by the Dark Brotherhood when she was captured by the Tanors!

There must be a reason for why the Dark Brotherhood is after her!
You said your name was Molly? We are the Silverlight Mercenaries. Could you tell us your story?

W-we don’t have time for this... We need to get away from here.

I feel my pursuers getting closer!

Let’s get to some place safe. We will still have time to listen to her after that!

Hurry, let’s set off!
Woah! You sure are good at what you do! I’m so grateful, meow!
What?! That stingy cat sent you? Hahahahah!!!

What?! John got away, meow? I knew this would happen! Did you at least get the money?!

You sure are reliable! Oh, this is the payment I promised you.
Meow!!! We got a female! All that’s left is to use this female Windsus to find the mushrooms!
I feel at ease, meow! I just so happen to have finished taming the female Windsus! Good girl, Coocoo!
Hmm? You found some, girl? Is there truffle under here?!
Meow!!! We’re gonna be filthy rich! I’ve never seen such a giant truffle! What a good girl, Coocoo!
Ugh! Long time no see! I must be getting old... To think I’d be defeated by spiders!
Perfect! I feel the effects of the poison dissipating! Hahaha. Thanks a lot!
Sigh... Thank you. This should prevent the spiders from breeding. Though, I’m not quite sure if the situation will return to normal anytime soon...
Wait a second! Hold it, meow!
Did you see the corpses of the hunters while we were defeating Atrox? There seems to be more and more the further we go in. This is scaring me, meow!
I knew of your abilities, but seeing them with my own eyes is something else, meow! We would’ve been eaten alive if it wasn’t for you, <YellowBold>[player]</>!
H-how could this be? The town was attacked?!
Durzel? It’s you! Thank Einhasad, I glad to see you!
Don’t you worry. We shall defeat the Bugbears.
I contacted the Silverlight Mercenaries, Hardin told me to kill the lot of them! Well, let’s get to it!
Well done! I was surprised we experienced so little resistance from the Bugbears, but I guess they were sleeping!
Phew! Are you alright? I didn’t expect the Bugbears to be so strong!
Oh, so the blood hasn’t dried yet? They may even still be alive?
Haha. You defeated them with complete ease. You have improved beyond anyone’s wildest imagination!
Haha. Our plan was a success!
Phew. Seems we’re over the immediate danger. Durzel agreed to take the hunters back to their town.

Be quiet, fool! Stop talking!

You’re bleeding!
Phew. What a relief. Thank goodness you were so quick, <YellowBold>[player]</>.

What is this? Pollen?

Ah... I feel so dizzy... What is this?
Is everyone alright? Damn! Seems this is where Russel was defeated by the Nymphs!
Thank you for rescuing us. I’m Steiner, an Oren Royal Knight. I will be sure to repay this debt.
Well, I’m glad I’m not too late.

Russel! You came to rescue me!

What took you so long? Were you planning on rescuing a corpse?
I know of a secret path! Follow me to escape.
You found some that fit. Well done.
Shhh! Quiet! The merchant that Aymel saw is over there. Ah, he’s setting off!
Hey! I heard that you would be coming.
Well done! Haha. I love watching them panic!
Thanks to you, I was able to punish that traitor and come back to my original place!
From here on is the Tanors’ base. Stay on your toes!
What?! We still haven’t found out where Durzel is? Sigh... If the Training Captain doesn’t know, then we have no one else to ask but the Tribal Chief!
Sigh... They sure are hard to communicate with. We need to find Durzel quickly...
The Dark Brotherhood at such a place... I don’t have a good feeling about this.
Ah, so the battle was happening here.
Huff... Huff... The others should be okay, right?
Awesome! You did well to gather so much within such a short time! This should help us put up a decent fight!
You have my thanks. Without you and Durzel, we wouldn’t have been able to stop the Bugbears!
Darn it! How dare they trap us in a cage!
Phew. Seems like most people got out. Thank goodness!
Woah! Why is this underground tunnel so confusing?!

Thanks, but I already got some meds from Russel. Hehe.

I’m going to get some rest now. This whole day has been hectic. To think I would have been trapped in a cage...
I can’t believe the merchant was actually a Lizardman! There is no doubt the ones from Lizardmen Marsh are involved!
T-this is... This was Salein’s favorite handkerchief!
It’s the people who were abducted! Thank goodness they’re still alive!
Thank you! I thought I was done for.
Nice! Haha! Now we can teach those damn lizards a lesson!
Hehehe. This is revenge, you dumb lizards!
That could’ve turned out very badly. I highly doubt the lizards would’ve devised such a plan on their own...
Well done. I only fear that, as you must’ve seen, this was a small part of a larger scheme...
Look at this! It’s a crystal used for dark magic!
I’m bothered by what the Lizardmen said... Let us hurry!
So... the Lizardmen are being controlled by the Dark Brotherhood? But... why? Then are all these occurrences linked to each other?
Haha. Well done! Watching the Lizardmen eggs being destroyed is so satisfying!
Oh no! They’re trying to kill the captives!
Those damn Lizardmen Guardians!!! They’ll fully prepared to stop us!

Huff Huff... You say Christine is a lizard?! That’s ridiculous...

I can’t believe I’ve been toyed with by a lizard all this time. This is ridiculous!
I’ve heard of your impressive accomplishments. I had no idea you would become this strong when I first met you on Talking Island. Hardin is also very proud of you.
You are very strong! I’m sure you could help us! Please help us!

I can’t believe you set a fire to the food storage!!! All that tasty food...

It’s okay! We Orcs like to eat burnt food!
Well done! Hurry, we need to rescue Caraku!
What? They’re making my minions do slave work?
I like how you fight with so much passion, much like how I fight. I’m sure you could make friends of other races!
Haha. You must be quite skilled to have rescued me without even a scratch on you.
Hyaaaaa! A human body isn’t that bad! Well, I am very skilled after all!
Haha. I am fueled by rage and the heat of battle. I don’t remember the last time I fought like this!
Sigh. I thought I was done for.
Ah you’re here! Haha. I saw what you brought. Hardin will be extremely pleased.

Who were they? They seemed to be after this girl. I’m supposed to meet Hardin after things are wrapped up here. Since that’s done, let’s go see Hardin!

What was that explosion? Something must’ve caused it. Do you know where Theodore is? Oh, there’s a new girl!

The Ivory Tower has asked for help. Try to help out Emon as much as possible. I think it will be a good opportunity to gain the Ivory Tower as an ally. I’ll have the others join you as soon as they arrive.

We received urgent news that a violent mana explosion caused problems to the Ivory Tower magic device. That’s not even the worst thing that has happened!

The Sea of Spores is expanding! I’ll explain the details to you slowly, but I’ll need you to defeat the Blind Reaper and bring me the dark crystals first.

We set up a barrier by the Ivory Tower to counter the Sea of Spores expanding, but the explosion has caused problems.

Take a look at the situation for yourself. Those are some peculiar mutated monsters, I’ll need to investigate.
